Title: A Reliable Old Friend!
Text: This, for me, is the quintessential G Shock watch. Simple to operate, cheap to own;  I was able to completely get it squared away in a couple short minutes without looking at the docs. Just like the last one and the one before, I expect it to last at least 5 years or so. The watch gets scratched eventually--since I won't baby it--and the EL light will grow dim, and finally the watch band gets stiff, and might even break. Along the way, a battery or perhaps two (self-installed) will keep everything humming. Additional bells and whistles available on other models, the solar, the setting the time, etc. are for me merely gimmicks, and truly unwanted. They all add greatly to the cost and complexity, while for me reducing the enjoyment that is a cheap watch. That's what makes this watch so great. It can be used, or heavily abused, your choice. No worries. I have yet to outright break one. They have all lasted for years, and keep excellent time--less than 15 seconds a month variance at worst, and typically not even that. It will never impress anyone, regardless of model, so you forget that. It will keep accurate time and date through rain and snow and mud adventures of your lifetime. Join me and this watch at the start of The Great Divide Mountain Bike Route (and Race!) this second Friday in June, 2014 in Banff, Alberta, Canada. Have fun, make lots of memories! Bottom line: Has all the useful features without a cluttered dial of half-filled lcd circles that mean nothing. Big enough to read even w/o reading glasses, a plus!

Title: Classic for a reason
Text: Indestructible. Good for divers, boating, hiking, sports, etc. Water resistant, salt resistant, UV resistant. I'm pretty sure that if the batteries are kept in good condition it will outlast me, outlast every nation, outlast Earth, and possibly outlast the sun. I've heard there are some out there pushing 40 years old that still work great. Can't beat the durability of this watch for the price. Pairs nicely with a NATO/Zulu strap, and with the bull bars sold here on Amazon it will put up with reef/wreck/cave diving bumps and scrapes, and it looks pretty cool with them too. Timer and stopwatch are great for low-tech diving or old school dive planning as well. Be careful pressing the buttons underwater though, I've heard (have not experienced though) that it can cause fogging. Otherwise 10 out of 5, best watch I've ever owned.

Title: Smaill Display, Difficult to Use
Text: I'll start off by saying I am returning this watch.  Fortunately Amazon returns are pretty painless so I'm thankful for that. The watch contains the usual functions:  time, date, count down, stop watch, alarm, back light.  They all seem to work OK.  So it gets 3 stars. The watch is adequate but nothing really stands out.  There was nothing that rose above the $15 Timex I was replacing. Pros I have a pretty big wrist and the band was plenty large. Cons. First, the reason I returned it.  All the buttons are difficult to push.  They are recessed somewhat and I found that they did not work by just pushing my finger on them as you typically do.  I had to angle my finger or go at the button with the edge of a fingernail to work it.  I guess some might count that as a pro as there is no way these buttons are going to be triggered accidentally.  I think I would have lived with that if it weren't for the top left button.  That's the button you use to get in to setup.  It is also the button you use to get in to the countdown settings and to reset the countdown or stopwatch.  I could not operate that button except by pushing it with a slim object.  I don't know whether this was defective or by design.  If it was just the original setup I would have lived with this but I use countdown timers a lot and couldn't live with finding something to push the button to set the countdown.  So back it is going. Although the button issue was the killer, there were a couple other features that I did not like. Like some other watches I've had (but not all), when you are in setup or perhaps setting a countdown, the is only an 'up' button.  So if you overshoot your minutes, you have to roll all the way around again.  Some other watches used the other button on the same side as a down button so if you over shoot, you press 'down' a couple times and you're done. The display itself is smaller than I expected, but that's probably a personal choice.  I don't think it is as obvious in the picture, but when I actually got the watch, the bulk of the watch over powered the display.  It was not difficult to read but would have been better if the display and numbers  were larger. The backlight seemed to turn off too quickly for my taste. as I only had this for about 1/2 hour, I can't really comment on the ease of use or how well it wears day to day.

Title: Incorrect Image
Text: Watch displayed in the images is the Fox Fire model from Japan. What you will receive is the Illuminator model. Other than that this is a great watch. The OG of G Shocks

Title: Reliable Companion
Text: As months go by since purchasing this basic G-Shock I have found myself wearing it exclusively every day to the exclusion of other watches I own. It is reliable and tough, has both a timer (used daily for making my coffee every a.m.) and stopwatch. Also a watch with a digital timer is great when you are on a plane or train to gage remainder of your trip. It may not be the most elegant thing but it just works and feels solid and comfortable on my wrist. Has been dropped several times and not even a scratch- still looks brand new. Seems like it will last a very long time. Highly recommended this watch especially for the sub-$50 price. Huge value here.

Title: Great Value
Text: This is my first G-shock but not my first Casio watch.  I have worn the model with the vibration alarm for many years as my beater/workout/weekend, etc watch and really like the features it has.  Especially the vibration as you can 'silently' be notified of an alarm or your countdown timer without the high pitched beeping.  I've been considering the DW5600E-1V for a few months as I was wanting something a bit smaller that also provides the water resistance and like that it has the additional shock protection.  The biggest adjustment has been to the small buttons used to make the adjustments.  While I understand the principle of having them recessed a bit so they don't accidentally get pressed, I believe they could have made them stick out another millimeter (especially the "A" button, the one that allows you to enter the adjust mode) while not affecting the protection of accidental button pushing.  I do like the size of the case but kind of wish the light was a different color than green...but that's just my preference and something I have to get used to.  Like many people have stated on several different reviews, I would have liked to have an easier method for changing out straps without having to purchase adapters. But, at least I have some options!  Very solid value for what you are getting!

Title: Retro, but simple and to the point.
Text: As a security officer who has to see the time at a glance, this watch is perfect. It has a button that illuminates the background, which isn’t the easiest to push, but not hard. You may be kind of a dorky watch but it’s tough, water proof and easy to use. Top of the hour beeps is also a useful feature.

Title: Great watch for active individuals.
Text: I had this exact watch for my trip down to Costa Rica.  (The adjustment hole that I used all of the time eventually wore through after a couple of years.  Although the band can easily be replaced, I lost my Casio and have since bought another, because I really like this watch) This is far and away the most affordable watch with 200m water resistance rating.  It's accurate and very functional.  I specifically like and use the count down feature.  I also like how the day and date are displayed on the main clock screen. PROS: I don't really use my watch alarm feature all that much, but it is easy to use and functional when I have used it. I use the countdown timer all the time for cooking, rest between exercises when I am working out etc. The stop watch feature is excellent and goes up to 24 hrs.  It gives minutes seconds and 1/100s of a second, so it is incredibly accurate. It is a large watch, so just be aware.  But I love the old school look. CONS: If you have fat fingers, the adjust button may be hard to press. The illumination light could stay on for a tad longer. SUMMARY: Great functional dive watch.  Indestructible.  Fairly large and bulky (again, I like that look).  I would definitely recommend if you are in need of a tough and functional sport watch.

Title: Simplemente EXCELENTE para uso de trabajo

Title: The Toyota 4Runner of Watches
Text: On casio's website they advertise this can handle a hockey slapshot, that is probably true. I was not good to this watch and after a year died on me  because I let a friend throw it at a padded wall cause he was angry and wanted to throw something. He missed and hit the concrete but that's besides the point. Before that point this watch had been buried in mud, sand, taken in the ocean many times and slammed against the ground by my arm (accidently). This watch is the toyota 4runner of watches. It is a great value, supremely capable, ugly in a cool masculine way, and cheap enough to not give you gray hair over scratching it. It is everything an apple watch is not and I love that. As opposed to overprice innovation this watch is unadulterated bare to the bones solid construction and the embodiment of "if it ain't broke dont fix it." Buy this watch. It is the perfect blend of quality construction and durability and a price that makes this relatively disposable compared to all those GPS weather predicting BS sensing high tech computers other people wear on their wrists these days. UPDATE: I just bought my second one and it is just as I remember. Initially I thought it had lost 4 seconds in a day and panicked but in fact two clocks that claimed to be atomic had a difference of 4 seconds between them. since them I have been setting my watch using time.gov

Title: Great everyday watch for the price.
Text: Reliable everyday watch at an accesible price.

Title: It's the watch you need, not the watch you think you want
Text: Getting the DW5600E was another step I took on the path of simplifying my life. I've been using smart watches since the Pebble Kickstarter funding campaign but it was only recently I understood that instead of making my life easier, smartwatches were just another complication I could very well do without. The DW5600E is as basic as a watch can be while still maintain the same ruggedness and durability for which  the G-Shock watches are famous. It's not an overly large monstrosity as the G-Shock I used to wear in the army and it fit comfortably on my wrist. There are functions for stopper alarm and timer but who really needs it on a watch when we all have a smartphone can perform these functions better? So let's summarize: It an almost unkillable watch that displays the time and the date accurately and you really don't need anything else beyond that in a watch.

Title: Always come back to this watch
Text: I've had several of these over the years.  I scuba dive and have never had a failure.  The buttons can be a bit tough to press, but that is most likely because of the need for a tight seal for the water resistance.  I don't care, because this thing just works.  My daughter went into the military and took my last one and I bought a Fitbit Sense.  It sucked.  I returned to my old standby.  My wife even got one so now it is the "family" watch.  If you value function over form, and just don't want to worry about it, this is a great watch for you.

Title: Great everyday/beater watch
Text: Great everyday/beater watch. I haven't had is long but it feels very well built and is one of the few things I've ordered that looks better in person than it did in the pictures. All graphics and text are very crisp. This watch has everything I need for the gym/jogging and shouldn't be phased by years of sweat. The resin band also shouldn't stink to high heaven like my last gym watch with a cloth band. Unlike my last gym watch, this Casio is stylish enough to wear out and I often opt for it instead of my heavier, metal watches. I don't have very large wrists and imo this looks so much better on my wrists than the larger G-Shocks. This is my first Casio and the controls are all very intuitive. So why only 4 stars? The pushers. They work, but they are more difficult to press than Timex watches I've owned. Not a deal breaker for me, but worth noting. I will say you do get used to them, but there is no getting around the fact that they aren't as easy to use as many sport watches. I get that the pushers go with the overall retro look of the watch, but if they had used pushers that protruded maybe half a mm more, they would have had a nearly perfect everyday watch.

Title: Poor Quality
Text: The :outer Shell holding the watch is of poor quality.  It is molded so poorly that one or more of the adjustment "buttons" is always partially covered and held down making the process off adjustment(s) very difficult. I can see why it was offered at a "low" price

Text: Looks and fitting is a 10/10 however one flaw that is consistently popping up in reviews is the stuck button. I’ve come to like it as I mean it prevents accidental touch of settings. One thing for me that almost made me return was the horrible packaging it was crushed but watch was perfect. Too bad tho because I like keeping the package but it’s only paper.

Title: NIce Simple Durable Light Watch!
Text: I bought this after I returned a g shock mudman cause it was way too big and clunky.  This watch is much better.  Super light, easy to use, simple and it seems strong enough.  We shall see on this last one.  I never take my watch off and I surf all the time so it will take a beating.  I will report back in a year.  Highly recommended! Here is my review for the mudman which I returned: This watch is defintly everything that the write up says it is. Super rugged and it has all the features. One thing I hated about it was the size. I felt like I had one of flav a flavs giant clocks on my wrist. I have a medium sized wrist and it just looked kind of ridiculous. If you are used to giant g shocks this wont be a problem but I didnt like it at all. Also, the display is tiny. I am sure this watch will last forever though. Just make sure you know what you are getting. UPDATE************* After having this watch for 4 months I would say it is an excellent and durable watch for surfing, working out, and daily use.  In fact, I left mine on top of my car after a surf session and drove off so I just bought another one.  I love it UPDATE 2 >>>>>>>> Perfect surf watch.  Its been 2 years and the thing is still rolling no probs although the band has one hole ripped open---you put a lot of strain on your wrist and a watch when you surf so I am not surprised the band finally ripped through but my cheap butt just moved one notch down.  Enjoy!

Title: Just like the 80’s version
Text: I remember my 2nd watch and it was just like this one. Can’t believe this is retro now. I love it.

Title: Great for active people
Text: I've had this G Shock in the past that I wore diving in 40+ feet water. It went everywhere I did. I had it for a couple years before the battery died. Having got my money's worth, I didn't replace the battery when it started dying. I bought a new one recently and it looks just like my old one. It will definitely stand up to anyone's active lifestyle. It's like the GoPro of watches.

Title: BAS from Boston - A must have in anyone's collection
Text: This is my 3rd G - Shock 5600 in the past 25 plus year and for me it's a must have. I lost my 1st G - Shock in the early 90's before purchasing my 2nd.  I wear this as my casual/weekend watch and would be lost without it.  My 2nd G - Shock finally died on me Nov 2016 which started my hunt for an identical replacement.  You can imagine my disappointment when the clerk at a watch store told me it was not the battery and they discontinued this version :).  I was finally able to find it on Amazon.com and for an amazing price.  My watch collection includes a Tag Aquaracer and Breitling Super Ocean but consider through years of rugged usage the G - Shock 5600 my all time favorite.  Not only does it look and feel like a New England Patriots 4x Super Bowl Champion but it is durable and almost impossible to kill.  My last one withstood a beating on land, air and sea plus a tour in the Marine Corp the battery lasted well over 20 years and it kept perfect time.  I would recommend this watch to anyone looking for a sharp looking long lasting durable watch.  For all you single cats out there it will greatly improve your chances of getting a little stink on your hang-down.

Title: GREAT watch, but have a self problem
Text: First off, I love the size and the looks of the DW5600. I have small wrists so I found other G-Shock models not very likable. This watch fits perfectly though and the retro look of the watch makes it extremely stylish. This watch doesn't have advanced features like other G Shocks, but I just need all the basic features; time, date, alarm, timer, stopwatch. Also the fact that the watch is a matte finish rather than a glossy finish is great for those who don't enjoy scratches on their watch. Time looks very clear both at night and daytime. To add, the watch is extremely light, which is a plus. Though I'll probably never wear this watch while swimming or near water activities, its great knowing its essentially water proof. I've been looking for a good looking yet affordable digital watch and it seems I have found it. If your looking for a smaller G Shock rather than the huge ones you found your perfect match. Though I had love at first sight with this watch, I found a small grayish scuff on the left side of the bezel where "Protection" and "G Shock" is located upon examination after opening it. I will be exchanging it with a new one through Amazon and will update my review once that is complete. I'll put how my exchanging process was in the updated review. But I'm sure that when I get actually get my "new" DW5600, I'll have the DW5600 at 5 stars! I'll probably add more to this review when I get my new DW5600 and have more time with it.

Title: Your search ends here
Text: This is probably my favorite watch I've ever owned, and I own $500 pilot watches from Chase Durer. The thing is absolutely indestructible, keeps great time, and all the different functions on it are easy to use and sort through on the fly. I really love having military time along with the date on the main display, it's very clear and easy to read and the backlight is great for pitch black conditions and is just barely bright enough to use as a flashlight if you're trying to find something in the dark. This thing survived weeks and weeks of Air Force Officer training and has been dragged through the dirt and come out looking brand new. Unfortunately the band has decayed in some spots from being covered in bug spray and sunscreen and god knows what else that has just eaten into the rubber, but that is at no fault of Casio. I haven't taken this watch off in months and shower with it every day and haven't had any problems - I haven't yet gone swimming with it but I would be very confident in it. It has survived rain, mud, dirt, impacts, etc. and aside from the wear on the band as mentioned it looks like it just came out of the box. I love this watch and I'll probably never take it off until I have to eventually replace the battery.

Since I do construction and military duty this watch is perfect for everyday use. Non conspicuous and ergonomic this is highly recommended watch!

Text: Casio’s are hands down AMAZING. Super reliable, durable & look good on everyone. This watch is perfect for big wrists or small wrists. It’s perfect for jobs that are very physical cos you can bang ‘em around & nothing bad happens. That’s why I love casios, they can’t take a hit & not break

Title: One of the best watches out there!
Text: The majority of my small watch collection consists of analog automatics (Seiko, Omega, Hamilton) so I didn't think I would ever go back to wearing a digital quartz Casio, but after seeing a fresh one on my friend's wrist and rewatching a few classic 90's action flicks, I started looking around online and kept gravitating towards this one. After wearing it for a while I have to say it is simply amazing. If you don't care about price or status with your watches and are more about pragmatism and great functional design, it's hard to beat this watch. It's like the Glock 17 of watches. It knows exactly what it is and what it's supposed to do and just does it faithfully. Also, after wearing automatics for so long I can't help but be blown away by the accuracy of this thing. I also like how this particular model is more moderately sized compared to most other G Shocks, so it fits under shirt cuffs easily. If you're on the fence about getting one I'd say just take the plunge - the price is unreal for what you get and you never know when you'll need a low-key near indestructible watch on a job or a trip.

Title: MUST BUY FOR G SHOCK LOVERS
Text: How can you not want a g shock for such a perfect price? This one is practically being given away at 43 dollars. I would buy this one to wear, but also to give your more expensive watches a break. However that said this bad boy is a steal! The time function is accurate but I would reset this at least every 30 days or so. In my experience they lose up to 10 sec per month or gain time in some way but I think that is just my human error and inability to 100% accurately set the time .  I WOULD give this as simple gift to your son or daughter , to co workers, fathers , mothers, anyone in general who is a fan of g shocks. This really goes a long way for your money! Trust me as a proud owner of a view g shocks my self I can proudly say my more expensive models do the same and they cost twice or even more than twice as much.  BUY THIS you will not be sorry. g shocks are wonderful hobby to get into.

Title: Really a bargain
Text: This is a simple watch by modern standards, and there are much fancier ones available from Casio.  But this model does what one wants: it tells time (and date, and a few other things).  The battery lasts a long, long time: probably several years.  Its battery lasts hundreds of times longer that in a computer-watch, which must be charged every day. This watch is sturdy.  I am always working on things, and it does not make sense to be smashing up a delicate watch.  The Casio model will hold up: it is designed to be rugged.  It is not a piece of delicate jewelry, but a practical time-keeper. It all depends on what is important to you.

Title: Reason Behind The Recessed "Adjust" Button...
Text: The reliability of this watch is 20 Bars none the best in watches. Simple yet elegant. Unapologetically plastic but durable & rugged. It's a timeless classic. However, I do see a lot of people's video reviews that they always seem to nag about the recessed "Adjust" button on the top-left. But the problem is that they always seem to fail to mention why it is as it is. So, I will get this straightened out for you if you're curious. The reason for the recessed "Adjust" button is because when compared to other Casio G-Shocks or any other digital Casio watches that does not have a recessed Adjust button, the purpose of it is because it only takes a single click where as the others that's not recessed, you actually have to hold it down for a second for the Adjust button to register. That is the only reason. Nothing else. It is recessed so you do not accidentally press down on it since it only takes a single press to register. You do not need to hold it down for a second unlike the other watches that have a non-recessed Adjust button. Bottom line is; that's all nit-picking. Just buy this watch. Stop complaining. Don't listen to the people complaining about this on their video reviews. Just buy it. You won't regret it.

Title: If You have eagle eyes to see tiny digits, and tiny fingers for pressing hidden buttons, go for it-!
Text: I like Casio G shock watches, and I don't have any complains about its shock resistance or its basic functions-I wanted this. For the price You are really getting a lot, but what spoiling good first impression is that digits on the display are without enough contrast with the background, to light and to small, so they are not visible enough. Buttons are not easy to reach with a finger tips so you need to try several times, finding the right angle or to use nails to finaly press it correctly. If You set waking alarm, alarm will wake not just You but everyone else in a room until You find the best angle to press one of four buttons to stop it!

Title: Great one!
Text: I bought it for my father, and he loves it. Is one of the best watches I had.

Title: Excelente relación precio producto
Text: Lo compre como regalo para mi hijo de 6 años, le queda un poco grande, creo que lo que mas le juega en contra es el diseño de la correa, porque la caja en si mismo no es grande, pero los ajustes mas pequeños no se pueden usar. Lo demás es excelente, lo que esperaba, un reloj práctico y que el único cuidado que deba tener es no perderlo.

Title: Absolutely a favorite
Text: I wore watches for a long time. I stopped for several years when I started carrying a phone all the time.  Then I went smart watch but got tired of the hassle. For 40 dollars you can not beat how robust this watch is.  It's not fancy but it keeps time pretty good. I'd loses a few seconds a month. Looks are subjective but I love it.

Title: Easy comfort!
Text: Second Casio; same watch. First for 8 plus years. Now this one. Comfortable. Easy wear in sun & rain. Band will last outdoor exercise & heat. Happy guy!

Title: Gran Reloj
Text: Es un excelente reloj y llego muy rapido.

Title: great classic but...
Text: this is all around a great little watch. does everything i need. However it has one quirk that is a real bummer. If you change through the functions it will turn the indeglo off each time you change to a different function.

Title: Second G-Shock is as good as the first...
Text: I had one of the original G-Shocks that was so old that it was a DW5600 with no letters after. I had it forever, but finally I was unable to find replacement wrist bands for it, and the resin case was starting to crumble. I beat the crap out of that watch, and I can't ever remember replacing the battery in it. The only thing I disliked about it was the terrible light. If I was to rate that watch now, I would give it a 4 because of the light, but everything else was great. So anyway, I need a watch that can take a beating at work, so I ordered one of these new ones. After hearing about the new back light, I thought for sure I'd give it 5 stars this time around. And the back light is amazing compared to the one on my old G-Shock. But no, there's no dual time like on the old one! As a ham radio operator, having dual time set to UTC was the most convenient thing when operating. So, because there is no dual time, 4 stars again. But an easy to use, bombproof watch nonetheless. As people have said in previous reviews, it is pretty much a chick repellent. That said, I'm getting to the point in my life where a good solid watch is more important than what women think about me, so maybe this isn't really a bad thing.

Title: Great old school Casio at a great price
Text: I just bought this watch. It is my third G-Shock. It was on sale for $38 and I had about $5 off with reward points to make it $33. So far it runs great. It looks great. I highly recommend this watch. 5 stars!!!!!

Title: Nice watch
Text: Not too big, which is the reason I don't wear more G-shocks. If you want a tough watch that you can knock around with but don't want 80 different settings to muck about with this is the watch for you. It melts into your wrist and can fit nicely under a long sleeve shirt.

Title: Just buy it and solve your watch problem for the next 20 years
Text: My G Shock finally died.  I bought it in SOI in the Marines in 1998.  It was cheap, you could see the time in the dark, and it had an alarm.  This was all the functions I ever used during my 15 years in the infantry.  I had to change the battery twice in 20 years.  I also replaced the band in 2005.  My G shock survived brutal training,  a billion field ops, and two tours to Afghanistan and Iraq each.  It went to the deserts of Africa to the snows of Alaska.  It went to the jungles of Thailand to Death Valley.  It's was dunked in every ocean on earth except the arctic ocean, along with most of the great lakes.  My old rottwieler chewed on it, as did my two dobermans.  I never take took it off. It finally died this week. You know I bought another G Shock.

Title: Size does matter
Text: I am happy with my purchase. I have only had it for a week. It there have been no issues so far. It has all the features I wanted. It is larger than I was expecting but then again I have very tiny wrists. I like that the time displays in the upper box even when using the other functions. It takes some playing with to figure out how to use all of the features but as long as you've owned a digital watch and are familiar with how they typically work you should not have a problem. The buttons are a little hard to push which can be seen as a good or bad thing. The upper left adjust button is a bit difficult for me to press because it is somewhat recessed but with a little bit of work I can get my finger in there. It is not a button you should have to use very often but if so I would suggest growing out at least one nail and filing it into a point. I haven't gotten too far with the manual but I am not sure if you can make it so the watch doesn't beep when changing from one mode to the next. I will update this post once I know for sure. All in all, it is a good watch and I would recommend it to my neighbor that I like.

Title: Lindo reloj
Text: Lindo reloj para hombre

Title: Simple and Durable
Text: This watch has everything you need and nothing you do not. Use it for situations were you should not be wearing a watch. I suppose burning it would kill it, other than that it is virtually indestructible. After many years the strap will split and you may lose the watch. This one will be converted to have a nato nylon strap, problem solved. You will receive goofy comments from time to time. Thicken your skin knowing at the end of the day thru thick and thin you will have fairly accurate time and know the day and date. Not everybody has an ultimate beater retro style watch but you can. I would recommend, enough said.

Title: Ten years and still going
Text: Amazon just sent me a notification about my purchase back on 21 Feb 2012. This watch has been on my wrist since then. Never changed the battery and the backlight is still bright as new.

Title: '83 GW5000 modern variant
Text: Casio watch fanboy here. Always have been and grew up in the late 80's. This watch is quite similar to the very first original 1983 GW5000c gshock. Only difference is the absence of the outer red ring, the brick pattern background, and a couple words. The remake high end model of this original comes with a hefty price tag though and it does look a bit closer. However this watch's price is way more affordable and is still almost completely identical. Not to mention it even has a couple other features that resemble the original '89 F91w model. Very good! So if you wore casio digital watches in the 80's(nostalgia) or you want a watch of that effect, here you go! Fits the bill nicely! If you want a variant of gshock that does look even closer to the original 5000, solar powered, under $100 and has that red ring inside the bezel like the original, go with the GWM5610-1.

Title: Great work watch
Text: My hands/arms are constantly wet, covered in hot grease, or generally just at constant work with my job. this watch has held up wonderfully, doesnt irritate my skin, the big face is easy to read at quick glance. major game changing purchase, and its a real catch at its price

Title: Most comfy GShock
Text: I have different GShocks, this one being so ancient and least attractive, looks like $13 watch, I paid zero attention. But you cannot stop how popular it is now. Feel so comfy in/out of the uniform sleeve, usually big watches bother me. No one really cares about the functions, it does the same as those $13 watches. 😆

Title: The watch is easy to use
Text: The watch is very simple, there are no complicated functions, the timing function is very easy to use, the time is accurate, and the waterproof performance is very good. It is a simple and easy-to-use watch.

Title: Easy to program.
Text: Easy to read and use.

Title: These watches last forever
Text: This review is for the Casio Men's DW5600E-1V G-Shock Classic Digital Watch My mother is in her late 70's and as we all know, parents in that age range stick with what they know. My mother is not one for technology, she can barely use her TV, phone, and lets not even talk about computers. There are three things in her life which by all counts must absolutely remain constant, they are her toaster, her microwave, and her watch. Well, her watch died. I was charged with the task of finding a watch similar to the one she had from 1980!  Yes, 1980. I searched in stores, I searched online, and I'll be honest... I wasn't amused at the price for this watch. It's plain, basic, and simple, and I feel it should be less expensive than it was. However, this thing was identical to the watch she used to have and that's all I needed. I haven't worn a typical digital watch since I was a kid, I'm in my 40s now... but I was able to pull this thing out of the box and set it without any hesitation; it's just like it was in the 80's. More importantly it made my mother VERY happy which makes ME very  happy. 5 stars for that, but subtract one star for the price.

Title: Nice watch
Text: Got it for a gift and has worked out well lots of nice features very happy with it

Title: Ultimate beater watch
Text: A g shock for 40 bucks? I couldn't pass it up. It's the smallest gshock that I've ever seen, but I actually kind of like that. It's my kayaking, camping, swimming, mountain biking, or who knows what I'll be doing watch. I don't think I could break it without actually trying to bust it.

Title: Great Watch for a Child
Text: It's a G-Shock so it's a fine durable watch.  However, it's so small that it's suitable only for a child.  I gave it 3 stars because as an adult I can't use it.  Looks ridiculous on my wrist (and my wrists aren't big).

Title: Awesome little thing!
Text: I work in a psychiatric hospital and everything I wear needs to be able to take a beating,  and this little watch has held up very nicely.  I am quite impressed with it.  The only thing I can think of is that the straps feel a little flimsy,  but they haven’t broken yet.

Title: Solid well designesed Casio mens watch.
Text: When adjusting time you had to push the pin down far or the setting would not change.  Took me an hour to find that.  My wrist is 8 1/4 inches and the wrist strap still held but i wish it was longer to go through the little strap holder further.  Info said the strap was good for use of up to 8 inches so technically is a fault.

Title: Basic GShock, you can't go wrong.
Text: Very basic GShock, not a lot of functions but the ones it has are enough. Very legible, small, comfortable and light. Love the case shape. The buttons are a bit hard to manage sometimes until you get used to them.

Title: Nice watch!
Text: I haven't had this watch too long but so far I'm very pleased with it! I like the old school features and the price was great! I would recommend this watch to those looking for a rugged type watch.

Title: Great, simple, durable
Text: This is a super affordable watch that can take some bumps. I bought this to use here and there and I tend to wear it more than any other watch. It’s not bulky and super light weight. It has taken some bumps into door hinges  and still looks great. It’s super easy to read with a clear display.

Title: Reloj histórico
Text: Un Casio es sinónimo de calidad indiscutible

Title: Great, inexpensive watch until battery replacement is needed or other repairs.
Text: I've had three of these watches. Have two of them currently. Made in Japan, Thailand and China! They are great, basic watches for every day wear and are durable and capable of taking some "shocks" and other knocks. But...battery replacement is kind of a hassle. That o ring that seals everything is prone to get damaged when removing the back plate and parts like the straps and such are expensive when compared to the initial value of the watch. These are almost "disposable" types of watches. I change my own batteries and straps as needed and I use these watches on a daily basis but to be honest I finally broke down for the first time in my life and bought a mid level Swiss "automatic" watch for dress or casual wear. (no batteries!) Oh, to service the G shock yourself, you need small, watch type screwdrivers and CARE and PATIENCE and a steady hand. Don't lose those screws and try not to displace the o ring or damage it when removing the back plate. To "initialize" the battery when you've replaced it, remember to perform the "voodoo" procedure--using tweezers or such (conductive metal) touch the "crosshair" etching on the battery and the small "ac" marked spot on the watch and hold until the watch become active again and then reset your settings.

Title: Just Average
Text: I wore Casio watches during the 80's and 90's and was eager to give this watch a try.  It just does not live up to the quality of my past watches.  The most frustrating thing is the buttons are too short.  Pressing the buttons is incredibly difficult because of this.

Title: Took a wrong turn !!
Text: I have purchased several chinese watches, and they are just ok.  However by the time you buy several of these, I realized i could have bought a G - shock.  The knock offs are ok.  they lack a timer, the crystal is plastic and the water resistance isn't as good as this one.  The accuracy on the G - shock is excellent compared to the knock offs. The counter sunk button is designed that way, I have good finger nails - no big deal. You can dive with this watch plus numerous activities which won't harm it.  When it comes to quality, dependability and reliability,  nothing else compares.  A G - shock is a great investment that you won't regret.

Title: I really like this watch.
Text: I really like this watch.

Title: Almost perfect watch with one HUGE defect
Text: The main adjust button is recessed apparently to prevent one from accidentally adjusting it , but this seems overkill . It makes it impossible for me to adjust my settings without having a small poker available. I have big fingers. This is a pain in the butt , if my watch button was not depressed like this I’d give it a 5 star rating

Title: Useful, great value
Text: It would be impossible to find a watch with more useful complications and durability at this price-point. While common now, this was an engineering breakthrough that we now take for granted. It's a classic versatile design, much more so than newer G-shocks (which I consider the ugly Humvee of watches). No one will likely notice this watch, which is a good thing to me. It's light and comfortable and does what it needs to do. I only wish it had a snooze alarm. I can't imagine that the module with a slightly more complicated program would add much cost. I have to take away a star for quality control. There was a raspy buzzing sound when pressing the buttons because the contact spring was not sitting flush to the case. I had to open it up and reposition it -- but then the issue reappeared. You need to be careful when replacing the flimsy waterproof gasket when opening this up to either change the battery or fix the contact spring. I probably just had bad luck, because many others have had no problems with this. I'll probably upgrade to a Tough Solar.

Title: G Shock - The Professional's Digital Watch
Text: I always like to have a digital watch in my collection. They take a beating, are great for the gym/travel/working in the mud and sand. I had a Casio databank all through college and law school, and always replaced the resin band with a silicone strap. When my Databank died, I bought a hardy 'no-name' digital in a stainless steel case to replace it. It died when I went 3 feet below water. I wanted a no-frills watch that could handle the gym and business casual wear. This watch is tough, yet unassuming. I was worried about it being a bit too boxy or plain, but it's masculine but without being too utilitarian. The buttons are easy to work and the functions are exactly what you need and nothing less. It's certainly prettier than any other G-Shock IMHO. If you want a digital watch that embodies a 'drop it in the mud and it still fires' work ethic, this is your timepiece. $40 is a great price for it BTW. Only reason for the 4 stars is that I tried to replace the band, but it couldn't go on. I usually don't like the resin material, but it's grown on me. The band really works with the watch face itself, so don't even think about swapping it out with something eye catching (like I stupidly tried to do). I left on the original strap and I feel confident that it will last as long as the watch itself.

Title: It’s the OG
Text: Original and still the best great watch!

Title: Countdown timer on a G-Shock!
Text: This replaces my 30 year old Tag Heuer Submariner for everyday use. Lighter and more practical.

Title: Great watch with a great price.
Text: This was the first real watch I ever had back in the 80s. My dad got it for me when I was 8 or 9. Just recently saw they they still make the original so I picked it up. Can’t beat the durability to cost ratio.

Title: I think this watch will be great like last one except...
Text: For some reason the button to change the time has to be held down with 'extreme' pressure to work which requires holding the watch at the correct angle....then one can update the time.  I almost returned, but was able to change time consistently after testing....so since don't change time that often, think it will be okay.  Still it seems to be too hard to push down the button.....I have had two other casio watches which had same button, but was not as difficult.  Other than that...which may be a fluke with this particular watch, I really like the G-Shock watch for use at the gym.  I.

Title: Excellent and classic watch!
Text: Seek, doesn’t irritate the wrist and is water resistant.

Title: It's a G-Shock
Text: I beat the crap out of watches and live in a very harsh climate. I needed a watch that could stand up to sub zero temperatures, snow, impact, water and a myriad of different abuse. So I got a G-Shock. The screen is easy to read, the timer function works well, the movement keeps spot on accurate time, it displays day of the week and date and the backlight is a cool cyan type color. For $50 what more could you want?

Title: The best bang for your buck watch there is
Text: In my opinion, squares are the best G Shocks and this one is under 50 dollars, you can't go wrong

Title: Solid watch at a great price.
Text: I like the fact that this watch performs all of the functions I want in a simple and straightforward manner. There are no unnecessary dials and clutter on the screen. It is sleek and lightweight. If I could design a watch, it would look and perform exactly like this watch.

Title: Old school simplicity = breath of fresh air
Text: Bought this for the simplicity and old school 'classic' factor. Does not disappoint, especially the backlight.

Title: Super pleased with this watch!
Text: This is probably the most bang for your buck watch on the planet.  It has lots of useful functions (timer, stopwatch, alarm, 24hr/military time, day and date and a backlight.  Plus it is super durable, well proportioned for most wrists (unlike the other tuna can sized g-shocks), looks great and, to top it off, this watch is approved by NASA for use in space!  Super happy with owning this and am tempted to buy another one as a backup. July 2017 year update - watch is still going strong with no signs of battery fatigue.  Only signs of aging are that occasionally when I push a button it no longer beeps.  This never happened on my previous one (same model that I had for 5+ years), so I am inclined to think this second one is mildly defective. However, the inconsistent beeping doesn't bother me, as the alarm still works 100%.  Second thing is be careful when spraying certain kinds of bug repellent - I used my friend's spray last weekend and it left spots on the resin strap (hard to believe it is ok to spray on skin when it will chemically react with resin!).  Will probably get a new one as I can't stand looking at the part of the strap that looks like it's been dropped in acid, even though functionally this watch is 100% ok.

Title: Adjust Button issues.....
Text: I received a watch where I could not use my finger to push the Adjust button.  I sent it back and Amazon send a replacement.  The replacement watch had a similar problem, but was able to pull on the casing allowing my finger to push the Adjustment button enough to activate. This appears to be a new flaw in assembly.  I have had three (same model) watches over many years and this has never been an issue.  Recommend the manufacturer pay closer attention to assembly.

Title: Casio - Solid as always!
Text: I picked this watch up since it was on sale. I have been a long time user, and fan, of the Casio brand. The G-shock is just like the rest, durable, comfortable, and has it's own type of style. I am a big fan, and would easily recommend this to anyone out there for a great daily use watch!

Title: Seemed like a good watch but to small for me
Text: Got the watch and it was to small for my wrist so I was going to return it and our daughter saw it and asked if she could have it so gave it to her

Title: Timeless classic Casio
Text: This is a great digital watch from Casio and I like the quality and simplicity of it. Need I say more with other high reviews of this watch,take the next step and buy it.

Title: Perfect size for smaller wrists
Text: My wrist is 6.75 in circumference.  The 5600 is perfect for me.  I have a ga 100 and it hangs a little over my wrist.  The buttons can be hard to use at times and the reset button is a bit of a pain to press but I understand why they are recessed.  It's a good looking watch.  I think its a steal at 38 dollars.

Title: Sturdy watch - built to last
Text: bought this watch after my last Casio strap broke. I was looking for a Casio watch with auto-repeat countdown time, a google search returned this as a watch with this capability. This is my first G-Shock watch. Other things I like about this watch are, i) it's built to last ii) replacement straps are available iii) the buttons cannot be accidentally bumped, my previous watch was notorious for this and most of the time would be displaying the time in another part of the world iv) the backlight is great. v) waterproof, great for surfing and snorkelling Things I'm not so keen on i) the Adjust button (also resets the stop watch and countdown timer)  is so far indented that I cannot push it in sufficiently with my thumb or finger nails. However this is a plus too (see iii above). If I take the watch off, the adjust button can be pressed sufficiently with the buckle on the strap. Overall I'm impressed with the watch, it's converted me to G-Shocks and I expect to wear this one for a long time. I'll be buying more for my kids.

Title: You get a lot of watch for your $30.
Text: The finishing is what surprised me first. This is really well made. The matt black absorbs light in a way that says it's not just cheap plastic. The crystal remains pristine and scratch free. The watch is light and easy to wear, the band being quite flexible. It's a bit bigger than I imagined, not quite G-Shock big but will still snag on a tight shirt cuff. The value for money is extraordinary. I hesitated to upgrade for atomic sync and tough solar, but that drives the price up more than twice. The whole point of this watch is that it is very simple to keep costs down, and the consensus on watch forums seemed to be that the 10 year battery and the tough solar technology die at about the same time anyway, whilst the former is a lot cheaper to replace. As for atomic sync, it would be nice but I'm always near the internet and it takes literally a second to adjust the hour for a new time zone. I wear this a lot over much nicer and more expensive watches, because it's comfortable and looks neat. I'll reluctantly put on a mechanical watch if I need to meet clients. There's something just great about the minimalist toughness and value for money in this watch. It's philosophically great.

Title: A truly tough watch
Text: I am not known for being gentle on my wristwatches.  I have had analog watches that I have broken within weeks of purchase.  But this watch has lasted me six and a half years (so far).  I am not a desk jokey - I work a job in manufacturing, which is a fairly harsh environment to put a watch in.  In my free time, I enjoy hiking, the occasional swim, and ultra marathons.  On trails.  Some of which are muddy.  I did not buy this to be a dress watch.  I bought it to survive, and it has done an exceptional job doing so.  I have gotten it wet, I've gotten it dirty, muddy, and I've (unintentionally) bashed it and generally beat it up.  It just keeps going.  While today I did have to repair some of the bezel with industrial strength glue, it only failed because I had somehow managed to put a previous crack in the area.  I haven't even had to change a battery. About the only knock I can give this watch is that the wristband is about ready to go on mine.  But after six plus years of hard use, that's not surprising.  If you are looking for a dress watch, look elsewhere.  But if you are looking for a watch to take on any adventure, or as a daily wearer, this is worth every penny of it's current price.  It's impressed the heck out of me.

Title: Classic with a few headaches
Text: It's a timeless watch, and it's ruggedness is beyond question. I don't doubt it'll take a beating. But there are a couple things that kinda suck. First, a tiny one - the screen is harder to read (more washed out) than other Casio's I own (specifically the World Time). I assume that's due to the tougher "glass". On the flip side, the light is better. Second, and a doozy - the adjust button is more recessed than the other four. This is apparently on purpose, as it only takes a tap to enter the mode where you can change the time. (Other Casios, you hold it down for a couple seconds, which seems better to me.) That would be fine except it's so recessed you can't push it. I needed a tool (a pen) to push it. If it were only for changing the time that might be ok, but you also need it to change the alarm, set a timer, reset the stopwatch. Everything uses this unpressable button. In my case, I fixed it by removing some of the outer rubber bezel around that button, which works fine, but you shouldn't need to hack up a new watch so it can work at a minimum level. Form what I've read online, this is a recent change due to a new factory. Pretty disappointing.

Title: Best value g-shock “square” watch
Text: I bought this originally because I just wanted to own a “square” g-shock and this was not a disappointment. When you first handle it, it will appear much smaller than what the online pictures appear but it’s not so much a bad thing because the display is still very clear. The lumination is also excellent and you can make out the time perfectly clear in complete darkness. If you want more info on this watch, YouTube has tons of videos on this model and other G-Shock squares. The next two things I had an issue with are that the display phases out when you look at the display from above and perfectly clear when looking directly or from below at it, which I guess is not so uncommon a thing for certain digital watch displays. The other is the top left adjust button is a little harder to press compared to the other buttons, so as long as your nails are a little long, you’ll have no problem pressing the button. So all and all, this is an excellent value buy if your looking for a solid digit g-shock watch.

Title: The best thing out there if you don't need/want fashion.
Text: This thing just plain rocks. It rocked when I was 19 in the 80's living in Rio de Janeiro and it rocks now as a 45 y/o dad living in the Suburbs of a major north american city and driving a R/V. Yeah. Don't ask. Granted, if you are not a special forces sniper, Harvard educated arctic diver with a post-doc in marine microbiological thermal-vent martian life or a U.N. cardiologist with a history of open heart field-surgeries performed at candlelight during the Bosnian War, or perhaps the owner of a Multinational Russian Oil and Gas empire piloting your Carbon-Kevlar-Carbon yacht on the America's Cup, you may not get the expected nod of approval from your significant other when it comes to style. Like, for example, when getting dressed on coat and tails for your significant-other best friend's wedding. It is, after all, a black resin encased digital watch. And this is why I keep my broken Rolex around: To wear once or twice a year when I can't justify the ring around my wrist from wearing my G Sock classic year-round. You will, however, get the most bomb-proof, forget-about-it, dependable piece of timekeeping ever made at a very reasonable price. It will outlast any other watch you have. Guaranteed. Just ask me how I know. I still have my 80's one. The fact that you can tell time, month, day, weekday, night or day in a 1 second glance makes this thing unbeatable.

Title: The best money I ever spent on a watch
Text: I have bad luck with watches -- bracelets fall apart, crystals get scratched, and smartwatches go dead as disco. This Casio, though, is my Old Faithful.  I've had it for eight years, it's still on the original battery, and it looks and runs like new.  It looks retro cool and keeps perfect time, year after year after year.  It's the best money I ever spent on a watch. A man needs two watches, and this is one of them.  The other is a decent dive-style. I have a Casio MDV106-1AV and an Invicta 9204 -- I wear them both, but I prefer the smaller Invicta. Get this watch!  In fact, get one for every man and boy that you buy presents for.

Title: It's a great watch but...
Text: I love this watch, it's great and as advertised very durable but, Amazon needs to improve the package where they send this watches , I bought a case for a cellphone and came better protected than this. I left some pictures for your appreciation, it comes in a bag that protects it from nothing, it looks like the package was crushed and/or under some other heavy objects. I think an item like this and on this price range should be packed in a box with better protection in it.

Title: un-pressable "Adjust" button.  Useless.
Text: It seems like there is an universal problem with this watch. That is the "adjust" button on left-side top button.  it is so much depressed in that I just can not press the button to adjust time, reset the timer & stop watch.  I do not know whether it is a defective watch from Casio or just Casio made that way.  If Casio did it that way on purpose, it is a huge issue for this watch. The only way that I can press the button is to take the watch off and use a pointed sharp object to press the button which is quite a hassle. Also, the display numbers are very small and if you are wearing a reading glasses, it is almost impossible to see under dim light.

Title: ok but not what it used to be, disapointing....
Text: update: I sent the first one back to get another. It came today I am wearing it now, it works fine but has the same issues as the last one but this one has a better strap. on the down side this one is put together so poorly the "adjust" button is almost not push- able.had to use the tip of a pen to set the watch... the metal button is lower than the plastic rubber of the watch. look in the picture, three silver metal buttons show but not the fourth for adjust. and yes for those of you that cant wait to call me out i know it is inset slightly on purpose to prevent unwanted mishaps, but this ones way too inset. I know how it should be, this isnt my first 5600 frame g shock.  blah.  and just like the first the screen still moves under the crystal when i push any buttons. I realize this old model is not the expensive g shock any more but i jeez g shocks used to have better quality control? i figured one bad one now and then is nothing but two for two.  ive had six g shocks and about 25 casio watches,most all of them were great, not these two. not the sellers fault both showed up on time well packed with everything they should have with them like warranty cards etc.  ill keep this one i guess,  just trash it when the battery dies. watch showed up on time already running in the correct box with all the correct cards etc. it looks like the one i had two decades ago but it dont feel like it. I loved my old g shock but lost it and never found it. bought a new one when the price was right this week, was excited about it. opened it and looked it over and the watch was a little disappointing within just a couple minutes. the quality control for casio must not be what it used to be. the old one i had i remember it being very well made and very tough. on the new watch the strap feels cheap, the buttons are not crisp to push, its no longer metal cased in front but a plastic / rubber that is separate from the watch.  the most disappointing part, while setting time and date i noticed when i push the buttons for the light or start / stop  or in manual speak buttons b and d, the face of the watch moves to the left inside the case and plastic rubber cover overlay even with the slightest pressure on those buttons.  so to explain further, when you push buttons b or d with enough strength to make the button function for its purpose the digits on the face actually shift to the left inside the case and you can clearly see it happen from a normal distance that you would look at the watch to see the time of day from! its moving fractions of an inch but still, it shouldnt at all. the g shock 5600 i had years ago was like a little tank and i played baseball went fishing went to work at labor jobs and more and it held up. this one i suspect will breakdown after about a year if im careful with it. maybe i just got a bad one that slipped by. ive had a lot of casio watches and nearly all of them worked well and lasted longer than the price i paid for them would have justified. its good looking classic watch but im sad in the new build quality.

Title: G-SHOCK or nothing
Text: The best regular production watch ever made, Casio is Casio accept no substitute.

Title: Nice watch, classic design
Text: This watch replaces a 20-year-old version of the same watch. (Why change when you’re happy with what you have?) Just about everything is the same, which is great. The only thing that I’m not thrilled about is the band. Yes, it works fine now. But it seems to be a purpose-built design that cannot be replaced by a standard band. That means that new bands can only be purchased so long as these specific bands are being made. What that means is that the watch’s lifespan is limited by the availability of the band. With my old watch, I replaced bands over and over until I decided to replace the watch itself. That option may not be available for this watch. Of course, for another few bucks I can replace the whole thing, so it’s not that big a deal in the grand scheme of things. A first-world problem for sure.

Title: NASA Approved
Text: I've been wearing this model watch for decades. It's easier for me to buy a new one every ten years when the battery finally dies than to change the battery. I recently learned that this watch is approved by NASA for astronauts to wear to space. I swim and dive with it regularly. It is built like a tank.

Title: Okay, but NOT Great!
Text: Bought this as a replacement for another G-Shock watch which I had for approximately 15 years. (The watch band wore out.) The band on the new watch is much shorter and not as comfortable as the older watch band had been. The watch itself keeps good time and is easy to read.

Title: Great watch!
Text: Got this for under $40 and it is a great everyday watch. It can take a beating and looks great on the wrist. I wear it without any concern that it will stop working or get damaged. If you are looking for a great everyday digital watch- this is your best option.

Title: Really cool design
Text: I bought this because I wanted something I wouldn't mind getting covered in sanitizer or super wet from thorough hand washing. I'd always thought g-shocks were neat, so it just seemed like the right reason to get one The super 80s, super Japanesey design is really cool. So much flavor text! WATER 200M RESIST! ELECTRO LUMINESCENT BACKLIGHT! MODE! ADJUST! I like that aspect of Japanese design, you see it all over old beatmania and IIDX arcade machines too. The date and day of the week functions are really useful. It's cool to have a watch whose aesthetics you like, but where you don't have to worry in any sense about being delicate with it in order to keep it looking fresh.

Title: Clacic G shock square
Text: Super comfortable super functional watch that is so very close to my old DW 5200 that it's like a time machine on my wrist. (one for moving about in time I mean it's also good for telling when you are). In short get one you will love it. K

Title: Amazing watch for certain people
Text: This little watch is amazing pretty much does everything you need it to do time, date, and day also a indigo backing. Now to the certain people part if your wrist is any bigger than 8 inches don’t bother getting this watch it’s too small and it’s going to be uncomfortable. Anything under that should be fine. There are two options however there is a metal band that you can buy for $30 and you will have to get two of them and assemble the metal band yourself or there’s another watch model that might fit but Casio does not recommend it pretty much way too much stuff to think about for this $40 watch.

Title: Great Watch For The Money
Text: This is a good inexpensive, reliable watch.  I actually bought this watch for my wife who was wanting a watch that would work for her.  She didn't like the looks (haven't met a woman who does.) but she has been through 4 watches in the last year and none were reliable.  She gave it to me after I bought her a Deep Blue Lady Sea Ramic which is a very, very nice watch but it costs way more.  I got this one for $25.00 after using some accumulated Amazon points.  The only thing she didn't like besides the look of the watch was she couldn't read the digital display well.  So, she gave it back to me.  It is simple to operate, waterproof to 200m, very light and comfortable to wear.  It is a good watch to wear with your blue jeans or when working in the yard or whatever.  While I personally like the look of the watch and its simplicity, I gave it 4 stars simply because the digital readout is not what I would call small, but smaller and harder to read than the display on my Solar Atomic GW-500A.  If you are looking for an inexpensive, reliable watch for just a little money, this one is hard to beat.

Title: good heavy duty waterproof watch
Text: This is probably my 3 replacement of this model over the past 15 yrs.  I tried to replace the battery on my latest but failed (now will know what to do when this battery dies). I have not had a problem with this model underwater snorkelling and is my goto for inwater activities.  I would not trust it diving but it is better than other supposedly water resistant inexpensive watches. It is a bit heavy and the display a bit small but is backlit.

Title: A True "Beater" - and That's a Good Thing
Text: You don't want to wear your nice watch when doing yard work, home improvement projects, working on the car, working out, hiking, etc. You need a "beater" - something that can get dirty, take a knock and get wet. Something that won't be a disaster if scratched, or worse. At $42, this G-Shock is the perfect beater. It's comfortable, easy to read, has a great light and has a countdown timer, which is a very useful feature that is often missing on inexpensive digital watches. Best of all, at the end of a dusty day you can just rinse it under the tap.

Title: One unfortunate feature
Text: Unlike other similar model watches, the timer must be reset by pressing the upper left button- a button traditionally used for only adjusting the time, date, etc. This button typically requires a finer tip (pen, pencil, toothpick, etc.) and using your finger or nail is annoyingly difficult. As someone who regularly uses the timer function for different applications, this is a deal breaker for me. I'll be returning it. Otherwise, it's a great watch.

Title: Cool
Text: Muy cool

Title: You pay for water resistance, indestructibility and a reasonable size!
Text: I know there are cheaper quartz watches out there, but most offer only 50m water resistance (against the 200m of the classic G-Shock), lack a timer function, and feel flimsy. I bought one such other watch and, although pleased with what I got, I found it to be disproportionately large and somewhat delicate (within limiations; they're plastic after all). This G-Shock on the other hand preserves the dimensions (size and height) of classic watches, and feels sturdy and light at the same time. I use all the functions constantly. One thing true though is the difficulty of accessing the adjust button; until you get used to it, that is. Then the pressure you need to apply becomes natural and second nature. For the price, definitely worth it!

Title: This watch is truly the BEST!!!
Text: Pros: 1. Watch fits nicely on wrist 2. Display is quite remarkable but definitely not a terrorist watch (lol)! 3. Water Resistant? Yes! In fact, I though that this watch was going to crack under the heat and water in a shower and it replied, "Not a chance!" 4. Daily-routine-type-of-a-watch, in which fits me perfectly and probably most practical-oriented people who like a watch of simplicity, yet a sleek design and look to it. 5. Bomb.com Cons: 1. Buttons can get a bit irritating sometimes and adjust button is a little weird but OK. 2. May pinch at your "wrist hair" (if you'd say), which to me can be at times a bit of a stinger but no big deal. Final Verdict: After hours upon hours of research on a watch that is budget-friendly, comfortable, practical, and sleek, this is the watch that has stood out from the rest, not to mention the Casio F91W-1 Classic Resin Strap Digital Sport Watch and the Casio Men's W800H-1AV Classic Sport Watch with Black Band in terms of all the elements listed above. Overall, this watch is a must-buy for people who don't want to spend a whole lot of money on a watch. Thank you and good day!

Title: Great watch
Text: I bought this watch when I was in construction. I wanted a watch that would take the pounding and still work. It did just that. The battery went dead after 22 years. I took it to the local wm and when they put the back on it ruined the gasket so I have been without a watch for 15+ years. When I saw this watch I could believe they still made it and that told me that it really was a great watch. Would recommend this watch to anyone in a physical working environment. It will hold up. It is also a very good looking watch.

Title: It may be tough, but it is also tough to wear.
Text: It may be tough, but it is also tough to wear. I hate to be a contrarian on such a popular watch.  For what it is, it has told time for a year, and hasn’t malfunctioned. In my case, this watch hasn’t seen any abuse because I am reminded why I don’t wear it every time it comes up in my rotation—it’s hard to wear. In a world of mens sleeves, this watch is the drawbridge. Sleeve walks up to the drawbridge and stops. This watch is thick, and the corners are boxy.  It catches on tables, keyboards, doorways, pockets, even the dog’s collar.  Even if I wear the watch on top of my wrist (none of us keyboard operators do so), it catches on things I don’t want it to—but primarily shirt sleeves, sweater sleeves, and coat sleeves. I really, really want to wear this watch for hunting season, and cramming it under three layers of sleeves is like trying to hide a porcupine in a bowl of jello.  Not happening. The functions all work. The buttons are kind of tiny. And it works.  But I don’t wear it.

Title: Muy buen producto, en excelentes condiciones
Best digital watch
Text: Love this watch. Its not the original old school gshock but its pretty much the same thing just different serial number. This gshock is a great investment when it comes to performance and cost. It will take a beating and the battery will last a long time. The only complaint would be that one of the buttons is sunk in and its very hard to press. Besides that I love this watch. The light function works great and makes it very legible at night. Can’t ask for more at a $44 price point.

Title: Replacement of a very old version of same watch
Text: Bought this as a replacement of basically the same watch that I bought probably 20 years ago.  The old one's battery was recently changed (not by me) and it failed in water the next time I wore it in pool.  I look forward to at least 20 years with this one.

Title: Solid little watch
Text: Looks like the picture. Pretty basic watch that can take a beating. Recommended

Title: Very comfortable watch
Text: Great sized watch not too big...i bought this watch for work , I weld and I dont carry my phone on me , it usually stays in a tool box...this watch shows day of the week.. month and date perfect for time card entries...one button did come kinda sunk into the watch and is hard to press but I'm not really going to use any of those functions anyway....otherwise very comfortable and normal looking watch for someone whose never worn one before..id advice getting a screen gaurd if possible.. ive already got metal sparks embedded in my screen from work.

Title: Buy it. It’s cheap and durable.
Text: I’ve had many g-shock watches but this one is my favorite. I wear it to work at my job at the hospital, at a retail store and everyday around the house and around town. It looks good and is very durable being a g-shock. I’ve always loved Casio watches and especially g-shocks but the g-shocks can be a bit thick and heavy and can hinder you from slipping your hand in small spaces and pockets. But this one has a perfect profile. It is very lightweight as thin but still has the durability of a g-shock. I dropped it off a 6 foot ladder onto concrete by accident and it wasn’t even scratched. It has good features. It has time, day, date, alarm, time remaining and stop wat h feature. You can also set the alarm to go off everyday at a certain time. It also looks great and can be dressed up with formal attire. I started wearing a Casio f-91w because of the thinness and lightness instead of my other g-shocks but when I bought this it had a perfect balance between size and durability. Great watch love it.

Title: He felt a lot worse than I did
Text: The one I am buying today will be my fourth DW5600E.  The first one started to fall apart after about 8 years but, despite it's condition, was taken by gunpoint in Mexico City.  My buddy lost his Rolex to the theives.  He felt a lot worse than I did.  When the battery ran out on the second watch I sent it in to have it properly replaced in order to maintain its water resistance.  After that battery ran out I discovered that it's cheaper to buy a new watch than to pay for proper battery replacement.  The battery on my current watch needed replacing after about 5 years and I went to the local jeweler who replaced the battery for about $5, but I now can't wear it in the rain or it will start to fog up.  No diss on the watch, it will be fine if send it to the repair facility for battery replacement but a new watch will cost about the same. This watch gains about two minutes every three months but its not a big deal.  Thank you Casio for continuing to make this fine watch.

Title: Very durable watch
Text: I bought the exact same watch about 30 years ago and used it daily until the outer case finally cracked and broke.  I was so happy to see that the same watch was still available after all those years.  Proves that it's a great product--very durable, stylish for a sports watch, and very functional.  Has an alarm, calendar, back light, stop watch function, 24 hour function, and a very soft, flexible but rugged band.  Of course, I had to replace the band a few times in the 30 years I owned the first watch, but it's an inexpensive fix.  I won't be around in another 30 years, but I'll bet the watch will still be going strong.  It's a great buy.

Title: Great watch
Text: Built to last I've purchased other casio watches The bestbthus far

Title: Un gran reloj de batalla
Text: Es el gran reloj de batalla que todo aficionado a la horología o simplemente que le gustan los relojes debe tener.  Es indudable que se trata de uno de los mejores y clásicos relojes de Casio.

Title: Robusto, bello y fiable (con un pero)
Text: El reloj me gusta mucho. Es el perfecto reloj de batalla, pero además es bonito. Me encanta usarlo. Las funciones són bastante básicas pero suficientes. Por pedir más, podria tener más de una alarma, pero tampoco es importante éste detalle. El mayor pero que le veo es que el botón superior izquierdo queda muy hundido y resulta muy aparatoso de accionar. Tengo los dedos grandes y a veces tengo que insistir un rato para accionar el botón, que además es imprescindible para muchas de las funciones. En fin, una maravilla de reloj, pero mejorable

Title: Great watch with a few minor drawbacks
Text: The good: 1) This may be the most accurate watch I have ever owned. The day I received it, I set it EXACTLY to the official NIST time.  Two months later, it is still right on the money TO THE SECOND.  2) G-Shock watches have a reputation for being pretty much indestructible. Though I haven't had a major accident with it yet, I have no reason to believe that this isn't a very durable "accident-proof" watch. Nice to know. The bad: 1) Might be just my aging eyes, but I wish the day, date and time numbers were a little bigger, and there was more contrast between the numbers and the background. For me, the watch is perfectly okay under ideal conditions (well-lit room with plenty of time to look at the watch.) But in less than ideal conditions (low light and/or when driving and a quick glance is all you have time for) I find it difficult to read. 2) The light button is recessed and a little difficult to find and press when you need to light up the face. My Timex Expedition is much easier to read but not as accurate or as indestructible.  All in all, though, a very good watch.

Title: It's a good watch
Text: I didn't know if I would like this watch when I ordered it, but I like the watch more than I thought I would.  It's not bulky like my previous G-Shock.  It doesn't look out of place on my 6.75 inch wrist.  Very good

Title: I've been happy with other Caicos I have purchased.
Text: This watch is a base model I can't get all features to work.  Cant get timer to work.  Keeps good time. Fairly easy to set time but not other  features like stop watch and timers.  Light feature works briefly doesn't stay on vert long.  I will probably return watch.  Works fine as a watch!  says it's good to 600 ft in water.  If i'm that deep it wouldn't be my decision.  I'm a little disappointed in this Casio.  I will have to spend a little more money on my next Casio.  I've been happy with other Caicos I have purchased.

Title: Plane Crash Proof
Text: My father was an old school agricultural spray pilot and I first heard of the G Shock series from him.  One day when I was in high school, I pulled his old G Shock out of his desk drawer and he jokingly said that it was in that drawer because its batteries were dead, but quickly let me know he was wearing it during his bad plane accident.  There wasn't a scratch on it.  That crash should have killed him, and the fact this watch survived a burning plane crash without a scratch says a lot to the quality.  If you're on the fence, just buy it.  They're pretty much bomb proof and still stylish.  Oh and did I mention it's only $50... JUST BUY IT.

Title: Great watch
Text: Very light compared to a stainless steel bracelet. Fair readability although not when there is low light, have to turn on the watch light. Haven’t tested yet the water resistance. In summary: Good watch, useful features, feels sturdy.

Title: Surprisingly waterproof
Text: First of all, the only reason I did not give it 5-stars for "Easy to read" is because my eyesight is not the greatest.  Under "normal" lighting, there is no problem. However, under low light situations, I find that the "Illuminator" light is inadequate and quite useless. Aside from that, it's a very good inexpensive watch. What really impressed me is its waterproofing.  I recently misplaced my watch and it ended up going through a full wash cycle in my washing machine.  And, it came out still working!!!  (and a bit cleaner) I can't guarantee it will work for your watch, but, it worked for me. (disclaimer: don't try this just to see if it works.  It might not.) I can't say that it won't stop working tomorrow, but, for now, I am impressed! Also, FYI, the watch is 7 years old and I have replaced the battery, once.

Title: So cool!!!
Text: I LOVE JAY CHOU!!!!

Title: Great watch for a great price!
Text: The watch is everything you need in a basic watch. I workout with it at the gym and swim in the pool with no issues. And you can't beat the price for the quality.

Title: Great G-shock for small wrists
Text: Every other G-Shock looks ridiculous on my annoyingly small 6.5 inch wrist. This one looks cool. Definite wrist presence but not overpowering. Neat retro vibe, very legible, definite military aesthetic, very light but doesn't feel cheap.

Title: but at the same time it looks good and cool
Text: Classic, standard, g-shock quality, at what I believe to be one of the lowest (if not the lowest) priced g-shock. Not flashy, but at the same time it looks good and cool. You can literally wear it doing anything, although you might want to take it off occasionally to clean it a bit, because it will gather up your sweat and dead skin cells and whatever else you come in contact with. Its a great watch, easy to use, great functions (stop watch, alarm, timer), and tells everything that you basically need to know (time am/pm and military, date, day of the week). Super sturdy and its been an essential for me, I wear it everyday for the most part. In the ocean, in the shower, in the hospital, playing basketball, you don't really need to worry about taking it off because it won't break. In fact you should take it off during basketball because you might hurt someone if you hit them in the face with the watch.
