It's pretty indestructible, just youtube the tests they put these watches through. It's reliability is part of what makes this watch so appealing. Its durability in combination with its classic design and many functions, its probably the best value watch to go for at its price.

Title: I like it
Text: Others have griped about this being a Chinese knock-off of the original watch that was made in Japan.  I have been using it for a few weeks now and haven't had a problem with it.  I took it in the pool a couple of times and wore it in steamy, tropical conditions in Laos on a job.  The band is reasonably comfortable.  The button you use to access the time setting function is a pain to press, but you can operate it with your thumbnail with a bit of trouble.  I took off one star for that issue.  Other than that, it does the job and is a rugged, inexpensive watch.  I bought it because I travel and work in some rough places and don't want to take a watch I'll worry about getting stolen or broken.

Title: Virtually Indestructible
Text: I love this watch. I purchased a replacement after my prior G shock gave up the ghost after about 12 years. It's easy to read under water.

Title: G-Shock hyper accessible
Text: Le meilleur rapport Qualité prix,je l ai acheté de France et même avec les taxes elle est moins chère que en France.

Title: I returned the 5600J for this watch...
Text: Just as the title says... I had purchased the 5600j because I thought that the Solar + Atomic features would be worth the extra +/- [...] or so... In reality, as many have mentioned, those things are nice, but not necessary. This watch is just rugged, timeless, and reliable. Many people have had theirs for years and years and they go strong. I have no reason to expect anything less from this watch. After getting this one in the mail, I went right back to (x) and returned the J. With the J, I felt I always had to be mindful of keeping it around light and trying not to damage or bump it because it is a nice watch after all. The E is my terminator watch. It can go anywhere and I never have to worry about it charging or updating. The Atomic time is available online to sync the watch with every few months anyhow, so that negates the value there. End of story is that everyone should have a 35 dollar watch that they can take to space if the need arises! hahahaha. Buy this watch already. I will note, however, that the side by side comparison of the E and the J proved to be pretty interesting. The J had probably 30% bigger digits, which I liked, but the E seemed to have a wider screen in that there was more room for information on the home screen. I know they are the same size, but I feel the E does the job just fine. A+ watch! Great Price! Thanks Amazon and Casio!!!!

Title: Watch surface scratches easily
Text: I have had it for 2 weeks and yeah, it’s a watch. However, as a shop teacher I tend to be working with metal or wood a lot and the surface got a big scratch on it. Wouldn’t say it is scratch resistant by any means, but the watch still works.

Title: You can't buy a better watch
Text: This is my daily beater watch. I work in the hospital and usually go swimming after work for exercise. This watch is THE best. It is extremely reliable and very water resistant. It has every function you need. It goes with my daily outfit as well.

Title: Excellent
Text: Nice watch

Title: Outstanding Product
Text: This is my 3rd G Shock purchase since 1982.  My first got me thru college and all the rough housing we did as rugby players. It survived beer busts, mountain climbs, beach/ocean swims, etc for roughly a decade.  I went thru 3 bands and finally threw the watch away when the rubber casing broke away - even though the watch itself was working fine. Years later - I found myself working construction as an electrician and bought another g Shock. It survived being banged around while operating drills, grinders, saws, hammer drills, etc.  It lasted thru 5 years in the war zones of Iraq and AFG.  Nice to have  dependable watch that will wake you up at 0300 chirping top catch your help home after working 6 months of 7/14s! Just bought my 3rd G Shock and a cheaper Casio dive watch for working at the local refinery.  I am hoping to retire with this watch in 20 yrs at age 75:) These watches are almost indestructible.  The G Shock was at one time what the US military issued to it's pilots and troops. I laugh every few decades when I buy another one.  I spend more money on steak dinner than I do buying a watch that lasts me 10+ years of seriously hard use:) Can you beat that for value?

Title: Adjust button stopped pressing a day after purchase.
Text: the watch fits great and feels great. does what a watch does except the adjust button stopped working. it seems stuck and i am unable to take it out.

Title: Great everyday watch
Text: G Shocks are great value.

Title: +aaa
Text: +aaa

Title: It has last for 7 years
Text: I love this watch. My husband had it for 7 years this is second purchase.

Title: Battery replacement
Text: I got one of these about five years ago- it has run fine since then, and recently the battery died.  The light stops working before it stops keeping time, so that is a good indicator that it is going.  I got the readily available replacement, and with some instructions I found on line was able to replace the battery myself in less than a half an hour, and it is still working flawlessly.  A few notes on this.  The screws are really small so have the right small screwdriver, and a small container ready so you don't lose them.  You have to loosen the bracelet to get the back off, but it is fairly easy.  Once you put in the battery you have to reset the watch by connecting the battery to a point on the circuit board.  (See directions for this- it is really the only tricky part)  Essentially, you are briefly shorting it to get it to reset.  Once that is done, it works fine, although, of course, you have to reset the time  and date.  Have some silicone grease so put on the gasket so it will remain waterproof. You can, of course send it to Casio, but if you are comfortable taking things apart, and putting them together, this is very doable.

Title: Great watch!
Text: I wore a similar watch for many years in the late 80s and early 90s.  I was a police officer and needed a durable, reliable watch to wear on patrol.  This watch fit the bill and never failed me.  When I went on to be a detective, I started wearing more dressy watches and my watch went to who knows where. When I saw my old watch being offered, I had to have it, even though I own dozens of watches (I collect them).  This watch is the same as my old warhorse and appears to be just as rugged and reliable.  I glad to have it again.

Title: Best overall watch for the price
Text: The buttons are hard to press so if your old it might not be the best option . But durable and dependable this watch certainly is. Best watch for the price.

Title: I can give a review on this watch for sure
Text: I first bought one of these Casio G-Shock watches, this exact model, after it was recommended by my scuba diving instructor on Okinawa back in '85 while in the Marines.  I've worn one ever since, and that's saying something.  I've worn one down to 130 ft off Okinawa and no water got in the watch.  I've had it covered in oil and other fluids while working on my vehicles and it was not damaged.  Supposedly, if I remember right, the buttons can be pressed down to 15 ft but I've never tried it.  Another major plus for me is that the band is long enough.  I have big wrists and very few watch bands are long enough for me.  I use the 2nd notch and tape the keeper in place every morning to make sure it stays on.  One time I didn't do that and it did fall off and I lost that one.  EXCELLENT watch.

Title: One of the best G-shocks available
Text: Even though it's one of the cheapest G-shocks available, this watch is a fully featured. Stopwatch, timer, alarms, backlight, waterproof, shockproof, etc. Even though it's not solar powered, the battery should last 10+ years if you're easy on the backlight. The best part? at $40-ish dollars, if you lose it (sad) or break it (difficult) you can just get a new one. I own some high end G-shocks, but I still find time to wear this guy a couple times a week. Every G-shock fan should own this watch.

Title: Very rugged and durable watch, Perfect for the outdoors and its price.
Text: I purchased it for my son, who is doing a lot of hiking and strenuous physical outdoor activity. It has held up well in very cold weather conditions, and the time is relatively easy to read in the dark. It has also endured the mud, rain, rocks, and heat, without failing. My only gripe are the buttons, as they are somewhat difficult to press. By all means, it’s not as pretty nor advanced compared to an Apple Watch, but the durability and price is extremely good. I recommend you purchase this watch, especially for the outdoors and rugged activity.

Title: The Quintessential Beater Watch
Text: I dont think theres more to say about this watch. For me this is the best value beater ever. Nuff said

Title: A classic, practical, bang for the buck watch
Text: I've owned many watches in the past, ranging from entry level quartz analog to automatics in the $1000 range. I've always ended up selling them for one reason or another. For the more expensive pieces I was always worried about getting them damaged during everyday wear and eventually just got tired of worrying. With the high priced automatics also came maintenance and care which would add up as well as constant readjustment (automatics tend to lose or gain several seconds a day) and while they are very cool and mechanically interesting watches, eventually the novelty faded for me and I just stopped caring as much. Eventually I was just looking for a watch that kept time well, was functional and practical, looked good, and one that I didn't have to worry about getting banged up.This watch definitely fit the bill for me. In not implying that this lowly g-shock is "better" than a high price automatic (though if you are talking about pure timekeeping performance and functionality, I would say this will beat out most automatics anyday but you really can't compare the two since they are both very different in philosophy) but if you are looking for something that just works and yet maintains a simple yet classic aesthetic, this watch is certainly worth the money.

Title: Classic Simplicity
Text: Far and away one of the best digital watches on the planet. The Casio 5600E is 30% lighter than its predecessor the 5600C and therefore feels more comfortable on the wrist, although not as collectable. Also the 5600C featured dual time. However, the styling was left unchanged, except for some very minor cosmetic changes with the writing on the face. You cannot perfect what is already perfected. The comfort is simply amazing for a what appears to be a bulky watch. The G Shock has internal dampners installed to provide outstanding shock resistance, including full contact sports, chainsaws, jack hammers, etc, 12 rounds with Mike Tyson and full cage fighting :-) Not to mention skydiving, space missions and scuba diving. Features: Classic Casio 1980's looks, which many people love. 24 hour stopwatch, but...the time is kept displayed, very useful. 24 hour countdown timer, again, with the current time displayed. Backlight, which flashes for the duration of the alarm and hourly time chime & timer. One alarm, not 3 0r 5 0r 19, as some people are annoyed by this, which I find kinda interesting. Extremely comfortable resin band. And of course the Illuminator...bring it on. I could go on all day and night about this watch, or perhaps write a novella on it, or even base my whole life memoirs, that is how much I love this watch, but I won't, for fears of repercussions from my wife, my boss, my friends, and maybe even Casio themselves.
Good watch but not the stop watch. Buttons are recessed Esp A (top left) too much. Makes stop watch not avail.

Title: This is a great watch for practical purposes.
Text: I had one previously that I wore for years and never had to replace the battery and it never lost a minute of time.

Title: Watch works well, but came with a broken button
Text: The watch arrived with the  adjust button, on the top left, depressed. The head of the button is just below the guard, so I can't press it to adjust the time. The watch itself works well but it was annoying to set. I needed to use a metal spoon to set the time

Title: Everyone should own a DW5600
Text: One of the 5 watches you should own... but what are the other 4?

Title: Great watch for basic training in the Army!
Text: We bought this watch for our son before he left for basic training. He wanted one that was digital and that had an alarm. He has been gone for five weeks now, and said that he absolutely loves to watch. As you can imagine it’s taken somewhat of a beating, but it’s not broke and he said he’s amazed that the screen hasn’t broke with how many times that he has had it. Absolutely a great watch, I recommend greatly.

Title: One of the best watches ever
Text: Very cool classic from 80s. This timepiece has everything that you want from a wrist watch. There is not much to say since the whole world has loving it for almost 4 decades. It’s a great looking must have Casio.

Title: The only watch I wear
Text: All my other watches are uncomfortable or don't keep time well. You don't have to pay an arm and a leg for a good g shock. The price is unbeatable in my opinion

Title: Great watch for the money.
Text: This is my 3rd DW-5600E in 15 years.  I like it because of the recessed bevel and recessed buttons.  I am extremely active and wear it 24/7 where it gets banged around all the time.  I also spend about 2 hours in the pool with it every day.  My only disappointment is that when I have to change out the battery, I don't have too much success getting a watertight seal again and in the latest battery replacement I couldn't even get it to come back to life.  Oh well, still love it and just ordered another one.

Title: Best watch purchase i have EVER made!
Text: I had a bad experience with a digital watch (bought a timex ironman). The band practically melted when i left it in my truck on a hot day. So i figured all inexpensive/digital wristwatches were the same. I had seen G-shocks, and thought they were too clunky, but needed an inexpensive beater-type watch, and after reading the rave reviews for this watch, figured to take a chance. After a few weeks of using the watch, I can now say it is my favorite watch to wear. I used to use a black monster Seiko as a daily wearer, but this has now taken its place. First, it isn't an automatic watch. No need for a winder, or to constantly be wearing it to keep accurate time. Second it is very comfortable, I forget I have it on most of the time. Third, it is cheap! As in very inexpensive, while still being a quality wristwatch. Fourth, it is pretty durable (or at least it seems to be) without too much  added bulk. So to sum it up, I am very satisfied with the watch. Would I recommend it to someone i know? yes Note: I haven't read the manual, and hate reading manuals in general. I am sure there are tons of features this watch has, but am too lazy to figure them out. I just need a watch that keeps time, shows me the day, time, and that's it. This is by far (for the money) the best watch purchase i have ever made.

Title: Great Watch for Proud Air Force Mama
Text: Bought this for my son going into the air force. To be honest he never tested the water resistance yet. His only complaint was it is hard to press the adjust button but to me thats a good thing so it's not sensitive or easily bumped.

Title: Solid as ever
Text: I had one of the originals when I was a kid and very hard on watches. It stood up to a lot of abuse and kept going. This watch is the spiritual successor to that one.

Title: Great Watch !
Text: I just received this watch today. It is a gift for my 11 year old Grandson. I am thrilled with the quality of this . You can buy a square Casio for as low as around $10.00, but they are other versions and not G-shocks. I am sure they are all good value for the money.  I just wanted him to have a G-shock !! I've just become interested in these square G-shocks a few weeks ago. Kind of a nostalgia type thing. I saw these around when I was in my late teens and '20's, but never owned one until now.  I just spent some major $$ here on Amazon for a GW-5000-1JF and another with the negative display model GW-5510-1BJF. MY POINT BEING ::: You don't have to blow your income tax refund like I just did and get the solar/atomic bells & whistles ones.. This  $46.00 G-shock is a great ,quality, nice looking watch!! From a foot away you cannot tell the difference between this watch and the much, much more expensive GW-5000.  You'll change a battery every few years but they are an easy job.

Title: Great watch
Text: I've worn and loved G-Shocks for a few years now. I can't believe I'm just now getting this one. I love the simplicity of this watch! It's very easy to read as well. At my job, I'm always having to keep track of the time. I have a number of other G-Shocks. And while they perform flawlessly, they could look bulky and tacky wearing them around the office. But this watch isn't too big, and displays the time and date very well.  All around, this is a great watch for the price. I would highly recommend this to anyone wanting to buy a long lasting dependable watch. And for those people reading/writing 2 and 3 star because one of the buttons in "stuck", it is not stuck. That is the adjust button and is made like that by design so you accidentally bump your watch on something (crowded subway; outdoor activities) and start adjusting the time by accident. Imagine looking at your watch to find the time 10 hours off 3 years in the future...

Title: Casio DW5600E-1V G-Shock Classic
Text: I am a fan of this watch.  The beauty of this watch is that it is as utilitarian as a hammer and just as indestructible.  I bought one for myself and another for my father as a gift.  Mine has been covered in paint, gone diving in salt water, and gone skiing and camping in tough conditions.  It is routinely used while I run and ends up dripping in sweat.  Over nearly 1.5 years of this activity level and there is not even a mark on the plastic band.  My dad is finding out the same thing after destroying his past two watches due to inadvertent impacts or water intrusion.  I have owned a couple of Timex Ironman models and this watch is much more robustly constructed.  Very simple and easy to read interface, controls are intuitive.  You can throw the instructions away.  The Amazon price is great, as well, compared to other websites or retail outlets near me (Chicagoland area). This watch is not cool, it is not fancy, and it has zero "bling".  I don't know if that makes me like it even more.  I am a watch collector, and have a number of very nice swiss timepieces in my collection.  However, the Casio ends up being on my wrist more than any of my other watches, even for work functions or places where I am typically dressed up.  I think the Casio is so anti-fashion that it actually makes a fashion statement.

Title: Un clásico imprescindible.
Text: Hace todo lo que uno necesita que haga y lo hace bien. No es tan grande como parece, de hecho jala más bien hacia el espectro de los relojes pequeños. Apenas recibí el mío y ya estoy enamorado, este reloj no va a decepcionar a nadie.

Title: Practical and hardy
Text: The year function the me off as it is based on 99 years... but I imagine that's standard. The instructions could have been more clear about how to set the year in my opinion.  Overall, I would highly recommend this watch.  It's practical and hardy (so I'm told)

Title: All the features you need, with a clean, uncluttered display
Text: This is a great alternative to those stupidly large (57mm) G-Shock watches that look like they were designed for King Kong's wrist. Those watches feature three gratuitous circular "moon" displays that do nothing but tick off seconds with a supposedly cool graphic display. This is just a waste of space designed to, well...to waste space. The DW5600E, on the other hand, gives you only the information you need, in a clean, uncluttered display. I had one for years, but it leaked after I had the battery replaced. The watch store gave me a pricier G-Shock Illuminator for free, but I sold it on eBay to buy this model. The only negative is that the four setting buttons are relatively small and slightly inset relative to those on the big G-Shocks.  As a result, they are a bit harder to use. The only display NOT on this watch that is included in the big G-Shocks is a world clock. But who needs it?  It is simple enough to change the time zone when you fly somewhere. Do you really need to know the current time in NYC -- or in Kabul, for that matter?

Title: Good!
Text: Good watch!

Title: An OK buy for the money ... MAYBE.
Text: This is my third Casio watch in this product/price range and they have been durable and accurate -- though the backlight feature weakens and dies over time, a fact they previously failed to mention but now admit in the product info.  My concern, also sparked by the new product info (more a disclaimer, really) is the water-resistance feature.  I understand this is not a dive watch, and I have no intention of taking it down to 200 meters -- but my previous Casios I have showered, and bathed in; more to the point, I swim about 3-5 miles a week and have done so wearing those watches to no detectable ill effect. T his model, despite being "resistant" to 200m, the company goes overboard in counselling me not to shower or bathe wearing the watch, let alone (heaven forfend) swim in it...I can't tell whether this is an actual  warning that I've wasted my money this time around because the watch will die the first shower I take, or just a massive effort at butt-covering, Just In Case.  If the latter, I don't care. if the former, obviously, I do.  Will revisit this post with further information down the line. O yes -- I found extremely annoying the fact that you cannot change out the bracelet on this watch.  I hatehatehate those resin bands, and have always in the past pulled them off and put on my stainless band in their place.  Apparently there is no way to do this with this watch (Thanks a bunch, Casio) so I'm stuck with the band that is uncomfortable and makes my wrist sweat.  That alone will prevent me from ever buying a Casio again.  YMMV.

Title: I've bought for gifting
Text: This is THE BEST INEXPENSIVE DIGITAL WATCH IN THE HISTORY. Period. I'm a watch nut, I have a dozen mechanical wrist watches, from cheap to expensive ones —TAGs and Tissots—, a very old android Motorola —non Moto, Motorola— smartwatch and a Casio DW-5600-E, the direct descendant from the original G-Shock. This is guys and lads, the best sub $50 object you can buy anywhere. Light, indestructible, almost invisible in your wrist when You don't need to know the time (or the date), really easy to see whenever you need to know. Everything you need, nothing you don't and a watch afficionado never will see you like a moron whenever you are using one, because people in the know, know. This is the best.

Title: Definitly a classic.  Maybe too classic.
Text: The bottom line is that I sent the watch back because one of the buttons was pushed in permanently (i.e. flush with the case) and therefore was nearly impossible to push.  While I did not take this review down a notch to four stars for that reason (since I assume I could have gotten one with 4 good buttons) I did take it down to four stars because the buttons, even when at their normal position, are not easy to push. The watch had everything I wanted and I was really psyched about the small current time display in timer mode.  But in the end, I asked for a refund rather than a replacement due to the small buttons.  Compared to the Timex Ironman I eventually settled on, the classic Casio was too classic.  Those buttons need an upgrade.  (I will admit I have virtually no fingernails, so that may be part of the problem.  However, the Timex buttons could be pressed even if I had no fingers.  They're, like, real buttons.) By the way, for the really cheap Casio and Timex alike, the resin band is about as basic as can be.  It looks really cheap and, well, these watches are really cheap, so it should not come as a surprise.  We'll see how it holds up to daily use and some swimming this summer.

Title: Replacement for same watch except prior larger.
Text: Keeping time.

Title: A classic
Text: Really great time piece, trendy , classic , and old school all in one, priced fairly and a Japanese product regardless were it was manufactured.

Title: No se puede presionar el botón
Text: Todo excelente, salvo el botón de ajuste que no se puede presionar con el dedo

Title: Exactly what I expected, no more, no less.
Text: The G-Shock has a reputation for being a rugged watch, which is what I wanted.  I ordered the most basic model because I don't need all of the bells and whistles of the fancier, pricier models. Nor am I looking to make some macho statement.  This watch is exactly what I expected it to be-a rugged digital timepiece.

Title: Delivery and product as expected.
Text: The good: Waterproof, and tough, which is what I was looking for after getting frustrated with smartwatch recharging and delicate nature. Time Day, Date, Stopwatch are what I really need on my wrist. The bad: Need my glasses or really bright light to read. The countdown timer is a bit unfriendly to use.

Title: Calidad
Text: Para mí este reloj me trae muchos recuerdos, ya he comprado dos en Amazon, el anterior lo usa mi hijo, son fantásticos para el fin de semana no tengo nada que reclamar al respecto, muy buena máquina.

Title: Good watch
Text: Its fuctional and does well being water resistant. The only complaint to point out is that the Adjust button is flat, which makes it harder for me to press, so I have to use the end of my tactical pen to apply enough pressure to press. It would be easier if they could have the Adjust button to have the length be like the other buttons. Overall, I'm alright with the watch

Title: Great price for retro Casio
Text: Love and collect Casio watches! Bought this retro style Casio to commemorate my first Casio and I love it. Very comfortable to wear and looks great!

Title: Great durable watch
Text: I am an electrician and I tend to dabble in many other physical activities. I beat the hell out of this watch for the past 4-6 months and it has came out completely unscathed. It is comfortable, durable, and attractive. I also have the cheap, sold at Walmart version and that falls way short of this watch. I never accidentaly press a button, the screen is clear of scratches by some mirical of god, it has always accurately kept time, and the band is still holding up just fine. I never take this watch off and it looks brand new, other then the white paint specks from a paint sprayer. Highly recommend this watch to anyone who does hard labor and or just thinks of a watch as a tool. I’m interested in the solor model but that would probably be the only other watch I’d buy now. Maybe a lenox if I want to go analog for a bit. Good luck and just go ahead and buy it.

Title: Pretty nice watch
Text: Nice looking watch, I work in construction so let’s see how it does, also one of the buttons came damaged I have to use something to press it.

Title: Tough and Still Trendy
Text: I bought this watch when they 1st came onto the market. Very tough and simple to use. I would swim and even SCUBA dive with it. ( Within Sport Diving Depth Limits.) I literally wore it out. Contacted Casio way before Amazon and ordered a new basil, watch band, battery and repaired it. At the time, ( 80's) my little sister was going through training to become an EMT. She needed a good rugged watch to use in the field, so I gave her this one. That was about thirty years ago. It still works to this day. I was browsing watches at Amazon the other day and came across it again. The type of work I do is pretty rough on watches and I knew this watch was tough so I ordered it. I've ordered many cheap throw-away watches and they are exactly that. It's a tough watch and still looks good for the times. Besides, I didn't want to damage my Vintage Casio AMW-320C dive watch. Note the "C" and I did say vintage and still working like new to date. Casio builds some pretty tough watches for the money.

Title: Decent quality, but disappointed
Text: Overall the watch's build quality is nice, the features are nice, the illumination is nice, but there is one very annoying flaw.  As others have mentioned the top left "adjust" button is recessed into the watch case.  This is done on purpose because this is the button you push on the main time screen to set the time.  The problem is that this is also used as the reset button for the stopwatch, and the button to set the time for the timer.  It is near impossible to push when wearing the watch, and extremely difficult to push when the watch is off using just fingers.  With something pointy like a pen, it's no problem, but you shouldn't need a tool to reset the stopwatch.  I understand making the set time button hard to push so as not to accidentally change the time setting, but either don't use that same button as the reset button for the other features, or use a different method to access the set time function.  Overall kind of disappointed since I like Casio watches a lot in general and really like the overall aesthetic of this watch.  The functionality limitations to easily resetting the stopwatch and timer are sort of a deal breaker.

Title: Durable watch that can take a beating.
Text: I bought this about 4 years ago and it's lasted me until now when the battery died. I never took it off and used it during missions, running, swimming, hiking, showering, sleeping, and everyday ordinary use. Very reliable and sturdy, and it started to show signs that the battery was dieing about a month before it did allowing me time to get a replacement. It's got a few minor scratches on the face, but no other visible damage. The buttons are inset so you'll never accidentally hit them. The alarm is a little quiet so don't rely on it to wake you up unless you're a very light sleeper. It also has a stopwatch, timer, and backlight feature. Plus you can easily change the time to 24hr time (aka military). Only 4 stars because it did get a little moisture in there which would only show inside the face when I was hot and the weather was cold (ie. hiking through the mountains in 10° weather) which partially obscured my view, I expected the battery to last a little longer, and the alarm was silent.

Title: excelente
Text: just is describe it's easy to read the number, comfortable and nice. i recommend it

Title: Worth the money
Text: I've owned is type of watch for always 30 years. I first purchased one while working as a LE ranger for the Dept of the Interior. It has been submerged in cold icy rivers, been on my wrist while I fought wild land fires, and while working in temperatures above 120 degrees. This is my fourth watch. The main reason I purchase a new is the cost of replacing the band usually exceeds the price of a new watch. I own a Apple Series 5 but wear this one most of the time.

Title: Ya no los fabrican cómo antes.
Text: Antes cuándo eran fabricados en Japón tenían mejor calidad.

Title: What I wanted
Text: I don't need to tell time in 500 time zones, the one will do nicely, thank you.

Title: Great for on between changes
Text: This is such a great everyday watch. It came fast and my friend just loves it .

Title: Pretty good digital watch
Text: Apart from the stupid height of the adjust button, the rest of the watch is great

Title: Lost one second accuracy in a month
Text: Surprised and happy that in the first month the time has only fallen behind one second. I don't know whether to reset or keep tracking.

Title: Very tough watch
Text: It’s a g-shock. It’s practically indestructible and durable. I’ve had several over the years and they last almost forever. I only replace one when I lose it. The display is a little small on this model and usually need the backlight to see the time in dim light. It’s just my old eyes. No fault of the Casio If you want a watch that will last get one of these They are not pretty but they will be worth your money

Title: Simple yet functionally useful that don't break the bank!
Text: I always wanted a simple and functional watch that was easy to read (day and night), not afraid to abuse and most importantly wouldn't break a bank. If you are like me, don't look any further and get this Casio G-Shock. Forgot to mention, it looks good too!! I saw some folks were complaining about the adjust button hard to press - it is like that for a reason, so it is not pressed accidentally. I have short nails and I haven't had an issue with pressing the button. Since I have got it, it is my daily watch!

Title: Awesome watch!
Text: Love my new casio dw5600. I had one of the 5600c's back in the 80's when they were still relatively new. I wore that one for seven years on the original battery. I had to change the band a couple of times but that was the only maintenance required. I was working construction at the time and I never gave it a second thought. I ran a chipping hammer, dug holes, sawed wood, Pounded  nails. After work I swam in the ocean, sat in a sauna and water skied, you name it, and the watch never skipped a beat. My friends got sick of me bragging that the watch was virtually indestructible. The only negative thing that I can say is that the watch was a little heavier than other watches I've worn since then. The new version (almost identical to the first one I had) now has a resin case that is much lighter than the old version. I couldn't be happier with the new one. If it lasts half as long as the old one and withstands half as much abuse, It is worth the purchase price. Thanks Casio and keep making them.

Title: Love it but runs big on my wrist
Text: I love this piece from top to bottom. So good to feel. So easy to read, and so stylist. But it is too big for my wrist.

Title: Good choice
Text: It's what I expected.

Title: A Basic watch with no frills.
Text: I didn’t expect anything special when I purchased this watch. Having owned numerous extra rugged G-Shock watches (which this is not), I understood I was getting a basic watch with basic features. Once the watch arrived, I saw that the display was difficult to see and that the illumination button is recessed to the point that I find it difficult to press without fumbling around trying to find the button. The band is not very hardy. After a few days I noticed a little stretching. I have had bands like this one before so I knew I might as well replace it with a nylon beaded band with Velcro. See the pics in this review. With or without this band, most wearers will know this is a basic shell of the Casio G-Shock line. 3 stars because I like the brand. A new Casio band is half the price of the new watch. Not worth it for me.

Title: This watch is legendary, and the name speaks for itself!
Text: I'm not going to add anything new to people by noting that this watch is extremely durable, reliable, and long-lasting.  It's been on the same battery for over 3 years with plenty of life left to go, and it just keeps on ticking.  If you just need a tough watch that will tell time, get used for its alarm or stop watch, this is the watch for you. **NOTE** DO NOT GET BUG SPRAY ON THE WATCH!! It leaves permanent marks on the band and watch bezel that can't be removed.  Not a huge deal but it is unsightly.  Both of those parts are very easily replaceable, if it really bothers you.

Title: good watch
Text: enjoy this watch bought 2

Title: Great classic from 80s
Text: This watch is actual for almost 40 years. Great and simple. Thank you Amazon everything was  perfect with delivery.

Title: First g-shock I’ve had and is now my favorite
Text: Ok this is my first g-shock and I gotta say it’s actually my favorite. I bought this watch cause I lost my other Casio watch at home but this one is by far my favorite. What I like about this is that it’s got some of the hidden features I didn’t know about and this thing is built like a tank. Not only that I dropped this watch a couple times and there are scratches and it still works. Worth the money.

Title: beautiful watch
Text: i like it alot

Title: Best watch I ever had
Text: Strong, durable, easy to use. Slightly thinner but much more comfortable than most G-Shock watches.

Title: I would give this 5 stars, except....
Text: I bought this watch as a gift for my husband, and we were both looking forward to it. However, when we got it, we saw that it had the same defect that's been reported by other buyers: the adjust button is pushed in a lot lower than the other buttons, making it harder to press and use normally. This hinders the watch's features because you have to use this button to adjust EVERYTHING. It's a really annoying flaw in an otherwise really good watch.

Title: The only watch you'll ever need!
Text: Great affordable everyday watch that will last forever. It does everything you need a watch to do. Time, date, day, year, stopwatch, light, alarm.

Title: This is the Classic G shock to own
Text: I used to stay away from digital watches, but i realized that sometimes I would just want to wear a very light watch especially in the summer. It must be because I'm a 80's child that the 5600 appealed to me, I remember people wearing a similar watch back then. I decided to give it a try since for $40 you really can't loose much, you'll always find someone who will buy it form you. Very glad I did this watch looks great, has only functions you really need,  it is not fancy or blingy, it just has a very utilitarian look, all of the information is nicely depicted, such as the box with the date. I have heard the battery lasting for many years, this is another advantage of this watch. With It's low profile it can go with just about anything, I prefer this to the 6900. Just took it on a trip and it performed flawlessly, including in the water. I might just buy another as a backup. Pros: Classic looks Useful features Low profile Lightweight Long battery life Shock resist Inexpensive Cons: For the price, none

Title: Accurate and durable
Text: The GShock 5600e has retired my small mechanical watch collection. They are delicate and costly as they require servicing from time-to-time. I got the 5600e as to have an low maintenance, low cost, reliable and durable watch. It has been accurate by an outstanding +2 seconds since purchased a month ago. The only waterproof tests has been COVID-19 scrubbing with soap and water. I prefer small watches and while the 5600e is larger than a typical mechanical field watch, its light weight wears very well. The larger Gshocks don't appeal to me. Replacing the battery would seem more environmentally sound than replacing so I'm interested to see how the resin and mineral screen hold up over the years.

Title: Wristband is not comfortable
Text: Not comfortable wristband

Title: A great watch for the $!
Text: We bought this for our 13 year old for Christmas. It  looks almost like my first "real" watch, which was a Casio, when I was about 11 years old. I don't remember what happened to it? He say's he doesn't like to wear watches and will not wear it. I only ask that he give it 30 days to get used to it, before he passes judgment. The watch has all the typical Casio features, styling, rugged while not being/looking bulky, and a great first "real" watch for tweens. I gave it four stars, rather than five, simply because the bezel doesn't sit a bit higher, to better protect the crystal from scratches and abrasions. I foresee it getting scratches because of this. We ordered the Casio Men's DW290-1V "Classic" Sport Watch for our 11 year old as well. It's a great watch as well! It has more of the G-Shock look to it, which our 11 year old appreciates.

Title: Awesome watch, but beeps
Text: I really like this watch. I spent a week reviewing it and I was looking forward to get it after going though timex watches every 2 years. I thought the casio shock design would help and I liked the features of the watch such as the clock display in the stopwatch and countdown timer modes as well has the nice clean square face. Its a great protected watch without being bulky and is really comfortable on the wrist. However here is the reason I returned this item. Every time you transition the watch mode it beeps. I did not like this. After some research the only way to resolve this was by disabling the watch alarm by taking apart the watch. After this some other slight annoyances made me realize that this was not something I wanted to keep on me and rely on for the next 2+ years. The adjust button is hard to press, I'm sure with time I would have learned to live with. The second thing was the adjustment of numbers only went up. The timex watches I have always had had an up and down adjust setting, its just a nicety that makes adjustments quick and painless. But like a said those were minor inconveniences which I think I could have learned to live with, but ultimately the beeping between modes without an option to turn off was the reason I returned this item.

Title: My favorite G-Shock!
Text: I am a huge G-Shock fan.  I love a watch you can wear nearly anywhere without worrying about it getting beat up and still looking great with a quick rinse.  This is by far my favorite G-Shock I've ever owned and a no brainer for the price.  It's the best of G-Shock without all the extras that seem to get in the way (satellite reset, DST, etc).  Additionally, it is much lighter and the lower profile, compared to my other models, allows me to wear it under long sleeves, even dress shirts.  Also, if you have smaller wrists, this one will feel more natural and comfortable. Most people who don't know G-Shock won't get it.  They think it looks like its cousin ($15 black plastic basic Casio).  For me that was one of the things that drew me too it.  It is a no fuss, get it done watch, but still looks good with a dress shirt and tie or steel toe boots, especially when the guy next to you dropped a couple grand on his vanity watch.  This watch says "I'm confident with who I am and don't need an overpriced watch to make me feel better about myself."

Title: Nice low profile.
Text: It's a cheap but durable watch

Title: Good Bang for your Buck
Text: This is a good price for a rugged watch. I have a habit of swinging my arms hitting a doorway and scratching the face of a cheap watch. So this watch face is protected a tad because it is set down in the watch a little. Works great and I hit something with it and no scratch at all. I also didn't want a large G-shock because I have skinny wrists. This fits the bill perfect and doesn't look big at all.  Like a lot of folks mentioned the upper left button is used to set the watch and it is "set in" a little making it hard to push. I took off the watch to get to that button when I had to re-set the time. I have been in the ocean with it with no issues. It has an alarm/timer/stopwatch, 24hr time and that is about it. Light on the bottom right. It is a good sturdy watch for not a lot of money.

Title: Setting
Text: I’ve attempted multiple times to set this watch and haven’t been able The inserted button isn’t helpful Little disappointed in this purchase

Title: Tells time and day and date and I can read it
Text: I disliked that the 4 side buttons were hard to press while setting.  My previous Casio had rubbery things to press.  The new watch is nice for me and if the plastic/rubbery band doesn't come apart while I'm sleeping fitfully, I'll be happy.  I haven't tested the new watch in the ocean yet.  I don't use the timer because I already know I'm slow.

Title: So far it has great water resistance And the size Is just right for my wrist
Text: I like to watch in general But I was told when I bought the watch That it was a brand new model And I don't think the one I got is Because There's some wearing On the lettering Also another thing I don't like about it The button are really hard to push Because those somewhat recessed Other than that the watch keeps perfect time And it's easy to read

Title: Beautiful watch, but not without drawbacks
Text: This review translated automatic translator, because Amazon does not want to understand the Russian language, and so I have no respect for it. I will not waste my time on the correct translation of the text. The finest of the G-shock, probably, and the smallest too. On the hand, though I felt, but do not bother. How to put on after purchase, so do not strip more. Waterproof, shockproof, as tested by the batteries do not know, a few years promise. There are stopwatch, timer, hourly chime, alarm clock .... but the settings button (top left), which resets the timer and stopwatch, and customizable clock completely recessed into the body so that it can not press any finger or fingernail, and therefore these functions are absolutely useless, until you find something sharp than you can push it. It is absolutely unclear why Casio engineers have made it so, and how they use it, but for me, these features are not particularly in demand for this oversight is reduced by only one star. In all other respects, these watches are perfect

Title: Has no features. Perfect!
Text: This is by all means no dress watch. And that is why I bought it. It is the epitome of rugged bare essentials, and that is just what I needed for my exercise watch. The old school 80s look adds to the cool factor. My daily gym watch was an $8 Walmart watch that ran fine. But you get a sense of quality in design when operating this 5600 Casio. What I love most is that unlike many other G-shocks, this one has just what I need, and no extra features to slow me down. I have an alarm, the time, a stop watch, a timer, but not a single concern with whether or not the McDonalds in London has Wifi or if the moon is going to pull the tide out of my basement toilet. I will admit, for a more aesthetic approach, the 6900 makes a fine piece, but this watch should be the staple to every watch collectors collection, because it will be the one that lasts the longest, and I can feel that every day that it's on my wrist!!!

Title: Durability and nostalgia at a unbelievable price.
Text: I had this watch when I was younger and it wistanded a lot of punishment, so I just bought this for the nostalgia thing. Looks smaller than I remembered and lighter. The back is not a screw in part anymore and that is a setback for me, but I still love the watch, still looks durable and reliable. Is super easy to set up. And for the people complaining about the setting button been inside, reseeding like that is for a purpose, imagine the setting button activating everytime it get pressed accidentally. So it is by design. Nice watch for a super nice price.

Title: while maintaining a simplistic yet sturdy frame to withstand those harsh conditions
Text: Very well constructed watch! It has one alarm, stop watch, timer, and time keeper (the default). -Set up process: Very straight forward if you skim over the manual or even if you lose it, you can simply wing it. This watch has a 24 hr function and a 12 hr function, it also has the 2 letter abbreviation of the day, month, and day on the top. -Build quality: Initially, I wanted a slim profile watch for my workouts, but I realize that there has to be a compromise if I also wanted a watch to withstand all the running, swimming, and biking that I would go through from day to day. To my surprise, the watch wasn't as thick as I thought it'd be. It maintained a slim profile to some extent, while maintaining a simplistic yet sturdy frame to withstand those harsh conditions. I'd say that this is a great watch to wear for almost anything other than formal/semi formal attire. -Design: Very simplistic, it has everything that I need; time, date, and timers. More or less, to wrap it up, I would highly recommend this watch for it's simplicity, build, and quality.

Title: amazing watch!
Text: This 1980s style  g-shock truly is a workhorse of a watch. I purchased it here 4 years ago in 2010 and put it in my toy chest for storage ever since. Granted, I am handicapped and am limited in physical activity but this watch was still showing the correct time and date when I took it out of my toy chest today. I am now convinced the positive reviews were all correct. What a testament to the watch brand's prestige. After taking the watch out and playing with it for a minute or two I casually put it back in my toy chest for undoubtedly a few more years. Truly, amazing watch! I am impressed by its build quality as I hold it in my hand. Wearing it feels very rugged on my wrist. Im amazed at how affordable at $40.00 this was everywhere that carries this piece. I wear it all the time and know it will keep time for decades more. I suggest to send it to Casio repair for battery replacement. And for the longevity of its battery life the costs to send it to Casio every decade is not a bad trade off.

Title: Old faithful after 3 years of construction work
Text: After almost 3 years of wearing this watch 5 days a week on construction sites this thing is still going strong. It looks heavily worn, but that is the nature of my work. I do, however, have a few issues with it. Most importantly, the backlight stopped functioning after 2 years. It will turn on for an instant before shutting off without giving me time to read anything. The other problem is that it hasn't kept the most accurate time, as I must re-synchronize it once a month or so when it gets to be a couple minutes off. Rather than worry about the shortcomings of an incredibly durable $45 watch, I will simply invest in a better g-shock model when this one's battery dies. (Probably one with solar charging) It has been a reliable, simple, everyday watch, and I highly recommend it if you just want to tell the time and not worry about breaking your watch.

Title: Great watch
Text: Excellent watch! In all honesty, you probably don't need another G-Shock, but this is the watch we all get hooked on, be warn :D

Title: Pretty darn good
Text: Great product from Casio. Well be heading to army basic training. Needed a watch with an alarm to wake up 15 mins before wake up time to get situated. The countdown timer is also a plus, for the run. The watch is slim and light. The light feature is bright. Wish it would stay on maybe 2 seconds longer but it work great. Overall very pleased with the product and great for the price point to get bashed around

Title: great product
Text: Great for the money

Title: lives up to reputation
Text: comfortable, durable, reliable. Great watch

Title: Classic G-Shock that continues to impress
Text: This is the perfect G-Shock for me. Its super durable, has every basic feature I need and is perfectly sized. Its not too big and its not too small. The LCD is crystal clear and sharp! This watch does have Casio's EL feature so the display will light up evenly making it very easy to read in the dark. It also has a mineral glass crystal which is a big step up from a plastic screen cover. When you buy a G-Shock watch your buying something that's way more durable then a standard watch, your buying something that can be used and abused without worrying too much. The price that Casio sells these at makes this particular G-Shock something of "beater" or everyday watch. I am going to try and keep this watch clean, but I'm also not going to worry about it getting bumped or dropped. This watch is timeless in its design. It will continue to look good even twenty years from now. Its just so simplistic yet good looking.

Title: Adjust Button Needs a Design Adjustment
Text: Adjust button is a pain to press in. The adjust button was designed smaller to avoid being pressed by mistake. The concept is fine if all it is used for is to change time but the adjust button also is used to reset the stop watch. This is one of the key complications I use on my watches for workouts. It's very frustrating to spend time trying to dig your finger in there to reset the stopwatch. You would have to spend another 20 bucks or so for a replacement button to mod it to sit out like the other buttons. I may consider this but that just adds to the price. I do appreciate that this is one of the only square watches from gshock that allows you to set the timer in second increments which is great for timing down rest periods inbetween workout sets. Keep the adjust button issue in mind when buying. If you have smaller fingers or nails it might not be such a big pain. Looks very nice though.

Title: Everyday watch I was looking for
Text: The watch is everything it's been acclaimed for years, so nothing much to write here. The adjust button is depressed a little bit more than the others by default, so it's not a flaw.

Title: Very affordable
Text: Perfect for work and very comfortable. It's a basic G Shock with a retro look.

Title: Best Value Watch Period
Text: This thing is perfect. Comfortable enough to sleep in. I never take mine off. Always have the time, an alarm, stopwatch, timer, and dim light.

Title: Wear the best, forget the rest.
Text: I have several expensive Swiss watches, but since I got this one about 3 years ago as an everyday beater, I rarely wear the others. It’s comfortable, light, accurate, compact, and easy to read. It’s inexpensive, but it’s not cheap. I love it and so will you.

Title: Great entry level g shock
Text: It’s a great beginner g shock for a young person, mainly because of its size and basic functions. It definitely feels small on my wrist. I normally wear much larger watches rangeman, mud master (MOG), frogman etc..and It doesn’t have the features I value like solar powered or atomic time keeping. I’ll probably hardly ever wear it. I only purchased it because I am a g shock collector and it was used for 40$. I’ll probably let my son wear it.

Title: Great watch for men and their projects!
Text: My husband has worn these since retirement. Has several good watches that he never wears. These are on his wrist day in and day out! Lasts for years!

Title: Value for money
Text: This it not a great product - not very accurate (need to adjust it every month or two), BUT: 1. It is resilient - survives water exposure (have not tried deep diving) and extreme abuse (hitting. scratching, etc.) 2. It is great value for money, if all you need is a sturdy watch that survive pretty much anything (I had the same model for the past 6 years, before battery died, and was happy with it.  6 year for $45 - what not to love!) 3. It is not nearly as huge or expensive as those "tough solar" models" (had one of those as well, it lasted about 4 years).

Title: A great simple watch
Text: A great simple watch.  Nothing fancy but covers the bases. Accurate digital time, light to read in the dark, alarm, stop watch, dual time to keep track of 2 different time zones, and waterproof.  Use your smartphone if you want to know the weather, temperature, barometer, altitude.  The same if you need a compass.  It's boring but I have been using this same watch for over 20 years.  Whenever the strap breaks, 5 years or so, I order a new one.  Sometimes I think of getting a fancier watch that looks dressier and has more features and then I ask myself why.  I can easily afford any watch Amazon offers regardless of price.  For the fourth time I bought this one.  By the way, the battery can last 10 years or so.  When the strap breaks you can buy another one for $13 on Amazon.  As inexpensive as they are, I just splurge for new one.  It's up to you.

Title: Great Watch for Diving!
Text: I haven't had the watch for more than a week or so, but so far so good.  I'm a scuba diver and that is why I've owned this same watch for so long.  My last one I changed the battery myself once, then the second time the battery went out the watch was never water proof again.  Plus buying a new o-ring for the watch was almost as expensive as just buying the new watch.  I've had this same watch for well over 10 years and never had any problems with it.  Hopefully this one will last as long as the previous ones I've owned.  Also, the watch is not as bulky as the other G-Shock models.  That and the water resistance to 200 meters is why I like this watch so much.  Price isn't that bad either!

Title: It's the perfect, affordable, functional, simple cool look
Text: Easy to see and functional

Title: Great quality for an amazing price.
Text: I've always considered myself a "watch guy" and own a fair share of high quality, expensive watches. This can be a problem, however, when you just want something cheap and reliable to bang up on a hike or helping your friend move. As one who always has to be wearing a watch I finally got tired of the paranoia of putting a ding in the side of my Tag Heuers or Omegas and figured I'd spend a few bucks on a watch I wouldn't mind utterly destroying. After a good amount of research I settled on the quintessential G-Shock Classic and couldn't be happier. Not being one to particularly like the feel of resin watch bands, I was pleasantly surprised at how comfortable this watch was right out of the box. Usability wise, all the features are handy and easy to access and the construction quality of the case and band are surprisingly good. No rough edges or anything to cause discomfort have been discovered as of yet. I also tend to have somewhat sensitive skin when wearing synthetic bands and haven't suffered any irritation so far. My only 2 minor gripes are the fact that the beep sound when cycling through features cannot be turned off and there is no way to keep the back-light on while adjusting functions. Other than that, I'd say this watch is the watch the buy if you're looking for a durable, utilitarian digital watch at an affordable price.

Title: Classic G-Shock watch
Text: Heavy duty water resistant watch.

Title: sometimes less is more
Text: I really enjoy the look and function of this watch, it has a classic, understated look that is a lot sleeker than many of the other Gshock styles, yet it has the same reputation of toughness that is expected from the gshock brand.  This watch can go with you anywhere.  On the beach, in the office, in the gym, on the golf course... you really don't notice its there until you need to look at the time.  I like that it easily fits under a dress shirt sleeve, unlike my other gshock.  Function is simple and has the utilities you NEED.  You can easily glance at it and quickly identify the time, date and day of week without trying too hard to read it.  I found that 90 percent of the functions on other gshocks I would almost never use.  For the price point, it would be hard to find a watch that is as durable and as good looking as this version. Replacements bands and CR2016 batteries are fairly inexpensive, or if you just wanted to chuck it or toss it in a drawer, a new one can be had for less than 50 dollars shipped.

Title: Time not the easiest to set
Text: I had a model purchased many years ago and was very satisfied with the watch. The only shortfall with the new model was adjusting the time. I returned that recently purchased model and Amazon immediately sent a replacement. I was able to adjust the time setting on the replacement model fairly easily. That was the only problem with the watch.

Title: easy to use
Text: well built

Title: Durable
Text: Great watch. Hold up well and is extremely durable, easy to set up and maneuver considering its a budget watch. Had to get a new once since my old one died after 8+ years of hard abuse and exposure. Got the same one for work and general use. Over all Great set up for the price.  I like the old school look, added the aftermarket "bull bars" this go around to give the glass some extra protection. Would definitely recommend.

Title: problemas con botones
Text: reloj de buena construccion general, pero con problema de botonera a los pocos meses de uso incluso siendo cuidadoso

Title: Nice watch!
Text: Use as an everyday active lifestyle watch and alarm.

Title: Buen reloj
Text: Excelente reloj. Un clásico

Title: Great classic Casio
Text: Bought for son.  Classic watch that should last a long time.  Looks great.  A little big on a 7 year old, but strap fits.  He loves it.

Title: Looks awesome
Text: Great product, gets the job done !

Title: Classic
Text: It’s an amazing watch. Hold up to the abuse of an 11 yr old boy who wears it on the daily

Title: A Bulletproof Classic
Text: Tell time of a watch with a timeless design. This thing is great. Perfect utilitarian watch. I love it

Title: Great watch!
Text: Great watch at a great price. Had it before, so I knew what I was getting.

Title: Good Retrofitability
Text: Good quality performance, packaging is a cheap carton

Title: Great watch for the price!
Text: The price of this watch is amazing. And I know it’s gonna last for many years to come.

Title: Quality, Indestructible
Text: Can take a beating. Use it when working offshore, swimming in the sea, exercising.

Title: Classic Looks, Poor Usability
Text: I love the classic look, size, and durability of the G-Shock. The Day/Date display and backlight are all great. My issue is that the upper left "adjust" button is impossible to reliably push, it's so far buried into the watch body I assumed it was defective until I saw everyone else's comments on it. I have to hit it with my fingernail at just the right angle or use a pen to click it. Now, you can make the argument that's not a big deal, because you're not going to be frequently setting the time, which is fair. However, if you ever actually intend to use the timer, alarm, or stopwatch function then you're stuck, because the adjust button is integral to all of these functions. It's a little crazy to me that I need to have a pen to reset the stopwatch? How is that a thing? I decided to keep the watch because it was relatively cheap and I like the look enough to outweigh the fact that essentially all functions other than time keeping are useless due to a poor design.

Title: Great watch
Text: I work in the construction field and it’s a great watch to wear everyday.  It’s easy to read, water resistant, and durable.  Overall great watch if your out in the field and/or active.

Title: Rugged and reliable
Text: This is my third G-Shock watch, though it's been about 20 years since my last, which was replaced by several more expensive analog watches. I used my previous G-Shocks while on active duty. My watches still get banged up and being tired of spending too much on more fashionable chronographs, I was thrilled to see that Casio still produced this old favorite.  This is a rugged watch which will take a lot of punishment. The button arrangement becomes second nature in no time and the batteries on previous examples were very long lasting. At this price you will not be disappointed.

Title: Tough as nails, takes a beating
Text: The first watch I bought with my allowance was in 1986 when I was 12. That watch a Casio G-Shock identical to this. It lasted until 2002. The band was gone, the plastic protective shell had rotted away, the screen was cracked from being dropped off a 26' scaffold. The battery finally gave up the ghost after 15 years. I bought this for my friend who was having issues finding a respectable quality watch. I got this for him as a gift considering the pure hell I put my first watch through, and it still worked. I figured it will last him till he retires

Title: Durable watch that does exactly what it needs to
Text: I have absolutely no complaints, whatsoever.  I've had this watch for over two years now, and it has performed flawlessly.  It can take a beating, get dirty, get soaked in water, etc. and it works great, and feels comfortable.  I have no doubt that I will keep this thing will last longer than I do, and I cannot recommend it enough.

Title: GREAT watch
Text: Purchased this watch for the classic Casio look. Compared to other G-Shock models this watch is not bulky at all and fits my average sized wrists comfortably with no issue. Of the 2 other watches I have ranging from a 20$ Casio A168W-1 to a Seiko 5, I find myself always wearing this classic G-Shock.

Title: Dim digits
Text: The digits are irritatingly dim, looking at it from a straight angle. Need to tilt, for them to clear up. Is it bearable? Sure. Is it pleasant to have this inadequacy frequently on your wrist? For sure not. I returned. Will try another square model.

Title: Adjust button inoperable
Text: Tool needed to press adjust button. Finger or fingernail will not activate. Replacement sent, same problem. Nothing like similar watch I had in the 90’s. Contacted Casio customer service who advised me to write about the problem on Amazon review. Would not recommend this watch.

Title: Full featured sports watch, but with difficult buttons
Text: I had to return this watch because of the difficulty I had in using the buttons that control the stopwatch and countdown timer. In particular the reset button was hard to use, in that my finger alone would not reset the stopwatch. I had to use a stylus on the reset button to make it work. I would not recommend this watch because of this difficulty.

Title: Great watch for outdoor activities
Text: Very pleased with the quality of this watch at a very reasonable price.  I use it for working outdoors and have been pleased with the schock performance and water resistance

Title: simple... good
Text: The only reason it doesn't get a 5 star is because it seems to me like one of the 4 side buttons is not aligned like the other 3. Still, doesn't change the day to day.  This watch is simple and good.  I don't miss my previous triple the price G-shock.

Title: The Deathproof Classic
Text: Based on the original design of the very first Casio G Shock engineered back in 1983...  We have the royal king of all G Shocks...  The model 5600 Casio G Shock.  From Police officers, to firemen and women, soldiers, first responders, mechanics, explorers, and just good old fashioned hard working men and women...  We have all come to understand, demand, and depend on the Casio G Shock family of watches to take a massive beating right alongside us since 1983.  You simply can't go wrong buying this classic testament of a watch that can take a beating and keep on ticking.  Try doing a YouTube Search on all the stress tests that many have placed G Shocks under and you will be amazed.  You may never put your watch through the limits of abuse that it can take.  But the watch will certainly last you so long that it will become a part of you.  A part of who you are as a tough full of potential and dedication individual that can withstand the test of time.  Cheers Casio!!  Great job as always!!

Title: This watch is built better than you
Text: Need to check the time? As long as the batteries get changed every 5 years or so, this watch will be keeping perfect time long after you’re gone, friend. Need an indestructible timepiece? I’m pretty sure you could hit this watch with a sledgehammer and your puny arms would give out before you did any real damage to the watch. Anyone complaining about this watch should stick to watching Glee and maybe order a Fossil. Buy it.

Title: I absolutely love this G-Shock!
Text: Although I'm a watch geek, I was never a big fan of G-Shocks because of their bulkiness and plastic look. This G-Shock completely changed my mind. It is not too large, and fits my 6.5 inch wrist perfectly. It's a great watch for wearing to the gym because you don't have to worry about banging it around. I use the stopwatch function constantly, and being a quartz digital watch, it keeps almost perfect time. For the price, this watch is a no-brainer.

Title: Ruby little time machine straight back to the 80s!
Text: I am an ironworker and needed a tough  simple timepiece. That is exactly what this is, and it took me back to my childhood as I had pretty much the same watch back in the late 80s when the G-Shocks first came out.

Title: Good replacement for the DW-240
Text: After I somehow managed to break the screen of the DW-240 I was happily using since the mid 1990s I had to look for a replacement and the DW-5600E was the closest thing I could find. The DW-5600E looks a little like the DW-240 but is more bulky because of the extra protection if offers. The buttons are a little harder to press because they are somewhat recessed. Talking about buttons, while Adjust and Mode on the left have the same location, Start-Stop and Light on the right are switched. The screens are very similar but the DW-5600E offers indigo backlighting while the DW-240 only had a little useless light on the side. Oddly the DW-5600E does not offer a dual time feature or a Rem(ember) function. Instead it offers the possibility to have the light turn on when the alarm is ringing. Finally the DW-5600E is built in China and not in Japan as the DW-240 was. Only time will tell if this has any impact on the robustness.

Title: Great value, not overly bulky like most gshocks
Text: Used mine for Army Sapper school, held up fine minor scratches on the face. Only issue was one of the buttons was depressed and stayed depressed. Had to use a pencil tip to manipulate button.

Title: What a great watch.. I have 2!
Text: Tough,  reliable , and good looking

Title: on time
Text: good watch.. fast delivery

Title: En este caso todo salió bien
Text: Practico para un regalo

Title: Good solid digital watch
Text: Watch arrived on time and in one piece. Worked flawlessly out of the box, as advertised. I did notice that the face was smaller than I expected. My previous Casio digital watch (model SGW100-1V) matched the size as it was depicted on the product page.

Title: Love it.
Text: One of my favorite watches.

Title: Wow
Text: To sum it all up... Wow. I love this watch. It's simple, durable, and gets the job done. It has a comfy fit and a unique design compared to most watches you will see. There is a reason only the toughest choose G-Shock. This watch will probably survive longer than I will. This watch isn't a gimmick. This watch isn't a fashion statement. This watch is here to get the job done, no matter the environment or task. Truly a watch that stands at the top.

Title: keeping great time, but time to get a new one
Text: I have had an earlier version of this Casio G=Shock watch for twenty years which had a chip out where the pin for the band goes. As this was my everyday watch, I was always banging it up in the shop, doing things around the house, etc; I finely caught it on something in the truck & made the band pin hole even bigger so it would not hold at all. The Watch itself is still going strong, keeping great time, but time to get a new one. On this new version, they have attached the band with what looks like screws, so will have to see how it holds up over the next twenty years. (I am an Octogenarian so it will outlast me) I also have a higher priced SS solar powered G-Shock for dress up, which is still going strong. Very happy with these two Casio watches.

Title: Excellent value for the money..
Text: To date I have been pleased with this watch.  I have not yet had occasion to test its water resistance, however, It is keeping accurate time and the time associated functions all work as represented. This is my second purchase of this watch.  I had the first watch for many years and wore it swimming and in many other challenging environments.  It was a very fine watch that served me well.  Ultimately the band became brittle and broke.  I just figured it was time to purchase another.  I have no reason to believe my latest watch will not give me many years satisfaction as well.  Fine value for the money...

Title: Classic Casio
Text: The watch looks and works great.  The backlight is greatly improved over the little bulb the older watches had. I'm not a big fan of resin bands so I installed an old model Speidel179BL Twist-O-Flex band using a Jays & Kays adapter shown on the right in picture.  Now it's perfect.

Title: I like it
Text: I like this g-shock

Title: Oh yeah!!!That is the one I was looking for
Text: I could have written a review about this watch ten years ago but,I wanted to make sure it was the same watch I have owned in the past.These are truly excellent watches.They are low profile,rugged and very dependable. I don’t scuba dive so, I cannot tell you whether or not they are actually waterproof to 200 meters.What I can say is,mine withstood a decade of showers,brake cleaner,degeasers,kerosene,paint thinner,bumps,bangs and,severe abuses. I thought they quit making these. I am happy to find out it is still available.If someone gave me a new Rolex, I would sell it and buy this watch and pocket the rest of the money.

Title: Second One I Bought
Text: Good watch. Wore out in five years (case started to fall apart).

Title: There's a reason GShocks are renowned for toughness.
Text: I've worn this everyday for about a year; going to work, wrenching on cars, motorcycles, trips to the shooting range, clearing snow in -40 weather, whatever.  It never stops. It never quits. It never offers a hint of protest.  I wouldn't be surprised that if tomorrow an asteroid struck the earth, ending everything, all that would be left would be cockroaches and the Casio G-Shock DW5600.  Great watch.

Title: Love this watch
Text: My first DW5600E lasted about 15 years, until the strap broke. It is an amazing watch and one I love wearing. If you are in doubt about buying one, just go for it. You won't regret it. One added plus of this model is that it fits very well on smaller wrists.

Title: The Best
Text: I bought this watch from Amazon about 6 months ago.  I am a VERY tough to please customer; I give this watch 5 stars.  I do have some minor issues with it, but none that would keep it from the 5 stars.  I have wore this watch nonstop for the 6 months I have had it.  Yeah, I know that sounds kinda nasty, but once you have this watch you will understand.  It has held up to clunks, wacks, temperature fluctuations, swimming, hiking, everyday work, animal bites, and on an on.  I don't know how, but there is not a scratch on this watch...it "almost" looks like the day I got it.  The only thing I have noticed is some very slight speckling/color change on the bottom of the band (this might have been from the chlorine-my bad).  The only other issues I have are these: the buttons are not the easiest to push-takes some practice.  And finally, I was a bit disappointed to see "Made in China" on the back of the watch...it's not like I was expecting to see "Made in the USA", but was maybe hoping for a "Made in Japan."  One final note, I was worried about the size of the watch, as I have smaller size wrists-no problem with that.  Looks really good.

Title: Practico y muy bueno
Text: Excelente reloj

Title: Producto original
Text: Producto original, hecho en Tailandia, comprado de la tienda de Casio en Amazon, muy feliz con mi nuevo reloj

Title: The most durable watch you are likely to ever find!
Text: EXTREMELY durable.  I have had two of these.  The first one I just simply wore out.  It took a long time and truthfully it was still working when I retired it.  After wearing it every day for about 15 years the rubber outside case had disintigrated and I was wearing the watch with the bare metal inner case showing.  I replaced it with another one and had it for about 7 years when it was ruined in a house fire.  All of the plastic/rubber got melted away, but the watch in it's metal inner case was still running for a month or so after the fire.  It eventually died but who expects a watch to survive a fire? I purchased this one as a birthday present for my Dad.  He has worn this same watch for years with similar stories about durability.

Title: Best watch I ever had!
Text: After loosing my old gshock classic, I went back on amazon and got my self a new one.  I mean, this watch is 100% best of all watches in the world that you can buy for any price!  It's not a gold, $15,000 Rolex, but you do actually get REAL WATERPROOF, SHOCK RESISTANT watch with a scratch-less "glass."  For the past year, I haven't take the watch off my hand!  I go swimming on regular basis (pool chemicals don't affect it), I go wind surfing (water or hitting it doesn't affect it). In fact, I always open doors with my watch instead of my wrist :)  I love this watch so much, I can't even express it enough!  Buy it, you won't be disappointed, I guarantee.  It's not bad looking either ... kind of bullet proof look to it.  Classic version is also pretty nice size comparing to the other bulky, crappy looking gshocks.  Buy the battery powered version for $40 and the battery lasts 8 years.  I would rather replace a 50 cent battery in 8 years then spend $150 on solar powered watch.

Title: Died 13 months after purchase - Do not Buy!
Text: After moderate use for just over a year, the watch completely gave out. Sent it into Casio for service and the cost of repair was $46.58 (not including the cost of sending it them in the first place). Unbelievable that the cost of repair would exceed the cost of buying a new one! So much for G-Shock toughness and resiliency, and so much for Casio customer service. I'd give this zero stars if that was an option. Do your self a favor and buy something else.

Title: Great $44 watch
Text: Runs 4 to 5 seconds fast a week.  Still more accurate than a Rolex.  How many $44 watches have 200m water resistance and are certified by Nasa for manned space missions?  Not too many.  I own 50 watches but this is the one I wear daily.  I can actually see the display.  Battery life is up to 10 years if you go easy on the light.  My new Suunto Core battery lasts up to 1 year and it's impossible to see day or night at any contrast level.  If Bill Gates can wear a Casio so can I.  Great watch for $44.

Title: Like a Rock
Text: Okay, so maybe it's not in a Bob Seger song, but this thing just won't stop. For 7-8 years I had an earlier model G-Shock that Casio no longer makes (forget the exact model number, similar to DW-003), and it was retired and given to a relative. It still worked like a champ, and I only had to change the battery once. It was subjected to pretty rough use, including flow testing water systems. But I had always liked the simple, clean looks of the 5600 series -- so I snagged one of these DW-5600E-1V's from Amazon back in Jan. 2009. We are now into 2013 and the watch has been doing great. At this point it has been taken on hikes, worn in the river, carried in triple-digit and freezing temperatures, and generally been beat up doing just about anything and everything. Other than some wear and small nicks on the band and case, and a microscopic scratch on the bezel, it works like the day I unpacked it. (Wish I could have said the same of my Seiko SKX173 diver! One drop to the floor and that thing was history.) Bottom line... the G-Shocks just work, period!

Title: Was there ever a better watch ? Not for me.
Text: I'm on my 3rd one of this Casio watch type -- that's  20+ years worth. Overall the best watch I could hope for. Day, date time, alarm, glow in the dark, and more. Work, boating, fishing, in the shop-- then wash it off and go to the movies. Turn on the glow in the dark. Got a schedule? , tun on the 'beep on the top of the hour' feature.
