Band gets beat up or brittle, buy a new band and mount it up. Batteries last almost forever.

Title: GRAN RELOJ
Text: Exelente reloj, el diseño es muy bueno y la resistencia unica

Title: Great beater watch, accurate timekeeper
Text: I own four Casio watches. Two of them are tough solar, atomic G-Shocks. Another is a Triple Sensor. I bought this DW5600E-1V G-Shock as a beater watch on Black Friday for $33. I couldn't be happier with it. Not only is it tough as nails, waterproof, easy to read and comfortable to wear, but it's also the most accurate quartz timekeeper I've ever owned. After two and a half months of wear, I haven't had to adjust it. It's still in nearly perfect sync with my G-Shocks that sync to the atomic clock. Maybe I just got lucky, but the accuracy of this watch is very impressive.

Title: Absolute tank of a watch.
Text: This is my work watch (truck driver/road construction) and I tend to be hard on anything I wear to work and it has held up fantastic. I added a bumper and nato strap adapter. It has all of the great functions you would expect from a Casio watch. Overall very happy with it.

Title: Great for on my smaller wrist
Text: I use this on a daily bases all day at work as a powrsports tech. It gets beat on pretty good and holds up great. Oil and crud cleans off of it well. I also have small wrists and it fits supprisingly well, and it does not have an annoying knob digging into my wrist.

Title: Best Casio for the money
Text: I first purchased this Casio model while deployed to the Indian Ocean about 29 years ago.  As an Explosive Ordnance Disposal Diver, I grew tired of the five-pound Seiko dive watch issued by my diver locker.  It looked cool, but lost two minutes a day.  Because of the reliability of Casio dive watches, most Navy dive lockers purchased and issued Casios only a few years later.  When batteries died after a few years or the watch bands started cracking or broke, you were permitted to exchange for a new one.  After 26 years of Navy diving, I ended up with a few 6900 models which are bigger and bulkier than the DW5600.  When they all required new batteries and bands, I decided to go back to the first Casio I found truly functional without taking up my entire wrist.  The DW5600 provides all the features 95% of purchasers will require.  I've dove this watch on mixed gas to 200 feet and subjected it to plenty of mud and sand while diving on mines without issue.  No need to spend double for the "mudman" model.  This is the best watch for the money period!

Title: 6 plus year still works like new
Text: worth it

Title: great watch for the price
Text: This is my second G-shock.  I bought what looks like the indentical model about 11 years ago and amazingly, it was the same price...about $30.00.  Although I had to change the wrist band occasionally, they were easily available at mall watch stores.  The amazing thing about this watch was that I used it for 10 years without ever changing the battery.  The downside I guess, is that when I did go to get a battery replacement, the watch had died...a new replacement battery didn't get it to work.  Well, it certainly didn't owe me anything after 10 years of keeping accurate time and never showing a scratch on the face despite heavy use during all kinds of work and play.  Its ugly for sure, but considering I've owned a lot more fancy and expensive watches, this one is the most reliable and dependable...it never let me down and its alarm always worked when I needed it.  I never did use the other features but they always functioned.  For the price and reliability and if you like 'ugly', its a good bargain.  I am very happy with my replacement but had hoped to get another 10 years out of the original for sentimental sake.

Title: Battery Replacement
Text: I purchased this watch almost two years ago and it has served me excellently and faithfully thus far. I could not be more pleased with the actual watch itself. As to be expected though, the battery is getting towards the end of its life and needs replacing. No surprise there. However, I have contacted Casio three times now (only twice receiving a response in reply) with regards to the cost of a battery replacement. Both times the representatives informed me that Casio does not give estimates for repairs without first examining the watch in person. I explained clearly each time that what I desired was a quote for a simple battery replacement, a base cost for the procedure with the understanding that the price was an approximation of what the service would cost (obviously this would not be legally binding in any way) and could scale up from there. Essentially, I wanted them to ballpark it for me. Still I was given a long winded song and dance about Casio's policies and procedures, but wouldn't you know it - no price quote. That was when I was lucky enough to get a response at all. This did come as a surprise since I expected more in the way of quality customer service from Casio. I assume all the sheepishness regarding a quote on a battery replacement is because the servicing is likely to run higher than the cost of the watch itself. Of course, I have no way of knowing this for certain because I cannot get a straight-forward answer out of Casio to save my life! This secretive behavior regarding the pricing of a simple battery replacement is as frustrating as it is bizarre. This experience has really turned me off on Casio. I guess that I expected more in the way of honest well intentioned help and transparency from Casio. But I won't have to guess again, because now I know! 1 Star

Title: The honey badger of wristwatches
Text: The original tough timepiece. It's kind of the "honey badger" of watches - it doesn't give a ****. I wear this when working in the garage or when I'm outdoors. Bang it against a wall? No problem. Hot motor oil running down your arm? G-SHOCK don't care. Diving in after a dropped fishing pole? Non-issue. Crash your bike? No biggie. This thing is durable as all get out. Price is great if you consider the 200m WR, warranty, and features. Yes, the alarm is loud enough to wake you up. It's large, but not HUGE like other G-shocks. Out of all the watches I've ever owned, this is the one I feel I can count on in any situation. This is a casual/hard-use watch that reflects its utilitarian design mandate. Goes perfectly with workwear, steel-toed boots, adventure gear, space suit, etc. It "almost" works with business casual but would look out of place with a 3 piece suit.

Title: Cheap but reliable
Text: Cheap but sturdy, works well right out if the box, easy to adjust. G-shock basic but all I need. Will update this review if anything changes.

Title: Keeps great time but feeling for light switch can be difficult.See above
Text: See above. To answer your question, I use it for keeping time.

Title: Your new watch
Text: I cant think of a better watch to wear if you desire affordability, function, and toughness. Easy to read, super accurate, you can do your own battery changes. Wear it in the shower, run it over with the car. It is the same watch we had back in the 80s. I love it!

Title: Tough watch! Definitely get your money's worth!
Text: Husband loves this watch, it's the only watch he'll wear.  He has been wearing this particular style for 20+ years. We've only had to buy three of them over that time, only because the bands break, and we were unable to find a proper fitting replacement, the time piece still worked!

Title: All you need in a daily watch
Text: Barely taken it off since I got it! I got it since my other g shocks are not super readable, this one is  very easily readable, has alarm, timer, stopwatch and light, so everything I need for work or for exercise. As far as water resistance its a champ, I'm a butcher so this thing gets soaked in beef and chicken purge, marinades, soap, sanitizer, bleach, hot water. Easy to clean and keeps ticking.

Title: One of the best values for money
Text: I love the medium size, light weight, comfort, resistance to everything. Just an amazing value for money.

Title: Cheap G-Shock that lives up to it’s reputation
Text: I am not much of a watch expert, I've had a few cheaper automatic watches ( Seiko 5 ) and I own some of Casio's cheaper digital watches. With that being said, this watch is a bargain at $45. The functions are fairly intuitive, it keeps great time, and I feel that it's going to last for a very long time. This is the lowest rung on the ladder of the "square g-shocks" but after wearing this watch for a week I am very impressed by it. It is comfortable, accurate ( have not gained or lost any seconds in the past week) and the light is particularly good. I have used the alarm a few times but if you sleep with the watch on it may not be loud enough to wake you up. Overall this is an awesome, overbuilt, budget-friendly watch that will last for a long time.

Title: An enduring classic
Text: It will never let you down, it's inexpensive, and it looks great. Just buy the darn thing.

Title: Tough
Text: This watch is the most awesome watch.  I believe it is the original GSHOCK.  It’s not huge like the other ones.  Perfect for me.

Title: the display is smaller than the promotional line
Text: strange that the display is actually smaller than the promo line, I mean the dial may be bigger but the actual letters are smaller and more difficult to read. the buttons are classic Casio, which means it's more difficult to reach than Timex. I still like Casio for its classic looks, but Timex seems more ergonomically designed. Oh well, these are definitely not expensive watches so I can own both... many of both.

Title: Adjust button recessed too much, impossible to press
Text: It's surly a great watch for the price and I understand they purposesly made buttons recessed for protection. However, when I get one of dw 5600 on hand, the level of recession of the adjust button is just too much for me. There is no way I can push that button with my fingertip. I used to own a variation of 5610 never had I have any problem accessing the adjust button. Is it common for dw 5600 or just bad my luck.

Title: Awesome!
Text: It has a sleek and smooth stylish look. I love how it’s not bulky like some watch are. Simple and classic.

Title: Marine infantrymen and Navy SEALs use it for a reason
Text: This is the watch worn by the toughest men on the planet, and there are three simple reasons for it. 1. No moving parts means better shock resistance and waterproofing than any moving-parts (ie analogue, and particularly mechanical or automatic) watch can deliver. 2. Casio has perfected ruggedness in watches over the last 30 years - they are better than anyone at this game by now. 3. Simplicity of design and use means the timepiece is functional under the most stressful situations. The format of this excellent watch harkens back - way back - to the Casio Mariner, a watch that accompanied me to five oceans and six continents over more than two decades, and only gave up after I had beaten it mercilessly in surf, snow, desert sands and the occasional urban adventure. At under $40 shipped, this is the best value in a timepiece I'll ever get, and the same goes for you. The folks who retail radioactive luminescence on analogue dials want you to think that Navy SEALs use their watches, and maybe that's true - when they're on leave and trying to pick up recently released female felons at sleazy roadhouses. On the job they do what Marine infantrymen do - they strap on a G-shock and twist its face downward to minimise glare and movement when checking the time.

Title: alarm is not vert loud
Text: Need a louder sound on the alarm

Title: Timeless design & undisputed quality
Text: I was researching this watch for over six months, reading and reading several reviews, since my timex iroman strap and clap broke appart after two years of usage (and I wasn't even wearing it everyday), I decided to go for a more durable and realiable daily sport watch, which I can wear on the office, on weekends, working out, playing with my kids, off to the countryside, anywhere. This Casio was certainly the best choice, I've no doubt on quality and functionality, my only concern was the size because I've a small wrist but I solved it by trying one on at the local store.  The design now it looks more like a classic instead of a old model, everyone will notice a classic G Shock because of the brand/model combination, it's even more captivating than newer G Shock models. Best of all, I saved about 40% of the price compared to the local retailer, I took less than a week for Amazon to hit my local PO box outside US.

Title: Great value for some nostalgia and true beater watch.
Text: I purchased this watch for nostalgic reasons. I wore this watch in the early 90's while in the Marine Corps. This watch is is fantastic. We all know how robust it is and simple. It feels great on the wrist and does everything it's supposed to. The only issue I have is pushing the adjust button. I can't do it, I always have to use something like a pen tip. So it makes it hard for me to change things like the timer on the fly. Other than that I have no complaints. For $40 it's well worth it.

Title: Do Yourself A Favor And Buy This Watch
Text: I purchased this watch in June of 2007 from Amazon (just looked it up).  Since that time, it was been my "go to" watch and has been on my wrist almost constantly.  From every ocean vacation to every backpacking adventure, it has never failed me.  In the last eight years, I have replaced the band once (to be expected) and that is it!  It is practically military grade in its build quality and has handled everything I have thrown at it with no issues.  I am, FINALLY AFTER EIGHT YEARS, going to replace the battery because the backlight is beginning to dim when depressed.  It seems to GAIN about 30 seconds every six months but that is not a problem since I synchronize it every DST time change.  I cannot reccommend this watch enough.  If you are looking for a no frills watch that tells time and date and that is it, purchasing this watch is a no brainer.

Title: Delivered on time.
Text: The watch is a little on the heavy side. It will take time to get use to the weight.

Title: Love it
Text: What more can I say.  When I wear it, I shower in it.  It is light, not huge and not thick.

Title: Takes me back to High School
Text: It's the most basic G-Shock sold - very easy to use and operate. It's a modern version of the watch I owned in the early 90's with some welcoming positive changes. First of all, the illuminating light makes it very easy to see when dark. Secondly, the hourly chime is not nearly as annoying as the only one.  Instead of a loud "Beep Beep", it's 2 faint beeps that are the perfect volume. This one also comes with a 'light flashing' option when the alarm is going off.  Not sure what the advantage of this would be unless you were hard of hearing and happened to be looking @ the watch, but there's no drawbacks to the option. All in all, it's a very basic watch with 1 alarm, a timer, a stopwatch, an hourly chime and the time, date and day on the main screen. My Dad stole my old G-Shock from the early 90s and still uses it today, so if this one is even close in durability and reliability, then it will be around a long time.

Title: nai  cao
Text: the  watch is  naicao

Title: I wish I knew about this huge design flaw
Text: I've only had this watch for a day, and it seems like a perfectly good watch to use, with the exception of one giant flaw in its design. The button used to adjust the time, alarms, timer, and stopwatch, is extremely recessed into the case, with a big piece of the case material hanging over it. This makes it incredibly difficult to press the button. Some might not find it so tough, but my fingers strength isn't the best, and my fingertips are sensitive to pressure. You have to press the button VERY hard, even with a fingernail. Without a fingernail? Next to impossible. I don't want to have to use a pen or a key to use the button. I feel as if I should be able to adjust the watch using my hands, like most other watches. The presence of this hard-to-press button makes this watch a product that is not for me. As for the other functions, they all seem to work pretty well. I like the addition of the current time to the stopwatch and timer modes. The face is bright and easy to read. The other three buttons are fairly easy to press. If you can get around the adjust button issue, this seems like a good, solid watch for the price.

Title: good
Text: top quality

Title: Awesome!
Text: At first I wasn't sure if I really wanted this watch  but once I got it and started wearing it I began to like it more and more. This watch is made so well, you can tell just by looking at it and holding it. It has kept perfect time . It's a simple watch, it doesn't have a lot of extras for a gshock but that's what I love about it. I have a lot of watches but since I bought this watch I haven't worn any of my others. I'm also a girl and this watch is definitely big but not so big that it's looks weird on my wrist. I like using the the timer and I love using the stop watch for walking on the treadmill or any kind of exercises.I would recommend this watch to anyone and everyone. Don't hesitate you won't regret buying it for a second

Title: Purfect
Text: For the money, this watch ticks a lot of boxes. Has the "G-Shock" and Casio name. With that name it obviously has the reliability and durability factor down. It definitely had a pretty strong retro look, especially for a gshock. But honestly I like that kind of look. Just a good watch to keep in the rotation.

Title: Great for the price, no problems at all.
Text: Short review: Works great, just buy it. In depth: After 2 weeks of wear 24/7, I have worn this at work where it has been banged against doors, steel shelving and other things. No marks and no scratches. This is the main reason I bought this and it has served this purpose well. I’ve worn it in the woods and no problems with the cold weather (20F to 30F) for hours of hunting and hiking. Been in the shower every morning and no issues there either. Overall it is a very useful and robust timepiece but maybe lacking some style.

Title: The perfect accurate, tough, good quality watch
Text: This watch is awesome. I am in my 50’s. This is my 3rd g shock. The watches never failed, the bands did. I carried one of these bandless for 3 months in USMC bootcamp. Made it all the way! After graduating I bought a new band and wore the crud out of it for a couple 3or 4 more years!!!!!

Title: Great watch for the money
Text: I have been wearing one of these for years and it is finally torn up enough to replace. Actually I will keep wearing it, but I just bought a new one to wear when I am not working. Really durable watch. Great value for the price.

Title: I love the no frills options
Text: This is one of the simplest and classiest G-shocks out there.  I love the no frills options, ease of use, and clear view to see the time (I mean this is the main purpose of a watch).  Along with a great price, I get a watch that will be able to withstand the elements.  I swim/shower with the watch and the watch gets a lot of sand (from spending time at a beach) and have had no issues to date.  I even dropped the watch a few times and not even a scratch.  For those of you that want a watch with a heart beat monitor, thermometer, barometer, automatic time setting feature, etc. then look somewhere else cause you're not going to get it here.  But for those if you that want a dependable and easy to use watch, then this is the one to get!  I'm most interested to see how much battery life I can get out of this.

Title: Just a great watch! With a dim display
Text: Originally purchased this thinking it might become my “on the weekend” beater watch. It’s great! Size is perfect, light weight, great features, great price. My only negatives: display is relatively small and dim. Not sure. New battery would help this but from other reviews I’ve read, seems to be common. Awesome watch, just a tad hard to read easily. I’ll probably upgrade to the 5610 or perhaps go higher. GShocks rule!

Title: Great!
Text: Excellent quality, as expected from a G Shock, great value.

Title: Casio, Rolex & pi
Text: I have other watches but this one I can't seem to take off i enjoy wearing it and the fact that I don't have to worry about it even better I just know its going to survive everything I put it through and for the price you really do get the bang for your buck classic design easy to read I do wish the light was on for atleast a few more seconds thats my only thing, Overall great product I've already gifted 2

Title: Great Simple watch
Text: Great little everyday watch for the price. The buttons are a little hard to press but other than that it's been great

Title: Accurate - sturdy - all goog
Text: After six years and eleven months I had to replace the battery that came with this watch!  The watch continues to be remarkably accurate - typically gaining between six and ten seconds a month. I am a bit of a time nerd - no surprise! GREAT WATCH!

Title: One and only....!
Text: If you can only have 1 watch to survive anything anywhere and any situations. This is it. I have Rolex GMT master Ii, Omega speed master. Brietling Chromat, panerai... you name it I got it. Apple watch too. But if world is ending and we are being swept away by chaos... this will be the watch on my wrist. Love it!

Title: Justo lo pedido
Text: Compre el reloj hace 20 años y lo perdí, excepto por la manilla es exactamente el mismo 😍😍😍

Title: One of the best Casio watches
Text: Love Casio watches and this watch is such a classic. It is very durable and use it for working out, going on hikes or just casual wear and does the job. Great value for the money; cannot go wrong with a Casio.

Title: Very cool classic
Text: Just like the watch my pops used to wear. Absolutely love this purchase, going to buy a 2nd.

Title: Cool watch
Text: A great go to watch for heavy work!

Title: Good dependable digital watch at an affordable price!
Text: I purchased this model for a “beater,” for days when I want to wear a G Shock but not damage my GW-M5610. I own 2 GW-M’s & 2 DW’s. The GW-M’s are made in Thailand; the DW’s are made in China. Though there are differences in size & quality, the DW5600E is well-worth its low price. The display is clear and sharp, making it easy to read. I don’t care for the strap (same style as the GW-M but not as sturdy) so I installed a conversion kit from JaysandKays to install a 22mm Zulu strap—making it much more comfortable. If you are new to square G Shock’s or just want to add to your collection, the DW5600E is a good choice. No negatives are serious enough to prevent me from enjoying it.

Title: Muy excelente
Text: No hay nada en contra todo bien

Title: Excelente pieza de relojería
Text: Me encanta su tamaño, su diseño atemporal, fácil de leer, completa la información en el dial, sus funcionalides básicas y creo que suficientes para la mayoría de las personas. Se siente fuerte, de buena calidad. No se puede pedir nada mas por el precio. Altamente recomendado.

Title: Simple With Everything I Need
Text: This watch is simple at first glance, perhaps too simple. but once you get into its functionality and operation, it is just right. I have owned many watches that were too flashy or too simple, and I often didn't wear them because I had no use for them, or was tired of all the useless bells and whistles. With a new job that required a watch with a second hand and preferably a countdown timer, I began researching digital watches. This one popped out because of the simplicity of the face as well as the stopwatch and countdown timer. an added bonus was that it keeps the month/day up to the year 2100 when you put in the current year, that's a nice feature. Also, the watch is very durable: I do work with wrenches around pipes and cement and have banged it against many things and it is none the worse for the wear. the outer protection protects the face, and it is shock resistant, so I don't even hesitate putting it in places I wouldn't even think about putting any of my other watches. A great buy at a great price, I expect it to last a long time.

Title: Small top left button
Text: I like Casio watches. They're easy to use. I bought the $13 version, but the band broke in a matter of months. This watch is durable and the rubber is thicker which is probably why it has lasted longer than the cheaper quality version. One con about the watch: 1. The top left button is difficult to press as it is shorter than the other buttons. This is a huge inconvenience at times when I am exercising and trying to reset the watch count down timer. Pros: 1. Durable 2. Thick rubber band 3. Water tested - works well 4. Stylish for a cheap watch (my style standards probably need to be updated) 5. Works as intended and the count down timer is the main reason I bought it

Title: Casio G- Shock Men's Classic Digital Watch DW5600E-1V 200M Water Resistant
Text: So glad they're still producing this watch and have not changed it. It has everything I need (use) and nothing I don't. It's the right size- not over bulky, a quick easy read and extremely tough. The time, date, and alarm are all displayed on the main face. Very easy to use, waterproof with a light, alarm, stopwatch, and countdown timer. The timer & alarm also have a silent (flashing backlight) option. Hourly chime, military time, and split stopwatch are the other functions. This is my second watch. My first one lasted 11 years & only ended due to being crushed by a machine. If you don't set the flashing backlight with the daily alarm the battery lasted me five years-otherwise its about two. It's survived the heavy vibration of operating 90 pound jackhammers for construction and the tough and abrasive cleaning of gasoline and solvents from working on cars. Its nice to have a reliable watch that you don't have to take off everytime you go to work. Normally goes for around $65 to $75 but purchased it for just over $40 on Amazon. Great deal for a great watch.  Casio Men's DW5600E-1V G-Shock Classic Digital Watch 200M Water resistant.

Title: This is an amazing product and is about as close to perfect as ...
Text: This is an amazing product and is about as close to perfect as a digital watch can get. All of its functions work well, the illumination is more than adequate, it's lightweight, waterproof, and the batteries last at least a couple of years.  Unlike other, larger G shock models, it fits beneath the cuff portion of a sleeve so that it's comfortable even with a long sleeve shirt.  I have worn this model and its predecessors for almost 20 years, and have used all its functions regularly with no problems ever.  I wear it to shower, and to swim and dive a few hours every week, and not one of them has ever leaked.  The illumination function makes the watch face easy to see, and it's bright enough to double as a night light, when one is needed for a quick moment.  The band will last a long time, and even so, the watch Itself will outlast it.

Title: Survived 6 years in the Marines and still works great!!
Text: I served in the Marines for 6 years both in the conventional infantry and special operations. I put this watch through hell and back, and it still works as good as the day I got it. If you want a watch that will out live you LOL and make it through any situation you can imagine, then this is the watch for you!

Title: very rugged watch
Text: I've owned 3 of these watches and just purchased my 4th since around 1988. I am a heavy equipment mechanic and wear one all day and with the abuse i give it all day it holds up pretty good. Replaced my last one after roughly 6 years due to repeatedly bending and breaking the pins and finally wearing the holes so it wouldn't hold a pin anymore. I don't really fault the watch for that cause i am always catching the watch on things while im working on equipment and proper fitting replacement pins are hard to find unless you buy a replacement band with pins. Only problem i have with this watch is that everyone i've owned either gained or lost a minute about every couple months. Not a huge deal since it takes the abuse i put it through, just go to time.gov and reset every once in awhile and reset. All in all its a pretty good, not too big, water, grease, grime and shock resistant watch for the money.

Title: A great product
Text: Bought this watch because I was nervous about wearing more expensive watches around downtown chicago but it has proven to be a joy. It is legible and easy to use, particularly when I need to change time while moving between time zones, something I do fairly frequently.

Title: Easy setup, long lasting.
Text: Awesome watch, cheap but well worth the money. I have a high end G-shock but wanted something not so fancy for work as I am in the dirt. This definitely cuts it, it gives you all the high tech features at a clean, crisp, high quality, low cost price.

Title: Great watch
Text: Like it a lot

Title: Classic, works great
Text: Watch is fantastic as a regular wear/beater. love it

Title: The Dreaded Sunken Adjust Button
Text: I loved, loved, loved the design and look of the watch. So very, very easy to look at you wrist and tell the time with a crisp, nice sized "positive" digital display until....I'm timing my round of golf and the adjust button gets stuck below it's housing...I'm fidgeting with the thing for three holes and just can't get to the button. I go home do my research and discover...I'm not the only one..The button will end up being sunk deeper in the case than it was originally, making the stopwatch feature and other controls reliant on the adjust button useless.  I had the watch for a week. Amazon's customer service was excellent. They provided a refund almost instantly. Guess what I did? I bought another one!  I'm hoping to luck up and get a version of the watch where the adjust button doesn't get stuck and I can give the watch a five star rating.

Title: Works good for surfing
Text: Use it every time I surf and  works well with cold water surfing so I can never be late for work or any lame important adult business and still catch as many waves as I can!

Title: Lack of product description
Text: The watch has a button that is permanently depressed that wasn’t mentioned in the item description when I went to purchase.

Title: abused and neglected: still going
Text: I have been wearing this watch every day for 2 years and 8 months to the day. Here's is what I have done to it in that time: -Fine woodworking with high grit (1000+) abralon sanding, covering the watch in ultra fine wood dust (at least 100 times) -Fallen off a motorcycle at about 40mph into the sand (twice) -Banged it into walls/corners (countless times--I work in a restaurant and I am clumsy) -Soaked it in water (countless times--see above) -Hot, cold, rainy, snowy highway motorcycle riding along the east coast (1200-1400 miles) -3 months of brutal heat (upwards of 120 degrees) in the Saharra dessert, complete with constant exposure to dust and sand -much more Every feature of the watch still works, and it still looks just as bad as it did the day I bought it. This watch is a great tool that I am privileged to own. For tactical and active applications, I wouldn't choose another. Buy with confidence.

Title: My 3rd one since the 1980's
Text: Love this watch but replacing the bands is a bit tricky and you will have to do it because the watch lasts for ever. I still have the first two but I bang them up pretty bad in my construction job. The first two ran a little fast (half a second per day) but this one seem to be right on time after 5 days

Title: No frills, rugged little watch
Text: I'm a soldier and attended training earlier this year where we actually were prevented from most modern watch features like GPS, step count, compass, barometer...etc.  This watch worked great and has grown on me.  I think I'll keep wearing it even though I'm no longer restricted to such a bare bones model.

Title: A fast easy replacement for a watch.
Text: I have had a duplicate watch for many years. I was unable to change the time for the end of Daylight Savings Time. I wanted a replacement.

Title: Does it all and price is right
Text: Seems well made

Title: Classic and Tough
Text: Classic design and rugged durability but someone at Cadio please fix the adjust button issue. Unless you have long nails there is no way your pushing that button in to reset a timer or alarm.

Title: Perfect watch
Text: I like this watch very much

Title: cheaper but reliable
Text: it can be user over five years or more

Title: Recessed Adjust Button
Text: QC issue. The Adjust Button came pushed in so far, that it's flush with the side; very difficult and annoying to set because of this.

Title: simple perfect watch
Text: First off this watch is great. I own a couple other g shocks that are much bigger with a lot of useless dials that aren't necessary.  What I like about this watch is that its smaller so it wont get caught on stuff. Time and date are easy to read and the green light mode is great. Screw down back so changing battery is easy. The resin housing and band on this watch along with other g shocks is amazing.  I work construction and this watch gets dirty a lot and all you gotta do is rinse it off with water and it looks like new.  Its nice not having a crown that sticks out because my other more expensive watches will get caught on my jean pocket while pulling my hand out and the crown will pull out causing to change time, dont have to worry about that happening with this, and its nice that its 200m water resistant. For 40 bucks, I highly recommend buying this watch.  Very accurate and will last a very long time.

Title: The one watch every aficionado needs to own
Text: Fits well on the wrist.  Lower profile then other bulkier G-Shock options.  Easy to set and very readable.  Excellent value for money. The only negative was that it was shipped in a very flimsy cardboard box that was crushed upon arrival.

Title: Every guy should have this watch
Text: A gshock is the toughest watch out there. It can survive anything you throw at it. Water, mud, ice, etc. It’s can be a daily driver for people that workout, do yard work, work in healthcare, police, etc. Easy to wash and no need to worry about damage or scratching it up!

Title: Indestructible
Text: I'm an avid surfer, swimmer, hiker, and skier and have owned this watch for three years. I've put this watch through thousands of hours of surfing and hundreds of hours of the other things. I've taken it diving down to about 25 feet, buried it in the sand and the snow, left it in the sun for hours, camped in temperatures from 110F to 0F. I wear it every day, in the shower, at the gym, at work, and playing sports. The watch just doesn't care. The latch, strap, and all buttons still work like new. An incredibly robust design.

Title: Loved my last one, tough as nails!
Text: I had one of these from the 80’s that finally lost it’s bezel.  It looks too rough to use and they don’t stock replacement parts anymore, so I purchased this one as a replacement.  It is noticeably different in that my old Japanese model had a diver style back that was screwed in, this model is made in China and has what appear to be eyeglass screws holding the back on.  This may make changing the battery easier.  That’s the only thing I had to do for my last one. So far it has worked great, and is water resistant as expected.  We’ll see how it holds up over time.

Title: Rugged, reliable basic watch.
Text: Have been using this model watch exclusively for probably 25 years. They generally last at least 5 years of daily abuse. Kayaking, scuba diving,  construction work, etc. Time & date are right there & easy to see. I have to initial & date a million pieces of paper per day, and I get to where I don't try to remember the date - just glance down at my wrist. Don't think I've ever replaced a battery, they last forever. Usually get to the point that one or more buttons sticks to the point that I can't adjust the time at the DST time change, so I get a new one. Thought about getting the solar version, but don't see the point. Almost never use the stopwatch feature, but it's there and works as expected.

Title: Old school
Text: I can read the time with out wearing my glasses.I don’t need all the bells and whistles…And loved the price

Title: Best Casio watch ever!
Text: I purchased this watch 33 years ago and it just stopped working this year.  I hope this new one can last at least 20.  Casio makes the best watches no doubt about it. Highly recommend if your needing a watch that can take a lot abuse and keep going.

Title: Adjust button hard to press but is awesome watch. Love it.
Text: Awesome beater watch for me. The build is light and though also the black color is one of the reason i buy this watch. The back light of this watch is bright and acceptable compare to my previous watch which is casio f91-w. The one thing i dont like the most is the adjust button. Is so hard to press. I need a pen or toothpick to press it. Idk it happened only to mine or maybe is built like that. If the adjust button can be easly press. I might give this five stars. But overall is nice watch to wear daily. Update... my adjust button is getting harder to press. It hurts my finger. So sad such good watch has this kind of problem.

Title: This is The Only Watch I've Ever Owned...Several Times (It's That Good)!
Text: I've had this exact model, three or four times, in my lifetime up to this point. These never break; you'll lose them before that happens! Ultra durable, waterproof; perfect first watch for a kid. This thing grows with you. I will never not seek out this model first and foremost!

Title: Not the watch in the picture
Text: This is the Illuminator version of the gshock not the fox fire.

Title: The best 1 Watch Collection
Text: Anyone who collects watches should absolutely have a 5600.

Title: Quality
Text: Excellent watch/ Im a vet used the g shock overseas in 7 different countries/ water resistant held up long battery life Great watch

Title: An icon
Text: THE iconic G shock. Great watch. Not too big like some G shocks. Retro look without being too nerdy. Fits under a sleeve of a shirt but also matches t shirt and jeans. Obviously it's not a dress watch so you probably wouldn't wear to a wedding or anything but day to day it's fine. 200m water resistance so can be worn scuba diving as I've done and it's more than up to it. The strap is comfortable, though I changed mine to a NATO using the adaptors available elsewhere but it's better on the original. Great watch. Simple. Lots of features..bit fiddly hitting the buttons but not much to complain about. For less than 50 quid you get an icon.

Title: basic watch - very durable
Text: so far so good.  used in pool very often and no problems thus far. *update* after 3 years, no issues.  i take on runs, out in surf, in pool.  all no issues.  even a jacuzzi (with 100 degree water) did not seem to phase it.  there are only a few features, but it does those few things without issue.  it's "chunky" to wear, so it's not always comfortable with a jacket.  important: there is no gps function or other "modern day" watch features.  this makes it more limited in use, and less attractive for everyday ware compared to what else is available today for purchase.

Title: good basic
Text: This is a very good basic take a beating won`t let you down watch. I like a cell phone that makes and receives call, THAT`s IT, And I like a watch that tells time and date. No faze of the moon no time in butholeastan. Plus the band is big enough for a big wrist. GOOD WATCH  Almost a year now and I like this watch very much. .......'..'......2 years later still working great, But I did manage to break the band, ordered another, I'll let you know witch fits best. The only weakness of these watches seems to be the bands,the older casio's I had showed the same weakness in the band, It would not stop me from buying this watch, but be forewarned... ....3 years 3 months later the cover of the watch has broken and the replacement is 14.99, The only flaw in this watch is the band and cover, If casio would adress this problem the watch would be dam near perfect

Title: The definitive watch
Text: I have been using this watch daily for the past year and a half, it is the first watch that I have owned. I can say that this is the definitive watch and there is no other watch that I would prefer more. After researching and reading reviews I choose this because it had the two specifications I was searching for; function and style. First, the style is discrete, it's not flashy, bulky or have unnecessary parts thrown on it. It serves to tell you the time which it does really well. One feature I love is that when in other modes it will show you the time in the corner of the display. It has all the mode functions you could need to tell time and it has a simple layout for executing actions. I needed a watch, nothing grand or overly complex, something that had a high build quality and was simple to use. That was exactly what I found in this watch. I would recommend it to any and everyone.

Title: El mejor reloj Casio G-shock!!!
Text: El mejor reloj G-shock para mí. Pequeño e indestructible!!!. Ahhh..... Y barato!!!.

Title: Best G Shock every built.
Text: I have several watches, this is the cheapest watch I own, but this is the one I wear basically everday, very comfortable easy to read, has the date, day and military time for work, it's perfect.

Title: Toughest cool watch, tiny numbers make it hard to read.
Text: I wanted to love this watch but when I got it I couldn't believe how small the display is. I can barely read the time! Maybe I'm getting old, a younger set of eyes might see this just fine. Also, overall watch size is a bit smaller than I like. Other than those two points, I think it's a great watch. Instead of wearing a nicer watch when it might take a beating, use this as a go to, thrasher watch. The 10 year battery and 200m depth ability is worth it. it was in Guinness Book of Records for strongest watch with a tank sitting on it or something...

Title: Wrong day setting
Text: I’ve had this watch before and was pleased with it. This particular one would not allow the day function to set properly. I didn’t consider this defect worthy of going through the process of returning it.

Title: Best bang-for-buck
Text: I'm a scientist and a scuba diver, this watch delivers in every field. 10/10

Title: High quality, always reliable.
Text: Terrific watch at a very reasonable price. Perfect for swimmers, runners, or any other activity where a timer/watch is needed.

Title: The adjust button was unpressable
Text: I know many have said this, and I didn't believe them to my detriment. But the adjust button was simply unpressable, and that button happens to be critical for not only setting time, but especially for timer and stopwatch features, making them next to useless. In order to press it, I basically had to push my hardest using the tinyest corner of my thumb nail to engage the button, and even then it would only engage every few times. I promptly returned it, which is a shame because I really liked that watch, it looks and feels great, but function over form.

Title: best resistant watch
Text: love it, only issue is that one of the buttons is kind of hard to press.

Title: Wanted Durable, Got It!
Text: Nothing else to say about this piece! Bought the protector roll bar and some stick on screen covers and it's been along for the ride working on heavy equipment with me every day since I got it.

Title: Could use some visual tweaks, but nice overall.
Text: Pretty good. Nice that it is waterproof. Very durable. For $40 this thing is a steal, and its pretty slim. Really glad it displays in 24 hour time. If I were redesigning it, I would have less writing on the face, make the screen a little bigger, and improve the viewing angles. Maybe make the alarm a little more simplified. Update: Still going strong as of 11/6/17, though sunscreen will damage the finish of the device! The mineral crystal glass is much harder than I originally thought, and it has survived sand and volcanic grit, which is impressive. No scratches thus far! I would like to see it auto update to account for daylight savings time, but that is a small complaint. Overall, great watch.

Title: Rugged and practica;l
Text: I wanted a watch that keeps good time, has a mineral crystal, and is reasonably waterproof that doesn't have to be babied and is not too expensive. After looking at many this one stood out. Satisfied after about a month of daily wear. Like the back light function.

Title: Great Watch
Text: I've been wearing this exact watch for over 20 years. I gave the last one to a relative, so had to buy a new one and fully expect it to last the rest of my life. Typically, I get 4-5 years out of it before the battery needs to be replaced. This is the G-SHOCK you want, don't settle for the cheaper models. I never take this watch off, it goes in the pool, shower, ocean and during all activities and continues to go no matter what I throw at it. The wrist band, for me, under these conditions, usually only needs to be replaced once every 4 years or when the battery needs to be changed.

Title: Watch buckle
Text: Bomb watch only thing I don't like but really isn't an issue is the watch buckle. Was hoping for the OG g shock ones but anyway its koo. The buckle is silver and has a weird shape

Title: Great watch. Awful shipping and packaging.
Text: The watch is perfect. It works great. It looks great. It fits great on my small wrist. 5 stars. It was, however, shipped as if it was garbage. The fragile box was tossed in a padded envelope and the box arrived crushed. 1 star. That lowers the rating to a 3 star average. The watch survived because it's a G-Shock but any other watch would have died in the mail. Please treat your customers with respect.

Title: My favorite watch to date; very high quality for the price
Text: This watch is a brilliant device, and I'm forever grateful to the innovation that transpires in Japan. It stays secure on my wrist without strapping it tightly, in contrast to my other watches that tend to slide over to an awkward angle unless I tighten their straps so much that the watch parts uncomfortably impress my skin. Not only is the watch comfortable, but its display is also very easy to read with all the important data stated on the "home" screen. The light is easy to use, the buttons remain protected, and you know that the watch as a whole will be able to take a beating for years to come.

Title: Replacement in Kind
Text: After 19 years it was time to replace my G-Shock watch.  About three years ago the watch band needed replacment and then three months ago the battery finally went.  When replacing the battery they didn't have the correct tool to remove the back and cracked part of the front the case (noticed this after leaving).  When replacing the battery they said it wasn't as good as the original one and would only last few years at best.  So it seemed like a good time to replace the watch.  It would probably cost more to replace the battery again that what I originally paid for the watch. With all the different models and features that G-Shock has evoled into at first it was a hard decision for what model to get.  In the end--I just needed a rugged watch with good time accuracy and basic functions.  Feels comfortable to wear--forgot how nice the original watch band is versus the replacement I had to get with the first G-Shock.  Expect to get the same life out of this one as the first one.

Title: Just Replaced After 15 Years
Text: This watch has been a fine companion for over 14 years.  I'm a semi retired guide and this has literally been round the world and back.  It has all the features I really need and none of the crap I don't (I do have a Sunto that I don't wear and a Seiko that I do).  I liked the DW5600e so much that the protective rubber casing eventually cracked and wore off.  I guess I got my moneys worth. Saturday I caught the replacement velcro band on a jib block while racing the Hobie Cat.  Whoops - guess the fish in Cacasde Reservior won't be late for dinner.  Purchased the replacement today for less than what I think I payed for the origional.  Thats value. If want something that works and will last a long time buy this watch.  Otherwise move along - you will not appreciate new school coming back around the circle to old school simplicity and form.  I don't often review gear but this deserves it. Truly a classic.

Title: Awesome watch - can't beat the value - you will want to wear it every single day
Text: This watch grows on you. Initially I didn't make much of it, but then it just grew on me.  That classic 80's timeless design is incredible. It's an almost indestructible watch that just tells you the time and you will wear this every single day for decades and decades.  Compare this to 'smart' watches which are nothing more than a distraction on your wrist that you goes out of style in a few months.

Title: Sturdy, solid design with minor problem
Text: The adjust button is unreachable. You would have to use some sharp object to press it. Digits can only be seen at a certain angle under illumination.

Title: Es bueno
Text: Esta bien el precio con relación a las funciones

Title: Actually Unbreakable.
Text: I am not easy on anything. The term "unbreakable" doesn't apply to me. But this watch has been through it all. Oil, dirt, water, welding, saw dust, it has been run over by my truck, dropped off my house, and closed in my door. Nothing can stop this watch!!

Title: Good not great
Text: Not quite the same watch of 25 years ago. Band cheaper and harder, plastic vs silicone feel. Thinner as well. Not disappointed but not super excited either. Probably pass it on to a buddy.

Title: A must have!
Text: My husband loves this watch for its simplicity, durability, and functionality. It’s nice to go with most any style of outfit. Great buy!

Title: Fantastic watch for my boyfriend
Text: Very comfortable watch, although I plan on getting a jays and Kay’s adapter for a cloth band as well as their bull bars to help protect this watch forever more. With care and a supply of batteries, the Casio DW5600 is known to be able to survive for as long as you are alive and under normal circumstances, long after. It’s small size makes for an amazing fit on small and medium wrists, however if you happen to have larger wrists I would recommend a larger g shock. All the functions you need like alarm, timer and stopwatch. Keeps time accurately. Only costs $45. Just buy the watch, it’s great and you can return it if you don’t like it as much as everyone else.

Title: A Solid and Basic Watch NuttinFancy
Text: This is one of the oldest models of GSHOCK and i have had very little trouble with it. Sometimes Ill wake up and the screen will be blank but I think that is becuase of the battery save mode and my other issue is with the Edit button found on the bottom left which is very hard to press, which might be a good thing so I do accidently press it and change the time. This watch is great! Wish it was a little slimmer to fit better with dress shirts but this is deffinatly one of the slimest GSHOCKs you can get.

Title: KEEPS ON PURRING
Text: Simple, well designed and constructed, fairly inexpensive compared to others with most of the same features( some that I do not use)!! Keeps on running year after year( don't be jealous Energizer Bunny). Doesn't mind getting wet(rated to 300 feet-like I'm ever going to that depth). or dropped(not from the One World Trade Center though). For my preferences, is comfortable, is very easy to read, and has the option for the 24 hour clock, and 'just keeps purring(or what ever these electronic watches do(it's not tick tock though). If and when the battery poops out, send it to Casio( they are able to seal it back up so it doesn't leak), use a jeweler with the same abilities, or just buy a new one. I took my first one, many, many years ago, to a jeweler who changed the battery, but didn't seal it properly. Needless to say, even when swimming, it leaked.

Title: G Shock
Text: Great price, ended up returning

Title: JUST LIKE MY OLD ONE.
Text: WAS EXACTLY LIKE THE ONE i USED DAILY FOR 35+ YEARS ( AS BEST AS I CAN REMEMBER) WITH NO PROBLEMS EXCEPT NEW BATTERIES AND WORN OUT STRAPS. HAVE NOT TRIED THIS ONE IN THE WATER YET AND HOPE IT PERFORMS AS WELL AS THE FIRST ONE.

Title: Great Product
Text: Water resistant, great to wear anywhere anytime.

Title: Tough watch
Text: I've had several G-Shock watches since the late '80s. They've all taken a lot of abuse and held up well.

Title: Great , as always
Text: Great watch.  Fits great, looks great.  Very durable.  What more can you ask for out of a G-Shock ? The only reason I gave it 4 out of 5 stars is because out of all the G-Shocks I’ve worn, this one pulls my arm hair the most.

Title: Simply the best digital watch!
Text: This is the best casio watch that I've ever bought. I had only seen the watch through the internet and I was a bit nervous, thinking it was going to be too big for me but It turned out to be just perfect. The head of the watch is a bit big (I always used previous small models by casio), but I like the way it looks on my wrist, it even works on small wrists like mines. The watch feels well made,so you don't have to worry about taking a shower or swimmig using this bad boy. I would describe it as the perfect watch by casio, cause it's not too big like most of g-shocks neither too small like the previous digital models,it's just the perfect size for the people who's looking for that medium size on a wrist watch.

Title: Old School G Shock
Text: Recently received my G Shock 5600E .Classic  old school look with all the water resistance, tough but still a good looking sports watch , with that cool blue backlight that makes it an easy to read time display. Very happy  great watch excellent value for the price.

Title: Fine watch of substance
Text: After using a smaller, cheaper Casio for years, it is nice to have a heavier, more substantial watch.  The display is very clear, and the stop watch, which I use all the time for working out, running and swimming, as well as cooking, is easy to access and operate.  I highly recommend this watch.

Title: Perfect watch
Text: I got this watch for my husband for his birthday. He works in law enforcement and this watch was perfect for him. Price wise I think is very good. He wanted something simple

Title: Practical and cool lookin’
Text: Assuming it’s as water resistant as casio claims, this thing is dope. I have quite a few watches from the brand and they all perform well. That said, there is something to consider about this one that has an easy fix: its mineral crystal will scratch; simply get a screen protector and or a wire bumper/guard.

Title: Works as advertised..
Text: Works as advertised.. Love it

Title: Super
Text: Empingao

Title: Another excellent Casio product.
Text: I have owned other Casio watches and they are very accurate, with a great battery life.  The only problem I had with a less expensive Casio was the watch was great, but the band was junk.  And to replace the band cost more that to replace the watch.  This watch has a much better band and I expect to have a better chance of wearing it many years longer.  This watch is very well built and I expect to get several years of excellent service.  I use the stop watch functions a lot to time my rest intervals while weight training.  The only negative is the print of the watch face is almost too small to read.  Good thing the positions can be easily memorized.  Also, the "adjust" button is very hard to use, but the other three buttons work much better.  Time will tell but Casio is a good bet.

Title: Good watch functions
Text: I got this watch for the count down timer.  The one thing I don't like is how hard it is to use the Adjust button, it is recessed too far down to use my finger.  I have to use a pen, pencil or other pointed object.  Additionally, the watch has raised areas around each button so one doesn't accidentally hit a button.  That's something I have never had an issue with other watches that didn't have these safeguards.  All in all, this is a good watch that is better than their cheaper watches.

Title: Tough as nails. Gets the job done
Text: It's been through everything: the gym, hikes, swims, movie houses, heartbreak, runs. I have other Diesel and Seiko watches but I keep on coming back to my old trusty G Shock. It's been 3 years since it was shipped by Amazon and still the battery is going strong. I often abuse the light feature especially when running or hiking outdoors, but it's never given up on me. The strap and the glass face are still solid and have no signs of wearing out any time soon. Great at telling the time, good visibility and readable font. As for things to improve on: it has a very basic and linear Alarm and Stopwatch function. But you probably knew that because you bought this old classic model. G Shock: gets the job done!

Title: Not like my last watch
Text: The adjuster button is sunken in a little that I can’t adjust by hand. I have to use a pointed item to make  seconds blink. Also, the days of the week are numbers 0-99, not the days of the week abbreviated. Looks great!!

Title: Durable, Lightweight, Reliable
Text: Simply a classic watch.  I like the fact that the face isn't as big as the modern g-shock watches. It's subtle yet displays all the information you would need at a quick glance.  The viewing angle isn't as good as more modern displays but it does its job.  It's as durable as other g shocks and is a no nonsense time keeper.  It has a turquoise backlight that stays on for a few seconds when you press the light button.  It's very lightweight and the band is flexible and comfortable.  On a few occasions I've gone to sleep with my watch on forgetting it was there (yes, I was sober).  I would buy this watch again and now prefer it to the bigger modern g shocks.

Title: Almost a 5
Text: The only thing keeping it from a 5 is the "depressed" adjust button.  I do not like that you need an implement of some type to depress it.

Title: Keeps accurate time
Text: Works as expected. Four stars.

Title: Very comfortable and practical
Text: My main hesitation with this watch was about how comfortable it would be since all the other reviews already attested to its durability and functionality. I have never owned a Casio before, and wasn't entirely sure what to expect. After receiving the watch, I am very pleased with how comfortable the watch is to wear. I have a smaller wrist and the watch fits perfectly.The instructions that the watch came with were very easy to understand, and that made setting up the watch very simple. The illuminating function works very well and adequately lights the watch up at night for viewing purposes. I was originally interested in purchasing this watch for use while cycling, and after one ride I can tell that I am going to enjoy using during riding. It did not chafe my wrist or become uncomfortable when I really started sweating. I would recommend this watch for anyone that wants a simple to use watch for an active lifestyle.

Title: G Shock that started it all
Text: Classic G Shock, does everything well, also I like the repeated timer, it gives the ability to have a digital minute repeater; cool ! I work out with this watch, and if I am in the field this is a go to watch.

Title: Great watch
Text: I have several watches that are way way pricier than this one but this will never leave my rotation. It just works perfectly, is extremely robust so i never have to worry about it. Just grab it and go.

Title: Strong watch
Text: I’ve had this thing for 3 months, and it’s held up great so far. I’m confident this will last years. The only knock is that the button to reset the stopwatch is slightly recessed. This means each time I want to reset the stopwatch, I have to take the corner of my ID or the tine of a fork to push it. Fantastic watch, though. Very utilitarian-looking.

Title: Good rugged watch for a decent price
Text: Will this watch remote start your car ?  Nope. Will ithis watch defragment your network hard drive ?  Nope. Will this watch cleanse your lower digestive tract of environmental toxins ?  Nope. But you know what this watch WILL do, and do well ? It will accurately tell you the time. .Period. I work in a trade that exposes me to some fairly rugged environments: very hot, very cold, very dusty, very wet, very grimy. And this watch keeps on ticking (sorry for stealing your slogan Timex). It has an alarm function, countdown timer, and other stuff that I don't really use. What it does have, and it does it well, is TELL THE TIME !!! And at a decent price. Not a lot of "bling" here.  In fact, ZERO BLING. But if you want a rugged work watch that will last for years, here it is.

Title: The best watch I've ever bought.
Text: I love this watch. I owned one for 7 years, and I put it through hell. That one recently broke on me and unfortunately Casio doesn't sell the exact replacement parts for it but that is okay with me. After beating one of these down every day for 7 years it was an easy choice that I was going to get the exact same model. Seriously this think outlasts the $200+ watches sold by Casio. I don't know why or what they did differently with this thing, but smashing it against rocks, getting it stuck in engine heads, rolling over it with a 4000lbs truck (with my wrist still in it), and everything in between, doesn't bother it.

Title: Good work watch
Text: This model does not set to Atomic Clock every night like my previous 5600 model. Also the light does not fade out if inactive for a while which used to save on the battery life.

Title: Perfect, slim G-Shock
Text: I wanted a g-shock because of the unusually high reviews.  Online and from several friends.  These watches last forever!  A friend of mine actually found one stuck between rocks at the bottom of Kern River.  It was super crusty and covered with moss...  But it was still working! These are generally a bit bulky, which doesn't go well long sleeves or my small wrists.  So this slim design works well for me.  I've had this for 2 years now, not a scratch on it (and I have put it through some very tough times).  These watches should be worth a lot more due to their reliability.

Title: Solid Feel
Text: The actual watch was above my expectation from viewing the image on Amazon. It has a solid feel! The light is excellent! The only annoyance was the "adjust" button was a little recessed that the others so I had to use a pointed object to press it, since it was too far in for my fingers. I am not sure if that was how it was made or if it was a defect in the one I was sold! Overall I was satisfied!

Title: Great durable watch
Text: It's not possible to say anything new in this review, that has not been already said by the previous 21,000. It's rock solid, easy to read time, comfortable, waterproof, and does not break the bank. Peace...out

Title: Muy practico y liviano,para el uso diario
Text: Para trabajar, sin preocupación de dañarlo, buena compra 100%

Title: Very good operational watch
Text: Excellent multipurpose wristwatch with outstanding accuracy and function

Title: A bit bulky for my taste but does what I need
Text: I've worn Casio watches for decades.  I previously used the DBC-150 and DBC-310 calculator watches, both of which included a  countdown timer feature.  When they were discontinued I had to settle for the DBC-32 calculator watch without this feature.  Over the years I found that I valued the countdown timer much more than the calculator so, after months of research and thought, I chose the DW5600E-1V Sport Watch specifically because it had a countdown timer.  My only concern is that the G-Shock case causes the watch to be a bit more bulky and conspicuous that I'd like, but for the price and feature set, I can live with that.

Title: and it's the best watch I have ever owned
Text: This watch does what Amazon says it does, and it's the best watch I have ever owned, except-- While it is noted that the "Adjust" button is recessed to avoid unwanted, well, adjustments, I found I would rather it not be so deeply recessed. That being said, if a similar or nearly identical model is still available without the "Adjust" button at flush prominence with the other buttons, I would gladly go after that one. I returned this one until I can find said model. I highly recommend this watch for the roughnecks and sportspeople out there. If I still had the watch, I'd be wearing it during my practical sparring at the police academy!

Title: Similiar to the original DW-5600 model
Text: I purchased the original model (DW-5600) when it first came out over 20 years ago; never had a problem with it's electronics even when wet. Rubber outer casing and strap finally gave out, then lense cracked but the electronics to my original model in it's inner metal casing still works. The new model has the same functions as the old, but they switched some of the controls around and improved the light. The strap is now integrated into one piece with the front outer casing so it can't be replaced if the strap breaks.The rear of the casing was changed and seems to make replacing the battery easier. Had to buy this if it's anything like the original, so far no problems and I'm pleased with my purchase.

Title: Great Watch for Tough, Hardworking Dads Everywhere
Text: I bought this watch as a Christmas present for my dad because his Ironman watch's alarm function stopped working and half the wrist band broke off. So, obviously his work as an Aborist and outdoor enthusiast was too much for it. I wanted something reasonably priced but well built. He wanted something simple, with the time, date and an alarm. This watch was all of that. With the simple function control he was able to set it up in minutes. Other reviewers mention the style of the watch being unattractive, but Dad doesn't care. It fits him better than the sleek new-age looking ones. He likes it a lot! I can't speak to the longevity yet, but I will update this review if we have any issues with it's function. Other buyers said their Casio is still ticking along after 15+ years of wear and damage. So i have high hopes.

Title: Strong and easy to use
Text: Unlike other G-Shock's, this one is actually a lot easier to navigate. For one, it has only one alarm which is good for me. It also comes with a countdown timer and a stopwatch. What I liked was that after adjusting the alarm, timer, or stopwatch, it takes you back to the time after clicking Mode, which eliminates useless and time consuming navigation through the modes. I also liked than unlike my previous Casio, the light stays on for 2 seconds turning it off; no need to hold it. One thing I found annoying is how hard the buttons are compared to my other Casio, but I guess it's necessary to make this watch so durable. As for durability, I've performed lots of tests since receiving it. I've frozen it, poured boiling water on it, and I've hit it against various surfaces throughout my day. The 'G-SHOCK' and 'Protection' letters haven't faded or anything. Overall, its a durable, easy to use, feature packed watch, and I'd recommend it to anyone. You won't get another great watch like this for the price.

Title: A must buy!
Text: I don't typically review purchases but felt compelled to do so with this watch. This watch exceeded my expectations. I have owned several higher end watches from Luminox to Suunto. I prefer this watch over the $400 watches I have owned. When the band broke on my Suunto Core, I priced them on Amazon for $40. For the same price I thought I would give this watch a try. The size is perfect. Not too big, not too small. If you are looking for a watch that has an altimeter, barometer, thermometer, and warns you when a storm is approaching, buy the Suunto Core. Just plan on shelling out $40 every 12 months when the strap breaks. If you want a no nonsense, rugged watch that only tells time and has basic functions, buy this watch. You will not regret it!

Title: Upper left button hard to press
Text: I like mostly everything about the watch except for the upper left button. I have read that other people have had trouble pressing this button. I know that it is recessed for a reason but I have to use a pen tip to depress it.  Other than that, the watch is everything that I hoped it would be

Title: For the money it's OK but I'm not enthusiastic.
Text: I purchased this watch mostly for the alarm.  Aside from that I'm not terribly pleased with this model.  I had a Casio a number of years ago and it served its purpose.  In general Casios have black digits on a grey background.  Not terribly easy to read in marginal light.  Actually not easy to see at all. If you aren't looking at the face dead-on, reading the time, etc. is at best difficult.This model's light is okay but it was so well protected with projections that one has to find the light button in the dark with a finger nail and is so bright when the light is turned on that for a few moments the digits are hard to read.  Whereas the Casio that I had many years ago the light button was easy to find and when the button was released, the light would immediately turned off; this particular model the light stays on for a few seconds before turning off. If you're of a tactical nature and you want instant 'off' look somewhere else. OK. Time for a re-evaluation.No matter what the instructions may say the day of the week is NOT tied automatically to the date. It SHOULD be but it isn't. To change the day of the week is a song and a dance, which I don't mind too much, but when part of the dance is a 'number' of no particular value that appears in the 'day' space it's a guess, at least to me, how far to advance this meaningless number to the day of the week. The bright idea of black alpha-numeric on a grey background is NOT bright. I'm repeating myself, I know, but this really galls me! Because I'm a prettry OK guy I'm giving this watch two stars. If I was a jerk, but honest I'd give it a single star and grind my teeth. Look elsewhere.

Title: Must have in your watch collection!
Text: Lovely watch. Looks great while being incredibly robust and tough.

Title: Comfortable and keeps good time
Text: Like that it's easy to read and the strap is comfortable

Title: Great classic simplicity
Text: Buy this watch if: You want a G-shock that isn't huge You like the retro square Casio look You like simplicity in features and don't need fancy bells and whistles You want a dependable and extremely durable watch Don't buy if: You have need of atomic time, multiple alarms, temperature gauges, compass, holograms, and other fancy extras You consistently use the stopwatch or countdown feature, you may want to reconsider, as the reset/program button is recessed and very hard to press (This is the reason why I didn't give it 5 Stars) You need a watch that can be totally silent, as you cannot disable the beep that sounds as you cycle through modes Summary: The recessed button is a pain, but this is one of the best watches I have ever owned.

Title: Great, durable watch.
Text: Very useful watch. The countdown timer only adjusts up and the buttons are a little hard to press which is intentional but excessive, especially the inset adjust button. Great watch though.

Title: Lo versátil que puede ser
Text: El reloj es super bueno, vengo comprando esta marca hace mucho tiempo y nunca tuve un problema, el tamaño es muy cómodo no pesa mucho y es perfecto para una persona que vive en la montaña.

Title: Best watch for the Money!
Text: I had this watch for almost 2years.still looks brand new. I work with it every day.You can't  get a better watch for the money up date l bought a new dw5600-1v. I gave  my  brother  my old one that still looks brand new  because  he needed a watch to where. So I bought a new  one still the best watch,you can buy for the money.updated September 11th 2017 .I love these gshocks. I have some pictures of my foxfire gshock and the gwm5610-1 That I love. Both are great watches. I now have 37 Gshock watches and 7 Protrek watches. I bought most of my gshocks from Amazon. The best company around. I  am a Prime Member. 2 day delivery guarantee. You won't find a better watch than Gshocks guarantee. This is the best watch for the money.

Title: Broken Buttons.
Text: I bought two of the most common G-shock watches. This one is smaller and is the perfect size for my wrist. Unfortunately I can’t use the stopwatch/timer functions on either watch because one of the four buttons (that happens to be the reset button) is buried deep inside the watch head, which makes it near impossible to press down unless you have small, skinny fingers. Everything else about the watch is great, but this one flaw was a major dealbreaker . I returned both of them.

Title: Durable
Text: Perfect cheap watch for work. I use this watch everyday for work and I have had it for 3 years. No complaints.

Title: Excelent
Text: Excelente para el trabajo diario muy resistente duro fuerte si quieres un reloj de hombre este es el indicado no le tiene miedo a nada ni al agua al barro o al aceite te olvidaras que lo traes puesto en tu brazo por lo comodo que es

Title: Tough
Text: Have had a lot of Casio's over the years because of their waterproof superiority as well as excellent time keeping. While I love the lighter weight of the cheaper ones, the bands are short lived ,they scratch easily, and the buttons get pressed too easily.  While this one is a little heavier, all the annoying features above mentioned are all but gone. Wish I'd bought this sooner.

Title: Why buy another watch
Text: I have a ton of watches. I hate the fact that I don’t wear any of them because I wear this all the time. It’s durable is accurate it’s attractive. It’s lightweight you don’t know it’s there. It’s a DW 56 what can you expect

Title: Yes! the year is pre-programmed into 2099.
Text: This is my first time owning this model.  As a regular g-shock wearer, this one is a bit smaller than I'm used to, otherwise it's the perfect size for everyone. For the price, it's an amazing value.  It's a great gift you can give to your kids/nephew/niece.  It's tough and takes a beating.  The only cons I can think of are the buttons are a bit small and when you adjust the time, you can only go up (but you can hold the button down to fast forward).  But those are really not a problem.  Just some design limitation. Don't hesitate to buy one as a g-shock fan/owner.  A must buy!!!

Title: Useful and sturdy, some annoyance
Text: I like it, but there are some annoying features. One thing is that the "adjust" button is hard to press because it is deep into its socket. Makes it difficult to press while wearing the watch. Also, changing the days of the week is confusing.

Title: 5 stars... almost
Text: I like this watch alot, its easy to read deisgn and functions make it very appealing to me. The watch is also very rugged. I wanted to give this watch 5 stars, but only a month and a half after purchasing, the adjust time button no longer works. I had to adjust when i first received, and had no issues, but when daylight savings time rolled around and i went to change it, the button no longer works. And now im stuck with a watch an hour behind til the next time change

Title: Generally it works but see below.
Text: We couldn't attach the link from the phone pm3229 to my smart phone. This enables you to get instructions on how to program the watch from your smart phone. Phooy

Title: An inexpensive durable watch that puts up with work.
Text: I am on my third g-shock watch.  I used the first one until the band finally broke.  The battery died on the second one.  I replaced the battery, but the watch did not run long after.  Because the watch is designed to deal with severe shock, the battery is not easy to replace, and it would probably never be as water proof as it was after a battery replacement.  The third one works great, is easy to read, easy to switch time zones when traveling, and puts up with pounding and shaking that would disable a normal watch.

Title: 2 years going strong
Text: Bought this watch in October 2015. It's really just become a part of my body. I felt like I don't really need it a couple months ago so I took it off for a few days and realized I felt naked without it. I work a job where the shifts are 24-48 hours working straight with 48 hours off between shifts. Always knowing the time and date is really a luxury. This watch has been on my wrist inside burning buildings, swimming in rivers, showering, chillin in a hot tub, sauna, a motorcycle wreck etc. Like I said I feel like it's become part of my body. I forget it's there and don't worry about it until I need it.

Title: Best at what's important
Text: If what you want is accurate, comfortable time-keeping . . . this watch can do it. It has for me. Light, easy fit on the wrist.  I set it exactly to global internet time (not that hard) and it has gained exactly one second in three months.  I use other Casios for stopwatch/timer work, but this is the daily on-the-wrist time-keeper.

Title: Un reloj genial
Text: Es un reloj que tiene un diseño genial, es fácil de leer y tiene una excelente relación calidad - precio.  La correa es muy cómoda. Se puede llevar todo el día sin problemas, la luz es genial. El reloj tiene un botón más adentro que los otros, es un poco más complicado manipularlo pero nada difícil he leído que es para evitar que se accione solo. Recomendado

Title: An iconic watch for an unbeatable price
Text: This is an outstanding watch, a true icon and a more robust watch comparing to cheaper Casio watches for not much more money. The only problem - I cannot wear it, as my son took it for himself the moment we unpacked the box. I guess I will be ordering another one for me.

Title: Just like my original 1980 Casio Water Sports
Text: In 1980 I bought my first Casio watch, a Water Sports model with a stainless steel screw back case made in Japan for $100, which is $300 in today's inflated dollars. I still have it today and love its simple no nonsense clear display with just the necessary information. This new G-SHOCK watch is the same basic watch with a much improved EL backlight and an auto calendar that sets the day of the week based on the date and can display February 29 in leap years. Although the base G-SHOCK is now made in China, it still has that nice Casio quality that is present in the original, but at a much lower price. I picked it up 10 days ago when Amazon had it on sale for just $35.39. :)

Title: Great Watch
Text: Two things, the watch is MASSIVE (And I am not small), and the time adjustment button is recessed so far that you need a pin or knife point to adjust the time. But, knowing these two things going in, this watch is awesome. Ridiculously tough. Ugly as sin though.

Title: previous models were more reliable
Text: I really like this watch type, but I have to say that the previous models were much more relaible. This is a second watch of this kind that gets moistures udner the glass.

Title: Sunken Adjust button seems to be a trend.
Text: Great watch in most respects. Stylish and functional. The one flaw, and I returned my first one to attempt to solve this, is that the adjust button tends (it is on my second watch) to be sunken deep in the case.
