On my first watch I couldn’t even press it. My second watch is less bad but still requires jamming my fingernail hard into it every time. If a watch is meant to a tool of convenience, this flaw hampers that purpose.

Title: Nice reintroduction to wearing a watch again.
Text: I hadn't worn a wristwatch for about 25 years before buying this one.  This is a nice watch that let's me not have to worry about needing to have my phone handy to tell the time.  The only thing I don't like about it is that the time is not visible in the dark without pressing a button, which is a little difficult to do.  I'll probably get another G-Shock with glow-in-the-dark hands.  This watch is a real workhorse.

Title: The original G-Shock, baby!
Text: Durable, washable, water proof, easy to read, looks great.  What's not to love!  This is the most current incarnation of the original G-Shock design. Only negative, the screws on the caseback occasionally snag my arm hairs.  This is not unsual for inexpensive watches.  My solution is to dab a bit of superglue around each screw.  By the time 10 years rolls around and the battery is nearing end of life, the rubber may be disintegrating anyway, so this is not necessarily a deal-breaker.  Your mileage may vary.

Title: Fantastic!
Text: I am more of a classic Casio fan. However you do have to appreciate the engineering Behind this retro looking classic. This will be my watch for the beach and when I am fishing. Stylish and much more streamlined than some of its counterparts which I find to be colossal. The Gentlemans G-Shock!

Title: This is the best G Shock to get
Text: It's tough, it's the cheapest of all the models, it does what you need and you don't care what happens to it. Getting other models may be fun, but this one is the standard. The only issue with this one is that the adjust button is recessed and therefore something of a pain to work with - the 5610 adjust button is better. But this one is the best starter watch in the Casio universe.

Title: What's not to love
Text: Simplicity at its finest. Easily became my favorite watch for everyday use. Whether it's: running, swimming, hiking, rock climbing, biking... you name it. this watch will be solid through it all.

Title: I got what I ordered
Text: I knew what I was ordering and am happy with what I got

Title: Outstanding!
Text: Just got the watch today. It looks great and feels great on my wrist. ***UPDATE*** I have had this watch for around 5 months now. I got this watch because I am a pool lifeguard and I need to constantly know the time. Although I bought it for work, I always wear the watch because it is very comfortable, durable, and reliable. I wear the watch when I'm in the water swimming and it always runs perfectly, even if I go down to 10 ft under water. Although I wouldn't recommend it, I even wear this watch in the hot tub and it is still perfect at telling time. Also I tend to be clumsy and bash it into walls and tables, but the watch remains without a scratch. Therefore I must give this watch 5 stars. It is the perfect watch and I 10/10 recommend it to everyone.

Title: Depressed adjust button
Text: First got the watch, awesome it's nice and it fits. Try adjusting the time and date, why is the adjust button do deep in the watch? I went back in Amazon to see the reviews and the adjust button is an issue. However, in my picture, you can see my adjust button is literally inside. Even with fingernails, it takes a few tries just to get it to work. I feel like I got a bad version because you can see my adjust button is extra depressed.

Title: Takes a beating, keeps on beeping.
Text: I like a simple, rugged and easy to use watch that I won't cry over when I destroy it out in the field.  I'm often taking my watch off of my wrist and hanging it on the front of my flak jacket where it gets exposed to twice the injury.  These are very simple watches that work well and take a pretty good beating.  I've had several of these over the past twenty years.  I always end up replacing them because I've ruined the band, never because I've worn out or broken the watch itself.  Somewhere in my "everything drawer," is one of these, that has been there a long time and still sounds the alarm every morning around seven o'clock.

Title: Great, Solid Watch
Text: It's a nice size watch, it is affordable vs other quality watches, it's is comfortable to wear, and it's not too large, I hate extra large watches (cookie watches).  Overall my first week impression is very high, it is exactly what I was ordering.  Mind you I would have liked atomic time, solar charging, and a vibrating alarm, but those are on different watches, and I wasn't willing to spend that much on a watch.

Title: No brainer for work
Text: My work requires that I write the date and time (in 24hour time) on every piece of document. Regardless, I always forget the exact date and it takes me forever converting analog time to 24hr time. This watch was perfect for me. Large clear display with date and 24hr time. Now, I just glance down at my watch and copy the data right onto the document without having to think. The fact that this watch is virtually indestructable is an added bonus. I look forward to using this watch for at least a decade. UPDATE: I've been using this watch for 3 years now, going on my fourth. This is my favorite daily watch by far. I have dropped it countless times, banged it (by accident) against walls and tables god knows how many times. Lived in really humid environments for long periods without getting any moisture inside the watch. I also swim regularly during the summer time with my watch on. It has yet broken down, nor has it required a new battery or strap yet. This thing is indestructable!

Title: Excellent watch, one small issue.....
Text: This is my fourth G Shock. Got it for a great price on amazon, $40 for a time tested, durable watch. My only issue is the top left button being too small. If this button was strictly for setting time and date, this wouldn't be an issue. Those are occasional use....The problem is that it's the reset for the stopwatch/timer also. Frequent stopwatch/timer users, may get a little annoyed using their nails or fumbling to reset. One alarm, timer, stopwatch, date, day, and time viewable in the main screen. Wish this came with the auto EL feature, but oh well.... Other than that its a perfect watch. Everything said about the durability is true. There are no 'cheap G Shocks', meaning they're all bombproof. Anything you can to to damage this watch will def hurt the user, if wearing.

Title: Does not have an auto light function
Text: After researching this and speaking with Casio customer service about this watch I bought it for the auto light feature.  After my purchase I contacted Casio again and after a back and forth they said they were just using the model of the watch and listing other watch features that this watch doesn't have.  Please do not blame this seller blame Casio for using a watch to sell features that do not exist in this model.

Title: excellent watch for the dollar
Text: i wanted a simple watch that was rugged and water proof so it if went in the water with it i would not have a problem.  this does exactly that and as described/advertised.

Title: Love my plastic watch
Text: I wore this in the Remy while on Disney's Fantasy, and I wore it with pride! I removed the rubber piece that covers the face, off the watch and placed a cut out piece of Zagg invisible shield protector on the watch's plastic face, placed the rubber thing back on and viola! extra scratch protection. I have bathed, swam in pools, oceans and washed my hands hundreds of times with this watch and it held up. The area underneath where the bands connect to the body gets pretty funky so I wash that under the faucet with some soap and my wife's toothbrush and it's still doing great. It lose about 1-3 minutes a month I guess, whooptedoo. Battery still going strong over a year. I usually have bad luck with watches, but thus far all is well. P.S. What is that little "sun" or "flash" icon you can enable/disable? above the seconds.. what the heck does it do. Have a great day!

Title: Vert good Watch
Text: Vintage style like DW-5600C. Very nice and perfect timekeeper. I love It.

Title: Durable watch
Text: Very tough and durable watch for a great price.  I don’t write very many reviews but this deserves one. This is my third one same model and each one lasts about ten years.

Title: BEEFY, WATERTIGHT
Text: Very well made...durable. Only the simple features I need. Wish the read out was a little larger for my old man eyes. Buttons are small, but by design, to stay watertight, out of harms way and to avoid unintended activation. Use your fingernails, get used to it. Setting adjustment does not activate the light- to save battery, so you will have to make adjustments in daytime or with additional lamp. So far watertight and holding up in freezing weather and humid environments. If it lasts past the two year expected battery life I will be very pleased. I beat the hell out of watches and so far so good on this one.

Title: Two years as general contractor
Text: I'm a general contractor and this watch lasted about two years. Buttons have stopped working, which would be okay if I didn't have to adjust for daylight savings time. A little disappointed.

Title: Rugged and dependable
Text: I had one of these watches before and wore the heck out of it.  It took a beating but kept functioning really well.  I like the recessed function buttons because I actually wear mine with the face of the watch on my inside wrist. I did that for as long as I can remember when I was in the Navy due to the harsh environment aboard ship(s).  We always had to be careful of machinery and other objects that would catch or snag the watch when you least expect it.  So once again I am pleased to be wearing the same watch again.  It isn't fancy or expensive but if I wanted that, I would have bought a high end watch......

Title: The Best Water Resistant Watch
Text: I have liked and bought Casio water resistant watches since the early 1980's. I started buying the 50m model to wear when I went swimming after ruining a few other watches by forgetting to take them off at the pool. I still wear one daily that I've had for quite a while. I bought a G- Shock in 2000 and just had to replace it after almost 20 years. I was surprised at the prices they still command but I think they are worth it.

Title: I'm in the military and my watch is my 24/7 ...
Text: I'm in the military and my watch is my 24/7 companion that takes a beating. Once it goes on my wrist it doesn't leave it unless I have to pass through security, take a test that doesn't allow them, etc. Honestly I think casio has completely under priced this watch as I would pay more than $40 for it. I did not rank it at 5 stars purely because of how hard it is to press the "adjust" button. However, Casio did this intentionally so it would not be pressed accidentally. Outstanding watch.

Title: Great 1st G-shock.
Text: Tough. Been dropped. No marks. EL is nice blue. LCD is easy to read. I always use the timer while doing laundry. Strap is comfortable. Rinse with clean running water if it gets dirty.

Title: I love casio g-shock
Text: I have been waring Casio g-shock for yrs I love how cheap it is and the quality you get when you buy this watch. I highly recommend this watch.

Title: Su calidad
Text: Un reloj super recomendado, me encantó su comodidad en la muñeca del brazo.

Title: Reliable; Budget friendly; Classical
Text: I guess it's time to review this watch since I have used it for over 9 months. It is as simple as it appears - time showing. I like its classical features. This sample watch is literally reliable and I feel like it could be with me in the coming years probably another five or even ten. This is my most appreciated good purchased this year on Amazon. I'm glad to have it. Very friendly price, and I assume people like a ​simple watch should have one.

Title: Great watch. Bought my first one back in 2008
Text: Great watch. Bought my first one back in 2008, wore it daily to work for 2-3 years, and my job is very tough on watches, I've had other watches ripped off my wrist in the past. After almost three years of wear, the band finally started to split at the hole on the strap I always wore it at. Bought a 2nd one in 2010 since it wasn't much more than a new band. Ended up putting a one piece NATO band adapter on the original watch and switching to a nylon strap, and giving the 2nd one to my son who is now 12. He never takes it off, and it still looks and works like new. Still wearing my original one to work every day going on 7 years now, I believe I've changed the battery once on it.

Title: It's an amazing watch for it's price
Text: It's an amazing watch for it's price. I've bought it for freaking $44 which is pretty cheap for a watch like this. I had a several watches before I got this one and I had to be very careful with them but this one, this one is just an unbreakable watch, seriously. I really love its night light, its look and size. This one is one of a few of G-Shock watches that's suitable size. It's quite light which is good and the strap color is matt black which prevents finger prints. TL;DR An amazing watch, I recommend it to everyone who moves a lot (sports, military, heavy work, work in difficult situations etc.) and who doesn't like huge and heavy stuff on their wrists..

Title: Quality
Text: Excellent service. Fast delivery and great product

Title: Wouldn't Buy Again.
Text: Casio makes good watches at their price points. My personal complaint with this model is the buttons are recessed in to the point they aren't easy to push. I suppose it could be designed like that so buttons don't accidentally get pushed but it annoys me. I'll keep the watch but I wouldn't buy it again. It's the second watch in 6 months I regret buying. The other is a Timex I loved till the indiglow light failed so I can't read it in the dark.

Title: Classic and Comfortable
Text: Fits really well in my husband Comfortable soft rubber band Face is not too big at 1.5” wide Classic 80s look It took him a minute to figure out how to toggle between setting time and regular time telling. It comes with an instruction booklet that took him a few minutes to read and understand. Once he got the hang of it, it was easy to use. Good value.

Title: Rugged, accurate, comfortable.
Text: This watch is tough.  I use it every day for a variety of tasks including mowing, carpentry, dirt work and painting.  It's still in prime condition. It's also accurate, staying within 2 seconds of atomic time (weekly).  It's also comfortable, and light.  I highly recommend this watch. Edit: Just ordered a second watch, as my strap is a bit rough.  Be aware that Although "Foxfire" is shown on the pictured watch, the one you will be getting has "Illuminator".

Title: Excelente producto
Text: Excelente producto

Title: The light button  could to easier to get at, and brighter.
Text: It keeps accurate time. Changing the setting was easy except for the day of the week. That was a real pain.

Title: Pretty nice watch overall. I'm satisfied, but have one small gripe.
Text: I've been looking for a new watch for awhile. This one suits all my needs. The only criticism I have is the adjust button is pushed in farther than the other buttons, making it a little difficult to press it.  This has been brought up in other reviews as well. Sounds like it was a manufacture decision. Regardless, I still recommend the watch.

Title: Feels Good Wearing a Rugged Classic
Text: This is my work watch. Also the watch I wear on hikes or when going to the beach. I enjoy the confidence of knowing that this watch isn't a delicate fashion piece (nothing wrong with fashion pieces; I own one myself). But this is my work horse and thus far, I have not been disappointed.

Title: Daily Driver.
Text: The media could not be loaded. This is the perfect everyday watch comfortable on the wrist, don't have to worry about it getting it wet dirty or oily, this watch is perfect "beater" watch.

Title: Reliable for water use
Text: Best waterproof watch got nothing else to compare to but i used this one for two weeks straight hours in the beach and pool never took it off once. Stayed on while tanning as well and still works like new 10/10

Title: Works well and brings back a lot of memories.
Text: It’s all good. For 40 years I wore a G-Shock while I was working in the elevator trade around a lot of electric. Since I retired 16 years ago I wore a stainless steel watch which served me well. Now this new Casio Works well and brings back a lot of memories.

Title: The only G Shock you’ll ever need.
Text: The classic square G. There’s not a whole lot to say other than at under $50 shipped you WILL NOT FIND A BETTER WATCH. PERIOD. Stylish, tough, functional. I’ve worn mine from environments well below 0 degrees F all the way to 120 degrees F. It will not let you down. Be easy with the sound alarms and back lights and this battery will last you every bit of 10 years.

Title: New watch
Text: Simple to set up. Easy to read. Instructions are tiny. Good eye test. Will see if strap lasts very long. This type notorious for breaking at clasp.

Title: Adjust button pushed in
Text: For anyone concerned with the adjust button being pushed in further then other buttons. There is no defect it is designed that way so the adjust button isn’t accidentally hit and changes time on you. Love this watch it’s a classic so simple. It’s perfect

Title: Helluva watch for the money!
Text: I was going to return this in favor of one of the solar/radio controlled models (5610-1) but decided to keep both.  I normally wear higher end mechanical or quartz watches but I wanted a knockaround field watch and this one (as well as the rest of them) meets this criteria with aplomb.

Title: Bonito, práctico, resistente.
Text: The media could not be loaded. Me agradó. Fácil de leer. Recuerde ponerle hora, día, mes, con la explicación adjunta.

Title: Nice Watch
Text: My wife bought this for me for Christmas. At first I thought that there was something wrong with one of the buttons on the watch. However, after researching I found that the button is made like that to prevent accidental resets. this is the third Casio I've owned and so far my favorite.

Title: great except for a flaw
Text: Great watch. As always. Only problem that gave me reason to rate it as four stars is that button A is broken and to be pressed, must be pushed with a pen or something. Kind of a pain in the rear

Title: TOUGH!!!!!
Text: I am a cook. I have been wearing this watch to work for the last 2 weeks. It comes in to contact with water,grease,chemicals,flour and various types of breading,various food juices, and gets knocked around a lot more than you would think. It has preformed flawlessly. I use the timer and stopwatch all the time since I usually have multiple thing cooking at same time. It has flour paste all over it and I just rinse it off under the faucet at full blast. I will try to give another review after a couple more months. Been about 2months now. Watch still looks new. I figured out I can take the soft rubber cover off with the 4 screws and clean the gunk that builds up in there. I do this about every other week. It has lost about 1/2 min. according to my atomic clock. Also I rub a little Armor All on the band and outside every once in a while.

Title: Simple and tough! Perfect for fitness activity....
Text: I was looking for a watch that I could wear during obstacle course events/gym (tough mudder, Spartan etc...). Also, something that could go under water. I owned a Fitbit charge and it fell apart in less then a year. If your looking for something fancy or something to impress your friends, this might not be for you. But if you are looking for something simple and tough at a great price, this is it! It’s light on the wrist and does what I need. Stop watch and time! It’s not bulky, so it’s perfect for gym use. So far, so good! Great product!

Title: Just like the original
Text: I had the original version of this watch until he case finally disintegrated from age. This new one seems like it will last as long. My only complaint is the stiffness of the recessed buttons which make a little difficult to actuate. Of course, that is a trade off for the extra ruggedness.

Title: Great Price, Great Casio Quality
Text: I love this watch. As a watch collector I was looking to reacquire the same watch I had in the 80’s. Is simply perfect. Great quality. It’s lighter than the first version which I really liked. Super reliable. 100% satisfied with this buy.

Title: -1 for The Wrist Band
Text: Absolutely perfect watch craftsmanship, quality, design and consistency than any other watch brand. The number one problem I face is the material and size of the watch band, I understand that if something doesn't fit, you should lose weight or get a bigger size. In this case, there is no bigger size and I don't need to lose weight! I have large wrists and this watch accompanies it with a price paid. The watch is either tightly suffocating my wrist as if I bought a wrist anaconda, or; the watch is so loose it goes upside down on my wrist so I can't read the time. I will be replacing / DIYing the band to my liking with some Zulu bands or the like. Cheers on your purchase!

Title: TAMAÑO IDEAL
Text: Lo compré para mi novio que es profesor de Crossfit y la verdad ha durado. Hace dos años que lo usa todos los días y está impecable. El tamaño es ideal para una persona de complexión normal.

Title: Fairly good, inexpensive wristwatch
Text: In general, this is an inexpensive, reliable watch that keeps accurate time as best as I can tell.  I am quite disappointed in the function buttons for resetting or changing from watch to timer.  They are tiny and difficult to press to convert from watch to timer or reverse.  My previous Casio watch which was a different model but otherwise nearly identical had reasonable buttons, similarly placed, which could be easily pressed when needed.  This model really requires me to remove the watch from my arm to activate the buttons.  I frequently want to use the stopwatch or timer modes and this is not easy with the DW5600E-1V.

Title: Nice G shock not too big
Text: I have some very nice watches. I buy a cheap black casio from time to time for summer outdoor abuse, so i dont kill my good watches. This is my first G-shock, however.  I like it a lot. I went with this model because i dont like enormous watches and it seemed to be the smallest G-shock they offer. If you are on the fence over the size, its really not much bigger than a typical Casio digital watch, I find it to be a good size for my small wrists. As for construction, it is definitely a step up from standard digitals they offer. I imagine it will take a lot of abuse...I will find out.

Title: Very Durable
Text: Used as everyday watch it so far takes a beating, display is solid it's been banged up to where I thought I may have broke the display and I look at it and it not even cracked or scratched,  very impressed, also been exposed to rain with no problems, keeps perfect time, easy to use and set ,the illumination is just the right amount of light, not blindingly bright but definitely bright enough in darkness, the band seems very durable and fits nicely, over all I am happy with this watch

Title: Great affordable wrist watch
Text: I prefer using a wrist watch to tell time over using my smart phone. The G-Shock handles my careless moves and give me all the information I require. I don't really use the timer functions, but they are available if I choose to use them.

Title: G-Shockin
Text: Simple watch, water and dust haven't slowed it down or damaged it. I bought this watch for work in areas with lost of dust and water, and it's done just that perfectly. I understand why they've been making this model for 30+ years

Title: Great Value, but same old problems.
Text: At $42, this is an incredible value. I particularly like the way you can see the time and countdown timer at the same time. Quips: 1) Adjust button is too recessed and hard to push. 2) Wish they made at least one g-shock that was more slim. I modified mine to address these imperfections. Also, I compare this model to other Casio models on my blog: http://wp.me/phJn8-5k And yes, I'm sentimental about the watch as I've owned g-shocks since the 80s. I can't believe with all the models Casio makes in both G-shock and other lines, that they can't make a digital watch with a countdown timer, that fits under cuffs of shirt sleeves! C'est la vie...

Title: My boy loved it
Text: I've bought it for my boyfriend and he is crazy about it. He goes to swim to the beach with this watch and all the time he trips about how amazing this is. Definitely worth it, works great so far.

Title: What hasn't been said about the G-Shock DW5600? The best value for money G-Shock!
Text: This is definitely the best G-Shock money can buy in terms of value. It's durable, reliable, easy to use, has the classic looks and fun to wear! My only complaint is that the display digits are not contrasty enough, makes you feel like the battery is low, however, taking into consideration the price of the watch, this is fully understandable. The higher-end G-Shocks and the ones made in Japan have better contrasty displays. Otherwise, a fantastic all-rounder!

Title: Classic Casio that can't be beat.
Text: I got this watch as a beater for the gym and for outdoor activities. Typically I have an automatic analogue for that kind of stuff but it wasn't too practical. I was worried this watch would be big. Description says 45mm but it's more like 40-41mm. It's super light and durable and doesn't feel like your even wearing it. I was apprehensive at first because of the claimed 2-3year battery life but unless you want to spend an extra $60 for the solar version, this is it. If your looking for a classic digital watch with history, this Casio gshock is the way to go.

Title: Waterproof and Comfortable
Text: Great watch and not too bulky but unfortunately not as durable as I hoped. Took it on a somewhat hardcore camping trip and the glass was scratched and one of the buttons was shoved into its socket making it hard to use. This is still a good watch and wouldn’t mind getting another.

Title: Let's see what it handles
Text: Bought this watch to use at work. I am a maintenance worker so it gets abused. I got a few welding splatters on it but not much you can do there. So far this is a great watch.

Title: Perfect balance of tough and simple
Text: I've owned several G-Shocks various price and ultimately have come down to this simple yet great model. You can't beat the price or the quality of Watch you receive. I've done all types of work in the construction field and I've yet to be able to break any of my G-Shocks. My top reason for buying this model specifically is due to its low profile shape that allows me to get in tight spaces without having to take off my watch. I highly recommend this model and if it's within your budget, buy the one with solar charge.

Title: Great watch.
Text: My dad has had one of these for many years and was obsessed with it. It stopped working and he was so lost I found that Casio still made the G-Shock and ordered it. I was worried about my dad’s attachment to his old one and considered making a sneaky switch, but decided to fess up. Glad I did as he noticed it was different with the day of week display in addition to date...which he is super excited about. Got the highly coveted, “You are a good daughter” praise for buying this.

Title: first G-Shock
Text: when the light gets low it is difficult to see what time it is. you must push the light button. 1) you need two hands to tell time. 2) in the dark it is difficult to find and push the button. to tell time. 3) you need the user guide to refresh how to use the different modes. (only if you do not use them often.) other than that, it is a rugged watch that i use during the day.

Title: Good solid basic watch
Text: I've had many digital watches, but none lasted long.  I'm hard on watches.  They get hit, bashed, and scraped often; their crystals get badly scratched and scraped; they're frequently dirty and wet; and they're dirty wet for long times, ....  I had never tried a Casio G-Shock, so I bought this one.  I like its design (although I'd prefer less text clutter around its display).  It looks and feels more rugged than any previous watch I've had.  A weakness of most of my previous watches has been the bands.  They break and they rot.  This one looks like it'll last.  l like the way the band is integrated with the case of the watch.  There are no pins to break.  (If there are, I don't see them.)  Ask me in a few years how long this watch lasted.  :-)

Title: Great inexpensive watch with minor issues
Text: I expect this watch to last longer than I will be willing to use it. But its not without its issues, the top left (adjust) button is recessed and all buttons are hard to operate with gloves. Personally I would like it much better without the yellow letters but that is just cosmetic

Title: casio
Text: had several they are indestructible

Title: Great watch just buy it
Text: I have watches that cost $30 - $1000 and I always seem to put this one on a regular basis definitely my favorite watch

Title: Great watch accurate time and able to be active in sports and physical activities without worries.
Text: See title

Title: Beautiful Classic style G shock :)  just kinda small to todays standards....
Text: I remember coveting this watch in my early teens, finally got one way back when.  These are still the same, ordered one and I must admit on my now adult wrist it just feels and looks too small.  Let me stress I usually wear bigger watches too...so by many standards this would be a normal size. I love it, but will pass it on to my grandson for his birthday.  A great watch for the money...no doubt!

Title: Great watch
Text: I bought this watch for scuba diving and it has been awesome. I also that it is a sleek design and not too bulky. First time buying a Casio G-Shock and I’m very impressed. I will definitely stick with buying this brand.

Title: Excelente
Text: Excelente reloj, ya que tiene un muy buen precio para la calidad que entrega, además, las características que posee son buenas y la construcción de este da una buena impresión.

Title: Outstanding quality & value
Text: My First watch as a kid was “the basic Casio digital” watch nearly everyone had. This watch is a remake of the original G-SHOCK, the one that changed everything. Nothing not to like about this watch: well made, accurate, dependable. I wear it everyday for work and out for a bite with the fam. No need to wear a $1,000 watch and risk banging it up on the back of a chair, this watch can take a beating and sill look fresh and ready to go. You absolutely cannot go wrong with this purchase.

Title: Simple Perfect!
Text: What can be said of the original, venerable G-Shock?!  Simple Perfection!  It looks and feels basically how it's been for 30 years - bulletproof. I've seen people purposely throw these against block walls and drop sledge hammers on them, to no effect.  I've worn them diving and mountain climbing.  This truly is the "takes a licking & keeps on ticking" watch. My old G-Shock still works after 15 years, but the buttons stick badly and the plastic around the watch cracked off the glass (due to storing it in the truck in dessert heat I suspect).

Title: reloj casio
Text: La caja estaba abierta y doblada, en mal estado. Por fortuna el reloj estaba bien. Saludos

Title: Great but maybe not on your first try
Text: This watch is great and a classic, but one of the side buttons was hard to access. This is not the first time I have read this from other people who have purchased this model. I returned it and got a new one and it was a little better.

Title: Just buy it!!
Text: Great watch for work, gym, everyday beater!!

Title: Best for my buck.
Text: Oh, how I shopped for a new, inexpensive watch. Replaced a dis-continued Timex. My Casio is easy to read for updates on the time, day, date, etc. It is attractive, and appears to be a lot more expensive than it is. However, 2 problems have raised their ugly heads; buckle and tides. The buckle on the watchband insists on rubbing, and cutting it's way into my wrist. I wear a small bandaid as a buffer zone, but how many years must I invest in bandaids? The tides are a neat feature for fishermen, and I qualify. However, even with my college education, I've been unable to adjust the tides feature. It's flashing.....but....for where....and what time????? In any case, I refuse to return it...Its other features outweigh the bloody discomfort and the way-out tides gizmo. Did I mention there's no need for batteries??

Title: Nothing Short of Awesome......
Text: Well now I am super jealous.  Bought it for my bro-in-law as a birthday present, and now I think I have to have one too.  He owns a landscaping company and will dish out plenty of abuse to this thing.  I recently got him into the magical and wonderful hobby of watches and this 5600E is everything you want in a retro G-Shock for such a good price!! BTW - The "adjust" button on the top left does not protrude from the case as much as the others.  I thought it was defective until I got online and looked at pictures then noticed that other reviewers had commented and even returned it because of this.  It is completely normal, all of them look like this.  It is so it is less likely to be pushed by accident and cause a change.  No worries! You will not be disappointed, unless you buy it for someone else and don't already own one!

Title: I’m so happy! (minor shipping issue)
Text: This product came as pictured and in great condition! I got it for my boyfriend who is a mechanic and has a problem finding durable enough watches. This one is perfect! Only issue was on the day it was supposed to be delivered , I was emailed that it was being returned because of an address issue and that I would be refunded. I was confused about this but figured I’d try again when I got refunded but NO NEED TO! It came the next day!

Title: Fantastic quality.
Text: This watch is awesome. I wear mine every day, ~24 hours/day. The only time I take it off is in bed with my girlfriend because it gets caught in her hair, but that's not an issue specific to this watch. I wear it in the shower, in the pool, in the ocean, etc. Although not advertised as a dive watch, I would have no qualms about wearing this watch while scuba diving. I've worn it free diving fairly deep and have never had any leakage.

Title: THAT THE BATTERIES ARE NEW.  AND THAT I RECIVE A NEW PRODUCT
Text: BEEN USING THIS MODEL FOR OVER 15 YEARS AND HAVE NO COMPLAINTS.  MAKE SURE THE BATTERIES ARE NEW THE NEXT TIME I ORDER ANOTHER ONE.  THANKS

Title: Built like a tank!
Text: This watch has been in service for over a year now and though it's been put through a lot, it keeps ticking! I've left this in the pool overnight, taken hot showers with it, took it into saltwater and dropped it from the top of the stairs but it doesn't flinch! If my experience is any indication, this little watch will last you for a lifetime, it's a great buy.

Title: blur numbers, nice design
Text: nice durable watch with great design. looks good on a hand. unfortunately numbers are not clearly visible and a bit shady. came out of the box like that. not sure maybe its because of the battery or just a watch defect. apart from that its good watch, numbers seen better under the angle

Title: Great work watch.
Text: I love everything about this watch, for the price.

Title: G-shock !!! Uno de los mejores relojes que necesitarás.
Text: Como fan de los relojes Casio, hacía falta este modelo en mi colección, estoy feliz con la compra. La operación fue rápida y como siempre con el respaldo de Amazon en seguridad y cumplimento.  En cuanto al vendedor estoy seguro que realizaré nuevas operaciones de compra, ya que es muy puntual y cumplidor en cuanto al producto que ofrece.  Excelente vendedor!!!

Title: Great watch. Tough and very water proof.
Text: Simple watch. Not 5 alarms, who needs half of the stuff in most watches. Have had this model many times. I dive with it. Work with it. It's tough. Had expensive ones, bling but not worth the time of day.

Title: Works fine, but large
Text: I forgot how large the G-shock series are, even though this is one of the smaller watches in the series. The watch works fine, is very reliable and easy to use.  It will withstand abuse as a G-shock should. What keeps me from giving it 5 stars however, is the large size and lack of adjust points.  Since the watch is large, it can weigh on the wrist.  When doing vigorous outdoor work such as gardening or swimming, I would prefer having more adjustment points.  Once, while doing a few hours of raking, the watch created a rub blister on my wrist bone. I also found the watch to be too large for lap swimming.  I prefer something simple and small for that activity, so I don't use this watch for swimming.

Title: Great watch
Text: This watch is awesome.  its a casio g shock, not sure what else needs to be said. The size is great for someone with small to medium wrist.  Very comfortable. My favorite thing about it is the stopwatch feature counts hours, not just minutes.  I have a few other watches that reset when they get to 59 min 59 seconds and i hate that My least favorite thing is I no longer own this.  I gave it  to my brother in law who was planning on attending AF basic training without a watch.  I guess I need to order another one!

Title: GREAT Features!!!
Text: Obviously, this is a very durable watch- which is why I got it.  I have only had it for about a couple months, but I can really tell that it's going to last.  Instead of talking about what other reviews  have covered, I would simply like to add that it has very interesting features.  My favorite feature is that the timer counts down,  beeps, then restarts on its own (for example: set to beep every 5 minutes). Additionally, you can use a timer and view the time (displayed on the corner) simultaneously,  which makes it really nice on a run, or on a timed test. It is such a good watch for the price with useful features.

Title: Invincible
Text: It is a g-shock. It is accurate, pragmatic, and pretty much invincible. This is the most basic g-shock model, and while it feels like a g-shock on a budget, it will never quit on you.

Title: Wrist band too small
Text: This wrist band is listed at 9 inches, however it barely fits an 8.5 inch wrist. I'll make it work but dissapointed.

Title: Low Cost/ Strong and accurate
Text: I have owned 3 of these watches over the last 30 years. Recently my expensive Seiko watch got water in it so I went back to the Casio G-Shock. I was a carpenter and so the previous watches (all the same model) were extremely tested and passed with flying colors. I never take it off and swim in Florida every day. I fully expect this watch to hold up in a similar manner maybe last even longer as it will not be going to work as I am now retired!

Title: Amazing watch for not much money!
Text: Awesome watch for the money. Had it for about 3 months now. Holds up to anything I throw at it and that's why I love it.

Title: Best watch under $50.
Text: For the price - you can’t get a better watch. It keeps great time, has a great backlight and a good alarm (only one daily alarm, which can be customized to certain dates).  I sold my Apple Watch to make some extra money for the holidays, and have to say that it’s quite refreshing to have a regular watch again. I’m incredibly satisfied by this watch - very well made, easy to use, attractive design - and of course - virtually indestructible. Great buy!

Title: ... of these watches I have owned and I have loved all of them
Text: This is the third of these watches I have owned and I have loved all of them. Its a watch that I wear both to work and kayaking.  It gives me just the functions I need most, is not huge, and can stand up to wherever I take it.  I have heard that it can be difficult to find seals for the battery chamber when changing batteries so I just bought a new one when my power source ran low.  I am keeping my old one for when I can't get a new one.  With minimal use of the illumination feature, the battery lasted me about a decade.

Title: Great product as all the Japanese products are!!
Text: The media could not be loaded.

Title: and they are the best value of any
Text: I've bought 4-5 of these watches over the last 30 years, and they are the best value of any watch that I have owned.  Best of all, they are less than $50!  I've paid $300 for some nice Seiko watches before, but the last one I just put in the drawer because the chronograph date was messed up when I had the battery replaced, and a different jeweler I took it to wanted another $50 just to fix/reset the date. This watch purchase replaces another Casio G-Shock that I bought about 4 years ago.  When the band started breaking a few days ago, I figured the battery would go in the next few months, so I just bought a new one  online from Amazon.  No more trips to the watch / jewelry shop.

Title: Best Bang For The Buck
Text: After years of wearing other brands, I finally got a G-Shock. It is easy to read, easy to set the time, and other functions, and it looks good. The price was really good and it fits well around the wrist. All in all, I highly recommend this watch.

Title: The Original and Still the Best
Text: This watch is awesome.  All the functions you might need, and none of the gimmicky crap that you don't.  I'm not a flashy guy, so I prefer the look of wearing a watch like this over a shiny, dressy watch.  I also find it quite comfortable, as it isn't made of cold metal and doesn't slide around on my wrist at all. This watch is like an adult version of the basic Casio digital watch that you might have worn as a kid.  Nice and beefy without being circus big like some of the "fancier" G-Shocks. I seriously don't have a single criticism.  Would 100% buy this watch again.

Title: Reliable!
Text: I've had several of these Casio G-Shock watches over the years and they have proven to take a beating!

Title: Reliable
Text: I work at Home Depot and am not afraid to bang this tank of a watch up, I also use it when I surf on my days off

Title: Great Value
Text: This watch has everything I want in a daily timepiece including a small price tag.  It is so dependable, they should call it their Timex model.

Title: Kinda hard to read
Text: Kinda hard to read

Title: Love it!
Text: Great watch, Though, water resistant and very easy to set and read!

Title: Classic, hard working watch
Text: There's not much to say about the classic Casio "square G" that hasn't already been said. You will not find a more versatile, better performing timepiece for the money. It gets extra cool points for being a near clone of the very first 1983 G-Shock. Mine has survived many drops, whacks, and submersions, and it's still accurate to within a couple seconds a month. Get one.

Title: Really great watch!
Text: Casio makes great watches!

Title: Classic, timeless design, great everyday watch.
Text: Big fan of this watch, very durable and is pretty comfortable. Have been wearing it almost everyday and still looks pretty much the same when I bought it! It does pinch the hairs on my wrist every once and awhile but it's not big deal. I noticed have to rest the watch a bit higher on my wrist than the rest of my watches. When my wrist is in extension the watch jams into the back of my hand which was a nuisance at first but was any easy fix. Overall, great everyday watch.

Title: it holds up quite fine, I never had a problem with it
Text: I bought this mainly for its water resistance. I go swimming at the gym regularly; it holds up quite fine, I never had a problem with it. I haven't used it in the ocean or for diving, so you might want something more heavy-duty for those activities, but if you want to know the time in any other body of water or in the shower this is great. I like that it doesn't have any features besides the date, day, and clock. The wristband is also quite comfortable and I frequently wear it 24/7.

Title: As expected - just like online info/photo
Text: As expected - just like online info/photo

Title: Get it
Text: The media could not be loaded. Absolutely love it. Confusing at first while setting the time but its real simple. Theres a section on the upper left corner, that is for the year FYI

Title: Damn good watch.
Text: Super good durable watch.  If you work in the trades, or the elements and can't look at your phone for the time because you WORK!  This watch is perfect.  I also like that it's not huge like some other g-shocks can be.  My watch has taken some hits, scrapes, yanks, and water submersion that had me look down to check if I broke it, expecting it to be broken, but nope, this little guy just keeps on truckin.

Title: Very good sturdy watch
Text: This is a classic watch, I used to have one of these when I was a kid, so it was cool to have it again. Quality is great and looks like it will last for a long time.

Title: Great, timeless watch
Text: I. Love. This. Watch. I have a bunch of other watches-- the dressier Citizen watches, the tech nerdy Moto 360, what have you. But this watch it just great. By no means am I saying it can replace the aforementioned watches, but when it comes to any sort of physical activity or anything that may involve some sort of danger to my watches, this is my go to watch. Water, dirt, rocks, blood, whatever element I'm facing I know this watch can handle it. It is durable, it looks great and retro, and has every function I need and no more, and it is so comfortable, it is one of the only watches that I accidentally fall asleep with. Highly recommend.

Title: Great Old School Watch
Text: Simple and easy, all you need plus a little extra. Watch is comfortable to wear and very durable. Even if you ruin it in ten years the price is more than fair for what you get. My favorite part is it's not bulky, I have no problem getting my hand through my sleeve on a jacket taking it on or off. A Classic.

Title: Wears well and works wonderfully!
Text: Exactly what I hoped for and expected. Works perfectly. Has stopwatch, countdown, and alarm functions, 12h/24h options, great backlight, and feels very sturdy. My new go to for everything outdoors and even running and lifting. And most importantly, I have small wrists and this watch wears well for a 45mm. Couldn’t recommend more for a digital quartz option.

Title: Great iconic design, function wise can be improved
Text: Watch looks great BUT The buttons are hard to reach, for example button A at first seems defective since it is way too recessed and with my big fingers I can't use it easily, so every time I have to set time or alarm is a struggle. I am used to my Casio W800 so when I got the DW 5600 I thought that numerals are too somewhat faded and small. The light button does not work when in alarm setting mode. The symbol for the alarm and the signal are too small so I never know if they are activated or not. Alarm has no snooze. All these downsides make of this watch a no for me, even though I really wanted to love it because of the classic design and the great size.

Title: A bit of nostalgia. Best watch ever.
Text: So yes, this watch brings back memories of when digital watches were all the rage in the 80s. I love it.

Title: Built to last!
Text: I've been using this watch for the past 12 years and I love it! All the essential functions that you need in a durable watch. I am very active and my G-shock holds up extremely well whether it's work, sports, or outside recreation. This is the 3rd watch I've bought although my current one is still going strong, I can tell it will be ready for replacement soon. They usually lasts me 4-5 years before the face plate starts cracking or so covered with scratches that it's gets hard to see. I highly recommend if you are looking for a durable, sporty watch!

Title: Great watch
Text: Great watch for work

Title: Best all around watch in the world
Text: I've bought this watch twice because I gave my other one away as a gift to a co-worker. I work in a warehouse where I do lots of physical activity, and both watches are still going strong 6 months later. No scratches or any damage at all! My only gripe is that it loses or gains a couple seconds each month, but you could always get the atomic time keeping version if that's important to you. It's forty bucks that'll be well spent.

Title: The eagle has landed
Text: Wonderful watch. Came in same model as pictured in perfect condition. Much simpler to program than the chunky more popular gshocks. Also 100 percent authentic 🤙🏼 Might grab another as a gift for a buddy since the price is right

Title: great for work
Text: band like all of then area weak and hard to find proper replacement

Title: Bought this as a gift for my grandson.
Text: Purchased as a gift

Title: Good time keeper
Text: It's rugged. But, you'll need a pen or similar item to comfortably cycle through the modes.

Title: Awesome Watch!
Text: I've worn this watch swimming, working, and living for about 6 months now and have only taken it off on a few occasions. It keeps great time, every month or two I synchronize it with the internet and it's never been off by more than two seconds. I run lawn care, and carpentry tools that cause a good bit of vibration and shock at my work, these have caused no issues with timekeeping (see above). Also after so many months of use the Bezel doesn't have one scratch on it. (Quite amazing when you consider that another similar watch I bought became very scratched up within the first week.) The band is strong and has not caused issue even when I've been wrestling with friends and they start pulling on it.

Title: great watch for my adventures
Text: Great watch

Title: great
Text: needed a tough but slim to the wrist watch that would fit under my welding gloves. this is perfect

Title: Decent, low-cost, and basic
Text: There's no solar power or automatic syncing with this (the latter I always disable on the many Gs I have bought that had it).  When adjusting the countdown timer, the numbers only move one way, and it doesn't have multiple time zones.  The battery life may not be all that long (but replacements are cheap, assuming you can get into the watch and put it back together). The price is easily 1/2 or 1/3 of a more elaborate G-Shock, and when you consider how fast any of them basically stops working (5-7 years in my experience), you could almost save money getting this one and just tossing it when the battery fails, then buying another.

Title: hard to set time &date other wise works like a watch should. Buy one one & see for yourself.
Text: name brand

Title: Great watch, annoying backlight
Text: Incredibly durable, very easy to use, and all the features you need. My only complaint with this watch is in regards to the backlight, and when it refuses to work. When setting the alarm, the backlight will not come on, even though that button performs no other function in this mode. This means that you cannot set the alarm in the dark, which is very annoying if you are camping or in a shared room and don't want to turn on the lights just to set your alarm. The backlight will also not work when setting the event timer, but instead toggles the "automatic" mode which causes the timer to restart automatically when it reaches zero. Overall, its a great watch, but this one design flaw means I probably wouldn't purchase another one.

Title: Rugged, Waterproof and Relatively Inexpensive
Text: I tend to be hard on watches and the few expensive nice watches I've purchased haven't lasted long. I've been using this model of G-Shock for several years and it is a very sold product.  I can't even count the number of times, I've dropped it, or forgotten to take it off before going into the pool or shower.  I've done even worse, and this watch just (to coin a phrase) takes a licking and keeps on ticking. The only drawback is that it is sort-of ugly.  Now I much prefer function over form and this watch is ideal for me. If however, you need an attractive or dress watch, I suggest you look elsewhere.

Title: casio
Text: I have always liked the Casio brand of watches.  This one is a basic easy to use watch.  Has a count down, stop watch and an alarm that work great!  A word of caution though, FEDEX is a horrible company that AMAZON uses for shipment.  Not only did FEDEX cause delays in my order (the product sat in Arizona for almost 4 days before "FEDEX" decided that we better ship it out to the customer.  It sat another 2 or 3 days in Utah before arriving in Colorado.  Sat in the Post Office another 2 days before they delivered the watch to my house!  So, I would research other options of shipment besides their "FREE" shipment offered on the product. Pay extra for the better shipment!  Came later than promised which is unprofessional in my opinion.

Title: Nice watch
Text: Got this as a gift and it was well received even though it was not a pricey watch

Title: Excellent watch. Band is not as bad as I ...
Text: Excellent watch. Band is not as bad as I was lead to believe, based only these reviews. Plastic (? resin) feels robust enough, doesn't pull hair too much. Fits a skinny wrist just fine. Makes wrist a little sweaty, but not much different than my prior watch. Frankly, overall a very solid watch. I'm fond of it already. Who needs an expensive watch, anyway? I wanted it to tell me the time, and it does. Will probably wear it until the battery croaks (maybe two years?), then go for the Tough Solar variant. I'd buy it again.

Title: Awesome digi watch
Text: Hands down one of the top digi watches.

Title: Keeps On Ticking!
Text: This watch that I just bought from Amazon is an exact replacement for another of the very same model.  The original had a lithium battery that was advertised to last seven (7) years.  The battery and the watch lasted for over fifteen (15) years!  This watch is so accurate, it is scary.  I have worn this watch to my woodworking shop and have subjected it to all sorts of dust, sweat and other abuse.  When it gets dirty, I drop it in the bathroom sink full of water and let it soak while I take a shower.  Then, I scrub it with a nail brush and hand soap and then rinse.  The old one never missed a lick, nor do i expect the new one to.  For a $42.00 watch, that ain't half bad!  I only hope that my Rolex Submariner does as well.  To be honest, the Casio G-Shock is more accurate.

Title: Finally ordered one
Text: I have wanted one of these for a long time. Every time I watched a video about this watch the people praised it for it’s durability. I finally ordered one and am happy with it. Look forward to many years of use as I rotate wearing it between my other Casio watches.

Title: The best
Text: Possibly the greatest watch design ever. This is just a classic device that everyone should own. The only downside is that it looks a little small on my 7.5" wrist.

Title: A simple "Tough Watch"
Text: Watch that simply tell time with basic function you will used.

Title: Perfect Watch!
Text: I've been wearing this watch every day since I got it. It's really tough, I have scraped it against sharp metal roofing and stuff at work accidentally and it hasn't gotten any scratches. Having the day of the week and the date on your wrist is really really convenient and being able to switch between 12 hour and 24 hour time if you prefer. It's also really stylish. It just looks cool and like the 'classic' sort of digital watch. It's good for my wrists, it's not HUGE but it isn't small either. This makes me want one of the solar versions. I don't think I'll wear another type of watch I like this one so much.

Title: Nerdy, Retro, Reliable, Awesome :)
Text: This is the perfect watch for any guy. Im a 41 yr old male that is HARD on everything I own. I work in the repossession business in GA (hillbillies are the craziest!!), and I need a watch that is just no frills, take a beating, accurate to a fault GOOD! This is it. Driving and operating a wrecker is hard on everything that touches it. If you dont think its hard work THINK AGAIN! Its nothing like what they show on the tube. Not even close. This watch can take the punishment required for the job. The only thing its missing is the retro pac-man function that some watches had in the 80's. That would be too cool. Then I could play pac-man while staking out a car ;p But seriously, this is a really awesome practical everyday watch. And less than half of what some other big box stores want for it. Thanks Amazon!! Sincerely, Happy Customer

Title: There are few products that i truly gloat over...
Text: ... This is definitely one. I work in a kitchen. My watch rutinely hangs over boiling pots. Is submerged in hot soapy water, to be followed by immersion in cold water. It is on my wrist when I reach into an oven and walk into a deep freezer. I have worn this watch and another like it for decades. The first was lost when my toddler tossed it out a moving car window. That's another story. I have never had a problem with this time piece. The band and buckle is virtually indestructable. I wash my hands over 30 times a day. The casing is tough as nails. There is no hint of fade on the surface printing. The timer is used daily without fail. I would never do so, but Im certain I could throw this watch against a wall without issue. Well worth the nominal price.

Title: nice size for a small wrist
Text: nice looking watch fits and looks well made

Title: The best watch I've owned
Text: This is probably the best watch I've owned over the years. Its simple and practical. Dropped it few times already. The casing does feels like a real rubber and does absorb the impact from the fall.

Title: Outstanding buy for the $
Text: I bought this to wear on weekends and when on vacation.  It doesn't disappoint.  The build quality is outstanding, and it's smaller than other giant G-Shocks so it wears more easily on your wrist for a skinny guy like me.  It actually somehow looks less dated in person than it does in the pictures -- the design holds up really well.  I've taken it in pools, salt water, on planes, in the yard, you name it, it's done it. The only downside -- if there is one -- is that the screws on the bottom of the watch will grab your arm hair every so often.  Still, for just over $40, it's a steal.  Don't waste your $ on atomic or solar, it just isn't worth it when you can buy this.

Title: Way to go !
Text: Step-son works in a machine shop. The watch is subject to heat, dirt, grease, oil, cold and right out abuse. So far it’s stood up ! Way to go G-Shock !

Title: Excelente reloj!
Text: Volví a comprar este modelo ya que tuve uno hace 10 años y aun esta funcionando pero quise renovarlo es sensillo ente excelente y fuerte!!!

Title: Great watch. Easy to set, nice retro look.
Text: It is a great watch, my only issue is that the alarm isn't loud enough.

Title: Functional
Text: I work in warehouse and needed a dedicated time piece that wouldn't die on me like other watches. With a ten year battery this watch functions and out performs newer watches with added features. It's even stronger than newer watches and won't crap out on you if you get it wet. Pros: -simple to use. - one alarm, one button for glow, one for tone on off - lighter, and stronger than most other watches for the price point. -color is simple and appealing to the eye. -affordable Cons: it's non solar(cost 50 bucks more)

Title: Watch is fine, but...
Text: Just me but the two band length choices are either a bit too loose or too tight for my wrist size.  There are 4 buttons on the watch to set time, alarm, etc.  The "A" button is seriously recessed, making it difficult to push.  It is used to access the setting modes so not a problem as not done very often.  If you want to use it as a stop watch, the A button also has a function there, which would make it inconvenient to do splits and to reset the stop watch function.  Basically very difficult to use that button, which in general is a good thing.

Title: Indestructible y Cómodo!
Text: Es un reloj muy cómodo y clásico, realmente se adapta a las necesidades y para usarlo todo el día esta genial por su poco peso, no se siente sobre la muñeca durante el transcurso del día, es muy fácil de leer y la alarma suena bastante fuerte. es de mis favoritos de mi colección.

Title: It keeps time. What more do you need?
Text: A little easier to read than its predecessor. The light button has moved from an easy location to the lower right corner so not so easy to hit

Title: Good Watch for the Money
Text: Good basic watch. Can take it in the pool or shower and it does fine. Adjustment button is set in a bit but that is to keep from changing time accidentally. Plastic wristband is comfortable enough and easy to clean.

Title: Light weight with a classic look
Text: As a firefighter/paramedic my job can be very hard on watches. This watch is my second Casio, my first lasted over 5 years which is amazing considering the abuse it received. It is light weight to almost to the point of not noticing it is there. Also it is slim enough to make getting into turnouts quickly easy because it doesn't bind in the sleeves. The retro G shock look will also make the rest of your crew jealous at how cool you look.

Title: Short wrist band
Text: Short wrist band, Almost kids size!!

Title: Cheap, tough, utilitarian, and sporty looking.
Text: The quintessential G-shock watch. The only single improvement I would make to this model is the auto EL feature found on the solar atomic variants. It's tough, it's comfy, it's lightweight, it's legible, it's cheap, it's 200m rated. I don't know what more you could ask form a watch. The band on some of the variants of this model is a little softer, and the display on the more expensive models is slightly clearer from all angles. This model is also the perfect introduction to the G-shock line if you are used to smaller watches. It still has a lot of wrist presence but is not bulky or cumbersome like some of the oversized G's that are currently popular.

Title: I love this watch
Text: I had one for many years, and kept replacing the bands with cheap substitutes, and finally, I lost it. I was delighted to see that Casio reissued the model, and bought another, which I wear all the time, and finally another to keep new in box for the "next time." My only complaint is that the band is about 1/4 - 1/2"  (one hole) too small for my big wrist; I either have to make it a bit too tight or, if I use the third hole in from the end, it barely stays in the keeper. That's how I lost the first one. Or else, I  should just lost 50 pounds or so and hope my wrist gets slimmer, too.

Title: Straight up: it’s a good watch
Text: My husband works at UPS and really beats up his watches. This sucker is AWESOME! He wears it every day doing heavy labor,  10 hours a day. If he says it’s a good watch, it’s a good watch!

Title: Best watch ever!
Text: Bought this watch a few years ago as a Christmas gift to my son. Guess what, it is still working, though it went through a LOT as my son is not the most careful person in the world. Great quality!  Bravo Casio!!! 👏

Title: Survived my summer in the Sierra
Text: I purchased this watch in May and have been wearing it daily in the high sierras all summer.  Without exaggeration, it has been my best friend. It fits perfectly on large and small wrists alike and always looks brand new when washed off after a tough day. Alarm, Countdown, Stopwatch plus the sleekest home screen of any digital watch in history. Best 40 dollars a man can spend. I'm looking forward to using this in the snow all winter and will update my review in the spring.

Title: Just keeps working
Text: Bought this  because had the same one years ago, and it lasted me a long time with rough us,RK

Title: Nice watch, but difficult to adjust
Text: I have owned many G-shock watches over the years and been very happy with them, but with their latest model it is impossible to adjust the time, date or settings with the button on the upper left side using your finger or finger nail.  The button is so recessed that you need to use the tip of a pen or other pointy object to depress the button and adjust the settings.

Title: Simple, slim, perfect
Text: This watch is the best Gshock to ever exist.  The watch is durable yet slim, you can wear this while playing Magic and it wont interfere with your wrist movements or distract you with crazy gimmicks like multiple time zones, tide charts, or solar battery charge life.  Others who dont give this a strong review clearly arent buying the watch for what it is: totally awesome.  If you cant read the display G shock doesnt care, blind people arent its demographic.  The buttons are small and minimalist in design, but huge in terms of staying out of the way of your cufflink when your shifting from 5th to 6th on Need For Speed on your Playstation3. This watch is a black slab of plastic that is small yet tough.  You will probably lose it before it breaks.  I would recommend getting this watch after a girlfriend.

Title: Love the Retro Look!
Text: I bought this watch after carefully deliberating and studying the reviews because I wanted an inexpensive digital watch that would (hopefully) last me a lifetime. I chose this particular model for its retro appearance. My dad told me how he had this exact watch in the 80's and that was a big selling point for me. The backlight is nice and bright and it's simple to figure out every function. I haven't even opened the instruction manual yet. On a side note, some reviews on other sites said the back casing is made of resin. This is false (as far as this particular model is concerned) because the casing is made of stainless steel which has a satin finish instead of the polished screwbacks I've seen on the originals from the 80's (which is the only con about this model). Overall I am very pleased with my new favorite watch and look forward to wearing it every day.

Title: Go to watch
Text: A real go to daily watch that looks great and keeps good time. Durable as G-Shocks are known for. Not high on the wrist which is nice.

Title: not a fancy watch! but tough ass hell!
Text: i used this watch on a daily basis... at work mostly since phones are “not” allowed... just as i remembered em’ I owned one or two growing up

Title: This one on the other hand looks more formal and it has bigger number so i can easily watch the time at night and during day
Text: It has what you need, no problema with wáter, shock resistant, alarm, light, and crono. I first had the mudman but after 4 years i had to repair it and it was never the same. Got wáter in it and died. This one on the other hand looks more formal and it has bigger number so i can easily watch the time at night and during day. It Works great when running and when i wear my shirts at work i does not get caught up. I think this watch is perfect for a person that runs, work fixing things at home, sleep with the watch y fish with the watch, it really has the essentials.

Title: Goldie locks watch, not too big not too small, JUST RIGHT
Text: I’ve been wearing the same model for over 20 years. So happy to find it on Amazon. Just perfect watch for me, very physically active outside and iat work. Very very happy :-)

Title: Four months in....
Text: I've had this watch for 4 months and I've gotta say that it's the best digital watch i've ever owned! Simple, classic design, incredible endurance, and a great price, make this watch a must have for collectors, and everyday wearers alike. I wear this everyday. I've done countless stress tests of this watch that would have broken any other watch: swimming/diving in the Atlantic, dropping off a seven story parking structure, throwing it against a wall multiple times, letting it sit in water for up to an hour, etc.... still not a scratch! Casio went all in with the development of this iconic timepiece, and you'll love it more than you'll ever know!

Title: The recessed adjust button is impossible to press.
Text: Other than the inability to press the Adjust button without taking my watch off, this is a fantastic watch that fits my needs.  Would have given it 5 stars if I could only press the adjust button with ease like the other 3 buttons.

Title: Original Is Best!
Text: As one reviewer put it, "All tough and no fluff". I agree 100%. I got this for an outdoor watch. Namely, backpacking. It's got everything I need and nothing I don't. The Electro Luminescent (EL) light is a key feature for me. It lights the entire screen evenly and brightly. It's tough but not bulky and being a Casio it should last for ever. Nothing beats originals and this is a prime example. Very little to go wrong with less "frills", yet all the bases are covered. I highly recommend the original G Shock. They can also be spruced up a bit with adapters for any 24 mm custom band.

Title: Tough. Resilient. Renown for a Reason!
Text: I work in a major recycling plant in NC, and in Close/ physical contact with a variety of Metals and Iron on a daily basis. Not to mention the Dust, Sweat  and Elements... and this watch takes it all in stride! Would I recommend it? Without hesitation.

Title: Great watch for great price!
Text: Looks and feels great on my hairy arm, great watch, tough and reliable. This one is a tad bigger than the version that has solar and atomic time. Great daily for working around mechanical and electronics.

Title: Greatest digital watch ever made.
Text: This is simply the best digital watch ever made. Served me well through every conceivable environment during 20 years in the military. Replacing my original that I lost some time ago.

Title: A classic that doesn't disappoint.
Text: For those who read my previous review on this watch, I was a little hasty in giving this only 4 stars due to the initial comfort of the strap. After a little breaking in, the band fits nice and snug with very little irritation. The face now has a tiny scratch, but I'm sure it's a result of my knocking it against practically everything, including numerous warehouse racks, retail shelves and a forklift. There are not enough good things that I can say about this watch. It fits well. I beat the heck out of it on a daily basis and it's still working. It'll probably outlast me. The "Illuminator" feature doesn't cause temporary blindness; and it's capable of going farther down in water than I will probably ever willingly go. If it's good enough for NASA, it's good enough for me.

Title: I will work and last longer than myself
Text: The watch just works perfectly all the time.  I have an earlier addition of this same model of watch from about 1997 that still works.  I just needed a spare

Title: Gran reloj, buena relación calidad/precio
Text: Es un reloj muy bonito, sencillo, robusto, con resistencia al agua de 200m y una correa muy comoda. En definitiva el todo terreno ideal si no quieres nada muy grande ni colorido. Lo único malo es que solo tiene una alarma. Así que no es multialarma como dice la publicación.

Title: The lone wolf gshock
Text: I wanted a watch able to withstand any condition while being able to wear to any occasion. The g shock watches are perfect I thought but I really don't want it to look like I'm wearing a pip boy from fallout; also I way I'm paying over 100$ like most of the bigger gshocks are going for. The dw5600e is just perfect. The ruggedness of a g shock yet not a gigantic mess. This is the gshock that stands out from the rest.  It looks very classy and so far I am loving it. The only thing bad to say is that the adjust button is a *little* hard to press.

Title: G Shock
Text: I had one while in the military and I like how it holds up doing every day activities plus the extras. The name says it ALL!! G-SHOCK.

Title: Excelente!
Text: Tenía un G-shock G9000 hace ya sus 6 años. Primero el recubrimiento de goma de la cápsula murió y luego la correa. Con lo que cuestan ambos repuestos para el G9000 compré este reloj. Es funcional, no te dolerá mucho si llega a rasparse o arañarse. Puedes combinarlo con la Mi band 3 y ya tienes la mejor combinación por un excelente precio. Súper recomendado para personas que necesitan un reloj resistente, duradero, de calidad y por un buen precio.

Title: Easy to use watch
Text: Great watch very similar to one my dad had in the 80s. Got it for work need a slim low profile watch with simple function. Its great and comfortable compared to a standard round head watch. Light and durable.

Title: One tough watch
Text: This will be my second one. I lost my first one during a move but my first one survived 3 aircraft carriers and other surface ships and 4 submarines. One tough watch.

Title: Muy bonito, sin novedades hasta ahora, excelente producto
Text: ok.- sin novedades. muchas gracias

Title: great watch
Text: My last G-Shock lastest only 13 years (with one battery repalcement). I read a complaint from another reviewer about this new G-Shock not having "duel-time", so I am unable to keep time in two time zones but I don't travel that much and when I do I can do the simple math to figure out what time it is. Plus changing the time on the watch isn't rocket science. I love the new light on the watch. The old one was alful but with this new one I can easily read the time no matter how dark it is outside. Great watch, very tough and relieable. Very water proof too. If you are tired of repolacing your "ironman" watches get this badboy and you won't be disappointed.

Title: Good watch
Text: Very nice basic watch.  It's not fancy or flashy but it tells me what time it is and the date which is all I wanted.  I work outside in southern California where its 90+degrees all spring/summer and so far has held up great in the heat and sweat.

Title: One of the best watches ever made.
Text: Absolutely love this watch.  My father recently passed and this was the watch I remember him wearing when I was growing up, so I decided to buy one to relive those times.  The only issue I have with the watch (the same issue my father had) is that it's pretty small.  It barely fits around my wrist, but that's part of the charm I guess.  Besides the nostalgia, it's an exceptionally well-built​ watch.  Keeps perfect time and is an absolute tank.  The only reason for the 4 stars is the sizing.

Title: Great watch!
Text: This is a great, simple watch. The band is very secure and comfortable. I look forward to many years of service.

Title: Have not used certain features...
Text: Hey unless it arrives broken it works since it is Casio. I have not put it under waster and it was not bought for a timer function. I have had Casio now in one type another and all have worked until the band broke requiring me to get another watch. Maybe it is meant that way. Who knows? This one works fine,. RG

Title: Takes the Abuse and Just Keeps Ticking
Text: With my husband's very active life, this watch is the only one that seems to be able to last as long as he does.  With kickboxing 5 nights a week, hunting, farming and gobs of other very physical activities, Richard is hard on a watch.  He just replaces it every three years (or so) and keeps on going.

Title: Just like old times !
Text: The DW5600E-1V is a classic design that has a good "illuminator" and keeps great time. I love all the casio 5600s but really all you need is this for a reliable, durable watch that will be there when you need it. The alarm is plenty loud too as I know some others are quiet. I have programmed watches ( loaded operating systems on them ) and I am impressed by the simplicity of the casio. It takes me back in time when I look at the DW5600E-1V to the 1980s and also forward to the future. In my youth, when I would go surfing and sailing, I was often wearing a casio that looked just like it. Hope you enjoy the watch as much as I do. It is a modern classic with all you need to tell time and more. Thank you to Casio.

Title: Great cheap starter g-shock
Text: This watch is cheap and is a beast. If you never owned a G-shock before, you should go check out all the features... such as alarms, countdown timers and a bunch of stuff you'll probably make more use of than me. For me I needed a simple reliable watch that will last me forever. This is the one you are looking for and it's waterproof and shockproof. You can go to swim in this, take a bath in this for years and this thing will still keep on going. I don't even know why they offer warranty honestly, I own 3 g-shocks and none of them needed any maintenance.

Title: Packaging of valuables
Text: The watch could of been packaged alot better than just in a card board box half opened, The watch that I value and spent money on could of been placed in a box NOT an envelope! Maybe buying right from CASIO next time.

Title: EXTREMELY DURABLE
Text: This is the 3rd of these watches I've owned since 1987. They are extremely durable and the water tight seal is on point. These watches have endured 10 years as a US Marine and 20 years as a firefighter. Simple and effective!!

Title: Is this a quality control issue or not?
Text: Is it an issue that when pushing the B and C  buttons the module itself visibly moves around inside the case?  Not too much but enough to notice.  Hmmm....should I exchange it for another or are all DW5600's this way? Other than that I really like it, super comfortable on wrist! Update Dec 2018 - Best $40 you'll ever spend on a watch.  Pull the trigger already!

Title: Countdown timer alarm can be flakey
Text: I depend a lot on the countdown timer, and that has gone flakey on me. It counts down, but the alarm goes off only about half the time. At first I thought that I just wasn't hearing the alarm, but I've run tests where I'd just stare at the watch when during the countdown, and sure enough it sometimes just remains silent. This is a problem -- I count on the timer to alert me when it's time to flip the steak on the BBQ, shut off a running hose, etc. I've bought three of these watches in the past 8 years. The most recent one's alarm started going flakey after only 6 months. The one before went flakey after 3 years. In neither case did the battery seem to be the issue. I give it 3 stars only because I like the watch in other ways, and perhaps I've been unlucky and gotten lemons the past two times.

Title: Best practically indestructible watch for everyday or SCUBA use
Text: I've owned G-Shocks ever since Casio introduced them 40+ years ago. Dropped one off the 21st floor of my condo onto a tennis court. Yep, kept on ticking. Made many dives to about 140 feet. Kept on ticking. Suggest as you get older, buy the models with the larger digits like the one above. Too bad Casio doesn't make cars and trucks!

Title: Fantastic Watch at a ridiculously low price
Text: This is the best watch I have ever owned. You can tell it is extremely well made the moment you pick it up. I will concur with some of the other reviewers that the button on the top left can be hard to press if you don't have any fingernails. That would be my only complaint. Extremely functional with almost no bells and whistles (just the way I like it). Being in the military, I was looking for something simple and tough that wouldn't draw a lot of attention...this is it. I could not be happier...in fact I am ecstatic.
