This is the watch I should have bought 5 years ago instead of buying the cheap Ironman watches which always fall apart after two years of use. I have never owned a $25 Wal-Mart watch for more than two years. That was a sunk cost, but now I have a "real watch" that I am sure will last for years. Look no further.

Title: What’s the most important thing to know? It’s a G-shock.
Text: This watch is unstoppable. I swim with it, wrench with it, ride with it and everything else with it. You can’t stop it. It’s not humanly possible.

Title: nice night light
Text: Light weight, very user friendly, (you don't need a users manual to set it up),  nice night light, stopwatch, countdown timer, alarm, day and date and it as durable as they come. Great for outdoor sporting, and waterproof for swimming and fishing. This is my 3rd G-shock and the first 2 lasted over 25 years. You wont find a better watch for this price anywhere and if you do please let me know. I was not paid or compensated for this review.

Title: Great watch
Text: Great watch, good price everything I was looking for. The alarm is semi-loud beeping no vibration didn’t wake me the first time but after awhile I got it down.

Title: Great for the price.
Text: This thing can take a beating. It gets the job done.

Title: A G-SHOCK at a great price!
Text: This watch is awesome!  Bought it for the price and retro look.  It has the features I was looking for (countdown, stopwatch and alarm).  Illumination is bright and clear.  All the G-SHOCK features at a great price.

Title: Fits bigger wrist
Text: I like the watch it fits my wrist and would give it 5 stars but the button to change functions is recessed can't be pushed in with finger and has to be pushed in with a ball point pen to activate.

Title: Quality down from 25 years ago...
Text: I gave my original Casio 5600 from 1998 to my grandson.  It has had many battery changes but a great watch. This new replacement is the same model, but the "Adjust" button is very short and I had to grind the case down, to get it function like the 1998 button.  Okay. After 4 months, the button pushes made weak sounding beeps, and alarm would not work reliably.  I changed the battery, and good for another 8 months approx.  Again,  replaced, and repeat. I think I need to give this much newer 5600 to the grandson, and take back the 1998 one that had no design flaws.

Title: a great watch. I never take mine off
Text: Been buying these watches for 25 years.  The battery lasts about 5 years and then I throw them away and get a new one.  Tried a couple of times to change the battery but unless you get a new seal they will leak after the case is opened from the back.  Regardless, a great watch.  I never take mine off.  On when I swim, shower, scuba dive to 100+ ft.  Dropped repeatedly, beat around every day and they just keep on working.  The only watch I will ever buy.

Title: Nice
Text: great watch for a good deal. I drive a tow truck and I'm hard on watches this thing is so far indestructible

Title: My Missions Trip Watch
Text: I bought this watch to take with me to my missions trip. So far this watch has been amazingly great! And the best part is that it has a classic design! When you walk around the streets of villages during a mission trip, people see your watch and want it, but this watch is classic and less noticeable so you get less people asking you for watches. Yet, on the other hand, its looks are deceiving cause it still looks pretty awesome and it can withstand amazing amounts of activity! I think it's definitely worth it the buy and the amazing price. The only downfall of this watch is that I can't seem to find a way to turn off the beep sound when pressing the watch buttons - someone correct me and inform me if there is a way please! I don't think the instruction manual had it.

Title: ... watch I could wear every day and get a good beating on the job
Text: I bought this watch so I had a watch I could wear every day and get a good beating on the job. Being an electrician, I’ve knocked and dropped this watch all over and it has lived up to its reputation. I find the square look to be stylish and not chunky like the round faced G. The LCD screen is more faded than the tough solar equivalent but I only know this because I own both so unless you had the watches side by side you would never notice.

Title: good service
Text: good job

Title: Classic
Text: This watch is one I can't live with out.  Always dependable!  I use mine as a back up to my smart watch while refereeing.

Title: Great watch for anyone who works around water and anyone who doesn't.
Text: I think I'm on my third or fourth Casio G-shock dive watch since they were introduced back in the 1980's.  G-Shock is a great watch, and much more durable than the lighter-weight look-a-likes even in the Casio series.  I've tried some cheaper watches, but they didn't last.  The current version is a little lighter and more comfortable than the original, but it still has all the functions and capacities that made G-Shock a divers best friend back then.  The price is also a lot more reasonable now than 30 years ago.

Title: Great retro find
Text: This was perfect. My husband got this for graduation gift a long time ago and it finally died. So I was so thankful to find this watch.

Title: The price is high
Text: I dont  like  this  watch.IT looks  like  simple

Title: The boxing doesn’t look presentable for a gift
Text: Good watch. Bought it as a gift. Disappointed that it came in partially broken box and without it’s signature box.

Title: Simple. No Frills. Durable. Classic.
Text: I bought this watch from Amazon in 2015 (Amazon was the seller).  It is now 2021 and the watch is still going strong but now more beautiful with all the scrapes and scuffs of daily wear.  I suspect I will need to change the battery soon but that's an easy and cheap task to do.  The beater watch to end all beater watches. I've also noticed some reviews on many of the G-Shock watches on Amazon complaining about a defective adjust button and how it is too recessed into the case.  Folks, that's by design, y'know, so you don't accidentally screw up your watch settings.  All my G-Shocks are like that.

Title: THIS IS A GREAT WATCH AND HAS BEEN FOR MANY YEARS
Text: Had this sent to a friend for his birthday.  Knew it was a good watch because I have four sons that all like this watch over the last 20 or so years.  It arrived on time and my friend likes it very much.

Title: Affordable durable digital watch
Text: As always a Casio Classic G-Shock.  A trusty friend when the going gets rough.  I would recommend this to anyone who wants a good standard digits watch.  Can’t beat the price too.

Title: A Tough Timeless Classic Watch; A Few Minor Critiques
Text: This G-Shock Casio is a tough classic watch that has been on the market for decades.  It is relatively simple in terms of its features.  It is tough and thoroughly waterproof. There are two areas where I am a little critical: * The band can wear and break over time. * When it comes time to change the battery, it is best to let Casio or trusted professional make the switch.  If the waterproof seal is not reinstalled perfectly during a battery change, the watch will leak and fail. Other than that, this watch should last many years under harsh conditions.

Title: Great everyday watch for physical activity.
Text: Needs a simple yet tough watch to wear when doing yard work and other similar activities. This fits the bill perfectly.  Only “issue” is that the button to change modes is more depressed than the others and makes it hard to press.  But understand it is that way to prevent pressing it by mistake and was mentioned in other reviews...

Title: Great watch
Text: I used to have a watch exactly like this in the 80,s don't remember it being called a gshock , but it's the exact watch , lasted into the late 90's even after major beatings ! The band broke and I lost it or it still might be around ! Love being able to look at it on my wrist and remember the good old days lol , would give it 5 starts but it's new , so needs to past the test of time before I would give it 5 stars

Title: Replacing one I had for 15 years
Text: After 15 years or so my old G-Shock suffered a break in the frame where the band goes through. It could actually be fixed with super glue since the watch still works perfectly. I decided to get a replacement anyway. Unbelievably fast shipping. I mean, seriously fast. I ordered the watch online about 6pm on a Thursday. The watch was delivered Friday. The watch is fine and is the same old dependable G-Shock that I have worn forever. I am not a big fan of the band on this one, however. It appears thinner and a bit shorter. The only replacements I have ever had to make to the previous G-Shocks I have had (only 2 in 30 years) have been to the bands. I can foresee that coming sooner with this one.

Title: A must buy, seriously.
Text: I have been using this baby for almost a whole year now, and decided it was time to give it a review. This watch goes everywhere I go, no matter the time or place, it's performance is incredible. Whether swimming in a local pool, crawling through the mud, banging out your last couple of reps at the gym, or rock-climbing your favorite outdoor boulder, this G-Shock is well worth it, and ridiculously inexpensive for what it brings to the table. Highly recommend buying if you are looking for a practical, decent looking watch that will last a long time. UPDATE: 01/30/2021 I lost my watch, and miss this watch terribly. Still a phenomenal purchase.

Title: My 3rd G-shock in 20 years
Text: Great Watch at a reasonable cost.  Only knock is difficulty in changing battery. But they usually last for 5-7 years.

Title: Great watch
Text: Classic G-shock. Great every day “beater” watch. Very usable and durable. Backlight is better than other G shocks I’ve owned.

Title: One tank of a watch
Text: Classic! This watch is a basic beast. No frills just accurate time and it is nearly indestructible. Get this!!

Title: Battery life about 5 years
Text: I been using this Casio watch for over 20 years, this last watch I purchase was Number 5 or 6. I am very hard on watches and this watch holds up very well.  After five years the glass gets pitted from the type of work I do. When the battery starts to run down I purchase a new one. Great watch

Title: A must have G-shock
Text: Super comfortable watch. I sometimes forget i have it on. The lower profile helps with day to day task

Title: A bit different from the picture but I still love it
Text: The face isn't as clear, its more dark. The words "PROTECTION" and "G-SHOCK" are in gray instead of white, which weakens the aesthetic look. It functions well, nothing wrong with it. It is durable though! I was biking around 15 mph when I hit something, ate s*** and fell on pavement hard, I'm sure the watch hit the pavement too and it still functions well and there's no scratches. ****EDIT**** I ate s*** again riding my bike, going around 20mph or so, landed on my watch, the word protection got scratched off and the shock in g shock. It still works good though! If I wasn't wearing a watch, I think my hand would have been really scratched up.

Title: Budget EDC watch
Text: This watch would get a 5/5 but one of the buttons is smashed in and hard to press.

Title: It is a great watch
Text: This was my 3rd Casio watch. Approx. every 12 to 15 years the battery dies and instead of fixing it I get a new one. I am very happy that the same watch that I like so much is still available. I hope if I'm still around in 12 to 15 years from now this Casio watch will still be available. It is just a great watch.

Title: TOUGH
Text: I like the fact that the watch is very robust and very reliable, the strap that is fitted is of low quality but was my intention to replace to that of a Velcro type anyway so the supplied band isn't of much concern to me.

Title: Nicely priced waterproof watch.
Text: I wanted a waterproof Casio watch for kayaking. I've had good luck with Casio's. I liked this model because it is relatively compact compared to some of the bulky G-Shock watches. My only complaint is the button are a bit difficult to hit with large fingers. Specifically, the light button is difficult to hit. Besides that, the watch meets my expectations.

Title: Unlimited auto repeat countdown timer
Text: Besides everything else being great, this model has (unlike many others) unlimited auto repeat countdown timer. So if you need your watch to remind you at something every X minutes repeatedly throughout the day without the need to restart the timer ever this is the one to have. I would like that there's a solar version of GShock that has unlimited auto repeat countdown timer, hope they will make one in the future.

Title: sports watch
Text: My first Casio sports watch lasted about 30 years so I thought I would try the g-shock watch.  All works well except the button for the 'adjust' mode.  The button is permanently depressed and is not easily used.  You must use a sharp point, like the tip of a pen or stylus of a PDA, to push this button.  This is NOT easy or convenient when you're out using it.  I called Casio and the rep could not tell me if this was to be expected, normal or what.  Otherwise, it's a great watch.  Just keep a pen or one of your fingernails long and sharp to be able to use this key function of the watch.

Title: A classic for a great price
Text: One of the all time great watches, without a doubt up there with Rolex. You can’t complain about a good looking watch that only costs 40 bucks.

Title: Great warranty and works in all types of weather.
Text: I've always been big fan of  Casio watches for over 30 years. Its durability and dependability has always been my reason I only wear Casio watches only.

Title: Time will tell?
Text: The watch is well worth the money. Hope when I open it up to change battery it's not junk inside.

Title: Good quality, i’m happy with my purchase
Text: Good product

Title: Watch You Need
Text: This watch is what you need. Perhaps, you are tempted to look at a more expensive watches, but what you really need is this attractive, functional, and practical watch. Watch, so versatile you can wear them anywhere and do anything, while they keep accurate time and require little to none maintenance.

Title: Great Watch
Text: I've never tested it for water resistance , and I don't fiddle with it to use the timer function. I USE IT AS A WATCH ONLY! It keeps great time, appears to be very well built, and I am very satisfied.  I have no idea what, beyond keeping time, it may or may not do, and I'm certain I don't care.  I just wanted a watch and selected the one with fewest features.

Title: Excellent sturdy watch
Text: I've owned Casio watches like this one (G-Shock classic Digital) for over 15 years and I've always been very impressed. They are tough and dependable and reasonably good looking, though perhaps a tad bulky and with more words than one might want showing on the face. I believe that I had one break down and lost two during that period. I'm now on my 4th. The buttons are a little challenging to operate if you're not coordinated with your fingernails but I generally keep my alarm setting fixed for fairly long periods of time. I swim regularly without problems. I did recently purchase another Casio that was a bit sleeker and nicer looking. It has minute and hour hands- I was very disappointed because it was very hard to set the time. That watch has the number 3321 in a box on the back followed by AW-49H.

Title: Amazing
Text: Got this watch today and it came incredibly fast! Looked over the instructions and everything is really easy to use on this watch. It took me about 2 minutes to set the watch onto the perfect time and date! Not to big like other G-shocks and has everything you need in a watch! Tells great time in 12 or 24hr time also shows the day and date. Has an Alarm a stopwatch and a countdown timer. What else do you need? This watch looks great and is not heavy but yet it feels like you could drop it off a sky scraper and it would survive. Can't say enough good things about it. If your thinking about buying a G-shock or a sports watch in general save your money and buy one of these its unbelievable value for money and you  would be crazy not to choose it!

Title: Great Watch! Wonderful Gift!
Text: I bought this as a gift for a friend of mine in the Marine Corps, since he lost his during boot camp. He loved it, and I loved it. Not because of the great deal I got (2 day shipping here, compared to 2 weeks with another vendor) but because I also worked at a watch and jewelry repair shop. I knew exactly how to program it without looking in the instruction manual, and it was SO easy. You can set it for normal time, as well as military time. It also has timers and a stop watch. All of the basics you could ever want. It seems like a sturdy watch, and comes with a warranty, so you also get some peace of mind. Overall, great buy. Definitely would buy another one for him if he lost this one too. :-P

Title: Exactly As Advertised
Text: Purchased this before military training and it held up to all my training requirements. Highly recommend.

Title: I love it. Works great.
Text: Rugged, dependable. I love this for it's simplicity and reliability. I didn't need something with 41 times zones. This watch is perfect for me. The buttons are indeed quite recessed but I have no problem pushing them as I have strong fingers. I can see how someone might. Classic Casio controls that I'm used to make it even better.

Title: It's not too big and usefull to many sites.
Text: You can use it in formal and informal events. The Office, meetings, swimming pool, yards, construction sites, traveling are all the best places to use it. Maybe if you are wearing a smoking jacket could be too much, but noone would notice it. By the way, Perhaps you can't change the wrist dand or it's difficult to adapt another one, but I like it as it is.

Title: Durable timepiece.
Text: Cannot beat this for reliability and cost. Great goto watch for just about any event.

Title: Easy to read. Even in the sun.
Text: I like that it is pretty simple to read and change the time and date

Title: i need to use a pen to push the buttons in.
Text: nice watch, but the top left button is so flat i need to use a pen or something to push it in. the buttons are sort of hard to access, but yet they dont dig into your wrist so its a toss up. holding up fine so far, waterproof. comfortable. as most chinese crap its a bit confusing getting to the count down timer and stopwatch, but all around i expext to get a few years out of it. i dont see anything on this watch that sets it apart from any other. Nothing makes this watch industrial rated or bulletproof. its a w-mart quality watch. if anything, the thing is thicker plastic on the face witch will help with scratching. but so far so good. cheers.

Title: God Tier
Text: Best utility watch a watch enthusiast can buy.

Title: Favorite Casio (so far!)
Text: This is a great watch--light, tough, easy to read. It won't break the bank to buy one, and yet it keeps time as accurately as any watch costing 100x as much. Update, June 2013-- Minor note, the face illumination used to activate when the alarm went off but stopped doing so after about six months of use.  I'm not sure if this is a normal function of the watch to prevent excessive battery drain, but it's not a big deal for me.  It's still working on the original battery. The band has shown some signs of wear, but other than that, it's still good to go.  I don't shower with the watch on, as I've heard that warm water has a "drying" effect on watch bands made of this material. As I said earlier, a great watch for the money.

Title: Superb watch!
Text: Superb watch with wonderful features! I ordered it for my brother and he is extremely happy to have it. He is really impressed by the working of this watch that helps him schedule and manage his all task properly. Multifunctional alarm, shock resistant, seconds digits flash on the display, EL Backlight with Afterglow, an auto-repeat function is exactly all he wants in his dream wristwatch.

Title: A favorite
Text: Excellent classic G-Shock from Casio. This thing is so easy to wear because you don't have to worry about it. Get the thing dirty, get it wet, lift weights, go to work, go on a hike, go to a waterpark - do anything! It's reliable and easy to read and use. The thing simply won't let you down.

Title: You get what you pay for so this seems to be value.
Text: It seems to be everything they say it is, but I have not heard the alarm sound really, it is not loud enough for me so I intend to check if it has volume adjustment . 0 & two to the watch on sound at the moment but it is good value if you if you don't mind the alarm. See the video I have found on the watch it is accurate except does not mention volume. the buttons are not easy to use for me also. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gJV-p5RgrPg

Title: Perfect simplistic digital watch that packs all the abilities you need.
Text: Durable, long battery life. Shows time+seconds, and date with month, and day+day of week on the primary mode. On the second mode it has an alarm that you can set the date you want it to ring, and the time, or just the time everyday. There is also a hourly beep if you want that. On the third mode you have a timer. An than on the fourth mode you have a stopwatch. On all the secondary modes there is the time in the upper right hand corner, and what mode it is right next to the time.

Title: Meow
Text: The media could not be loaded. Very nice. I scratched it up at work but it’s holding up. Very well made

Title: Dependable
Text: I work in a mine. And can say this watch has stood the test. In water 10 hours a day. Been hit with rocks, took an accidental blow from an axe and still looks new.  The price is steep compared to the cheap Walmart watches. But when you never have to worry about buying another it something to consider.

Title: Good stuff for the price!
Text: Durable high quality product with the only downside being buttons that are difficult to push due to small size and stiffness.

Title: simple
Text: this was a gift to my cousin. he loved it. He speaks highly of it.

Title: Light won't work while setting the alarm, etc...
Text: I'll really date myself if I tell you how many years I've had these cheap casio watches, and find their sheer utility to be so unbeatable that fancy-schmansy expensive gold watches I have langish on a shelf. I've worn  these watches to over 100 feet diving, banged and pounded them while doing all manner of rough chores, and had them last for a shocking number of years between battery changes, despite the abuse. Unfortunately, since the last model Casio G-Shock I had, Casio apparently changed the control buttons so that, in this model watch, you cannot work the light while you are setting the alarm, timer, or watch. This is a MISERABLE flaw since, for just one example, if you use the watch as an alarm clock, you have to get up out of bed and turn on the light to see the darn thing. Ditto for setting the timer countdown for "snooze alarm" purposes. If anyone knows of a G-Shock model where the face can be lit while setting it, I'd love to replace this one.

Title: Beautiful, robust, functional watch
Text: Casio seems to produce a couple of gems like this one, tough watches which are accurate and will last you a life time, if you need a watch and are weighing your options this model definitely covers all the bases. Another model claiming to do more is spinning yarn, a model doing less is probably not far off the same price. A good buy.

Title: Its a great watch! Rugged and waterproof.
Text: We have had these before, so I knew what to buy. This one is actually a bit thicker than our previous watches, so it does occasionally catch on things or bump into stuff. But its rugged enough that this wont hurt it. The buttons are recessed so if you have a puppy, he wont be able to change the time as with the older style. The puppy did change the time a couple of times, when he hit the buttons with his baby teeth, but that wont happen much, its funny. And we really dont anticipate diving to 200 meters, even tho the watch will deal with that depth. But if you drop it over the side of your sailboat in deep water, you will at least know that it will continue to run.

Title: Best watch ever
Text: Best freaking watch ever, I decided to pull the trigger on this cause I have small wrist and before this watch I was using a g-100 1a1. Anyone with small wrist need to buy this watch ASAP and you get all the goodies that come with a g-shock

Title: The Perfect Digital Watch.
Text: This is the quintessential G-Shock. Everyone should own this watch. Everyone from a watch collector to the average person this watch can do it all. From a feature standpoint it does everything a watch needs to. If the Apocalypse ever happens this the watch I want on my wrist. For less then $50 you get a watch that is good to 200m plus water resistantance, which the buttons are designed to be used underwater.

Title: Skip the bells and whistles you know you will never use - this watch is basic, but for what it does, it does very well.
Text: What you see with this watch is what you get.  It's got the basics down pat.  If you are looking for something that keeps good time, has an alarm function, stop watch function, count down function, back light, and is tough as nails - this is the one you want.  I have had this watch for a month now, and the time keeps well +/- 15 seconds each month.  I swim, run, sit in the sauna/steam room, and shower at the gym in this watch and have had zero issues.  The size fits my wrist well, and is comfortable with a good weight.  The draw of this watch is that it doesn't have a lot of bells and whistles but for what it does, it does exceedingly well.

Title: Classic G Shock
Text: This is a very cool watch. The history that surrounds the Casio G Shock line all kind of stems from this watch- if people imagine a G shock this most likely is the design that would pop into their heads. It has a cool, rugged appeal to it and long-time users can attest to its toughness. For me personally this is my first foray into the G shock world- I have always loved my Suuntos but thought I would give the brand a chance. It is an extremely functional watch but it has some downsides for me. First is the comfort- the band on this thing is hard plastic which tends to dig into your skin after a few hours.. with my Suuntos' rubber straps I forget I am wearing them. The second downside may be more of a personal preference rather than an issue with the watch. I wish it were larger- this is a rather small watch for my wrist, if the face were 50% larger it would be perfect. So make it a little larger and give it a quality rubber strap and it would be 5/5.

Title: First G-Shock--Will not be the last!!
Text: Lost my last sports watch (Ironman), so I had a good excuse to treat myself to a new sports watch.  I was leaning towards an Ironman, since I've had 2 in the past and enjoyed them both.  However, after searching "sports watches" in the search tool, I came across the G-Shock brand watches.  As a veteran, G-Shocks aren't new to me (it seems as if all my Corps buddies had one except me). After reading several reviews on this model, I decided to make the splurge. My watch arrived yesterday, and I'm very impressed.  For starters, the watch looks nicer in person.  It has a strong, masculine tough-look about it. Yet, it's classy enough to wear outside the gym or "field". Additionally, the watch is extremely durable, and doesn't feel like its made from cheap parts. I definitely recommend. Enjoy!

Title: My husband  loves This watch
Text: I bought for my husband. He loves this watch. It’s his every day watch. It reminds him of when he was younger. It’s a simple watch that you can wear with casual clothes. He’s a T-shirt and jeans kinda guy and it works perfectly for his everyday wear

Title: Great watch.
Text: Bought this for my Son.  He is rougher than a dry cob on watches and they usually get lost in a week or two due to his working conditions.  He loves this one and say he thinks it would stop a bullet.  Maybe not, but he loves it and likes the idea that he can see the display in bright sunlight and he uses the alarms to keep appointments and to make calls at a certain time.  Great watch.

Title: Classic. MUST HAVE
Text: As much as I line wearing an SKX I needed something tough for work and this is IT!

Title: Good watch
Text: Nice watch. A little smaller than expected

Title: The upper left button is very hard to press.
Text: I have owned this G-shock watch in the past multiple times (or at least extremely similar model(s)).  I am drawn to the water resistance, ruggedness, and simplicity.  The upper left button is recessed making it harder to press, I presume to prevent accidentally entering the time set mode.  I don't recall having a big issue with this in the past, but this time it was so hard to press that I decided to return it and get a different Casio watch.

Title: yes
Text: It's just like the one I had years ago, if it last even half as long ( old one lasted 20 years ) I will be very happy

Title: The Watch From Hell
Text: 1.  Buttons to adjust all functions are indented.  Earlier models (that I have owned) had them extruded.  (think of an inny or outie belly button).  Result:  Very frustrating for fingers of any size to adjust anything on the watch 2.  If, in setting the time for 8:00 for example, you happen to go to 9 you have to continue through the remainer (10-11-12) etc to get back to 8.  The earlier version allowed you simply to back up.  If in fact you could do this with this watch, I could not because of the darn indented button design) 3.  It is difficult to tell if the alarm is in the on/off position and more difficult to tell if the hourly alarm is in the on/off position.  As a side note, who buys a watch with the goal of having an alarm that rings on an h ourly basis?  You may find that an hourly alarm during the nighttime bothers you or, if not you, your BFF.  During the daytime co workers tend not to be fond of that function.  Maybe a light or maybe shading of the watch face to indicate an alarm function is activated would be helpful 4.  A booklet that is so small and at the same time so lengthy it is intimidating.  We are in an internet age.  Put in a o ne page note that says  "For detailed instructions consult Casio/Net at Watch instructions and download the particular ones you need.  (That would save paper as well) 5.  Amaxon, please tell your representatives how the Review process works.  I could not figure out how to send this e mail so I called the Rep.  I told him I knew I was overlooking something and that it was my fault but he did not have a clue what the review process was all about.  Luckily, my daughter called and figured it out at once. I co ntinue to be a huge fan of Amazon.  I love the ordering process and always asking other companies why they do not adopt similar, simple procedures.  I love the book selection and the option to buy new or used. ChickMone  ckmone@gmail.com

Title: Really a fantastic minimalist protective everywhere budget watch
Text: Really a fantastic minimalist protective everywhere budget watch. Very accurate time keeping for those of us that smash into random things this watch last longer than most without scratching the face up. Still the same exact model as when they first came out but cant argue with the durability. To bad the straps the first to break but I have a 10 year old model in my sock drawer still alive and within 10 seconds of the time minus daylight savings.

Title: All you'll need!
Text: I own several watches from high-end Swiss watches all the way down the line and I just love this Casio watch. Keeps excellent time is durable water resistant just a great all-around watch honestly.

Title: GREAT WATCH
Text: We only buy G-Shock! Amazon is the place to buy them. Great prices.  Waterproof shower ,pool and ocean. Excellent quality! A little hard to set the time and date. read the directions once you get it you got it.

Title: Twice as nice.
Text: I bought the first one back in 1983 and had it till the wristband broke in the mid 90s. I'm so very happy to have found that Casio re-released it I bought an extra!

Title: Un clásico de Casio que no pasa de moda
Text: El mejor reloj clásico digital de Casio, con un tamaño intermedio, muy cómodo y que te sirve para todo. El precio es excelente.

Title: Great multi-function durable digital watch
Text: I have owned this same model Casio watch for about 25 years!  It does everything I need it to do!  It is very durable with all the multi-functions I use all the time.  This is the third one I have owned each lasting at least eight years!  It is the best.  Did good for over 30 years of field police service.

Title: El mejor g shock, sin añadidos innecesarios
Text: El g shock por excelencia, práctico, sencillo y con un diseño ya comprobado. La correa no es la mejor pero por el precio esta bien, la lectura a pleno sol no es del todo clara, se debe girar un poco para ver mejor contraste pero no es algo trágico, son solo pequeños detalles, en general es un relojazo

Title: IMPRESSIVE !
Text: A great looking & very durable watch at a great price i definitely recommend this watch !

Title: Great watch
Text: Great everyday beater watch. Wear it to work and the gym. Zero complaints.

Title: Nice, but I like to old one better
Text: I had one just like it, but the band kept breaking and the crystal was cracked so I opted for a new one.  The one feature I use the most is the stop watch,  which has been changed.  The old one had the on-off and reset buttons next to each other onthe right, the problem with the new one is the reset button is recessed on the left, very difficult to press every time to zero the stop watch.  if I had known about this change, I would have looked for a different watch.  Otherwise, it is a great timepeice. Bill

Title: Great watch!!! A +++
Text: Well for the longest time I’ve always gotten Casio g shocks. However they have been getting on the bigger size. For my wrist I prefer under 42mm. And this watch is the perfect size for me while still getting the g shock protection. If your thinking about getting this watch just go ahead and get it. You won’t be disappointed great fit and so light won’t even feel like your wearing a watch.

Title: Buy it, you'll like it.
Text: The only watch you'll ever need. Rugged, well made, excellent back light, easy to read. That's it.

Title: Great casual watch
Text: This is my 3rd or 4th purchase, of this exact same watch. I've been using the same model for a couple of decades, at least. I've used it to snorkel, do manual labor, to go running, in the gym... It's pretty indestructible. You'll mess up the band before the watch dies. The battery life is years. I've cleaned it by strapping it inside my dishwasher (no hot-dry!). For the price you can't beat it. The only criticism is that it's a pain to set accurately, but when you do it once it keeps time pretty close to perfectly. After that, just the hour for daylight savings changes twice a year. I recommend this very highly.

Title: Boton defectuoso
Text: El reloj lo compré hace un año para mi hijo de 8 años, hasta ahora ha resistido y me parece que es un producto de calidad. Sin embargo, desde que se sacó de la caja el reloj presentó un botón demasiado hundido lo cual hace muy dificil ajustar la hora y poner el cronómetro en ceros, lo demás funciona correctamente.

Title: Great watch short wristband.
Text: I have had this exact same watch before and the band was never this short. I'm not sure why it is so short but it is and I don't have a real big wrist.

Title: GW5600 Watch Review
Text: I liked the watch but the adjustment pin was too short and the whole not recessed enough to get my finger and finger nail in in order to adjust the time, the stop watch and count down, etc. I had to try to open the area up so the pin was far enough exposed to be used. This is a flaw that needs to be addressed. The basic design is good, but the specs need to be held more tightly.

Title: Great working horse
Text: This watch is just amazing. I've been using it for almost a year now, It survived 7 days of sailing and swimming in the sea (was a bit whitish during those days because of all the salt - but it's all black again now), I've been in the sauna with it, in the pool, skiing, working with powertools... ZERO issues! It's a perfect work/outdoor/activity watch, that will not let you down. It's not as bulky as other G-shock watches, but also doesn't look cheap and flimsy like non G-shock casio digital watches..

Title: great watch. the band just will not last as long as the watch.
Text: the watch will last longer than the band. I wish they would make a band that lasts as long as the watch! if the band was as good as the watch I would have gave it a 5 star!!

Title: No solar feature
Text: Casio Men's DW5600E-1V "G-Shock" Classic Digital Watch This watch is the same as the one that I have had for many years. I wanted one with the solar feature but the one that I bought which had it, didn't have the auto reset on the countdown timer. I had to have that feature so I bought one that had it but didn't have the solar feature. The new one works fine and I didn't have to learn new software so I'm pleased but would still like to have the solar feature.

Title: If you have a large wrist you won't like this
Text: I am a huge G-shock fan and own several but this original 5600 is much smaller on my wrist than I am accustomed to. Great watch, but too small for me. I'll probably gift it.

Title: The band is very good quality and comfortable
Text: I bought this watch for my job working in a pool, I needed a digital, easy-to-read, waterproof watch and this definitely delivers. The band is very good quality and comfortable. The only very small complaint I have is that buttons are very hard to press, I had to use my house key to press them but this is probably just to keep the water out so I don’t mind it. Overall great watch, I’m sure it’ll last me forever.

Title: A watch.  It tells you the time if you look at it.
Text: Tells you what time it is.  It is only accurate to what ever time you set it to.  It's a watch folks.  Buttons are stiff, but it is water resistant, so give and take.  It's a watch, not a wizard Harry.

Title: Awesome watch. Built like a tank.
Text: I have had a lot of Casio Watches, and the case always seems to go before the mechanism. Usually no more than a year or so. This one seems different. It is much more rugged than the non "G-shock" models, but at a much better price point. Don't expect all sorts of gizmos. This watch tells the time, has an alarm and stopwatch, a good light, and not much more. I love the recessed dial which has kept the crystal like new, despite rough and tumble treatment. Wish it had "world time" because I travel frequently. Casio, are you listening? I will buy it again when this one fails.

Title: Nice watch
Text: I like my new g-shock watch and here is why: Really tough and durable compare to others watches including Timex ! No any extra crap features like Pressure ,temperature and some random circles ))) Simple, small and actually look OK on my ~7 inch wrist and yet very usefull. Can see date, time, and day of the week at the same time ..... no so with many new g-shock watches. After setting alarm, watch or timer return back to time mode with one click ...no need to go through 100 menus. Able to see time on top when in countdown mode or stopwatch mode. Keep very accurate time so i dont really see need for atomic signal. Battery should last 2-4 years depending on use, again i dont see need in solar power. At only $36 - BEST purchase i ever made.

Title: Bang for your buck
Text: Fantastic watch. It wears very easy. Also its easier to read then the negative display watches.

Title: Great watch
Text: I love this watch it is small and comfortable my everyday watch stock drip

Title: Worth the price.
Text: Inexpensive, durable, comfortable, and a good looking classic. You can’t go wrong with this g-shock. 👍🏻

Title: Great watch!
Text: This is a replacement watch. My old watch lasted many years, through lots of abuse. I expect this watch will last many years as well.

Title: Tough, inexpensive, accurate
Text: I've always preferred analog watches but after beating up a few decent ones at work I decided to go with the Casio. Not the greatest looking timepiece but tough as nails. I find that when taking a quick glance while working I need to be more deliberate and angle the watch towards me more than when I had a high contrast analog face, especially in dim light. (it does have a light but requires a press of a button) The rubber band though durable and comfortable does trap perspiration under it. I like the "Classic" style compared to some of the other style G-Shock watches, though relatively large, it's not overly so.

Title: Excellent!
Text: The watch is excellent for daily use and you don't have to babysit it all day, The only issue with it is that the display is a bit not clear if you see it in several angels, I think there is an upgraded version of this model that has a better display and sharper numbers. I gave it to my brother and he enjoys using it.

Title: Watch Came with a faulty button
Text: Sent it back. The watch buttons were incredibly hard to press. In addition, one of the buttons were completely broken. I had to use a pointed object in order to use the button. Overall, I lost my confidence in this model and decided to move on. I'd love to get one of the old school styles, but I think I will go for a nicer model than this one.

Title: Rugged Little Timepiece
Text: I use this watch every day I go to work. It can take a beating. I work with concrete and chemicals and the resin band makes it pretty easy to clean and is very comfortable. The stopwatch function is quick to access and great for staying on top of task time management. Highly recommend as a great timepiece that won't break the bank but will hold it's own against the elements.

Title: Las fotografias no pertenecen al reloj.
Text: Las fotos no son del color y apariencia reales del reloj.

Title: Water resistant to the upmost.
Text: I like my Casio digital watch. Keeps the time and date very well.

Title: Great watch that's for the active man
Text: Got this for my husband for Christmas. He's a SWAT officer so he needs something that can take a lot of everything. The watch is perfect.

Title: You can’t ask for more at this price point!
Text: Great price. Functions really well. It does everything it says it can do. Highly recommended!

Title: Solid watch for work and play
Text: I've been wearing this watch for almost a month and it's been great. I've accidently bumped it, been out in the rain with it, and sweated in it. It's held up just fine, as to be expected. My only nitpick is that the top left button seems to be more set inside the case that the others, which makes it hard to press when needed. But I don't need it that often. So it's not a huge deal.

Title: Classic Casio G-SHOCK
Text: This is a simple Great Casio watch with History highly recommended pass it down to your kids or buy as a gift.

Title: From a man who loves practical things.
Text: This watch brings me joy. I haven't had it long, but I've taken it to the gym, split and hauled wood, worn it at work, worn it in the shower...I love it. I got rid of my smart watch for this and I couldn't be happier. Don't believe me? Try it for yourself.

Title: I wanna own all the DW5600 series
Text: This is probably the best watch ever made for the price.  Totally recommended

Title: Sturdy, Simple and Easy to use. An everyday watch, for everyday tasks.
Text: It's sturdy, simple and easy to use. It may not have all the features that a new G-Shock has, but it's more than enough for what it costs. I swim every monday, wednesday and friday, has worked perfectly underwater, and its easy to read without too much trouble, so I totally recommend it as a swimming clock. Its display is as clear as new, and I havent noticed any fogging issue. I totally recommend it as a daily watch, for every task you can imagine.

Title: Package Damaged on Arrival
Text: I bought the watch and the G-Shock package was damaged on arrival, so I asked for a replacement. But the replacement package is also damaged on arrival. I am wondering if these watches are some randomly wrapped no-brands, instead of genuine G-Shock.

Title: Excelente
Text: Reloj recibido en perfectas condiciones.

Title: My Dad's Favorite Watch
Text: I bought this solely because I remember my dad wearing one as a child. It wasnt until after I watched a few reviews that this is an iconic watch that gets the job done. Only thing I dislike are how you have to push the buttons in, but its described as a feature so I wasnt caught off guard.

Title: Decent Entry Model
Text: I like this watch other than the 'A' button being almost too recessed within the case to be useful

Title: Lo mejor de Casio! Gama G-SHOCK
Text: Hermoso reloj! Casual y cómodo. Se ve muy bien en la muñeca, yo soy una persona de manos pequeñas y no se ve grosero.

Title: Awesome
Text: For under $50 you cannot to wrong with this G-Shock. This is the G-Shock that started it all and its easy to see why.

Title: still a stellar product.
Text: the purist cry that the original g-shock was metal and way better. it was tough but heavy. this newer one is lighter and yes, cheaper to make but still tough as nails. you don't see many broken ones. look at the price-for that money its hard to get a tougher,more functional watch, in my opinion. great lay-out, bright light (the light on the original stinks compared to this one),ect. this watch has been copied so many times,many may associate it with the cheap clones that resemble it. it may not cost much but it aint cheap.it has everything you need and nothing you dont. its a good dive watch and easy to use. i still love the original but this one is a very good timepiece. if people scoff at your "cheap plastic watch" just laugh at them like youre crazy. mean people leave crazy people alone. try it. it works!

Title: The ONLY G-Shock needed!
Text: This original Classic G-Shock Square was my third G-Shock purchase. I made the “mistake” of buying some newer models (which I love) thinking I would enjoy them more because of more features and unique looks. However, I was wrong.  IF I HAD TO KEEP ONE this would be it!!! MUST have in any “real” G-Shock collection!

Title: The BEST watch I ever had! Very comfortable for small wrist!
Text: I wear them daily for more than two years and I can tell that I've never had a better and more comfortable watch than these! I have a small 6 inches wrist so I wasn't sure that this watch will be comfortable. It is that comfortable that I often forget to take it off before I go to bed. Recommend!

Title: Reliable and indestructible
Text: It is reliable and indestructible. I use it for travelling, it is very accurate, has an alarm, is really waterproof and you just know you always have the time available, whatever happens. Only the ergonomics are not that great. The buttons are hard to reach and press, and the alarm is not very loud. And it is just ugly. But as a watch it is very good

Title: Good watch but weak band
Text: I bought Casio 5600E just about 3 years ago from Amazon. This was my main "outdoors & travel" watch, and I wore it to the office quite a bit. So far the watch is doing just fine - I am still on the original battery, all functions are working (as it should). But there is a weak link with this watch which is its band. My band started to crack around the eyelets and then developed a 1/8" crack on the side. To replace the band will cost me around $20, and the cost of a new watch (with a new band) is around $40. This watch uses non standard with for bands as well, they are hard to find. My local watchmaker did not have one in stock and said he could order one for me, but I am seriously considering a new watch. For "indestructible" watch 3 years is just too short to earn top marks. Fix the band, Casio! On a positive side I used to have Seiko 5 stainless steel watch & band and that used to leave black residue underneath on my sweaty hand. There was some metal to sweat reaction. Casio's metal back never left any marks on my hand.

Title: best watch I ever owned
Text: Unstoppable... except for that band...the band will break every 6 months or so if you wear this in the real world. Band aside, best watch I ever owned. It's been to 110 ft of seawater, doused in corrosive solvents, covered in paint, hit with everything you can imagine, wore in the sun, snow, rain, and heat and it just won't die. Every function I need without one I don't. If they could just make a durn band to keep it on my wrist I'd love Casio forever.

Title: You can’t go wrong with this watch !
Text: A great every day watch. Stylish for any type of event or day. You can’t go wrong with this watch. 10/10

Title: Its a Casio always been reliable for me.
Text: Watch is as advertised would and may buy again

Title: Great buy but one questionable point.
Text: As of day two of wearing it, the Watch is how I remember it except the adjust button is reset in. This makes it somewhat difficult to actuate. Not sure if this is done on purpose or is negligent assemble.

Title: Great watch.
Text: Great watch, perfect for my dad which is simple easy to read for his old eyes. He loves it

Title: I'm just not thrilled with the purchase.
Text: great product.  I'm just not thrilled with the purchase.  I hope this watch will serve me for many years.

Title: Good
Text: Good cheap watch

Title: Great wAtch, not news
Text: If you want a watch it's the only one you'll ever need. That being said Casio makes a solar version, but the battery in these ones lasts a decade. I think I can afford a battery a decade.

Title: Quality slipped on this one
Text: I gave this a 3 because the quality really slipped on this watch. I used a different G-Shock for about 3 years prior to buying this one, and I am very disappointed in the quality of this one vs the previously owned watch I had. Right out of the box, the buttons are recessed into the watch making it impossible to use your finger tip or even your nail to push the buttons. You’d have to use a pen or something similar to utilize the use of the buttons. Another thing was that it was actually more grey in color than black like the pictures perceive.

Title: That is keeps good time, and water resistance taking a shower ,so far.
Text: That the upper LEFT BUTTON IS  SOMETIMES HARD TO PUSH TO CHANGE OR STOP SOMETHING. THAT IS AGGRAVATING! I FINALLY FIGURED OUT THAT WITH THE END OF A PEN I CAN PUSH THE BUTTON TO WORK!!! I WAS VERY DISGUSTED WHEN I READ IT THE BOOKLET ,PAGE E-20,  "THE BATTERY THAT COMES LOADED IN YOUR WATCH WHEN YOU PURCHASE IT IS USED FOR FUNCTION AND PERFORMANCE TESTING AT THE FACTORY. THE TEST BATTERY MAY GO DEAD QUICKER THAN THE NORMALLY RATED BATTERY LIFE AS NOTED IN THE USER'S GUIDE (I didn't get that). NOTE THAT YOU WILL BE CHARGED FOR REPLACEMENT OF THIS BATTERY,EVEN IF THE REPLACEMENT IS REQUIRED WITHIN YOUR WATCH'S WARRANTY PERIOD." THAT IS VERY, VERY, VERY AGGRAVATING!!! WHY CAN'T CASIO PUT A VERY GOOD BATTERY THAT LASTS YEARS. I HAD A CASIO (THINK A G-SHOCK)YEARS AGO THAT THE BATTERY LASTED YEARS!!! I STOPPED WEARING IT BECAUSE THE EXTERNAL WATCH WAS WORN AND LOOKED UGLY! I WENT TO A STORE AND SAW ANOTHER CASIO MODEL THAT I THINK SAID, '10 YEAR BATTERY"!!!!! WHY CAN'T CASIO DO THIS WITH THE G-SHOCK WHICH IS A MORE EXPENSIVE MODEL?  IT IS  AGGRAVATING  OF GETTING A NEW BATTERY AND MAKING SURE THE WATCH IS WATER 200m RESIST. I TAKE A SHOWER WITH MY WATCH. THE BOOKLET ALSO  SAYS YOU CAN NOT USE IT FOR SCUBA DIVING BUT THE WATCH IS  WATER 200m RESIST.  VERY DISAPPOINTING!!!

Title: Simple watch, amazingly good
Text: I’ve owned this model of watch for over ten years, and it is almost bomb proof. My first one lasted me 7 years in the Air Force, a year in Afghanistan, and it is still going after five years as a cop. I purchased a second one as a backup, but I’m not sure I’ll ever need it. I’ve only changed the battery 3 times, which is insanely good when compared to others.

Title: great beater watch
Text: Classic G-Shock; great beater watch.  Swapping out the initial watch that was delivered as the "adjust" button was so deep-set that I could barely access it while on my wrist -- kind of defeats the purpose if I need to take it off to set an alarm or count-down timer, for instance.  That said, will always have one of these watches in my collection.

Title: Will last forever.
Text: Bought this as a gift for my dad.  I have worn this same model for years.  It is indestructible, no matter how hard you beat it.  Completely waterproof.  Easy to read.  Even in complete darkness.  Casio g shock is the only watch I’ll wear.

Title: This Is Great!
Text: This watch instantly became my favorite day to day wear! Looks great as is however I'm most likely going to mod it for a Zulu strap since I've never been a big fan of rubber straps. I will say the buttons are a little hard to hit at times and I do it them a lot to time things. Other than that it's probably the best $45 you can spend.

Title: Sporty watch w an affordable price
Text: I pretty much love this watch since I spend most of my times outdoors. And play sports.

Title: Most utilitarian watch I have ever owned
Text: I was a scuba diver in the service, having been trained as a Nave Combat Diver in 1963. We were issued Rolex diving watches. This watch is more durable and easier to use than the watches we were issued.

Title: Bueno pero no para cualquier tamaño de muñeca
Text: Un excelente reloj pero a mi muñeca se ve algo pequeño si tienen una muñeca de 55 mm y hasta unos 45 mm se te vera bien la mía es más grande y se me ve chico. De resto es un excelente reloj.

Title: Amazing watch
Text: Super accurate, comfortable, easy to read, good backlight, great water resistance. Yes, the top left button is difficult to push but that's by design and hasn't hindered me in any way.

Title: From house work, to on the job, my needs are met
Text: I ordered this watch because when I was a kid I always remember by dad always having a Casio when he did work around the house and more than 15 years later he has only had to replace the wrist band and battery. I have been very pleased with it thus far.  I have worn in it in the ocean, everyday in the shower, while laying, grinding and resurfacing concrete at home.  The watch has not stopped working even with all the dust and grit that I am certian has gotten into it.  I also wear it at work (hospital), have had multiple liquids spill on it, hit against a wall and has been grabbed off my wrist. Still looks, works, and fits just as well as the day i got it. Thank you!!

Title: meh~
Text: I owned this model back in the 80's and it lasted me 10+ yrs and when I stopped wearing it, it was because the plastic band fell part.  The digital watch itself was fine. So fast forward to 2011 when I decided to give this model another go.. different outcome this time~ I purchased this watch again - March, 2011 & it finally died yesterday (March 27th, 2015). Tbacklight began getting dimmer & dimmer over the course of the past year and a half or so.  At some point the backlight stopped working.  Now it's completely dead.  Most likely needs a new battery.  Considering this watch only lasted ~4 yrs, I'm done with Casio's.  It might be that the watch I got is a dud, but I'm not going to spend another $40 to find out.  Best Regards~

Title: Great watch. Does the bare minimum
Text: Great watch. Does the bare minimum, nothing more and nothing less, and that's what I wanted. The face G-shock padding around the face stands out a bit, but is nowhere close to the overly-fat-looking sports watches I've seen where it looks like you have a hockey puck for a watch. Main screen tell your time/date/day, has an alarm, has a count-down timer, has a stopwatch (that still lets you see time in top-right-hand corner), and screen lights up with that green background when you need it. It's also comfortable and really light. I wear it on bike rides and forget it's there most of the time.

Title: Simple. Good.
Text: My brother and I started looking at watches at the same time because our friend revealed how handy they were if you're hiking and don't want to carry a cell phone around. After browsing the internet, my brother was convinced that he needed a $200.00 atomic military-grade watch. I thought it looked great, but I went with this classic G-shock instead. I spent $40.00. We both got our watches. His is fancy, has a pretty big face, and a bunch of features he doesn't seem to use. It's fit for deep sea scuba-diving, which he doesn't do. Mine is simple, tells time, and I can set it to an atomic clock myself. Mine looks good, has an alarm, and a stopwatch and it can get wet and take a beating. I feel I made the better choice.

Title: Great watches for a Great price
Text: Watches are really fine and I like them a lot, but I have a problem with adjust button because it's stuck further then others and complicated to work with it, so I hope to fine the way to fix it

Title: Love my watch
Text: Gets a lot of compliments. Have had it a few months now. Doing great. Never take it off.

Title: Beautiful retro design G-Shock watch
Text: The watch arrived in brand new good condition and I am very pleased with the watch. There is a bit of confusion in the time setup though. Although the instruction menu says progressively pressing the "Adjust" button cycles you from seconds to minutes to hours and then to Day, it actually doesn't. It cycles you to the year on the top left panel where the Day is supposed to be displayed. As long as you key in the correct day, month and year; which cycles from 00 to 99 for 2000 to 2099, the moment you press the Set button, the Day will be reflected.

Title: Light is great, super good basic watch that you can really kick around.
Text: Awesome watch! Super basic, and cheap for a G-Shock. Unless you're an 80sphile and/or going fro something uber-hipster, it is NOT a fashion piece. But it will indeed take a lickin and keep on tickin. The stopwatch and timer work great, and the light (full screen green glow, as opposed to the actual light) is actually better than I remember the wwatches being when I had them growing up. Side visibility is limited, but unless you're not wearing the watch on your wrist, you won't notice. Also, read the instructions for a couple cool functions I didn't know existed!

Title: All you need
Text: As the titles states, this is the only watch you need on your collection. 200 water resistant, have dived with it and had no problem with. Stealing wrist time out of my more expensive pieces. Backlight is great just like the rest of the other functions on the watch, totally recommend it.

Title: RELIABLE
Text: Bought this watch for my dad and he love it.

Title: Classic!
Text: I’ve had it for two weeks and I can tell I’m gonna have this sucker for a long time. Favorite Casio, no competiton. Fantastic electroluminescence (2 seconds long), calendar all the way through 2036 or something, and great timer! I use it for exercise and daily work and I can’t believe I didn’t get it sooner! Best $40 I’ve ever spent! Edit: It's been three years, best watch I've ever owned.

Title: decent affordable digital watch
Text: This watch is a little heavier than some digital watches, but that is the G-Shock casing. It has the features you expect in a digital watch, day, date, time, alarms, countdown timer, stopwatch with multiple laps, and back light. The font size of the display is smaller than some but still readable. The band is a higher quality rubber?/silicone?/plastic? material. Generally the bands on these watches give out long before the watch does, it is important to be able to buy a replacement band, one is available for this watch. All in all, a good value for the money.

Title: Nice
Text: Nice

Title: A Great Watch for an Active Lifestyle
Text: I had an older (12 years plus) watch of this same model that was stolen, but was an outstanding watch that I had used for triathlon training, world travel, and soccer officiating.  Naturally, I sought out the same model again, and I have not been disappointed.  This timepiece is everything that it is advertised to be and then some.  Lightweight, but extremely functional and easy to use, an individual with an active lifestyle cannot go wrong purchasing this watch for many years of enjoyable service.  I would suggest that you have a qualified jeweler replace the battery about every two years to ensure that that the water resistant integrity is maintained. God bless!

Title: Works perfectly fine
Text: Works as it should. No problems so far.

Title: Great
Text: I have not had this watch long but so far it is great, I have a small wrist and this does not look overly big. I wanted a simple watch with the durability of the G-Shock and this fits the bill perfect. Only reason for the stars is the length of time I have owned it

Title: Simple, Effective...Perfect!
Text: Just received this watch a few days ago.  This is a no nonsense watch with basic features that most people will only ever use.  It's slim, easy to read, and fits well on my wrist (I'm a bigger individual...6'1" at 235 lbs).  I love how the display has the day, date, and time at the same time.  I also own a Suunto Vector, which is very bulky and useful for outdoor adventures...but for daily use, this Casio is perfect.  I bought a G-Shock Riseman about a month ago and although it was a great watch with great features, I found that I didn't need all the features and bulk for daily usage.  I returned the Riseman to a friend and bought this.  Happy with my decision!

Title: I love this watch. Great watch for nurses or anyone active
Text: I purchased this watch >1 year ago and this thing is still ticking I have taken this thing into salt water, fresh water, hiking and use it at work. I wear this watch everyday all day. The band is comfortable except in the heat but its bearable. I dont really use the alarm or stopwatch so I cant speak to their user friendliness, but I need it to tell tell military time and date which it does perfectly. I use harsh chemicals to clean it when I get blood or other bodily fluids, no issues. I would recommend this watch to anyone

Title: Good watch
Text: I know this watch since I was manager at a Woolworth store in Puerto Rico

Title: Do the job
Text: I had many g-shok watches as i served in the army. Most of them were bigger then this one. Now i understand that the simple one is the best, i recommend it.

Title: Pretty good, but Adjust button problem for me
Text: Great watch, I wear it most days, and I've loved it The one thing that frustrates me is the same problem that I had with my last g-shock watch which is that the adjust button is slightly further pushed in than the other buttons, it's still perfectly functional at the moment however I'm just nervous that I'll have a repeat of what happened with my last g-shock where the adjust button gradually became harder and harder to push and eventually that button stopped working Otherwise though the watch has been doing its job and hasn't given me any true problems yet. My hope is that customer service can help me fix this problem before it becomes worse.

Title: Great bang for your buck
Text: Great square Casio gshock. Less than $50.00. And it’s very durable.

Title: Durable watch with all the features you need.
Text: This has long been my favorite model watch.  All the features needed without the gimmicky displays.  The only reason to buy it this time is that I lost the last one.  Be sure to check that the seal is perfectly installed when you replace the battery.  Also, be sure to get this model.  Casio sells one that has a very similar display, but is not a durable.

Title: Very pleased!
Text: Bought  for my son as a Christmas gift. So far he actually loves it and it's not easy to find him something he likes. He wears it every day!

Title: Great watch
Text: Band is a little stiff and takes some time breaking overall this is an excellent value watch

Title: Beautiful watch
Text: If you want a watch that will last you forever this is the one. Everything works flawlessly. sits nicely on the hand and is of sturdy built. take it swimming with you too and in the shower. for the office or if you play sports. love it.

Title: Lasted me through college, grad school, and my first year of teaching
Text: I love this watch. I bought it when I was 17 and it lasted until I was 24. In the end the backlight caused the screen to flicker and the band snapped. For the other seven years it worked great through every day and night wear, through sleeping, showers, pools, and the ocean. I almost never took it off. Buying a new one now

Title: great value at less than $40
Text: good size and good looks.

Title: Long lasting.
Text: Great watch. This is my second one. My last went two weeks ago after nearly 15 years. This watch will last.

Title: Must have!
Text: Dependable end extremely durable. Can’t beat the price.

Title: Classic
Text: The original G shock, a beast for the buck, a simple watch, purchased mine for casual attire.

Title: It’s a good watch
Text: I like it. I’m a butcher and it has been resilient against everything

Title: Awesome watch
Text: Bought one for my Dad but I liked it so much i got one for myself.

Title: good watches. using it for kiteboarding
Text: would like more smart features, but this watches not about that.

Title: Great value for money
Text: Very good watch for the money. I will be using it daily and have never had an issue with any Casio product.

Title: The best, the original!!!! Dont get a newer one, this is it.
Text: Excellent, I had this watch when I was in the Gulf War. Its THE ORIGINAL!!! The one that started the GShock movement. Don't get a newer version, this is the best!! I got it for my 13 year old son, he loves it, wears it all the time, I'm happy because I know its indestructible and will last him into college with just some battery installs over the years.  I was sorely tempted to get myself one!!!

Title: Very functional watch at an affordable price.
Text: I've had this watch for nearly 2 years and it still works as new. It features functions such as an alarm, timer and stop watch that I use on a daily basis whether I'm working out, going on a hike or keeping track of the brisket I'm smoking. It's very easy to set the time and date. The buttons are a little difficult to press, especially the light button at night, but all in all this is a great watch that I highly recommend.

Title: Great watch
Text: What’s not to like about this watch. I’ve had it for 5 years and it still works like a charm. Very durable. Simple. The battery has even lasted that long. My wife got me a Apple Watch for Christmas otherwise I’d still be wearing it today. 11/10 would recommend.

Title: classic
Text: classic, and good looking

Title: Great Watch
Text: I bought it about 2 years ago and I love it. I feel very comfortable with this watch. Light weight and soft.

Title: Nice
Text: Nice watch for the price

Title: Its great!
Text: Came in perfect condition, looks great and its going to last a lifetime!

Title: Keeps Extraneous Features to a Minimum
Text: I was looking for a watch.  Not a camera.  Not a thermometer.  I don't need to know when high tide is at my favorite beach break in Costa Rica.  I don't need any cute features which I never use. I mainly wear a watch when I run, and I use the countdown timer feature for intervals.  Having the clock display while in the countdown mode is really useful. I actually set the time, date and timer without even having to use the instructions. How good is that! The buttons are rather stiff, and I can see where that could be a problem if you have big fingers.  But that is a small price to pay for this quality at a reasonable price.

Title: Good watch
Text: Good basic watch. No water issues swimming. Durable.

Title: Great watch, waterproof and durable. Strong battery.
Text: Great watch, 2nd G shock I've had the first one is from 2010 and still has the original battery. This one functions the exact same. I've used this one fishing and surfing in saltwater it's functions well. I can't figure out how to reset the stopwatch but I haven't looked at instructions. Very durable and scratch resistant for what I do for work/fun.

Title: Good looks, bad buttons
Text: The Good: Great looking watch Seems to be pretty rough Illuminator light is very good Functions are as expected: time, alarm, countdown timer, stopwatch Size is OK, fairly large The Bad: The buttons are terrible; mode, light and start/stop are very hard to use but I think can be get used to, but the adjust button (upper left) is almost unusable (This is a design issue to prevent accidental use of adjust button, not unique to my watch). If you want a tough good looking watch this may be it. If you want something cheaper (both price and quality) but easier to use go for the F-201WA (the light of the 201WA is terrible, it is not water proof, only water resistant, but the buttons are great, has all the 5600E functions plus dual time and 5 alarms. Size is also much smaller).

Title: I don't like this watch
Text: Why giving it 5 stars if I don't like it ? Read on. I have this watch for two years now. It does its job well giving time and date and even remembers the 29 of February without asking to adjust the date. I've banged it against metal racks at work too many times and it took the beatings without problem so far. Mine goes ~30 seconds faster every month. That's not bad at all for a 40-buck watch. That level of accuracy is good enough for me, I don't need sub-second accuracy. So why don't I like it ? This watch meets all my needs, and that's why I don't like it. It prevents me from having good excuses to buy more fancy watches that I want. Eternal needs vs. wants.

Title: Resisten
Text: The best watched in the world

Title: It is a Casio G-Shock
Text: It is a Casio G-Shock and can be run over by a tractor trailer and it will still work fine.  What's not to like.

Title: Good watch
Text: Watch have angels on the band and seems like male cologne. Definitely the watch I wanted but it’s too visible used.

Title: Reliable perfectly sized beater or everyday watch
Text: It’s just a great reliable beater watch. Purchased an metal after market case for 50$ and looks great. Just as nice as the metal-G’s

Title: Reset button
Text: The upper left reset button is very hard to push.  It seems to be inset too far.

Title: Buena compra
Text: Me gustó que mi esposo está encantado con su reloj de trabajo, y el es particularmente delicado con el reloj trabaja muy bien, lo recomiendo

Title: Good quality
Text: Awesome watch exactly what I was looking for. Needed more of a utility watch, it has everything you need for the price; date, timer, and alarm. Water and shock resistant is a plus, not gentle on watches so being durable is a plus.

Title: Excellent value for money for a classic watch
Text: It's probably one of the best value for money G-Shocks you can buy. It's tough, confortable and simple to read. no unnecessary functions and, as it's smallar than other G-shocks, wear very well on smaller wrist. the design is a classic. I love it as an everyday beater I can use on vacations, doing sports or just to let my kids play it with

Title: As described and quickly shipped
Text: Ordered for a specific vacation trip and received it on time. It is working very well and although the instruction booklet was not user friendly, there was a scan to a online instruction that worked very well.

Title: Recommend!
Text: Great watch! Easy to set and read. I have a smaller wrist and it fits it well. Definitely recommend!

Title: Excelente producto
Text: Cumple con lo pedido

Title: Everything is simply displayed and easy to grasp at a glance
Text: Can't go wrong with this one. Basic design, very intuitive, minimal features but in my opinion that's desirable for a watch. Everything is simply displayed and easy to grasp at a glance, and it's really nice having the day and date right there (two things I am constantly forgetting). I think it looks great too, I wear it everywhere. I even felt comfortable wearing it to a job interview. I've haven't had it long enough to speak to its longevity but it seems very durable and I imagine it will hold up for quite some time. If you're looking for a nice looking simple and intuitive watch, this is it.

Title: Buena marca
Text: Es muy buen reloj para trabajar ni te das cuenta que lo tienes puesto

Title: Great watch
Text: My last Casio watch was a piece of poop since it kept resetting itself so I was a bit hesitant to buy another. However, I am glad that I did. This watch is simple, easy to use, and the display reads well. I have skinny wrists so the watch face is a little big but it still fits great otherwise. It does have some weight to it but it I can still wear it comfortably. This watch does not reset itself like its predecessor. I am happy I went ahead and bought it.

Title: Like Right Date, 12/24 hour time & Stopwatch Function, many Casio's over years.
Text: The first year I got it, was leap year, it could not be set for Feb 29th. it is a pain to set properly compared to other $40 Casio's I've bought over many years, '97-98 and before. I do NOT like mechanical watches with a date, they are wrong, at one or more times a month, rather just have the time & a clean clear face. Have nearly missed a flight when the second hand does not contrast on a mechanical watches with Minute & Hour hands. This is the watch that most often appears in my pictures on Amazon, Twitter, Facebook, Gmail or Yahoo mail accounts & Pen Pal account images. - like owning it! Worth the money.

Title: Accurate, rugged, but with some limitations
Text: The watch keeps accurate time and is easy to read.  It also seems to be fairly rugged.  But I am somewhat disappointed with three features.  First the little buttons on the sides to control and set the watch are very small and highly recessed.  So using these tiny buttons with your fingers can be tricky and difficult.  Second is that the sound the Alarm function makes is very low in volume.  In fact it is so soft that it does not really wake me up from sleep (and I am not a very deep sleeper).  Finally, setting the watch is not intuitive, and you better have the instructions to read in order to not mess it up.  It would also be nice if the watch would be available in some colors other than black.

Title: Classic G-Shock is the best
Text: Fast shipping at a decent price.  Haven't put it through the test but appears to be well made as with all G-Shocks. Ive owned various G-Shock models including solar powered versions.  Bought this one because I wanted something simple and rugged without all of the distracting bells and whistles;  I like that the LCD only has the day, date, and time. Watch is not overly bulky like other G-Shocks. ***2017 Update*** After 4+ years, this watch is just now starting to lose battery life. I used it  during workouts, hikes, and travels overseas. Thats pretty good!

Title: Like it!
Text: I had this style watch in the early 90's and it got blown up on a military demo range in Okinawa since I had the only watch that had a timer to measure time fuse. When we went to see the effect of what we had blown up we did find the watch, which was laid on the ground about 8 ft from half a stick of C-4, it was still operational but unaware able. So 23 years later I found my favorite watch at a good price. Lesson learned? Don't loan out your watch on a demo range. This is a tough watch. Simple with no frills and keeps perfect time. I am very pleased with this watch. And there is even a solar powered version now!

Title: Its a watch.
Text: I dont read instructions so getting it to go to 24hr mode was hard. And there is still 1 button that I have no idea what it does.

Title: Decent but not worth $50
Text: So this is a basic watch which I like, however, it’s so basic, I don’t feel it’s worth $50. I see other G-shocks on sale time and time again for $60 or so at Kohl’s that are much more sturdy and better quality. I’m returning it. Again, it’s a fine watch but doesn’t seem worth $45-50 to me.

Title: Great watch
Text: Bare bones, old school military style.

Title: Bad band great watch
Text: Not a fan of the band so I put a NATO band on it. Other than that, it would be 5 stars.

Title: DW5600E-1V Classic Review
Text: This is my second G-Shock replacing the DW9052-1V Classic, just because I didn't like the 9052's look. But anyways. This watch is cool. It's an old model so it's isn't that stylish compared to the newer G-Shocks, but I'm fine with it. What I really like about the G-Shocks are mainly that if you move your arm around, none of the buttons will press by itself and that has to be my all time favorite feature on the G-Shock. And secondly it looks really cool, the brand itself. And this particular model. Overall it's a sturdy watch to own, which is good.

Title: Good watch for the price
Text: Item arrived fast..Looks great...This is a smaller G Shock so the numbers my also be smaller I like this G Shock because it is smaller then many other G Shocks but still is tough. Very happy with this watch...Again great for the price.

Title: Una maravilla de la ingeniería
Text: El G-Shock por excelencia. Un modelo robusto y confiable para cualquier tipo de situación.

Title: Simple, tough, functional digital watch
Text: This watch is just what you'd expect from a Casio G Shock - a simple, tough, functional digital watch.

Title: Perfect watch
Text: I love this watch! It’s not too large for a woman’s wrist.

Title: Need to get used to buttons.
Text: The top left button gets stuck but it works.

Title: Fast shipping and great product!
Text: Awesome watch but smaller than i thought... Buy this it will be faithful for many decades.

Title: Great durable compact watch
Text: I like minimalist type watches, slim and compact. This has been a rugged lightweight option for me and has served with me on a deployments and training and work ups. I serve with an infantry unit. This is my second watch of this type, and only bought this because I gave someone this watch to hold during a soccer game, and he never returned it. I don't take this watch off other than for when not authorized to wear a watch, and that is not very often.

Title: Have loved this watch since it's initial introduction
Text: Have loved this watch since it's initial introduction. Have purchased 4 or 5 over the years. For a waterproof sports-watch - it has a very thin/slim profile - which will slide easily under long sleeves.  However, I have yet to be able to damage this watch despite exposure to extreme conditions.  I end-up purchasing a new one when the band finally gives-out (cannot purchase exact replacement band).  Can't say enough. . .

Title: TAKE MY $$$$$$$$ After many months of contemplating purchasing a smart wrist device (Apple
Text: NO BRAINER!!! TAKE MY $$$$$$$$ After many months of contemplating purchasing a smart wrist device (Apple, Fitbit, Garmin) - I realized that all I needed/ wanted was something that told me the time and which had a programmer timer w/ basic alarm features. For $40 and over 30 years of un-changed technology. Where can you go wrong? It strange how happy I am.
