Almost the same satisfaction I got when from trading in my 2014 Jeep Grand Cherokee Overland in for a basic 2015 Chevy Equinox w/ zero bells & whistle's..... something about VALUE.

Title: Old School Classic
Text: Looking for a cheap back to the basics digital watch.  Nice to wear while working in the yard etc.

Title: Amazing watch!
Text: I purchased this a little over a year ago and couldn't be happier. I have worn it pretty much 24/7 (except showers) I've worn it swimming, I've worn it in 100+ degree heat and -5 degree winter cold. I've bashed it against walls, desks, you name it. It looks pretty much the same as it did when new, I don't even see a single scratch on the crystal. The original battery is still ticking and I've heavily used the light and stopwatch features. This thing is a beast! Some may laugh at these "ugly/bulky" digitals, I say bah..I grew up in the 80's and a digital child at heart..I'll take a digital watch over analog any day.

Title: This is my favorite watch
Text: I had three of these over the years. None of them ever quit working. I replace them only because I am ruff on them. After scratching them from my abuse I just choose to start over. With this watch you can forget about being careful with it. It can take it and is there when you need it. I have other watches given to me as gift but the is my everyday go to.

Title: A Perfect Watch
Text: Like someone else said - this is a 5-star watch at a 1-star price. I'm very pleased with it. Everything I need and nothing I don't need. Hey, it even has instructions that are understandable!! On a side note - after many years, we still can't figure out my wife's digital watch - incomprehensible instructions. That's what I wanted to avoid with this purchase. I also wanted to avoid the larger G-shock models - they have a lot that are too bulbous for my wrist. This design is one of the smaller ones - I wouldn't purchase anything bigger. Alarms? I only need one. Readability - I need good contrast so it's easy to read. And, Indestructible! For $40? I love this watch and highly recommend.

Title: Simple, sturdy.
Text: For the cost and durability, you can't beat it.

Title: Best watch
Text: Favorite watch.. had it for almost 5 years now and have changed battery only once. Not big and bulky and essentially became a piece of my arm. This is my number one favorite watch because it’s almost indestructible and reliable. Best watch ever especially for the price. If your a working man I recommend.

Title: As described
Text: I like this watch because it's durable and is rugged for working outside.

Title: Great Watch
Text: can’t go wrong with this watch. no complaints

Title: Nice watch
Text: My son plans to use this for college

Title: Do not wait. Click that BUY button
Text: This is awesome watch. Delivered on time. Well handled. Just want to write one thing for you guys: Do you like the shape of this watch? - just buy one; because, you do not have to worry about the rest, Casio knew what they created. I can even wait wait for apocalypse with my beer and this watch 😆

Title: 4 years of abuse, and still works perfect.
Text: I bought this 4 years ago, still running on its original battery. It has taken a few solid beatings, but everything still works. I'm amazed, it should have been broken by now, considering it is a cheap watch and how I have treated it, but it's not.

Title: Very nice, inexpensive watch.
Text: Small buttons can be difficult if one is looking for quick operation when using the timer/stopwatch function.

Title: Can take the hits of everyday life
Text: So far a pretty good watch for the money. As I use it as my daily beater watch and man can it take the hits of everyday life. I do not need to worry when I go out hiking or am at a concert that I will damage this watch. Very good buy for everyday use as it is not very bulky as i thought it would be and the band that it comes with is pretty comfortable.

Title: Perfect time
Text: Lots of nice features and foreign time zones for travel. Used a lot for kayaking and motorcycling. g Shocks are tough, reset with the atomic clock, and the solar power keeps it running continuously.  You can’t beat them for a work or sports watch. I have owned two for years.

Title: In G-Shock we trust
Text: Another great G-Shock... Basic functions: Time, date, ST, countdown timer, alarm, led light Easy to set up; Overall long battery life (depends on how it is used) Keep in mind: it's not a mudmaster... Pressing the buttons could be a little dificult to people with large fingers

Title: Great all-purpose watch
Text: You can't beat this Casio for the price.  This is the second one I purchased. The first one was getting pretty beat up (8 years) and the cost to replace the bands was about half the watch, so I just got a new one.  This is an all purpose watch and it truely takes a lickin' and keeps on tickin'. This watch keeps great time and has all the important features for me; date/time on easy to read display, good illumination for night viewing, alarm, event timer and rugged design. This watch has performed great in the water as we swim a lot in the summer, both in pools and beach.  Never a problem with leaking even after replacing the battery.  Good seals! I'll most likely buy another one after I beat this one around.

Title: buttons hard to use
Text: I have used variation of this watch for years.  I like my old one better but it finally died.  It was a bit smaller but they do not make small ones any more.  My real complaint is the buttons.  I find them difficult to use to the point I do not use the features I brought the watch for.  Another concern is the band.  Experience has taught me they last about a year and this one does not look as easy to replace as the my old ones.  There seem to be a lot of variation of this watch and I will be looking for a smaller one with easier to use buttons

Title: It has been running fine. It has all the features of the basic ...
Text: I bought this watch over 2 years ago. It has been running fine. It has all the features of the basic electronic watch that are actually useful, including countdown timer and stopwatch. It's practically undistractable, but if I lose it, I would just get another one. Very comfortable to wear. It also has this cool, 80's classic look :) (EDIT 2021) Still going strong. I can't believe it! No problems whatsoever. Very happy!

Title: It's a G-Shock
Text: Not my first G-Shock so I knew what I was buying.  As a paramedic I decided I wanted something else to wear at work.  Instead of my nicer mechanical watches so I wouldn't have to worry about cleaning it every shift.

Title: Great daily beater at a good price
Text: Great daily beater at a good price.  Not as feature rich as the tough solar or the multiband 6 version and not as tacticool as the M military variant.  But it gets the job done.  And if its good enough for NASA its good enough for your wrist.

Title: Nice addition
Text: Nice addition to my watch assortment. Its been years since I've owned a digital watch. I ordered this one as opposed to the 5610 because I didn't need all the other stuff. I'm am pleased with this watch. Size isn't so"g Shock" big but just right. I can read it even with my aging eyes. Now if they make one like this but with solar and atomic time I would be all over it. 5610 was just to cluttered.

Title: Caution
Text: I have owned several Casio G-Shocks over the last 20+ years and have always gotten good service out of them.  They have always lasted over 4-5 years each and I have a solar powered one that is still going strong.  I would still be using it but it had too many bells and whistles and I wanted a simpler g-shock that had only a few features like the alarm and a large display.  This one seemed to fit the bill perfectly.  That's why it also was a great disappointment. The strap broke after the warranty period was over at one year, 2 months.  I was lucky to find a generic replacement that fit, so not a big deal.  However, after one year, 6 months, the display got glitchy where only the bottom half of the numbers displayed.  A local Casio authorized watch repair shop said the battery was probably bad and possibly the lcd.  But the cost to replace just the battery would be close to what I paid for the watch itself and there would be no guarantee on the water resistence.  To send it back to Casio would be just throwing more good money after bad as I would have to pay for all shipping, insurance etc.  Just not worth it for this watch. I understand these are, in fine watch parlance, "throw away" watches.  Use them for several years and when they break down, throw them away and buy another.  But at only 1 1/2 years?  I expected much better from Amazon and especially Casio.

Title: El g shock perfecto aunque sería mejor más contraste
Text: Perfecto para muñecas pequeñas, el diseño clásico es muy sobrio y bonito, aparte es muy cómodo, no hay mucho más que decir que no se haya dicho de este reloj, y por 45 dólares, es el reloj digital perfecto. Si pusiera mejorarle algo sería mayor contraste y definición de los números en la pantalla.

Title: I would recommend any G-Shock watch for anyone who engages in physically ...
Text: I actually owned this watch once before. I am very hard on watches and have found that G=Shocks are the only watches that hold up for me for work. I get 10 to 12 years out of a G-Shock watch. For me that's a lot and makes them well worth the price.  I would recommend any G-Shock watch for anyone who engages in physically active work and/or recreation.

Title: Ready for action.
Text: Classic, durable and ready for anything. Slim and low profile design does not follow current trends and will always be in style.  There are many videos out there showing just how tough it is. Factor in the price and you have a great value. Ideal for law enforcement, military, security, space exploration (NASA approved model), construction, demolition, work outs, sports, diving (200M water resistance).

Title: Excelente Reloj, un superclásico de Casio
Text: Estoy muy contento con mi G-shock DW-5600E es una muy buena opción de compra, lo recomiendo 1000 x 1000, un reloj durable, con todo lo que se ocupa de un reloj.

Title: Great watch.
Text: Easy to use and straight forward design. Great watch for work or sailing (including racing with a count down timer for starts). This is my 3rd similar model over almost 30 years. The only knock is I wish the band were slightly longer. I'm a bigger than average person and the band is just big enough. If I were much larger it wouldn't work.

Title: Great sub $50 watch!!!
Text: Great watch. Probably one of the smallest "G-Shock" watches out there. Has wall you'd need in a watch. A timer, a stopwatch, an alarm clock, and regular time keeping. Shows the time, day of week, and date by month and day of month. It illuminates very well, has a complete backlight illumination and NOT just a small green led to the side like many cheaper watches do. The price isn't bad. Overall this is a great watch.

Title: classic
Text: classic watch

Title: Great Watch with a Major Flaw!
Text: The watch was really comfortable on my wrist. The functions were basic but practical. The biggest issue with this DW5600, the “Adjust (A)” button was completely recessed into the case and unusable. It’s annoying because I had to take off the watch and use a pen to adjust the time or clear the stopwatch/counter timer. Pros: well made, practical, fits comfortably around the wrist, displays time while in Stopwatch or Timer modes, and inexpensive Cons: recessed “Adjust (A)” button makes it impractical to use

Title: This is the second one of these watches that I ...
Text: This is the second one of these watches that I have owned . The original one got damaged during a recent motorcycle accident. Despite the case being all scratched and cracked the watch continued to run perfectly. I owned the original for over 5 years during which time I hardly ever took it off.... Showering , swimming , diving , rough usage, etc.... it went through it all without missing any time at all. I also found the additional features..... alarm , stop watch and count down extremely helpful . An ideal watch for every day usage . And  its rugged looks make it quite stylish too.

Title: Cheap: you get what you pay for
Text: Considering it was a G-shock I was hoping for durability and quality. The buckle is super cheap and one of my buttons were all the way presses in when I opened the box. Wouldn’t be that annoying if I didn’t use the stopwatch all day every day.

Title: Limited viewing angles
Text: I love this watch overall, but one thing disappoints me and I hope this makes sense... its easier to read this watch when it's on my right hand than on my left (and I don't like having a watch on my right hand - just not used to it) - see attached photos. There is something about the watch face where it has a very limited viewing angle. I hear that this is different on more expensive models. Who knows. This is still a solid watch and a decent purchase. I got it for the 80's retro look and I like it for that reason.

Title: Inexpensive, but not cheap.
Text: First impression, it is a nice basic watch.  It has a slim profile.  I don't want a watch that is too wide or too thick. The profile is perfect. However, the band has a somewhat cheap appearance and feel.  Also, my arm is not very big and I am three holes away from the end of the watch.  This should be ideal to wear in a production and warehouse environment. I purchased this watch based on the many positive Amazon reviews, especially about durability.  Reasonably satisfied.

Title: simply good. reoccurring alarm is great
Text: very good. good size

Title: Hard to read display and small buttons recessed to much.
Text: I'm 52 years old. Owned this watch when I was in my 20's, and it lasted me about 5 years. Great watch! Ordered a new one and discovered the digital readout is too small for me to read due to deteriorating close up vision. The buttons on the watch also seemed more difficult to depress to activate the different features. This watch will be perfect for a lot of you, just not for me anymore. I returned it.

Title: As shown in Amazon
Text: Easy to use. No need to charge it every single day.

Title: The problem was in the shipping and handling
Text: I have doubts about whether or not the watch is new. When I opened the bubble wrap I saw the box was squished and opened from all angles. Also, the “adjust” button on the watch is sunken into the hole/socket. Luckily it still works and I was able to adjust the time and date. The watch looks awesome, and I’m sure I can fix the button, but like I said, I don’t know if the watch is really new due to the poor condition the packaging came in.

Title: Absolutely love!
Text: I never used to wear watches because I always had my phone. Now I have a technician job where I'm often not allowed to use a phone. It is amazing knowing the time, knowing the date for writing service tickets, and I've beat it to death and it still looks beautiful. Had to replace the battery in the first couple months because my chime stopped working. Was 13 seconds fast over a 3 month span. Bothers somebody like me, but is a non-factor for most people.

Title: Very nice strong watch
Text: I find This watch very smart and attractive, and quite comfortable to wear for a g-shock watch. I really like the classic retro 80's look of this watch too. It has obviously the time, alarm, countdown timer and stopwatch. all the digits are quite large and easy to see. It also has a nice aqua green glow for the backlight which stays on for a few seconds when the light button is released. I might just buy another one of these watches, since I'm starting a small watch collection, so I'll have 1 to wear and 1 on display, it looks great on display! I heard these watches are used by the military, and emergency services like police and firemen etc.

Title: The classic
Text: Well, the Assembled in Thai version. Great watch.

Title: The only watch I've ever needed
Text: 6 years old and going strong! I've only had to replace the battery once so far. This watch is road warrior! The front glass barely has any fine scratches on it. The band is holding up great. I've had to clean the nastiest gunk off this watch and it still comes through. I'm pretty sure this watch will out live me.

Title: Poorly made, one of the buttons came loose
Text: My previous G-Shocks were really sturdy and well made, but I suppose this one was just too cheap. One of the silver buttons came loose after just a couple months of light wear, and doesn't stay in anymore.

Title: very good watch
Text: i like that it tells time

Title: My First G-Shock
Text: Nice watch, my first G-Shock. Took me 30 minutes to figure out how to set it but now no problem. Wasn’t sure I would like the band but it turned out to be very comfortable. Just what I hoped for.

Title: my first G-SHOCK, not bad~
Text: Most people in my country recommend 5600 or 6900 as the first G-SHOCK you should buy. Well, around $40, the price is acceptable. After a total transit time of about 20 days I got my DW5600E-1V. Good looking with time, week, day and month display, no solar no wave, that's rightly enough for me. I gotta wear it everyday, but for official business time I'd take it off. Not bad, I mean, very good watch. I love it! The package weights about 0.6 lbs, so you can add something else light (no more than 0.3 lbs better) if you wish, I mean, if you must pay for a international transit fee to get the goods just like me

Title: Classic G-Shock is still classic
Text: One of the best watches of all time. I wear it over my more expensive watches.

Title: A Must Have
Text: Purpose: Everyday use. PROs: It's a G-shock. Affordable Price for the quality and brand. Easy to configure Simple design, not too flashy but attracts attention from a watch/ timepiece enthusiast. Size is perfect. It fits under a long sleeved shirt. CONs: The light button is a little difficult to access at night. It's hard to differentiate the button with the protective groves of the face. I love this watch. I own a couple G-shocks and this is by far my new favorite, This is my 1st 5600 Gshock and i will definitely purchase another model in a different variant soon.

Title: Simple and not entirely overpriced...
Text: I use this watch and almost every function 10-20 times a day.  It's the perfect functional watch.  No frills, just features that work.  Real buttons.  Immediate access and stop/start/reset of timer and stopwatch.  I tried other watches with touch screens, heart rate monitoring, altimiters, etc, and as it turns out those are just worthless marketing gimmicks that didn't work (at least for me).  Their menu's were long and complicated and basic features like a timer or stopwatch were buried and hard to get to or unresponsive due to the interface.  If all you want is multiple ways to time workouts, runs, rests, or anything else that requires accurate and easy timing, this is your watch.

Title: Can't beat it for the price
Text: Works as expected. Took it free diving a few times now. It's been down to 40 feet of saltwater with no issues.

Title: Watch band
Text: Nice sporty wrist watch Light weight/ well shaped Only I dislike about this watch is the band I thought band would be wider than actual Anyway, overall its nice watch

Title: Best watch money can buy
Text: Best watch ever, God tier watch

Title: OK but too small
Text: OK, but not for me. After 22 years and two straps, my favorite Casio G-shock 2608 broke at the hub. Couldnt fix it so I ordered the DW5600 to replace it. It was the only one shown with a clean face and not all that clutter they put on them now. While this watch (the 5600-E) functions, I don't like it. First, it's too small to read (more like a woman's watch). Second, it feels cheap and light like it was stamped together. Finally, its buttons are very hard to work. I gave it three stars because it does work, it just doesn't suit my needs and expectations

Title: Mi favorito de siempre
Text: The media could not be loaded.

Title: awesome watch, very simple to use and not "fancy" ...
Text: awesome watch, very simple to use and not "fancy" and gaudy and I've probably owned one of these since I was in high school in the early 1980's.  they're great watches. I have used the Casio G Shock from this purchase on 37 scuba dives in fresh and salt water and have made multiple dives to 100, 90, and 80 feet and it stays waterproof just great!

Title: Perfect throwback watch!
Text: Awesome retro digital watch!

Title: Excellent watch
Text: It was exactly the watch my boyfriend has always used and he loves every single thing about it.

Title: A workhorse
Text: This is my third G-Shock.  I do wish they would make the watch band so it lasts longer.  They crack eventually and then break.  Replacing them is possible if you are handy and patient, and I am neither, so I buy a new watch well before the battery fails on the first, which is admittedly a waste.  Otherwise, I need no other watch or stop watch or travel alarm.

Title: Again, again, again
Text: I have purchased this watch for my husband of 38 years about 8 times. Obviously he loves it and it is reliable. What is not to love?

Title: Perfect
Text: Super reliable when all your devices die. Love the 80s vintage look of the Casio fused with G-Shock.

Title: Durable, no frills, workhorse
Text: I wanted a durable digital watch for the police academy.  When I thought durable, I immediately thought G-Shock.  I wanted something that would be easy to read and not be cluttered up with other information and dials that no normal person uses.  This was the perfect watch.  It gives me the date and time in the time zone I'm in, and I can set an alarm or countdown timer if I want, which could come in handy.  Of course, it has a stop watch which is also useful.  Unfortuntaely, I can't tell you the date, time or tide in Sri Lanka at any given day, but that's A-OK with me.  I give this watch 5 stars.

Title: I like the peace of mind that whatever I put it ...
Text: I confess I haven't had it long but have dropped it on tile once and concrete once and not even a blemish. Accuracy for me has been a half second to the minus each day on par with factory specs. I like the peace of mind that whatever I put it through on a daily basis it will perform. You can feel the solid construction when you hold it. Classic and disappears on the wrist with time viewing at an instance. The value exceeds the price and there are no worries.

Title: What's not to love, it's a G-Shock
Text: What's not to love, it's a G-Shock. Put em thru the paces, beat em up,yard work, manual labor the 9 & still coming up roses just wash it off & it's ready for another brutal day. What other watch can you say handles anything you throw @ it & still look like new when your done ?...None. G-Shock spans the distance between Beater & Tool watch.

Title: Stealth Tank
Text: This is a "Stealth Tank" of watches. Looks great. Works great. Not too big or small. Shows no signs of slowing down. I'm am very rough on watches, and I will be buying another one if the time EVER comes.

Title: All you need
Text: Great value and reasonable size for a g-shock. Fairly cheap and built to last.

Title: Husband in Construction Work
Text: I bought this exact model over ten years ago for my husband who abuses the watch daily in his work in commercial construction. I don't know how the watch has lasted so long with the rough wear it gets, but it worked perfectly until the day it "died." I replaced the battery once and the band once.  I looked at newer models, but my husband insisted that I get the same one he has grown used to. He doesn't like the more complicated features on the newer versions.  It arrived, was set to the correct time, and has now been worn daily. Husband loves it and doesn't want to change a thing. Good durable watch with simple features.

Title: Great beater watch
Text: Love this watch. Just bought it for the first time and love the comfort, fit, and quality. Takes a bit to figure out how to use it but once you do it just works. I have every confidence that I will be using this watch for many years to come. Can't recommend it enough especially for the price.

Title: Awesome watch
Text: Love it. It’s a great watch for the money and so much more

Title: DW5600 One Tough Watch!
Text: Once you put it on........ well....i won't bore you with my  experiences with it. I am sure you will have your own time with it.

Title: Very comfortable to wear and light weight.
Text: It fits very nice on my 7" wrist. The EL light is very clear. Nice watch!!!!

Title: Iconic tool watch
Text: Great bang for the buck, might be the best watch for a little money. Legend!

Title: Casio G-Shock reloj digital clásico para hombre, Classic, talla única , Negro
Text: Very good!

Title: Good all around watch.
Text: Seems to be a good reliable watch. Slightly smaller numbers than my previous Casio watch but also 1/3 the price.

Title: Its a pretty good watch.
Text: What i liked about this watch. Is that its very versatile and its great for every day use.

Title: its only $42
Text: I've worn mine basically everyday now for the past 5 years and its still going strong

Title: Se recibió en perfecto estado.
Text: Muy bien! En perfecto estado.

Title: Dependable classic at a value price.
Text: Dependable, accurate, durable, everyday watch. This is my fourth Gshock. When you find one that works, you stick with it.

Title: Timer and stopwatch difficult to use.
Text: The A(adjust) button is recessed too much making it very difficult to reset the timer and  stopwatch functions quickly.

Title: Great watch
Text: I've read nearly every review on Amazon about this watch and everyone was spot on about the watch. What I got was a great watch with no other fancy features that a lot of these new G-Shocks have (I own two other G-Shocks with those fancy features). Like a few other reviewers, the only downfall of this watch is the band. It's like if I don't put on and take off my watch with caution that it'll rip at any moment's notice. But I did pay $42 for a wonderful watch that I hope will last me for a LONG time, and the band can be replaced so that's the least of my worries. I am very satisfied with this watch!

Title: and has a cool sporty look as well
Text: If you need to wear a watch to go rescue hostages, this should be your choice.  It's simply the toughest watch you can get, and has a cool sporty look as well.  It comes with an alarm, countdown timer, and a chronograph.  This watch will put up with whatever you throw at it... or whatever you throw it at.

Title: Great wrist watch
Text: I wanted a good watch to replace my Casio Protec Solar watch. After a lot of research which involved considering other brands, I decided to buy this one. It is much lighter and costs a lot less.

Title: I like the general toughness,  water and shock resistance as well as long battery life.
Text: I like the general toughness,  water and shock resistance as well as long battery life.

Title: Great, small G-Shock!
Text: Great watch in smaller/smallest G-Shock form factor that I've seen.  Best thing?  The band stays put!  This made me crazy with my other solar powered G-Shock.  The replacement band kept popping out of it's holder.  This one stays.  Relearning the old settings has been interesting, but it is what I wanted; a great, basic, durable watch.  Very pleased.

Title: The forever watch
Text: I have worn this watch every day over the last 4 years. Original batteries. I served an lds mission for two years, and have been in construction for a year now. Every day in the shower. Riding motorcycles. Snowboarding. 120° Arizona weather. Skateboading. Swimming. Hot 90% humidity in the Florida keys. Gym. Basically to hell and back. And it works likes the day I bought. Little indentations on the top rubber, but I think this watch will out live me.

Title: Good price for a good watch
Text: Very happy, a good watch for work !

Title: Easy to wear
Text: I bought this for my husband and he loves it! He wears it all the time, even to sleep. He works for an industrial supply company delivering large items and it hasn’t scratched and is very easy to wear.

Title: De lo mejor que he comprado.
Text: Totalmente práctico, funcional y sobre todo resistente.

Title: Nice watch
Text: I have worn this style watch for >10yrs.  They are reliable, virtually indestructible and I have never had a battery run down. The band breaks after about 2-3yrs and it is simpler to just get another watch. Buttons are a little difficult, but I have yet to find a watch that better meets my needs.

Title: Simple, but just what I required.
Text: I like this watch because it has the things I use--time date and alarm--is light weight, and was reasonably priced.  My previous watch (quite a bit larger) had many many more features, but I never used them.  Good value for the money.

Title: Solid piece!
Text: The wrist watch is working perfectly well. It’s a rugged one.😍

Title: This is a greatwatch! This is my second one
Text: This is a great watch!  This is my second one.  I wore the other one 24/7. Swimming, showering, you name it.. I work construction and never had a min. problem with it. The only problem I had with the last one is it needs a new battery and little time to go get one. lol. The part I like about it is the buttons on the side are recessed and wrist movement does not press them and change time ect.  Have had the first one so many yrs I forget when and where I got it.

Title: Classic
Text: A classic. Hard to beat the durability and reliability of a G-Shock. Yes this a basic model, but what else do you really need in a watch. It features 12/24 hr time, alarms, a countdown timer, and a stopwatch. I own some fancier watches, but this edges them out for wrist time because of it's practicality. It's relatively inexpensive so I don't worry about something happening to it. It's easy to read the time day or night thanks to the illumination feature. It's more durable than almost any other watch in the relevant price range.

Title: The original beater watch!
Text: This is the base line G-shock.  It does everything you could ask for in a sub-$100 Watch and will do it for years and years.  I have been a G-shock fan for over two decades and this one is the heat.

Title: Quick delivery
Text: Gift for my son in law and he loves it!!

Title: I’m satisfied With my purchase
Text: I can not set the week day (Monday etc)and I’m not to happy not at all

Title: Very durable
Text: Bought this for a Christmas gift.  My husband had one before and absolutely loved it. He is extremely rough on watches, so its nice to see that Casio still makes this model because it's one my husband hasn't been able to break. It's very durable and it lasted for many years before the battery died. Highly recommend.

Title: Really nice watch
Text: Really functional watch.  I like it and will give it a good use

Title: Stop it bezos
Text: Great. Amazon can I have 5 more weeks at a minimum before I post a quality review. Please?

Title: Best digital watch!!!
Text: The best digital watch I've bought so far. Looks classy, feels comfy, and easy to use. Comes with one time zone, stop watch, chrono, and one alarm. It lights up the entire face. Can't beat it for under $40. One of the best features is that the time is always displayed in stop watch or chrono on the top corner. I plan to purchase another one if this one ever breaks. Buy it if you're thinking about buying it.

Title: Good
Text: It came turned on already. In good condition, good packaging. No complaints so far.

Title: This is just what you need.
Text: Love this watch. I know smart watches are the cool ones, but guess what with this watch you don't need to charge. Also I heard good reviews of the battery, in some cases it may last more than 3 or 4 years.

Title: My New Favorite Watch
Text: I was never a fan of digital watches until I bought this one. It has a classic style, and just the basic features that are useful in a watch--time/day/date; alarm; timer; stopwatch--without getting too complicated or looking too ridiculous with lots and lots of buttons, etc. The display is easy to read and the backlight is very bright. The black rubber/plastic finish is both durable and easy to clean. I have worn this watch in and around the ocean a number of times, and it still works great and required only a quick rinse to the remove dried salt and dirt. So far, it has been very durable, and useful, and the watch I wear more than any other.

Title: Simple, Durable Timepiece.
Text: Simple watch with standard features that is able to take a severe beating. Essentially, if you prioritize anything above extreme durability then you need to move along. Unlike the other G-Shocks, this watch will fit skinnier wrists (and big wrists too). Other G's are abnormally large and come off as a bit ostentatious. This one is reasonably sized for a man's wrist, and doesn't attract too much attention. Again- simple, extremely durable watch that will last a decade. If you're looking for anything outside that description then this watch is not for you.

Title: Tough and smaller than you think
Text: This watch tells the time and can take levels of abuse most items you own wouldn't be able to handle. Not my everyday wear, but I always have one in my edc in case I need it. Wears extremely small (32mm top to bottom of bezel). Thinking about grabbing a couple more as gifts. Great watch.

Title: Great ,cheap,tough
Text: Tits bro get it

Title: Overall satisfied with this classical time piece
Text: Extremely fast shipping. Item is brand new in the box. Great deal on a classic Casio

Title: Casio G-shock watch
Text: The Casio G-shock is a great watch. You can't go wrong buying this watch. This is the 2nd one I have owned. My first one I had it for years and it developed a short in the circuitry and was finished.  Bought other watches but was never really satisfied with the style or performance. So I saw the G-shock on Amazon and decided this is the watch for me again.

Title: Best watch ever
Text: Bought this watch because it’s the same watch I remember my dad when I was his age. What a great watch. This thing is tough and no nonsense. A true classic and understated in its rugged beauty.

Title: simple and works
Text: very nice simple watch. It is great for everyday use. It looks quite durable as well. I have not used it in water yet, but i don't doubt that it will hold up nicely. Obviously not a great watch if you want to be flashy, but it's not meant to be. Only reason I'm giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is because it is thicker than I would have liked, but this is a personal preference as most people do not care about this.

Title: Great watch
Text: It barely fit but I’m a big guy but works great

Title: Precio calidad
Text: Es muy cómodo y fácil de usar y configurar

Title: Almost perfect.
Text: 1 star removed due to recessed adjust button. This is the sleekest, smallest G-shock available. It doesn't draw attention like some of its more ostentatious and ludicrously-sized cousins but when noticed almost always draws compliments. However - if you're looking to buy this in order to make extensive use of the countdown timer, stopwatch or alarms then be warned - the recessed adjust button makes on-wrist use VERY tricky.

Title: Great watch, but took two months to arrive
Text: I love the watch.  My complaint is that it took over two months to arrive.

Title: Worth your time
Text: Really like the simplicity and rigidity of this model. I do pool maintenance and having a reliable time peace can make all the difference. Programming is easy, the strap is comfortable, plus its slimmer than most g-shocks  which means less snagging on long sleeves.

Title: 100% conforme
Text: 100% recomendable, todo puntual. muy buen vendedor

Title: A worthy tool watch.
Text: Other reviewers have detailed the most important things to know about this watch, so I wouldn't have much to add.  I can say that it looks good, has a great reputation for accuracy and durability, and isn't cluttered with too many functions or display items.  The display illuminates nicely.  The only "statement" that its aesthetics make to me is one of quiet competence.

Title: I've had a Casiowatch similar to this many years ago that lasted for ...
Text: I've had a Casio watch similar to this many years ago that lasted for about 15 years before the band broke.  I was happy to see this one available and I wouldn't give it up for any other watch.  It does everything I need and nothing I don't need.  It looks good and fits well.  The buttons work great and anyone can figure out how they work without the manual that comes with it.  I can't say that this one will last as long as my last one from Casio, but I'm confident it will.

Title: Grest watch...
Text: G-Shock durability in a low profile package. What's not to like?

Title: Easy to read, accurate, almost indestructable
Text: I've been using versions of this product for the past 40 years. It is reasonably priced, and incredibly rugged. You don't have to worry about banging in to something and damaging the crystal. It's waterproof to 200m, so you can even use in while scuba diving. For the price, you can't beat it!

Title: Was what I order
Text: Same as the one I have

Title: No es la versión Fire Fox y la tapa trasera tiene un golpe
Text: No llegó la versión Fox Fire, la tapa trasera tiene un golpe, el pulsador de ajuste no opera como debería, pienso que este reloj no es Casio Original sino una copia

Title: I love the design and simplicity of this watch and have ...
Text: I love the design and simplicity of this watch and have owned two. Unfortunately, they aren't the most reliable, and I'm not going to be purchasing a third. After a couple years, the indiglo on my first watch stopped working. After a year, my second watch's sound became unreliable (e.g. sometimes the alarm wouldn't chime).

Title: good not great like a solar atomic.
Text: good  not  atomic solar.  which at price x2  is what I really wanted.  such this one  cannot auto light so I want a one handed watch with  the other auto features.  other than that this is a great watch for knock around daytime or swimming or power watch and is well worthy of price.  sturdy. accurate. light. not cheap looking if you are familiar with Casio experience.

Title: Functions like a G-shock should.
Text: This being my first Casio watch and my first G-shock, reading all the reviews on Amazon and other sites. I had high hopes for a stellar watch. It is exactly that. A STELLAR WATCH! I have no complains about the performance at all. Lightweight, comfortable are just a few of the benefits. As for the complaints of the buttons being receded to far in ( to me it looks like the adjust button is the only one or the top left button)....what do you expect a watch that changes every time you look down at it. For what people purchase this watch for you get far more than you pay for! Especially on Amazon! Great product Casio.

Title: Ole Faithful...
Text: What can you say about a product that does what it supposed to, is simple to use, is not cluttered with extraneous features and is reasonably priced?  If you want to wear a hockey puck with tons of extra bells and whistles this is NOT your watch.  If, on the other hand, you want a reasonably sized dive watch with straightforward functions and layout that will give you years of service, this is a great choice.  I just purchased my third in nearly 30 years.  I've had others, but keep coming back.  I am glad they continue to offer this design.

Title: Bulletproof watch, the band could be better.
Text: I've bought several of this model over the years.  It's always the band that goes first.  I work on processing equipment and am constantly getting my arm in equipment.  I've even lost the band while driving nearly 80MPH.  In my mirror i could see the watch bounce nearly 20 feet in the air.  NO SCRATCHES ON THE BEZEL.  Unbelievable ! ! !  Great watch.  Amazon is the best price I've found yet for this and most of the things I buy online

Title: My only complaint it that this is a watch that is good for one battery only
Text: I have used this model of casio for 30 years, so it is proven.  My only complaint it that this is a watch that is good for one battery only.  We have attempted to change the batteries on the last couple of watches and screws have broken in the watch, or treads stripped in 2 out of 4 screw holes.  I am using one now with 3 out of 4 screws because the last stripped out.  I think it is perfect for 2 years, but after a couple the battery dies toss it and buy a new one.

Title: Alarms are very faint
Text: This watch is very robust and the light is bright but, probably because of its tight waterproof case, the alarms are practically inaudible. I have an 11 year old Casio with broken off strap that I can still hear 10 feet away. I cannot hear the alarms on this G-Shock watch when I’m wearing it if the face is turned away or if there is any other sound like kitchen fan. I typically use the countdown alarm when cooking. On my old Casios the alarm could be heard over the fan. Not this one.

Title: I like this G-Shock the best
Text: I have had many of these Casio digital watches over the years.  I like this G-Shock the best.  My last G-Shock is nearly 10 years old and still works perfect.  I have even worn it scuba diving down to depths of over 100 feet without a problem.  It is my favorite everyday utilitarian watch.  However when the band wore out it was impossible to replace so i bought this new one.  My advice; don't try to replace the band - just purchase a new watch.

Title: Accuracy, functionaliy, value
Text: I've only had this watch a couple of weeks but I've used it enough to appreciate the timekeeping accuracy, the functionality (timer, stopwatch, alarm, backlight), and the value. I feel this Casio product offers a lot for the money and I highly recommend it as an everyday watch.

Title: long lasting watch
Text: I purchased my first G SHOCK in 1998. It survived work on the railroad as part of the derailment crew, through many miles of back country excursions, and functioned flawlessly through millwright. It finally failed from abuse a month ago. (11/10/18) That is 20 years of awesome service. No other watch will do for rugged use.

Title: Great Watch But It Had to Go
Text: I love this watch, even if it's hard to set and the band's edges are sharp.  Does everything I need; keeps good time; rugged.  But I had to give it away.  Seems that every night at exactly midnight it (purportedly) beeps, reportedly about five times.  The only person who can hear it is my wife, who can hear a mouse tiptoeing across our neighbor's patio.  But it wakes her up, and that's Not Good.  Definitely Not Good.  I've checked and changed everything and it still (purportedly) beeps.  The only cure seems to be to take it off and leave it in the truck at night, but I keep forgetting to do it.  Farewell, Casio.

Title: Looks Great and is high quality.
Text: I like every thing about it. Reliable, functions, good looks.

Title: Best watch ever!!!
Text: I was extremely happy to see Casio offer a "Classic" line of G-shock watches.  This model is very similar to one I had back in the late 80's with the addition of improved backlighting.  To me this watch is as close to perfect as any.  It has the needed features of stopwatch, alarm, and countdown timer without having many unneccesary ones like multiple time zones, multiple alarms...  Also it is not as bulky as some of the other G-shock models.  This model is close to bullet-proof as any watch.  I truly hope that Casio continues to offer these classic watches!  For the price this watch cannot be beat.

Title: Best watch I've ever purchased!
Text: This watch is by far the best digital no nonsense watch I've ever bought, I've had zero issues with it, and I absolutely love the feel/durability of it. -In fact I sold my gshock 9600 because I hated how big it was and the "3 eyes" it had were useless. I wear watches reversed on my wrist, and this watch is perfect--- very comfortable. My only gripe is that the watch is made in china, I believe I was under the impression that the watch was made in Thailand. (like the picture shows) but apparently I'm mistaken. 10 out of 10, will keep till it dies. (or I die, ----which ever comes first)

Title: Great everyday watch
Text: Cool classic watch and durable

Title: Nice watch for a reasonable price.
Text: My new work watch, so far so good.

Title: Takes a beating
Text: BEST  watch I have ever  owned

Title: after 26 years  this is still the best g shock you can buy,
Text: I had the original DW5000 in 83 and even now that they have  plastic cases,this is still the best and more reliable af all g shocks,the tough solars are not reliable and the atomic time is not necessary,they havent made anything better than this.I been using casios since 83 and for the first time im back with the classic,its a little more compact than the old one and the price is great. I GAVE IT 4 STARS BECAUSE THE QUALITY OF THE BAND IS STILL TERRIBLE,THE SAME AS THE 80S MODELS.

Title: Very reliable
Text: I replace this watch every 4 or 5 years as it is very practical with it's basic G-Force features.  Have had one on my wrist since 1985.

Title: Rugged and Dependable
Text: I live on a ranch and I am really hard on watches. I have worn G- Shocks for years, because they can take the punishment. The last one lasted six years. I had to replace the band several times, and the battery a few. I would never consider buying anything else. They wouldn't look good if you were wearing a tux, but neither would I.

Title: I wear a watch everyday and this is easily my favorite weekend watch
Text: Solid watch. I wear a watch everyday and this is easily my favorite weekend watch. Rugged, reliable and pretty boring looking. It's on your hand, tells the time perfectly and stays out of the way. I ended up losing it and buying a flashier orange version but I loved the form factor and the resin band this watch has.

Title: Good looking and tough.
Text: Great watch, great price. I do not write a lot of reviews but this one deserves my positive review. I wear this watch daily even with my jacket and tie. Very good looking and tough watch.

Title: Great look
Text: Great watch love the retro Gshock

Title: Great
Text: Great every day watch

Title: Perfection
Text: Best watch I have ever owned. I have owned 3-4 over the past 10 years or so - never had one quit on me my dog ate one and I lost the others. Essential for the everyday carry.

Title: Durable
Text: I bought this as a replacement watch for my husband for his birthday. It replaced the exact same one which he had for about 10 years, so it's definitely a durable watch and you get your money's worth. There are definitely watches with more features but for a basic watch with alarm, stopwatch, and light, my husband really likes this one. The waterproofing works well, although over time and a few battery changes the waterproofing doesn't work as well and the watch may short out - that was why we ended up replacing his old one. But again, after 10 years it isn't too surprising.

Title: Get it. Right for the price. Beater watch
Text: I needed a beater watch and this one does the job. I did not test the  water resistance because I have not tried it. Is does say it is 200m Wyatt resistance. Love it. The price. Just right.

Title: Durable
Text: Does the job

Title: Excellent
Text: Excellent time piece.

Title: Casio G Shock
Text: Received the G Shock model DW5600E-1V which is a basic model and it has all my needs. The face shows the information I want at one time: day, date, time. It is large but not a monster in size especially as a sports type watch. Like the stopwatch with out splits, simple and direct.  I chose this model because it is not complex which I don't need.  Price is perfect.  Almost feel I should buy a second one in case it goes out of production.  I am purchasing one for a friend as a Christmas gift. Built tough, water tight, night light, great every day watch. Thank you Casio & Amazon.

Title: Ironclad durability
Text: This watch has everything anyone would want from a watch, along with complete durability.  Its only problem is the band, which is stiff and hard.  The strap mounting lugs are only 16 mm apart, so substitute bands are impossible to find.

Title: Good value for the money
Text: Not the Gshock of the 90s but it's a good work watch. LED works well. Can't beat it for the money.

Title: Excelente reloj para el uso diario
Text: Excelente reloj

Title: Muy buen reloj
Text: Me gusto el diseño, queda muy bien en la muñeca.

Title: Best watch ever for the money!
Text: This is the toughest, longest lasting and best looking watch for a man to wear. I am very happy with the size of the watch face and band. Back light looks great, easy to read face, even underwater. I have worn it in some extreme conditions already, snowmobiling, surfing, spear fishing, riding a motorcycle, working on cars, knee boarding, wake boarding, and even in some very hot natural hot springs! Looks great, feels great. Maybe I should buy another in case I ever lose this one... I think its better than the solar version, have heard many times that the solar ones dont keep their battery life very long. Mike B - SoCal

Title: durable, not fancy, relatively cheap.
Text: this is my 3rd one.  each one lasts about 10 or more years.  I wear it in pool and golf (salt water).  kids and grandkids play with them.  simple and works.

Title: Perfect 👌🏻
Text: I don’t get to excited about much these days, but I was about this watch , it arrived yesterday in a timely manner (yes I meant to say that) it’s a mans working watch, tough, no bells and whistles, tells time /alarm/date/timer/stopwatch and a light. Would be a perfect gift for any construction worker 👷‍♂️

Title: Too small for my wrist
Text: Great watch, but too small for my 7.8 inch wrists. Looks like a kids watch when I wear it.

Title: Dirty and malfunctioning product
Text: I was excited to get my first Casio, and this was a total disappointment. The box was already open with oily finger prints all over. I took out the watch, and there were more dusts. I thought the top left button was lost since it does not show at first sight. (See the photo). The watch screen was also different from the picture.

Title: It was on sale at a very good price.
Text: This is a nothing watch, that's complicated to use and set correct time. The light is good. You must wear your reading glasses under any circumstances. Outside it's most challenging to see. Obviously in the dark you press the light on, but you still need your glasses. It was on sale at a very good price. I probably will not replace the battery once it dies.

Title: Proven Tough
Text: Everyone has G-Shocks, like everyone has Wayfarers, and boat shoes. And if you don't have any of the aforementioned then you need to start by getting this true classic. Many of these classic products are making a comeback proving that their designs can withstand the test of time. With no doubt, this watch would definitely last a very long time. I personally use this watch for work and when I dress casual. Aside from the crease created from the lock, the watch looks like it's never been worn. It truly is tough and accurate. Many alternative and cheaper watches copy this iconic look of watches but nothing compares to the quality that is G-Shock.

Title: Beautiful easy to ready with sport style
Text: Excellent watch a classic G shock first generation!

Title: Reliability/Longevity
Text: This watch is the third I've owned over a period of many years, same Item Number, etc.  Obviously I hope that it will prove to be as reliable and long-lived as those I've owned in the past.

Title: Great watch
Text: Great watch, had one of the originals from the 80's had to get another.

Title: Great product!!
Text: Resists water, great to read, timer works good even though i hardly use it

Title: Is NOT accurate
Text: I bought this watch in 2014 for use when camping and hiking. I had owned a Timex (Expedition) for many years and it served me well and kept accurate time. Unfortunately, I lost that watch and Amazon didn't have a Timex (Expedition) in stock. So, I read the reviews and then bought this Casio. First and foremost, my Casio does NOT and NEVER did keep accurate time. The watch cost me $41.36 in 2014, which was about $10.00 more than the Timex (Expedition). The buttons on this Casio are almost impossible to depress, whereas the buttons on the Timex are a breeze to operate, especially the large light button on the face of the watch. Twice every year, I regret buying this watch. In the spring when I have to set it forward and in the fall when I have to set it back. It typically gains about 10 minutes over that period of time. I've never owned a quartz movement that gained 20 minutes over the course of a year. If you're looking for ease of use and accuracy, I respectfully suggest that you look elsewhere.

Title: Smaller display, but otherwise great watch
Text: It's the perfect beater watch. My dress watch for the office, this for weekends. It's a little bit hard to read with smaller display. My other (analog) watch with black dial and white hands is much easier to see.  but otherwise, the casio is very accurate, and band confirms perfectly to wrist keeping watch squarely on top of wrist. Very comfortable.

Title: Great Watch, Great Seller
Text: Watch was delivered quickly and packaged safely. I absolutely love it. Extremely comfortable strap, easy to read face, and a tremendous selection of functions. I haven't yet explored all of the functions, but I am excited to try them. Big fan of the backlight feature as well. Tremendous value you can't match.

Title: Grandpa approved.
Text: Just like a modern version of my grandad’s old watch that he has worn for as long as I can remember. When I told him I got it because it reminded me of his watch his face lit up with a smile. Mission accomplished. Watch is great quality and full of useful options.

Title: I am pretty hard on watches
Text: This will be the 3rd one I've owned in 30 years or so. The first one lasted about 8 years. The second one only lasted 6. I am pretty hard on watches, so that is pretty good. The only other one that lasted that long was a Seiko. That one cost 250. I can buy 5 of these for that much. Interestingly, I paid about the same for my 1st G-shock in 1983 as I did for this one.

Title: My everyday carry
Text: Dependable daily. From Mtn biking to swimming, rock solid for me at a decent price.

Title: As expected this thing is still going strong.
Text: 13 months after purchase and I've come to wear my G-Shock classic almost exclusively over other watches in casual circumstances due to its comfortable fit and extreme durability, without looking cheesy. I work in a warehouse and I wear this every day, and it really takes a beating, but it does NOT show. This is some amazing engineering, not even the rubber coating looks damaged. I expect this watch to run until the battery dies, 8 times, at least. (It has yet to need replacing.)

Title: Amazing watch
Text: Amazing time peace simple and Resistant.

Title: Great watch..Great price..
Text: Love this watch..so glad I bought it..i had one back in the 80s..the band seems heavier duty which is nice..really happy with it..haven't used in water yet..but over all great watch for the price!

Title: You NEED to buy this.
Text: Bought this for the academy. It’s worth it, cheap and super reliable. No need to spend more money, unless you want fancy options and looks. However if you want something simple that’s gonna be reliable 24/7, this is it.

Title: Happy buyer
Text: Everything is perfect. I am a happy buyer

Title: Functional & Simple
Text: This is a watch for those who lead an active life and just want a timepiece for its functionality without trying to impress others. Some wear a watch as an accessory and some wear a watch to know the time. Reasons why I love this watch: -Easy to set up -Functionality, stopwatch, timer, date & time -Simple design -Not too big on the wrist -Can wear with anything No complaints after a few months of wearing

Title: Casio classic is best watch for gym!
Text: I purchased about 3 months ago and using it since I am in gym. I do Cardio, bicycle, machines, and swimming everyday at gym and After that I even take hot spa to relax with me wearing this watch. At moment no defect or problem at this watch and working perfect to let me know the time while I am at running or swimming. I really like this G-shock the classic looks,how tough it is and has function that I need timer, stop watch and LED light. I would recommend this watch who are thinking to use it for gym!

Title: Great Product Great price
Text: I've had Casio G-shock Classic Watch for 25 years and it still works great.  That's why I ordered this product for my boyfriend who will be taking diving lessons soon.  The price was $20 less than I paid 25 years ago and works exactly the same.  I've had my dive watch down to 120' and it works like a charm.  After 25 years the illumination part doesn't work quite as good as it used to but that's okay.  This product is easy to set and use and will last a lifetime.  My Dad even has one. Amazon shipped it quickly and I'm very happy with it.

Title: Classic
Text: Simple. Great for work.

Title: Has sort of a cheap build about it
Text: The general feeling of this watch is cheap-ish.  I know it can withstand anything but how it feels effects my relationship to it.  Maybe get the $100 version and you won't feel this way.  Also, the buttons are really hard to push.  If you need to use the stopwatch a lot for work or at the gym this just won't work.  I'm just generally confused on why there is so much hype around the G-Shock.

Title: Great deal
Text: Great price and quality . Perfect first watch for my teenager

Title: Nothing
Text: I’ve been using this watch for years. No surprises here.

Title: Good basic Casio
Text: Good quality basic watch with a 200M water resistance,  which is twice the rating of about anything else out there, only wish the main readout was larger so as to make it easer to read at depth or in murky water, but overall a very good reliable watch, as similar models have served me well in the past.

Title: Great great watch
Text: Great great watch, however the packaging was broken. the plastic the watch sits on was broke. I was hoping to keep it and use it. Watch is okay, and the shipping was awesome. Only negative is the broken packaging. Otherwise happy with purchase. Will give an updated review of the watch in the future, but its a gshock, so what else!

Title: Great product
Text: Really great watch . This is my first review ver satisfied I’ll buy again

Title: Gets the job done
Text: Does all the basics

Title: Great classic watch
Text: Looks just like the one I bought in the 80s when I went to basic training. That one is still going strong. This was a gift for my son who is headed to basic. Hope it serves him well.

Title: Wears pretty neatly on the wrist
Text: Feels absolutely solid. Much more sturdier than the newer, bigger G-SHOCK's. Wears pretty neatly on the wrist. I did find the adjust button a bit of a bother to operate. Loving it. Would recommend to anyone who's looking for a no-nonsense beater watch

Title: Only downside is the viewing angle isn't the best such as when driving
Text: Original 1983 design, rugged looks and retro look.  It works for me, and reminds me of Casios I had as a kid.  Only downside is the viewing angle isn't the best such as when driving, you will have to angle your wrist a little.  No big deal though, this watch is a classic!

Title: Great watch for work
Text: Great watch to work for the price, looks ready for the action and kind of fashionable too.

Title: Good watch
Text: I liked it

Title: Very nice watch, and built like a tank
Text: Very nice watch, and built like a tank! The battery is rated for two years. It will probably last longer, but it is disappointing compared to some other cheaper Casio watches with similar features and a ten year battery.

Title: This is one of the best and most simple G-Shocks you can buy
Text: This is one of the best and most simple G-Shocks you can buy, there are a ton of reviews on this legendary timepiece, so I won't bore you with the details. I bought one in 1987 while in the Army serving as a combat medic in a light Infantry scout platoon. it lasted 10 years before I gave it away, original battery, worked like it was brand new. You can not buy a better watch for the money IMHO. The perfect SHTF watch!

Title: El G-Shock esencial
Text: Este es por lejos el mejor reloj en relación precio calidad 200mt de rsistencia al agua, resistencia a las caidas e impactos, sin mencionar su extenso uso por parte de soldados, astronautas y una que otra estrella de Hollywood

Title: Awesome watch! Old school styling!!
Text: FANTASTIC watch, FANTASTIC price !!! The styling brings me back to my youth!! Very wasy to use, easy to understand instructions, and the back light is plenty bright!!

Title: Good watch
Text: Good everyday watch. Had a similar model back in the 80's and it lasted forever.

Title: G-Shock quality without the expense!
Text: I bought this watch to replace an older Seiko automatic (mechanical) watch I have had for some years. I'd been seriously considering one form of G-Shock or another for some time, but the expense and the plethora of features on some of the other models had made me hesitant to buy. This particular model, however, has only the necessary functions that I require on a watch and did not cost a great deal like some of the other more complex G-Shock watches. So far I've been quite satisfied with the watch overall. If you are looking for a sturdy, reasonably priced digital watch this one should be given strong consideration.

Title: I like the watch
Text: I like the watch! The only drawback is that you have to look straight at it to really read the time. I also would like the "adjust button" the same recess as the others, hard to engage. I think I would have liked the black background with white symbols better, but didn't know about that option. Awesome for an inexpensive watch

Title: No son originales

Text: Buena relación costo beneficio

Title: Que no falle.
Text: Bastante sencillo. Todavía no he probado debajo del agua en río o piscina.

Title: It's ugly but it works.
Text: I keep one in my survival bag, just in case. It's cheap, reliable, accurate, simple and barring, an EMP, it's bulletproof. I have been waiting for the battery to go dead, to see how long they last but I guess I'll just have them changed for good measure since my 4 year old G-shock that I wear everyday is still on the original battery, I'm guessing that this one will run for quite a while as well. Definitely function over form though.

Title: Watch
Text: Got for my grandson and he loves watch.

Title: Little smaller than original.
Text: I suspect things must change, and in this world of 'smaller is better', so it is with this watch. Of course my original was over 15 years old! (never changed the battery!). I checked my old one with calipers, and it seemed the new one had the same specs, but it is noticably thinner, and smaller overall, but not really enogh to matter. All functions the same. I guess it's just nostaliga for my old one that made the changes stand out.

Title: Classy Watch
Text: The media could not be loaded. Great feel and durable.  You can tell Casio thoroughly thought this watch through.  I like the EL backlight touches.  Very bright.  When enabled, flashes on the hour and during alarms.

Title: Comfortable to wear and once it's set up it works ...
Text: Gift for my husband.  He couldn't figure out how to set this watch up and it was a little hard to understand the instructions for the settings.  After a few tries I was able to get it set for him.  He loves this watch.  I gave it 3 stars just because older people usually buy this kind of watch and it was hard for him to set it up.  Comfortable to wear and once it's set up it works great.

Title: Classic G-Shock Is a Winner
Text: This G-Shock, my first, is a great introduction to these tough and highly functional Casios.  It isn't as bulky as the other G-Shocks, (at 5'7", I don't have the wrists for those), and it's so comfortable that I sometimes need to remind myself that I'm wearing a watch.  The LCD display is clear and seems resistant to glare, the bezel is cleanly designed, and the strap complements it nicely.  The default time/date screen displays what most people would need, and there are a surprising amount of other functions for a watch of this price.  Considering the easy entry price, you can't go wrong with this watch.

Title: Great basic watch
Text: Great basic watch, retro/classic style, perfect for playing sports or working around the house. Personally I like the hourly chime to keep track of my time along the day, just simple and effective. Maybe not the best option if you want to impress people, like on a first date or a job interview at a fancy office. The band does not feel so resistant but for $40, it's great value for money.

Title: Super bueno
Text: Exelente reloj me gusta mucho 👍👍👍👍

Title: as beautiful as this watch is
Text: as beautiful as this watch is. im just a little upset it had a slight either dust particle or scratch on it when it arrived in mail. box was open for some reason as well. overall still looks good, but just improper packaging and slight scratch on screen

Title: Great Watch!!
Text: This is my first watch that I have ever purchased/used and now I feel out of place without it. Very durable for work!! I love the watch!!

Title: Best digital watch
Text: Every man needs a dress watch, chronograph, dive watch, and a beater watch (according to [...]).  I think the Casio Men's G-Shock Classic DW5600E-1V is the best beater watch for the money.  Clean and simple good looks, reliable, and a great value. It has everything you need in a beater watch--time, date, day on a single screen; timer, alarm, and stopwatch.  It has the precision of a quartz movement and a long battery life.  This is a no-frills digital watch.  I wear it doing yard work, house work, running, walking the dog, P90x, doing dishes, etc.  Very light and comfortable. 100% satisfied customer.

Title: OG G-Shock
Text: The original (as close as you can get) square G. Nuff said.

Title: We love this watch.
Text: I ordered the first one and my daughter laid claim to it as soon as she saw it. So I ordered another. It fits her 5 1/2 inch and my 8 1/4 inch wrist. I got them used but they were flawless. Thinking of ordering the gwm5610 as well.

Title: Great buy
Text: I like it durable and great!

Title: G shock is g shock absolute best
Text: Simply square gshock is the best. For someone who is known to walk into to thing, this is the best. End up upgrading the straps and bezel. This will be only digital watch I will ever own.

Title: Most reliable, low maintenance watch out there! It just works.
Text: great watch, love it!  Casio G shock has been my go to watch for many many years!  They're usually good for about five years on a battery with no other maintenance except keeping it somewhat clean. Very waterproof. Great watch!

Title: World Traveler
Text: I sailed around the world with a watch identical to this one and just replaced it because the rubber cover finally deteriorated. The original watch still functions, just the band and cover are gone. I especially like the dual time zone feature since I could keep my home zone intact and adjust the local time. I also used the alarm feature and night light a lot. It's a tough, reliable watch that goes well at work and play. Price is right, too.

Title: Adjust button! Argh
Text: Iconic, super-functional watch and it’s nearly impossible to actually use. “Adjust” button is further recessed (I say this because other buttons are protected by case and do not protrude) to a point where I have to nearly take the watch off or use a pen to use the button… everytime I want to set alarm, reset timer, reset stopwatch… it makes it easier to just use my smartphone! What a let down… I get it, but all the buttons on this watch aren’t “easy” to push - just make this button like the other 3! The watch is just a novelty to me at this point. Back to my Sinn 656 and smartphone features.

Title: Worth it  good product-  reasonable price
Text: Long life, rugged.  If use light a lot batter life shorter.  Bout 25 for jeweler to replace bat.  3rd one in 25 yrs.  Band wears out not watch

Title: Great Brand

Title: As expected

Title: My Favorite G-Shock of All Time

While GW-5000 may be better built with nicer quality and some more bell and whistle, I highly doubt that GW-5000 is that much tougher than the cheaper alternative DW-5600. Title: If you want a G-shock that doesn't look like it belongs on Ben Ten's wrist this is the ...
Text: If you want a G-shock that doesn't look like it belongs on Ben Ten's wrist this is the watch for you. I've had this watch for nearly two years and wear it every day. The face has taken some abuse but that is expected. I do alot of outdoors stuff, manual labor, and work in a kitchen. I wash dishes with it on, soap and bleach water haven't messed it up.

Title: Casio G-Shock watch
Text: This is the 2nd or 3rd Casio G-Shock watch I have owned over the past 18-20 years. Too bad that the bracelet/watch band isn't as tough as the watch. The only issue with my recently purchased ( May 2008) G-Shock is the fact that the chip--or firmware-unsure of the proper terminology--will only support the calender portion of the watch until December 2009 It is too bad that Amazon.com's product description does not state this. Had I been aware I probably would have purchased a different Casio model.

Title: It's a great work watch.
Text: Great all around watch that you don't have to worry about.

Title: BUEN PRODUCTO
Text: Facil de configurar y es muy comodo al pulso.

Title: Your friends might make fun of you
Text: I am 22 and all of my friends make fun of me for wearing this watch. They told me its ugly and that it's an old mans watch. There may be a little truth to this, but, this watch is PERFECT. I wasn't trying to go for fashionable but functional. It does everything you want it to and doesn't add too many features that would make it user unfriendly. The buttons are intuitive, it has a big face with digital numbers, beeps every hour, and it's rugged. I never have to pull out my phone in class anymore, and I can check the time while wearing gloves in my lab!

Title: Great watch

Title: Fantastic 👍
Text: Fantastic watch super classic looking g shock, I enjoy a more simple looking watch. This has everything I need. With easy to tell time. It has this vintage feel to it. And the watch wears very well when being active. A must of old school watch. Great price. 👍

Title: Like it
Text: This is my 4th , the black plastic wears out before the watch .

Title: But now. You won't be disappointed 😉
Text: This watch is solid. I collect Seiko watches and yes, they are tough but when I go to work, I throw on my G-Shock. I work outside and in harsh conditions, this thing is my companion and I know it can take whatever I throw at it!!!

Title: A basic watch to last for years
Text: Timeless classic. Durable, affordable, simple, and NOT ugly.

Title: Awesome.
Text: This is my second 5600E - my first one was misplaced years ago. This watch is durable, lightweight, waterproof, and will take a beating. I never think twice before I dive into the pool, go hiking, scrape it on rocks, etc. I love the simplicity of a digital watch that displays accurate time, the date, and the day of the week. I will continue to wear this watch until it dies - if that should happen I will surely replace it with yet another 5600E. The only way I would lose this watch is if a bear wrestles me to the ground and fights me for it. I love it.

Title: Great watch!
Text: I bought this for my boyfriend and he loves it.  It has great features, easy to read and it never leaves his wrist.  You can't go wrong with this watch.

Title: Great for price
Text: Good for what I need it for. Everything works as intended to.

Title: Alarm hard to start
Text: Alarm does work but alarm not loud enough to be effective. Also expected vibration and none so far as I can tell!

Title: Casio made a mistake on these buttons.
Text: The time piece should be sufficient for physical work and allows me record 24hr time at a glance. The buttons on the watch are sub standard and the top left button is always terrible. I've actually received a replacement because I had thought the original I received was a bit DOA, however these watches were designed to have awkward buttons. I feel as if Casio did not so much as review or use these watches for themselves. In the photo you'll not see a top left button - this is because the top left button arrives (2/2) awkwardly depressed.

Title: Extremely accurate.
Text: Didn't check the water resistance, no need to do this. The display is a little bit smaller for me, but is still ok. If you like the style (I do) this is the perfect time keeper!

Title: Great watch for the $$
Text: Great watch! Super comfortable and easy to read.

Title: Great Everyday watch
Text: I have had a few of these G-Shock watches for the last 20-30 years.  They are very durable, comfortable enough to wear constantly, they are water resistant and have the needed basic functions.  I already had one of these, but when I changed the battery I did not put the seal back properly and water entered it while swimming.  The watch was destroyed.  I purchased this watch for about $40 and I expect to have it for years.

Title: Defective
Text: Be wary that you may recieve a defective watch that is on the buy - return - buy merry go round. The watch I recieved was not new, and had a defective A button (I could barely press it). I don't expect much from $45, but I expect better.

Title: Perfect for me.
Text: It has an easy to read display and the watch functions are limited which I like. The buttons are recessed which eleminates accidental pressing. The only con is that the band is very short. I have an average male wrist size and there are only 3 "notches" left on the band to expand the size. There is about 3/4" left on the band after I put it on. This is fine for me but tough if you have a large wrist.

Otherwise, im happy with the delivery of this watch. Shipped quite fast and the tracking was precise somewhat. I can tell this watch will definitely go places!

Title: Just the Right Size!!!!!!

I shopped around for G-Shock watches, but they are all ginormous.  I have small wrist, and I wanted a larger, but not ridiculously huge G-Shock watch.  This watch is perfect size for me. My major concern is the band.  It's beefier, but if I abused it, I don't think it would withstand the wear.  Of course, I don't abuse it, and it might prove me wrong ten years from now. For now, it's an easy five-star purchase for me.  Very reasonably priced, and it's been a perfect delivery, all-around.

Title: Fits my eight inch wrist just fine

Title: Simple, durable, and practical.
Text: A true beast. This watch endured everything I could throw at it for five years. It functioned flawlessly, even when chipped and battered from time spent backcountry and working maintenance on a ranch. The only reason I ended up getting a different one is because I lost this somewhere in Joshua Tree National Park. Whoever finds you, my loyal friend, may you bless them as you blessed me.

Title: Rolex, Eat Your Heart Out
Text: It never loses a second and does everything I want it to. I've had this model since 2000. When the wrist strap loop broke in 2013, I patched it with a paperclip, then bought the same model. The old one still runs fine. I use it as a spare. Haven't even needed a new battery. I have a Rolex knock-off from China that I never wear because I like the Spartan image this model projects. Who do I need to impress, anyway?

Title: Good

Title: Classic G-Shock - Superb
Text: I can only agree enthusiastically with the very positive reviews of this digital watch. It has the four essential timekeeping functions: (1) clock, (2) stopwatch (count up), (3) timer (count down) and (4) alarm - no (in my opinion) unnecessary functions. And, *no* multiple instances, e.g., > 1 timer. This basic setup works for me, although others may desire multiple clocks, for example. I especially like the view of the time when in stopwatch and timer mode. A minor comment: I sometimes find it awkward to access the recessed buttons - although this might be a "feature" to prevent you accidentally activating a function. Highly recommended.

Title: Durability
Text: Best g shock watch for the money

Title: Good quality per money
Text: Versatile watch, good quality per price, basic functionality

Title: The adjust button is very difficult to press.
Text: The buttons are difficult to press. You pretty much have to use your nail to press a button. They are hard to press with the pad of your finger. The adjust button (the top left button) takes an unreasonable amount of force. The adjust button is recessed, whereas the other buttons stick out. In order to record a split you have to press the adjust button which is very difficult to do with the watch on your wrist. Also, the previous split time goes away once you hit the adjust button again, and you’re expected to write down the split time in order to record it. This is unacceptable when running races, where you want to keep track of your mile split times. The light only illuminates the screen for two seconds. It feels like a durable watch, but the buttons make the watch fairly useless.

Title: 5600 vs 6900? A clear winner
Text: The 5600 is perhaps less flashy than his cousin the 6900, but is more durable because it has less plastic parts and a smaller footprint. If you’re looking for a rugged piece, this is it.

Title: Classic GShock style at a great price!
Text: Classic style, easy to read, large without being bulky.  Really lightweight.  My only nock is that the adjust button is really recessed and my big fingers have a tougher time, but I guess it's to keep from accidentally bumping it.  Small quibble.

Title: Great Waterproof Workhorse Watch
Text: Ok, I had a similar or the same model watch when I was a swimmer, and it really holds up under all kinds of activities, and under the sun, and underwater.  It's a good, sturdy, classical design.  The reason I selected this watch, is because I frequently need to know the exactly date (for scheduling purposes) and, it's nice to see the day of the week, too.  I also use it to track medicine dosages.

Title: great basic watch
Text: this was a great watch, in fact the first one i used in the Army. I still like this watch and though I have a more advanced Solar Tough Atomic Watch Casio, my 12 year old has kind of taken that one over leaving me with this one, which works just fine. For travel, it only takes a moment to change time zones, so not much longer than if you scroll through them. My son and I check and it seems this one only varies a few seconds from his (mine!) that gets recalibrated every night via atomic time locations. For the price, really can't beat it!
