Title: Durable watch with limited functionality
Text: I was looking for a durable, water-proof watch, and I decided to purchase the Casio Men's DW5600E G-Shock because of its good reviews. The watch works very well for displaying time, but it does have some functionality issues. When setting the time, a timer, or an alarm the numbers can only be increased. Since I regularly change the timer from 20 minutes to 10 minutes and back again, I would like to have a feature where I could decrease a 20 minute timer to a 10 minute timer without first increasing the timer to 59 minutes and cycling back around. Additionally the adjust button is slightly recessed and it is sometimes difficult to push. Since the watch is functional, but not exceptional, I am giving it a three star review.

Title: oldie but goody
Text: This is an oldie but goody. Back in the mid 80s I remember this as being one of the first watches I ever purchased. I wore it till the rubber rotted off and it was just a metal case. I've always remained a huge Casio and g-shock fan and when one of my nicer metal banded g-shocks broke I decided to go back to the basics while I contemplated my next move. I love the functionality and durability of this watch! I wound up getting a titanium banded pathfinder but am constantly drawn back to this one especially if I'm in or around the water.

Title: Love these things
Text: I have owned these watches forever.  They do what they do better than any other watch I have found.  Easy to read, keeps great time, almost indestructible, waterproof enough to dive with, battery lasts (if you take it easy on the light) at least 10 years.  I was tempted to get another style of g-shock, but decided to stay in my comfort zone.  Love these things.

Title: Nice watch
Text: This is my third one.  Two drawbacks:  the band will break after a few years and the battery will eventually die.  Both are difficult to change, so I usually opt for purchasing another watch. Title: Great value for a watch!

I was stuck between this and the various comparable Timex watches.  After going back-and-forth, I chose the Casio mainly for the overwhelming number of high reviews. I'd highly recommend this watch.  It has all the basic functions I need, with a sturdy feel.

Title: Casio G-Shock - Best of the Best
Text: Over the years I have owned a great any timepieces.  Everything from Rolexes and Omegas to cheapy no-name pieces of junk.  In my work which involves a great deal of time on, in and under the water, there has only been one watch that has never let me down - the Casio G-Shock.  It does the job, day in and day out.  I've managed to wear out cases and straps on G-Shocks, but I've never flooded one or had it fail.  I really don't need fancy, I need dependable and the Casio is the most dependable timepiece I've ever found.

Title: Can't go wrong with the OG G-Shock

Title: Casio DW5600E-1V G-Shock Watch
Text: I Purchased this Casio watch almost 7 months ago.  I didn't buy it as a beater watch, I have other cheaper Casio's for that.  Really nothing to complain about-it has performed flawlessly.  I have smacked it pretty hard on a couple of occasions and it still looks new.  It has all the information that I need-just date and time, (1) alarm, countdown timer and chronograph-and the light works really well.  It runs slightly fast-2 seconds a week, which equals about 8-9 seconds fast a month...not bad.  Better slightly fast then a little slow.  Just buy it!

Title: Boton

Title: Gd product
Text: Easy to set time

Title: Efficient
Text: Instructions are easy to read.

Title: Great watch
Text: Great watch.. I use it only to tell time, and hardly ever use the buttons. I wore this watch everywhere everyday for four years until i had to throw it out because it got covered in someone else's blood. I'm bought the exact same watch to replace it.

Title: Reliving the 80's  a grest watch!
Text: I wanted one of these when I was a teenager in the 80's but could not afford it so I settled for a armitron. So glad to see these just like they where back then but had the indigo light that stays on for 3 seconds once button is pushed. Have not taken off since I bought it a week ago.  Kayaking swimming showering motorcycle riding works perfect. Not to bulky, just right

Title: Casio old model still good
Text: Almost exactly like its predecessor, which I used for about 20-25 years, including the very useful "time remaining" mode for refereeing Rugby matches.  I find, however, that this one is slowly losing a small amount of time.

Title: Best watch for the money
Text: Had one for 7 years till the band finally broke. Clock part still worked. Just bought another. This watch is a good investment. Nothing fancy. No useless crap on it. Swam in it, worked manual labor jobs and law enforcement, etc. Tough Watch

Title: Durable and worth the discounted price.
Text: Durable, one of the only watches due to its design and materials that doesn't have a crystal that scratches-up over time. This is my second one. My only complaint would be the the battery life, (but fours years isn't horrible) the wrist strap pins will oxidize, breaking over time and strap will wear out and crack within about the same time period. Button function is durable where most similar watches fail.

Title: Great watch
Text: Watch is great,poor shipping speed from seller next time will just buy from Walmart

Title: This watch will become like your best friend
Text: This watch is rugged and stylish. It will go anywhere and do anything. As an engineer and researcher, this watch has done a lot for me and been a lot of places with me. It's been a couple thousand feet below Earth's surface, on a ton of planes, covered in sweat, dirt, paint, cement, dust, grime, it's been underwater, you name it. And it still keeps going strong. I can't recommend this watch enough. Buy one and enjoy it for a long time.

Title: Great watch
Text: Worked great got for my husband and he used it everyday in BMT.

Title: A great classic!
Text: There are many positive reviews on this watch and this will be one more. It is just a great simple timepiece not freighted with all the unnecessary things you don't need but some very practical features that you do. I think my last G-shock lasted almost 15 years and I expect this one will as well. Great value overall and highly recommended.

Title: Classic G-Shock !
Text: I bought one of these watches about-1979 A commercial came out for the"New G-Shock' watch. They put it on an ice arena and 2 players came out and used it as a hockey puck. I literally wore it off my wrist working construction. It never gave me a problem. I hope this holds up half as well. It's light weight and easy to ware.and easy to use. The battery in my 1st one seemed to last forever too. Good watch!

Title: It's perfect
Text: Good for daily use.

Title: It also looks great as an alternative to a suit/dress/black tie watch
Text: The watch worn by both astronauts and soldiers and marines. If you were being transported to a desert island or another planet this is the watch you would take. It also looks great as an alternative to a suit/dress/black tie watch. This watch is nice enough to wear with a suit but you probably already have an analog dress watch for that. Use this watch for all other occasions.

Title: The best g-shock
Text: Nice and simple.  No stupid extra graphics that serve no purpose.

Title: It's a G-Shock
Text: Built like a tank, very handy, and functions perfectly!

Title: Simple, and Reliable
Text: Can’t complain, 45 bucks for a Casio G-Shock, that’s definitely a great deal, you’re sure to have this watch for a long time. Watch looks beautiful, Backlight is nice and bright, and it got here in 2 days. If you’re thinking about buying it, then do it.

Title: Great watch
Text: Can't beat a 5600! Great solid watch for the money.

Title: This watch is awesome not only is it the throw back g shock ...
Text: This watch is awesome not only is it the throw back g shock it's so durable and sharp looking I use it for work I'm in construction it is simply awesome perfect size easy to set and can take a beating al still look new with a wipe down love it

Title: Great watch
Text: Some time  ago I owned one of these watches for 10 years. Never had a single issue.

Title: Fantastic!
Text: I have taken this watch surfing, swimming, and rock climbing.  Very simple and easy to use, looks good, and shows no signs of falling apart even after a year or so.  It is able to be fully submerged for long periods of time with no problems.  If you replace the battery or take it apart though, you better make sure you close it up as tight as possible to ensure it stays water proof (I have not had to replace the battery).  Overall, this is the best quality for the best price.

Title: Great every day watch
Text: My new favorite watch. When this one gives out I will definitely buy another one to replace it.

Title: Buy it
Text: Classic design. Great quality

Title: If you like the way it looks then buy it.
Text: Bought it 2 years ago. Still works. Only one scratch... thats saying alot because i abuse the crap out of it.

Title: Good inexpensive watch
Text: Inexpensive watch that works well.  Bought one on Amazon to replace one whose battery died.  Had battery replaced on old watch, but did not seal out water after that.

Title: Great work watch!
Text: Works as intended! Great watch for the price

Title: Can't go wrong buying this one
Text: This watch is a classic.

Title: Fantastic watch!
Text: I've been using this watch for quite some time now and it really has held up well to all the abuse that I put it through. Time keeping has never been so easy, and because this is a digital watch the timing is accurate as when you set it! Features are well stocked and battery seems to last a long time, this is my first time purchasing a G-Shock, I am planning on purchasing some other designs very soon! Lastly, I wanted to add that this watch is very fashionable, it looks very modern! ~ Willie

Title: Simplicity that can't be beat, Durable and just great!
Text: My father had one of the original models of this watch, and it has held a great deal of sentimental value so I was very happy to be able to find this watch. It is very well made and highly durable. The illuminator feature lights up the whole display making it easy to read at night. I have several other Casio G-Shock models that are far more expensive, but this is still my favorite that I wear daily! Great price and fast delivery

Title: cheap watchband and poor customer service
Text: I like the  G Shock watches and wear them because I  spend a lot of time in situations wear the crystal might get scratched HOWEVER, my issues have been with the bands, they are not made to be easily replaceable. WORSE yet, the customer service is amongst the worst that I've ever seen.  My last watch was 18 months old and they insisted that I had to spend another $75 to get a new one.  Not only would they not give me a decent discount, I was never able to speak with a manager.  I couldn't get past the entry level phone bots. I've been in the retail business for 40 years and I go out of my way to make sure my customers are happy but not so at Casio.  Beware!

Title: Good watch, But not for a mature man
Text: I love Gshock. This one is tough. However, It looks like a student watch. I will try G-steel next

Title: 'Tough-guy' tough, but not 'Touch-guy' bulky
Text: For an object that keeps time, this watch is timeless.  It's retro-cool while still being modern.  Smaller than the modern 'tough-guy' G-Shocks.  Compared to my trusty Timex Expedition, it is smaller, but just right size I believe.  Much easier to wear under a dress shirt than the bulging mega G-Shocks of today.

Title: Very good watch. Even though it is a little bit ...
Text: Very good watch. Even though it is a little bit big for me, but it is light and the band watch fits my wrist. It has a lot of functions. I also like the G-SHOCK feature.

Title: The perfect watch
Text: This is my second one.  I had my first for 20 years.  I love this watch.

Title: "It is a sturdy, comfortable
Text: I purchased this as a gift for a gentleman whose supervisor informed him that he was returning back late from his breaks at work. Problem solved. With the built in timer/stop watch he no longer has that issue. When I asked him what he thought about the watch, he shared the following for this review, "It is a sturdy, comfortable, waterproof, practical watch with the date, day and light always available." Another job saved!

Title: Love it
Text: Best watch ever

Title: Great purchase
Text: Love it!

Title: Perfect
Text: The watch arrived right on time, was well packaged and there was no damage. The watch is exactly what it says it is, is light weight and easy to set up. Would recommend the Casio G-Shock to anyone looking for a durable everyday watch to wear. June 2018 I bought this watch in 2013. It is still one of my favorites. It is light, accurate, rugged and dependable. For the money I don't think you will find a better watch. October 31, 2020 Still have the watch and wear it almost daily. No problems, still the original battery.

Title: Nice gift for my husband
Text: It was one of my husband's Christmas gifts.

Title: I bought the first one for my son just recently and he will be able to enjoy it's reliability just as I have
Text: I have been wearing Casio G-Shock watches almost exclusively since September of 1984. They are durable, reliable, non-bulky and last a long time. I bought the first one for my son just recently and he will be able to enjoy it's reliability just as I have. There are so many versions available with special 'bells and whistles' but all I need is the basic one or the solar atomic one. GOOD job Casio!

Title: Good fit for skinny men
Text: As many other reviewers have written, this is a solid digital watch with classic styling for a fair price that really can't be beat. The only things I'd like to add are: 1.) This watch fits small men's wrists very well without leaving an excessive "tail" of watchband as is a common problem for skinny watch wearers; 2.) The recessed button is fairly easy to access even if you have short nails and you shouldn't be deterred from buying this watch because of it.

Title: Great Watch
Text: After owning this watch for the last four years and subjecting it to a great deal of stress both at home and at work on the ambulance, it finally broke. Without hesitation I bought a second one. Solid watch.

Title: ... Casio watches that were assembled in Japan are of better quality. I have found that the Chinese use ...
Text: The Casio watches that were assembled in Japan are of better quality. I have found that the Chinese use inferior or wrong size "weatherized" rubber "O' rings to seal the cases.  So if you haven't tried your watch to check whether it is truly water resistant, I would immediately leave it over night in a glass filled with same! This will be the first watch I've purchased via Amazon so we'll see! Otherwise the watch delivery and price were both within my expectations. Two prior DW-5600 shorted out before I had an experienced jeweler look at the first one and the second to see what happened!

Title: Perfect first or travel watch
Text: Classic G with the rectangular face. Very retro. This watch tells time and it's tough. Good first watch for a kid or to use as a disposable travel watch.  Wear it to the beach, to the pool or out on a tough-mudder run.  If it lasts, you'll know what time it is.  If it breaks (and it probably won't) get a new one.  Can't go wrong.

Title: Can’t go wrong with this Sqaure face G-Shock.
Text: Awesome G Shock hands down! It is a tough watch that can handle anything you throw at it. Love the fact that this watch isn’t bulky like other G Shocks. Looks great on my wrist. Highly recommended to anyone that is looking to buy their first G Shock.

Title: Husband likes it serves its purpose
Text: Husband likes it, serves its purpose.

Title: 3 years and still going strong
Text: I bought this as a watch to wear to work at the hospital. Dealing with phlegm, blood and poop regularly, this watch gets wiped down with sanitation cloths and alcohol non-stop. That has been it’s routine for over 3 years, and it looks good as new. No signs of wear or discoloration on the face or band. I highly recommend this as a rugged every day watch.

Title: G shock
Text: great watch, really durable

Title: This model is my favorite. I wear it everywhere
Text: This is my 3rd Casio DW5600E.  This model is my favorite.  I wear it everywhere, all the time, for the last 15 years.  They keep better time than Swiss automatics.  They are inexpensive.  I broke the first watch changing the battery.  I broke a battery terminal connection somehow.  The second watch still runs, but the strap and case are pretty battered from constant wear and my 2 year old labrador retriever chewing on it.

Title: Takes a beating and keeps on ticking
Text: Only downfall of this fella is that the buttons are a bit recessed so they’re hard to press

Title: like the others
Text: This is my 3rd Casio G-Shock watch and this, like the others, works well. It's very accurate and stands up to hard use.I like that all it take to replace the battery is a small screw driver. The only down side is that the buttons on the side for the stopwatch are a little on the small side.

Title: Great Watch
Text: I have this watch for the last couple weeks and I am extremely happy with it. For a watch at this price range, it has amazing build quality. I did lots of yard work wearing it so this watch got exposed to mud, water multiple times and had no issues.

Title: Great watch. I stay active as in running and ...
Text: Great watch. I stay active as in running and swimming so I use it a lot. Its simple, easy to use,  and comfortable. I like the alarm feature as well. I have another g shock tough solar watch that I have had for 9 years now and have never had to replace the battery so we'll see how the battery life last on this one not being a tough solar but so far I love it.

Title: Exceptional watch
Text: I bought the Casino as a wear all the time watch. I am a pilot so I needed something that was small but easy to read and VERY sturdy. This watch is all that. The reason for 4 stars from me is that it only has one timezone. I run on both Zulu and Local so the ability to switch timezones would have made this watch Uber instead of Exceptional.

Title: GREAT DEAL!
Text: I always needed/wanted a sports watch, but never could find the right one.  A lot of people have G-Shock's, but i had one, and it was too bulky.  Yeah, it's a name brand, but it wasn't for me.  So, i was looking for a slim, thin sports watch that is more suitable for me (because i have smaller wrists), and this is perfect!  It has everything that i need, time, date, day, and style. Overall, 5 stars all the way, and for the price, it doesn't compare! Highly recommend :)

Title: touf and reliable only trouble is findng batters and replaceing band
Text: have one just like it had it for several years liked it and got another couldn't find battery's. So just bout a new one wear it twenty four seven it holds up great even wear it in the shower

Title: Just buy it!
Text: Best dollar for value watch on the market. What's not to love, it's a g shock!

Title: Good deal
Text: Bought this for my son, top left button smooshes in too far. Doesn’t seem to affect anything. It’s 40 bucks and a classic.

Title: Great Watch, But....
Text: This is my third one of these.  I just love the watch.  I wear it in the water, almost never take it off.  Never any issues with the watch itself, which withstands all kinds of conditions.  But the bands eventually break and cannot be replaced separately from the watch.  So I end up having to replace the watch just because of the broken band.

Title: Watch size
Text: Such a good looking watch! I had been wanting a G-Shock for months, but didn’t want to deal with the XL you find these days. This one is the perfect size. It isn’t big or small. It has a retro-modern look to it.

Title: One Thing Well
Text: At the time of writing, I've been using my Casio for a month, and am quite pleased. It's comfortable, durable, and uncluttered with any useless or superfluous features. I use the timer, alarm, and stopwatch often and with no difficulty. It's a testament to the design of a watch when you can put it on and completely forget about it until you need to tell the time. This watch is durable enough that I need not worry about it getting scratched or wet over the course of normal daily tasks. It has a reasonable price to boot!

Title: He loves it
Text: Husband LOVES this watch-maybe more than he loves me. JK. Every night it sets itself to the Atomic clock. Always perfect time. Highly recommend.

Title: La marca casio
Text: Lo uso diariamente,es muy bueno.

Title: You will never go wrong with this watch.
Text: These watches are made to last. If I encounter one that proves otherwise I will still replace it with the same watch.

Title: Bargain price for this watch
Text: Great watch, great price!

Title: Great gift!
Text: Perfect for the cost. Exactly as described.

Title: Quality Watch!
Text: Almost the perfect watch. Very easy and simple to activate features. LOVE the countdown timer. Extremely durable watch. Took this on a rafting trip in the Philippines, had it smashed into rocks and constantly wet. Held up like a champ. The band is quality and feels very durable and tough but is also very comfortable and the watch as a whole feels very good on your wrist. Not clunky and awkward Overall: excellent, feature laden, comfortable watch. My only complaint is the lack of dual time... Not a HUGE deal but I've missed it at times.

Title: Best inexpensive watch out there.
Text: can't beat it for the money, great for active people. Need good eyesight as the display is a little small but not a big deal.

Title: Stylish
Text: Very stylish good for casual and professional ware work and sports

Title: Good quality.
Text: For work,it's cheap and perfect.i will buy another eventually for family and friends.good for gift.

Title: Great for women as well!
Text: The shock and water resistant women's watches are unnecessarily expensive, so I decided to purchase a men's. I was afraid the watch would be too large for my wrist, but the watch face is a reasonable size and the strap fastens extremely far, so I had no trouble fitting it to my wrist. I haven't had the watch for too long, so I'll return to edit my review after I've worn it through the Marine Corps officer candidate school.

Title: Good product
Text: It is what I hoped for.

Title: Button issues
Text: I’ve been a longtime G Shock fan and have owned several over the years since the very first model. Timekeeping, water resistance, and durability have always been great. I’m the odd guy preferring not to have a wall clock on my wrist and I thought this fit the bill again. This one has been frustrating however. The buttons are not sensitive and don’t work very well. Particularly the upper left one. It works intermittently and often requires using a tool (pen, etc.) to depress it enough to activate it. At first I thought I was just fat fingering around the button causing the issue, but that’s not it. If I hadn’t kept it and worn it for several days trying to “learn” it, I would’ve returned it for a replacement or perhaps a different G Shock model. Frustrating.

Title: Awesome!
Text: I love this watch! It has amazing water resistance! This is just one of three G-Shocks I own. Many people say they have owned G-Shocks for 10-20 years with no problems so I'm hoping to have this watch for quite some time. Also, if you take the watch into the ocean, make sure you rinse it with fresh water when your done. You will not be disappointed with any G-Shock you buy, the DW5600E-1V was approved by NASA and has been in space. How many watches in the 30-100 dollar range can say that?!

Title: Good watch! it seems pretty durable and resistance but ...
Text: Good watch! it seems pretty durable and resistance but be aware of the adjust  button ,its a bit sunk i can barely push it but it works fine, i dont know if any other customer have this issue

Title: Awesome
Text: Great watch for the price

Title: There is none better. The watch kept on working
Text: This is my 3rd, the  case on the one it replaced just disintegrated due to extremely hard use over 10 years.  There is none better.  The watch kept on working, but the case around the "works" is what finally failed.  Considering the tough conditions my watch has to endure, it  was amazing the band and case lasted so long.  I will never be without my G-shock.

Title: Beware of poor display quality!
Text: This is a great looking watch if not 1 critical issue — the screen quality is terrible. The numbers are clearly visible only under certain narrow angle interval. Because of that the wathes looks worse than cheap 5$ watch from 10 years ago. Shame on Casio for such poor quality control.

Title: Good quality for an affordable price
Text: Great value for the price.

Title: Does everything you need a watch to do
Text: It isn't too big like most G-shock watches are. It is tough and works great. If you are looking for a functional watch this is the one to get. What more is there to say?

Title: Nothing
Text: I like it

Title: Can Take A Beating (but watch out for that tan line)
Text: I got this watch and used it on shift as an EMT. Like: cheap, durable, even lighting for visibility in the dark, all the different functions Dislike: big watch tan

Title: A great watch
Text: This watch is exactly what G Shock is based around-- making an unbreakable watch that tells time.  I wear this watch to work everyday (welding).  It has yet to fail me in the time that I have had it.  It has some features, not as many as other G Shocks, but I like that about it.  It has an alarm, a countdown timer, and a timer.  It's elegance is its simplicity.  This watch is a perfect watch for work, and a great beginner to the world of g Shocks.

Title: Received!
Text: Thank you for the Watches!

Title: The basic and perhaps the best Square-G because one can see the the time when ...
Text: The basic and perhaps the best Square-G because one can see the the time when using the stop-watch function. I find it the most comfortable for my wrist. This forty-buck watch is, believe it or not, approved by NASA for space travel. I kid you not. Now, possibly I'm not expecting to be called upon to use it for galactic exploration but always best to be prepared....

Title: This is my third G-shock in thirty years. The ...
Text: This is my third G-shock in thirty years. The only reason I have to ever get a new one is because the band rots off my wrist from wearing it everyday covered by saltwater, concrete,epoxy, you name it. This watch has never let me down.

Title: It is very precise
Text: I like it so far, very precise, which I need at work. Have had it for 3 months. I hope the battery lasts long, which it looks like it will. I would recommend it!

Title: 4 stats for the product. But no star for ...
Text: 4 stats for the product. But no star for the shonky delivery. I know it's a G Shock but still, proper packaging and care needs to be done.

Title: Awful return
Text: Bought watch she day delivery. Watch was damaged, replacement watch will be delivered in a week now. Don't understand, should have got a refund and ordered again. Would have got it in a day not a week

Title: Adjust button
Text: My adjust button is pushed in far.

Title: liked my old casio better
Text: I don't like the design as much as my old casio.the displays a little small and the function buttons are a little hard to acsess.there is also a wrist turning function on my old casio which is not available on this model and the backlight does not seem as bright as my previous watch.seems to be waterproof and keeps good time though

Title: Good quality! Great price!
Text: Very good quality for the price. Easy to use and adjust. Less bulky then the other G-shocks. Very Durable and good material, wear it every day to work at a warehouse. Has all the necessities you need; alarm, day, date, TIME, light, and Waterproof. Great Price!!

Title: Returned.
Text: I returned this item because one of the buttons was partially stuck inside the case. Quality control aside, I was split on this item. I bought it because I thought it looked kinda retro. In person it just looks kinda cheap. On the the plus side, it's very light, and the band is more comfortable than larger G-Shocks I've owned.

Title: Recommended
Text: Good quality watch

Title: Classic / Historic Watch
Text: This is a classic / historic watch.  A must have for any watch collection.  I wear this as my "beater" watch.  For when I don't want to wear my nice automatic.  I have a smaller wrist and it is just a fraction too large but I am getting used to it.

Title: very nice
Text: very nice and comfortable :)

Title: Excellent Classic Watch
Text: I was looking for a fairly cheap rugged watch and am delighted with the purchase.  It is not "brick size" compared with some of the other G-Shock models and it has only basic functions - I only really want it to tell the time.  The screen is clear and easy to read, and it also has an alarm, stopwatch and countdown timer.  The light is clear in low light and the strap is comfortable to wear.  Overall, excellent. Update 2013-09-28.  Still wearing it as the daily watch, awesome.

Title: Toughest watch ever
Text: I gave this to my son as a first watch. He loves it and never takes it off. He is 7 so the watch has to withstand a lot. More than adecuate. Toughest watch ever.

Title: A Super Watch. A Tremendous Value!
Text: I've owned this watch in several incarnations for the past 20 years.  Although I've wandered and purchased competing watches, I always return to a G-Shock for its tremendous dependability and functionality. Time keeping and battery life have never disappointed.  As a military aviator, I was initially impressed by the ruggedness of this watch but after 2 decades where I have replaced it only twice for a broken watch band and a dead battery, the value of this simple yet sturdy watch has been astounding. The G-Shock constitutes a special place in a small yet satisfying pantheon of products that provides phenomenal value!

Title: Good watch
Text: Looks great on my wrist

Title: Wears a little smaller than anticipated based on the case ...
Text: Wears a little smaller than anticipated based on the case size of the watch. Outfitted with NATO strap adapters and bull bars from JayandKays, makes for a very attractive utility watch.  The watch i wear to the gym and other physical activities.

Title: Tells you exactly what you need to know and nothing more
Text: Simple and tough. This watch has changed very little in almost 20 years. I used to have one when I was in 2nd grade and the price and quality are pretty much the same. What I love most is everything you really need to see is right there on the screen and there aren't a lot of needless fancy controls that waste time and energy figuring out what they are and how they work. I just need the time, date, and day. That's it and that's what this great watch gives me.

Title: Great Watch
Text: Great Watch! Only catch is that the reset button is too far into the watch and is difficult to be pushed without something small and slim.

Title: Great
Text: Great time piece.. Good value

Title: Standby
Text: I have worn this watch for decades. Well, a long time. This is probably my fourth or fifth one. They last about two years and work OK until the light goes dim. It is not much in the way of decoration but it has more functions than I need and no dials to squint at.

Title: Great classic CASIO G-SHOCK watch, at a great price!
Text: Great classic CASIO G-SHOCK watch, at a great price!

Title: Good old standby
Text: I have been a Casio fan for a long time. I am a diver and a hairdresser, so the waterproof feature is perfect, as well as the stopwatch and countdown features. I recently bought a new solar powered Casio, which not only did not work well, (the screen would go blank, and would not turn back on according to the instructions.) So I went back to the old stand-by. The only fault is that the bands wear out before the watch does, and replacing it costs almost as much as a new watch.

Title: most reliable ever
Text: most reliable watch ever

Title: Loved it .......
Text: I had a very old model of this same watch and I had it for years and years.  I loved it.  When push came to shove the rubber/plastic band breaking is what finally forced me into a newer watch.  But this watch was simply wonderful!

Title: Great Bang for the Buck
Text: This classic Casio is great bang for your buck. I have a fairly extensive watch collection but I needed a good reliable watch that I can throw in a bag for the beach or washing the car, doing yard work, playing tennis or bicycling — without fear of damaging one of my more expensive watches. The Casio DW5600E fits the bill perfectly, as it's extremely durable and very water resistant. Well worth the price.

Title: My Casio f-91w is a better watch than this g shock
Text: This watch was a waste of money. Okay so one problem is that the time display is faded my Casio f-91w is easier to read than this watch. Another problem is that the adjustment button is lodged in too much so it’s a lot harder to adjust the time settings on this watch. The biggest problem I have with this watch is that it doesn’t have AM time settings which means that I have to change the date manually to stay with accurate time every single day. What a huge flaw that if I knew about this issue I would have never bought this stupid watch. Overall my f-91w is a better at telling the time than the watch and it only cost 10 dollars.

Title: Old school look in a fantastic watch.
Text: I had one of these when I was in High School... almost 30 years ago.  It was an impulse buy and I love it.

Title: Tough Mudder Approved!
Text: Update to review: Still own this watch, still wear it daily. I just completed Tough Mudder wearing this and it survived! Did not fall off, did not bother me and still working. Original Review: I am writing this review over a year after owning this watch. I wear this watch everywhere I am not in need of my nicer watch, including work. Very durable, have dropped it and banged it many times. This watch truly lives up to its "G-Shock" name as it it the longest lasting cheaper watch I've ever owned. Defiantly recommend

Title: Instant classic
Text: Great watch

Title: Will br great to finish off basic training
Text: I like the count down feature...

Title: Not what it once was
Text: The watches dimensions are noticeably smaller. It is the light version of its predecessor. The band is just about an inch too short. Originally the band was about right. It is the same digital display screen which is part of why I again. Chose this model. Overall not the best but not the worst as it come to fulfilling expectations . So if your a big old nostalgic g-shock wearing commercial construction kind of guy, this may not be for you. But, your welder wife might like  it.

Title: I wore one for 15 years doing construction and beat it up good and it always worked
Text: Indestructible watch . I wore one for 15 years doing construction and beat it up good and it always worked. I didn't even know they still made it but found this one And I'm glad because you can't beat the price 40$ for watch that will last 15 years ain't too bad . I recommend this over the other g shocks as it's not as bulky looking And the functions are simple and easy to use.

Title: Love it.
Text: What a great deal.  Watch is great and simple to use. Basic digital watch that looks good and works as advertised.  Hope to have it for a long time!

Title: I like the retro look
Text: I like the retro look. The stopwatch function, where you now have to reset the timer using the "set time" recessed button at upper left is a total joke. The viewing angle is not as wide as other G-Shock watches. I've owned a $250 G-Shock (actually four total) and I like that this one is less conspicuous.

Title: I love this watch
Text: I love this watch!  Easy to read and with a slimmer profile relative to other G shocks.  While I also like the Rangeman and the Mudman, this one and the DW 6900 are my two favorites.  Casio please dont ever change this watch!!

Title: I really like the clean simplicity of the watch and the quality ...
Text: I needed a watch and decided on this G-Shock.  I really like the clean simplicity of the watch and the quality feel.  I though the price point was very appealing for a Casio G-Shock.  This G-Shock is more subtle compared to other G-Shock I have owned or seen in the past but still presents like a tough watch.  Very Good Everyday Watch

Text: Super classic looking g shock, I enjoy a more simple looking watch. This has everything I need. With easy to tell time. It has this vintage feel to it. And the watch wears very well when being active.

Title: Such a neat watch!
Text: This watch is neat-o! Not only does it tell time but it also has an alarm clock and a timer! It tells me the date so I’ll never ever have to look at a calendar again! For sure the best 40$ watch I’ve ever purchased!

Title: This is the 4th G-Shock I have owned in the ...
Text: This is the 4th G-Shock I have owned in the last 30 yrs. As a swimmer and a diver I have found them to be quite durable as well as waterproof. The watchbands usually wear out before the battery does. Hard to beat the reasonable price and the outstanding durability.

The band, which is made of a rather stiff rubber type material, seems to be an integral part of the watch.

Title: A G-Shock for Adults
Text: If you’re looking for a g shock that doesn’t announce itself before you do, this is the watch for you.  It’s got a great matte finish.  The dial is uncluttered.  The functions are practical.  It’s also a good size.

Title: Really like this classic watch
Text: Really like this classic watch.  Only thing is, I have to remember what buttons to push to have the various functions do what I want.  Really, that's not a problem with the watch.  I think it's more a function of my age!  Let's see, which button turns time back?

Title: Whether your first watch, or your 20th, everyone should have one of those in their collection.
Text: Reminds me of my first G-Shock I had way back when, which was awesome!  Great price, super easy to use, indestructible.  Also fits great as some G-Shocks are incredibly massive and look ridiculous on my wrist.

Title: very nice watch

Title: Excellent watch, great value

Title: Ultimately dependable.
Text: Exactly what you demand from a classic sports watch with a legendary reputation. It's as reliable as it gets. It's not fancy. It doesn't quite work with "dinner parties." (Go ahead and use your Omega for tuxedo evenings) But this thing is die-hard tough, accurate, reliable, and extremely waterproof. Easy to use. No unneeded features (which usually don't work as advertised, anyway, or you don't need them). You can't ask for anything more in a tough-as-nails sports watch that refuses to die (or be killed).

Title: Came broken

Title: Great for active individuals
Text: Love this watch! Been wearing it for years now and prefer it to my other watches as a daily watch. Great watch for active individuals. I have worn it during multiple mud runs and wear it to the gym daily and it can withstand it all. If you're looking for a simple, affordable watch that you can wear daily, this is the watch for you.

Title: Great watch at a fantastic price!
Text: I have many watches much more expensive that this model of the G-Shock.  However, it seems that I always reach for this watch first.  Why? It's pretty close to being 'bullet-proof.'  I don't worry about breaking it and if it should happen to get damaged, $40 get me another watch.  In terms of style and size, it's clearly designed as a men's watch.  That being said, I like the size and fit of the watch.  Lastly, the quality of the watch is outstanding.  A great value. I highly recommend it!

Title: Great watch but...
Text: I have had several G-Shock over the last 2 decades. Good watches, but this newer iteration comes with a much thinner wrist band. based on prior experience, it is not likely to last as long as the older one have. Casio definitely cut corners there, hence only 4 stars

Title: A great budget g-shock
Text: This is a great way to get into g-shocks without breaking the bank. It has all the features you need and none you don't want. It is a lot slimmer than all the other g-shocks. The only thing I don't like is you cant turn off the beep when you switch between different functions.

Title: Tough as nails
Text: Great durable and extra-affordable EDC beater watch for its price. Certified by NASA. Very comfortable to wear on a smaller wrist comparing to other G-Shocks. The lume is great. I wish it had the dual time, but for this price it's just amazing. I'm totally satisfied.

Title: Excellent Watch!
Text: This watch is exceptional, I don't normally buy gshocks, but I though that this one was worth a try since it is smaller then the normal ones. This watch is definitely worth the $43 I paid and is defiantly going to stand up against the elements. I am an Eagle Scout and take it camping with my Boy Scout troop and it is a satisfactory piece of machinery that does exactly what it is suppose to without a bunch of unneeded bells and whistles. Three words; BUY THIS WATCH!

Title: Great Watch.
Text: Great watch takes all you can throw at it and comes back for more. Wears light and comfortable. Easy to read time and looks well on wrist. What’s more to say?

Title: This is a perfect watch. It is simple
Text: This is a perfect watch.  It is simple, rugged, and looks great.  The display shows time, date, and day of the week.  It has an alarm, stopwatch, and timer.  It has the illuminator backlight.  I can't think of anything else you really need.  I work in the oilfield and need a durable watch.  You can tell the second you pick it up from the feel of it that it is built to last.  Would recommend.

Title: May be a defective unit but at $46 I’m done
Text: Purchased this watch for work. Did not want to soil my expensive watch with the activities I perform in the hospital. I’ve had this watch for approximately 5 days and 2 issues has come up. Issue 1: Today is Wednesday. On Monday the watch had the right date displayed - Month, Day, and Year. This morning I woke up in a panic when I saw it reported the day as Thursday. For a moment I thought I missed work. Issue 2: if you look at the pictures, there are four silver buttons - two on each side of the watch’s interface. The top left button labeled A in the instruction manual is completely depressed in. To access the options assigned to this button I had to use pen and press down. I believe over time this button will sink deep in the leather contours of the watch. Other than that, watch is a decent watch. $30 at best.

Title: Great watch, great flaw
Text: I love Casio watches, and this is the classic G Shock. Looks great, and it's probably indestructible (only had it a couple weeks). It has one MAJOR design flaw though.  The set button is so recessed into the body, you can't push it with your finger.  I have to pop out my pocket knife or pen to use it.  That wouldn't be a big issue, except this button resets/sets the timer, which I use while cooking and during the day quite a bit. It's a pain. And a horrible design flaw. It handicaps an otherwise great watch.

Title: Great watch!
Text: This is probably the cheapest, most simple G-Shock you can buy, and I love everything about it.  The features most people need, and nothing more.  Tough as nails, I took it paintballing frequently, which is actually where I lost it, but at least it didn't break! Someone probably found it, and is using it still. Don't be fooled in to buying a G-shock with all the crazy features that you'll never use, this is really the best buy in terms of this style of watch.

Title: Product review:  Casio G-Shock
Text: Casio is superior in action based watches. This watch is tough yet looks good. Waterproof, shockproof, and dust proof makes it great for the outdoors and rough handling. Battery powered not solar which was chosen because of use in hiking through woods. Solar available. Battery has 10 year guarantee.

Title: Withstands childhood active lifestyle

Title: I've been wearing this watch for close to 25 years ...
Text: I've been wearing this watch for close to 25 years and was in the military beating and banging this watch around as an Aircraft mechanic!!! I'm in the water a lot now and it is very dependable!! For the price you cannot beat it!! This is only my 6th watch in the 25 or so years!!

Title: Totally worth money, and more!
Text: Probably the best of G-Shocks for money. It is thin, light, and the least expensive. The time keeping on mine is about 1sec ehead per week! If you want something on your wrist to tell time at work, look no further.

Title: Just Buy It
Text: As I recall this is the same watch I had in the '80's. It's got all the basics and does what it's designed to do. I do however wish it had solar and atomic. I would buy it again in a heartbeat.

Title: Utilitarian and durable
Text: I'm not a big watch collector. I just want something that works and lasts a long time. This does the trick. Simple to use, tells me the date, and has a very strong build. I constantly expose it to water when I wash my hands and it still works. Sometimes, I even smack the watch against a wall while it's on my wrist (I don't know why I do this), and no crack or malfunction has happened.

I've had one of these before, and I will probably have another whenever I somehow destroy this one, which will be difficult.

Title: Classic G Shock

I wear it while working, doing yardwork, even sometimes in the shower to clean it off. Not the fanciest watch around but I always know what time it is. Update 4 years strong, finally had to change the battery.

Title: I bought this watch for running, and it works ...
Text: I bought this watch for running, and it works as designed. It's also the only digital watch I can remember how to change the time on, which puts it (literally) in a class by itself. Yes, the buttons can be a little difficult to depress with sweaty fingers / closely trimmed nails, but for an inexpensive and indestructible timekeeper, you can't go wrong with this.

Title: Perfect time that lasts and lasts
Text: This is my third G-shock and I expect it to last as long as I will.  The first one lost it's ability to hold the band on my third band replacement.  The second one had a broken shell.  It was several years old and I decided to get a new one.

Title: The settings
Text: Cheap and I don't like it that it has less functions

Title: The essentials
Text: In preparation for an upcoming deployment, I was on the hunt for a rugged, dependable watch.  For the money, this watch cannot be beat.  I'm not usually a digital watch guy nor do I like rubber bands but this watch has changed my mind.  It's very comfortable to wear and provides on the details I need:  Time, Date, Day, Alarm, countdown timer, and stopwatch.  I don't need altimeters, barometers, solar power (don't spend that much time outside), or geosyncs.

Title: Highly recommend!!!
Text: I've been collection automatic watches(Seiko's, Orients, etc.) for a little while now. The problem is that they typically aren't that durable. This was a perfect addition to my collection. It utilizes the classic design from 1983 and yet is durable enough for any task you can throw at it. And you can't beat the price.

Title: Good Watch

Title: Good watch

Title: A Casio Classic
Text: This is a classic no frills g shock. Durable and easy to use. I can’t say enough about the toughness of this watch.

Title: Reliable while inexpensive.
Text: I have several G-shock watches but wanted a less expensive one for work.  Works great, back glow is bright, and the watch is durable.  I also like that it is not thick and easy to wear under a long sleeve shirt.

Title: Rugged and dependable
Text: I bought this watch to replace one exactly like it that I have had for well over 10 years. I may have just needed a new battery, but a couple of places around the face and bezel had the plastic casing starting to break away and the light function was kaput. New watch is excellent and I hope to love it for many years to come.

Title: You can't beat a proven classic!!!!
Text: The quality of this watch is great for the price. It is truly the best value in a rugged watch out there. You can order replacement parts. I often use mil-spec products for durability. I spent a few years in the Marine corps and this watch is built to withstand that kind of abuse. It's a G Shock guys! This model is an "Illuminator" which is basically like timex's indiglo. It lights up full screen clear and bright green. I'm proud to own one.

Title: Best watch for impact
Text: This is hands down the best watch for work. It's lightweight, thin, easy to format, & most importantly durable. Can't beat the price either.

Title: I love this watch I own 7 G-Shocks
Text: I love this watch I own 7 G-Shocks. This one makes 8 and is also my second of this model. The first is my work watch. I'm glad to see they updated the module. I modded it with a 2006 FIFA Germany bezel and JaysandKays Zulu and adapters. Awesome watch!

Title: Good Looking Watch!
Text: I like this watch a lot. It actually looks better on your wrist. It's well built and well designed. Only thing that it shys one star from being perfect is that it does not have a dual time. This is important to me since I travel oversea and having a dual time watch is really handy.

Title: casio
Text: After about a week of owning this watch everything is great so far. I like the thin profile of the watch as most other watches even among the g-shock line are unreasonably massive and cumbersome. I like the simplicity of this watch. It don't have all of the useless information that 98% of people don't need in a watch like moon phase or tide charts or any of that other crap. It does just what it is intended to do. Tell me the time. Bingo.

Title: SAME WATCH REPLACEMENT
Text: I got this exactly the same watch in 1995 and it still works like the day I got it, but the band was showing its age and starting to tear. After I bought this I found out that a replacement band and bezel still could be obtained. So I may also rejuvenate the old one.

Title: Tough and simple are a good thing.
Text: This watch is simple and tough. I have always wanted a g-shock and I am glad I went with this one. The classic look like the 80s style is awesome. Nice green glow light. Afterglow for about 2 seconds. Everything you need, no fluff that you don't. Waterproof for deeper than ill ever swim and shock resist. Meat and taters. Love it.

Title: nice and simple and TOUGH!
Text: Pretty much say's it all.  This watch simply gets the job done.  Need a tough as nails everyday watch?  Look no further here it is.  BUY IT!  Don't waste money on fancier atomic or solar one.  For two to three times the price you can just pitch this in 2 years when the battery goes and get a new one.  Its accurate enough.  If you need more accuracy you may need to up your OCD meds!

Title: Bought in 2015, Still Going Strong
Text: I've owned this watch for 5 years now and it just keeps running flawlessly.

Title: ive now had this watch for a good long while I like it a lot the alarm ...
Text: ive now had this watch for a good long while I like it a lot the alarm is not that great but it works for me it should last me a long time, a worth while investment.

Title: Simple G-Shock
Text: Pros: Great design. Good timekeeping. Awesome battery life. Durable yet good looking. Just your classic G-Shock. Cons: "Adjust" button is a little more recessed than I'd prefer. Watch is designed this way, however I've compared my watch to others, and it is a bit more extreme (Quality control issue?) Overall I really can't complain when you look at this watch in terms of value and function. It is a great watch I plan to wear and beat up for many years.

Title: Good Basic Digital Display Watch At A Reasonable Price.
Text: Very happy with this watch. Suits my purposes well. Would suggest to older buyers to check if they can hear the alarm. It is very high-pitched and I have trouble hearing it if there is any background noise.

Title: Inexpensive watch that gets through every condition you can survive
Text: I like that 80's techno look of watch, which has not been changed maybe since it was first introduced. Unlike those expensive mechanic/fashion watches, this watch was born to survive harsh conditions and provides accurate timing when you need. The battery lasts long enough. The functionality is basic but adequate. The best part is that it is so inexpensive to replace if you lost one or break one, which I doubt will ever happen during daily use.

Title: So far it is fine. I would be better if you only had ...
Text: So far it is fine. I would be better if you only had to push one button for the backlight.

Title: Somewhat like the original...
Text: Not quite like the original g-shock I had back in the late eighties and nineties. The function buttons are a bit different. This new version has a better light. however when you compare this  model  to the new G Shocks that are three or four times bigger in size, this original influenced design is much better to wear all day long. I once drove over my original G Shock with a Toyota Landcruiser and it survived just fine. I don't have confidence that this new G Shock will be as tough.

Title: Too bad I can't find a Speidel twist-o-flex watch band that ...
Text: The watch works as expected.  It's my third one in 25 years, the others just wore out.  Too bad I can't find a Speidel twist-o-flex watch band that fits it, as those were always great to have with this watch.  But the watch itself is great.

Title: Outdoor watch
Text: I thought it was going to be too big but it fits well. Really enjoy wearing it for anything I do outdoor.

Title: good watch , good price
Text: The watch is great so far but , thats expected from casio . I needed it for work . I saw the other g-shock's but , they were way too big , bulky & more expensive for a work watch thats gonna get beat up . i also wanted simplicity . Date & time is all i needed . Its nice enough to wear out on the town too .

Title: Great everyday working watch
Text: Been a fan of this watch for a long time.  Finally bought this to replace my first generation model that wore out after 20 yrs of use by my son and then me.  It has a good protective housing that protects the face.  I also like the green backlighting as opposed to the old incandesant bulb.

Title: Excelente
Text: Excelente para el trabajo

Title: Working fine
Text: I just received it for my husband and is working fine.

Title: This one is just like the one I had 20 years ago and I ...
Text: It works - it's not sexy, but it tells the right time every time I look down at it.  I had some blue tooth watch that was supposed to sync the correct time from my iPhone but it was always 10 minutes off.  This one is just like the one I had 20 years ago and I still remember how all the buttons work.

Title: it is all around good
Text: great product

Title: Awesome sauce.
Text: Great watch so far. Can’t complain. It feels very comfortable on the wrist. It very understated design as far far as G-Shocks go. Love this watch, especially for the price.

Title: Mens DW5600E1V- G Shock Watch
Text: I must say that this watch has everything that I wanted but I would have liked at least 3 alarm settings and could not find any from Casio. I stoped buying Timex because the last 3 watches I had replaced the battery in , the alarm had stopped working! I hope this Casio watch will be diffrent!

Title: Great watch
Text: Love this watch.  Not very expensive but built to last.  So far my favorite work watch.  I am very hard on watches, but so far not a scratch on it.  Lives up to the G-Shock name

Title: Durable and reliable
Text: Great durable and reliable watch.

Title: Excellent Watch
Text: I really like this watch. I can wear while working and it can take some abuse and continue to work.  It is a nice looking watch and can be worn for business functions as well.  The only drawback is that some of the buttons for setting are recessed to the point I have to us a pointed object to set them.  However, once they are set it is not a problem and setting is seldom.

Title: My First G-Shock
Text: I love the watch!  The blue backlight is perfect in dark areas like camping tent or a totally dark bedroom.  You can really see the display on the watch.  It has a tight push buttons indicating excellent water-tight sealing.  It feels it is a tough watch. It is not big for my small wrist but I wish it was a bit thinner for better handling.  I can't wait to go fishing and camping with it.  I am happy with this purchase, no complaint.

Title: Great watch, specially for military enlistment!
Text: If you want a watch that you can use during military basic training, this is the one! Great product and shock resistant, water resistant, military time, alarm, timer.... overall great watch!

Title: Nice quality build and it has this good
Text: My daily watch, it does what it does. Nice quality build and it has this good, conservative feel to it. What I like the most is that it's not one of those "bigger than your wrist" type of G-shock's, I walk a lot so that helps quite a bit that it doesn't attract unnecessary attention!

Title: Questionable quality
Text: Bought one on three separate occasions and each time I got a watch with the exact same defect The plastic was raised too much on the top left so unless you have fingers made of toothpicks you won’t be able to reach the button I thought to myself how could they mess this up the second time and then I thought this on the third try But it seems this vendor has only sold to me from a defective batch

Title: STILL A GREAT WATCH, BUT --- ??
Text: THIS MODEL DOES NOT HAVE DUAL TIME???  I have had this exact same watch for many years, finally having to replace it.  For some unknown reason, CASIO dropped the DUAL TIME feature.  WHY?? All of the other features are still available and no new features were added, so why did they drop a very useful feature for travelers.  Even their cheaper ($15) watches have dual time, so it cannot be an expensive feature.  Just does not make any sense to delete features from one of the most successful watches ever designed. A little disappointed in CASIO!

Title: Finally!
Text: Everything I was hoping for. Accurate time keeping, day, date, 24hr format, proper illumination (shuts-off within 2 sec.) alarm system (loud & clear), by-the-hour indicator, timer, stopwatch, compact (non-bulky) and my most favorite feature is the 200m water resistance. Best collab watch I've come across so far.

Title: Good watch
Text: This watch is exactly what I wanted.

Title: nice watch
Text: nice watch

Title: Great quality and value for the price!
Text: It’s simple and easy to operate, all while looking good too!

Title: Best digital watch manufacture around!!
Text: I have used this product since Casio first came out with the G-Shock and they always work great. This watch does everything that I need a watch for, and the battery lasts for five to six years. I SCUBA dive with it, work out with it, and bang it around all the time, and it takes everything that I can dish out. I hope that Casio continues to manufacture it in the future, because they will always have me as a customer.

Title: For women too!
Text: Was worried it would be a little too big but it's perfect!  Very sturdy, easy to use, and practical for those working with their hands.

Title: Greatest utility at any price
Text: This is the third time that I have purchased this excellent watch. It is light, accurate, easy to read, and comfortable. I can wear it in the shower and wash it along with the rest of Mr when I am very sweaty. It can go in the bay when I swim. It's light always works and the battery lasts more than three years. What more can I say about such an excellent time piece?
Muy buena calidad

Title: Durable
Text: On my wrist for four years. Feels fine. Time is always correct. Wear when getting wet outside or when washing hands. No issues. Works like it should

Title: The difficult "Adjust" button seems to be a pattern.
Text: As others have said, the "A"-Adjust button on the delivered watch required a pointed object (toothpick, ball point pen, etc.) to depress.  No amount of finger-pushing or using a fingernail would make it engage. The countdown timer was one feature I was looking forward to using as a barbecue cooking timer.  The beep when the countdown was completed was so extremely faint it was not audible unless the watch was held mashed into my ear. This is the 2nd Casio watch from Amazon that was defective.  I previously ordered a Casio G-Shock model, ~$250, from a major retailer that was also delivered defective, with the "A"-Adjust button missing. Extremely disappointed with this product line.

Title: Sleek watch that will last for years!
Text: I've had this watch for about 4 years now and I love it.  I haven't had to change the battery and the time hardly needs to be calibrated.  I'm an aviator and I am pretty OCD with my watch syncing up with the time on our planes.  If I had known about the solar version of this watch I probably would of bought that instead, however I'm extremely happy with this one!

Title: Very good product
Text: You get good quality for what you pay. Just one problem that i had with a sunked button but it got fixed

Title: Low Key Utilitarian Perfection
Text: This watch is so rad. It looks like a cheap plastic watch from a distance and to the untrained eye, but in reality it's a high quality product with a late 80's vibe. Functions perfectly and is completely waterproof in my experience. Super badass watch for anyone who lives an active lifestyle and is not insecure about their net worth

Title: My favorite watch
Text: I love this watch. Had one of these back in my middle school days, don't quite know why I ever stopped wearing it...

Title: Bad product!
Text: Too small, it seems that it is for kids, I have a problem with the buttons as appearing in the photos attached!! The watch now is in Egypt, and I cannot return it back, what should I do ?!

Title: To-The-Point
Text: Great watch, small size compared to any other G-shock, very basic functions to the point. The adjust button it hard to press like other people say, and IMHO it is not suitable for larger wrist people. Note: It is made in China not Thailand, but quality is there like any other G-shock.

Title: Has held up fine and still looks brand new
Text: Dependable and virtually indestructible watch for its price! It's light on the wrist so you will hardly know it's there half the time. Does what it should....tell time. Use this watch at work, exposing it to water, dust, bumps and scrapes. Has held up fine and still looks brand new. The DW5600E is a great digital watch for anyone looking for a classic style with long term durability. Highly recommended.

Title: Seems as advertised. It has the usual multiple buttons ...
Text: Seems as advertised. It has the usual multiple buttons to push to adjust time,date etc. Buttons are small and a little difficult to use. Otherwise performs as expected

Title: Must have watch
Text: Superb!! Perfect dimensions, tough as nails, light and reliable. Been using it for last 5 years and it hasnt required any battery change. I would wear it everyday if not for the formal business settings I usually work in. If there was only 1 watch I would have to own my entire life, it would be this one.

Title: Thiswatch was purchased for my granddaughter and replaces the exact ...
Text: This watch was purchased for my granddaughter and replaces the exact model she had worn for years. She loves it and I can say that it performed well through years of rough ROTC physical activities and school athletics. I cannot speak to the features as I don't know which, if any, she used, but she does love this watch.

Title: Great watch!
Text: My husband needed a good watch for work and LOVES this one! We will stay committed to the G-Shock brand for sure.

Title: Part of my body
Text: Great watch for the price. Feels indestructible and always in a good mood when I see it on my wrist.

Title: I bought thiswatch after wearing a Suunto that was $230 had broke
Text: I bought this watch after wearing a Suunto that was $230 had broke. This was Only about $50 but does exactly what I need it too. I am a Marine and have used this watch daily for almost 3 years. Very reliable and the size is perfect. I don't like most of the G-Shock watches because they are too bulky but the size of this watch is perfect.

Title: Fantastic watch
Text: I bought them as Thanksgiving gifts for the children of my sister. G-shock watch is always high quality and the price is acceptable. It's the third time I bought G-shock from Amazon. I love G-shock.

Title: Four Stars
Text: came on time n looked as described further comments will be made after 5 to 6 months use

Title: Classic, bulletproof watch
Text: I've got a bunch of G Shocks. I love how solid they are, but I've grown tired of their mammoth size and complicated functions. This baby is perfect. It's smaller size and shape is classic, and its functions are simple and easy to use. It's all I need. I thought about the atomic version, but what's the point? I can sync this online anytime I want, and its quartz, so it stays amazingly accurate once set. For $41 its a bargain.

Title: Very disappointed
Text: Watch arrived in a ENVELOPE! Box was damaged and looked to even be water damaged. Opened up the box and the watch's buttons were indented in and don't pop out very far. Making navigating and using the buttons extremely difficult. Overall watch looks nice and wouldve been a great watch if not damaged by poor shipping and packaging. Not trying to go through the headache sending it back to possibly get another damaged watch back. Hopefully it doesnt effect the long term functionality of the watch which is the main reason i got this watch since they last usually forever. Definitely wouldn't buy again at least online.

Title: Classic Looks and Great Value!
Text: I bought the 5600J 5 years ago, and so very pleased with this watch. Problem is, it's so good, I keep it for "best" - special occasions, vacations, etc. I've now bought the 5600E - a more basic version of the watch, but ideal for my day to day needs. THIS watch will be getting used! Attached photo shows the 2 watches side by side - for comparision.

Title: Tough as nails
Text: Got this one to replace another one of the exact same model that I had for 6 years. These are great for the price.

Title: Great for Value

Title: In person the watch is not the size as to what is pictured.

Title: Comfortable and VERY durable

I've has a couple of other similar watches but keep coming back to this one. It's rugged to the point of being indestructible.

Title: Excellent Casio watch

Title: Sturdy!!! Great for work...
Text: Great work watch, sturdy!  I love that I can wear this watch in the hot tub!  It also has the date and day of the week always showing, comes in handy!

Title: Simply a great watch.
Text: For an inexpensive digital timepiece, this watch offers most everything you could ask for: Accuracy (though, not HAQ, atomic, radio, or whatnot), durability, alarms, stopwatch, timer, date and a light.  It is also not bad looking for a plastic watch; I would not wear it with a suit or even slacks, but for jeans and boots it makes a nice companion.  in sum, this is my go-to watch for situations that may include water, mud or blood.

Title: Perfect for me
Text: I have been wearing this watch for about 2 months now and it is perfect for my use. If you are looking for a lower profile, practically functioning, and durable watch for a reasonable price this might be the watch for you too.

Title: Casio watch

Title: Four Stars

Title: Cheap but functional

Title: Great buy
Text: I bought this for a friend to replace the one he got while serving in Iraq. It is an awesome watch.

Title: great basic watch
Text: what kind i say what hasn't been said before?  its a great watch that does just that, tell you time and date.  i personally like the square design of the watch and i have seen them around a lot.  i find myself reaching for this watch more than my automatic watches.  the strap is comfortable and overall its light on the wrist.  would highly recommend for someone looking for a basic no frills watch.

Title: Awesome

Title: Durable, high quality
Text: Bought this for my husband and he wears it daily! He works outdoors and it has stood up through rain, dirt, humidity, and showers. He hardly ever takes it off and says it’s fantastic.

Title: The Only GShock you need
Text: This watch is the Epitome of the GShock and a must have for everyday use.

Title: A rugged outdoor activities watch.
Text: This watch is simple, relatively low profile, and rugged.  It is my third in about 20 yr.  I wear it in salt water and fresh. For the price I buy a new watch rather than replace the battery; that way there are no concerns about water leaks.  The only thing I wish it had is multiple vibrating alarms to use while bow hunting.

Title: Great product
Text: Top left “Adjust” button is recessed a bit, thus making it slightly more difficult to use than the other three buttons. Otherwise, absolutely no complaints. Great product.

Title: The best

Title: The best price-value watch and best buying experience

Title: Beautiful and rugged

Title: I'll probably die before this watch does.
Text: It's cheap, it's waterproof and it tells time. This thing will likely outlast me. And when the battery dies in a few years, I can just replace it with a new one for $1. You can't go wrong with this.

Title: Good price, fast delivery

Howevwr,  the top left button (ADJUST button or labeled A in the manual) is completely depressed in. It happened by pressimg once out of box. I took the watch out of box and pressed the button to adjust time and it never came back up. The button still works but I have to use my finger nail to press it.

Title: Cant beat the value for the money!
Text: Surprisenly good watch for 50 bucks. Was very impressed with quality of rubber & display. In person they look much better. Not even sure that want to use them as beater watch as planned :)

Title: True to the original
Text: The original was stolen off my wrist in 1993, only took me 25 years to replace. Glad Casio still makes it, it’s true to the original, no frills, but makes a statement to those who know watches.

Title: This is a good basic watch
Text: This is a good basic watch. It is accurate,rugged, and inexpensive. Would have given it five stars if it had a second time zone. Alarms on this type of watch are inaudible and worthless.

Title: LOVE This watch
Text: Best watch for everyday wear. Comfortable, not too bulky and tough as nails. Great for work and exercise. Get this watch and you won't regret it at all.

Title: Good watch!

Title: A blast from the past

Title: Perfect

Title: Greatest value for what I needed.
Text: Great value.  Time of day, year, month and day because ya gotta know those things to function.  Countdown timer because ya gotta know when to get off the computer and go cycle more laundry loads from washer, dryer, and folding table.  Stopwatch because calories burned depends on rate of burn and length of time of burn.  It doesn't show off.  It just does its job very well.

Title: Nice watch!
Text: This was a Christmas gift for my son. The reviews were great and he loved it. Smooth ordering and delivery.

Title: it's a great value at a great price
Text: i've been wearing these watches for a long long time - i want to say decades.  it's a great value at a great price.  i wear it all the time, in the shower, even scuba diving, i use the stopwatch for my jogging, the timer for my laundry, the alarm to wake me up.

Title: Simply Perfect...
Text: I love this watch.  There is a kind of beauty in simplicity.  The watch is not showy or fancy, it wont get alot of compliments from folks who could care less about what kind of watch is on their wrist.  However, those who do know the G Shock reputation and myth will absolutely respect and admire this watch.  Its the original tough as nails watch.  Thats all.  Cheesy review but its all true.

Title: Its perfect. This is my workout and physical work watch
Text: Its perfect. This is my workout and physical work watch. I have a Damasko Da36 for everything else but this watch will likely get plenty of wear and im very happy with it.

Title: great watch
Text: I HAVE ALWAYS LIKED THIS WATCH, I HAD MY FIRST ONE WHEN I WAS 14 YEARS OLD, SINCE THEN I'VE BEEN BUYING IT BECAUSE IT'S TOUGH AND RESISTANT. IN THE EIGHTIES IT DIDN'T HAVE COUNTDOWN BUT NOT SO LONG AGO IT HAS IT AND IT'S A VERY USEFUL TOOL. BESIDES, YOU CAN PROGRAM THE ALARM TO ACTIVATE THE TIME YOU WANT, AND OF COURSE IT IS RESISTANT TO THE WATER 200 MTS, WHICH IS VERY IMPORTANT

Title: Quality
Text: Awesome awesome one of my favorite watch so far I love it ...!!!

Title: Unbreakable.
Text: This watch made it through basic military training with no problems at all. Great watch and I would highly recommend it.

Title: Great, Durable, Cheap
Text: One of the best watches ever. Been using them for well over twenty years. Only time I replace them is when I lose them or the strap breaks. I still have on locked up in a safe that I've had since 1993 for nostalgia... It's very durable, simple, cheap, accurate. G-Shock Perfection.

Title: Perfect gift for my husband
Text: My husband needed a new sports watch and preferred one without a velcro strap.  My son has a different G-Shock model that he loves, so I looked at the G-Shocks for my husband.  Husband didn't want one as top heavy as my son's, so I was happy to find this one that is much more low profile.  He loves the watch, and it has enough functions to make it usable for his needs.

Title: Simple and good looking design
Text: Out the box it’s a simple but stylish design and seems to be well made. I like it.

Title: Quality products
Text: Very satisfied !!

Title: Not fancy but a great watch for a man who's not a pantywaist.
Text: The third one I've purchased since 1985, all have been great watches.  Not too big but large enough to see fine, not overly complex.  Comfortable since the buttons don't protrude like some do.  Keeps great time, takes months to need a half minute synchronization with my phone.

Title: Rockin the Classic on the Daily
Text: G-Shocks are truly timeless pieces and this is a perfect example. It's a straight up amazing watch! I wear it nearly everyday and it handles the wear and tear like no other. I am extremely happy with my purchase and would recommend this product to anyone considering it. Just buy it now, seriously!

Title: Excellent
Text: I have bought this watch close to three years ago. I wear it to go jogging, swimming, hiking, playing in the snow...just about any outdoor activity. It shows little sign of wear or tear after three years. I still use the same clasp (very good condition) and the same battery is still powering the watch. Timekeeping is good, but needs to be adjusted about once a month (30-45 seconds fast). Overall, well designed, tough watch!

Title: Nice product for money.
Text: Bought for husband. He like the indiglo feature. He doesn’t like that the recessed button is set to far in.

Title: He's very happy with the watch and the price
Text: My husband has been wearing this model for many years, the band broke and the price to have it replaced would have cost almost the same as a new watch - so I just bought him the new watch.  He's very happy with the watch and the price.

Title: A classic, these are tough and last forever.
Text: These things last forever. I have one that has lasted 20 years with one battery change, and it has survived being 120 feet underwater,  and workouts hitting  a speed bag (punching bag). I never use the alarm and rarely use the light, so this is part of the reason batteries last so long. Oh yeah it tells time also, never lost a minute.

Title: sturdy, useful
Text: Attractive, sturdy, useful. This is the third one of this model I have bought. I bought this one to back up one that I am still wearing. I use the stop watch, countdown watch, and alarm, all available and easily accessed. Great value. I have a large wrist and was concerned about whether the band would be large enough, but the one delivered fits fine.

Title: Bombproof Watch, will buy again.... If I ever have to
Text: Purchased this watch 4yrs 2months ago and it is holding up great! I have put it through hell and more. With an outdoor construction career I have picked concrete and mud from every crevasse of this watch and it seems great. Also exposed it to all water conditions, every summer in the ocean, lake and river with no signs of problems. Durable and "retro" enough to be fashionable.

Title: The literature indicates the battery is good for two years
Text: The literature indicates the battery is good for two years. I have had this watch nine years and have yet to change the battery! Very functional. Not a beautiful timepiece but I didn't buy it for that reason. Great sporting watch. Very tough and dependable!

Title: I just bought it for my father for Christmas when earlier this year he remarked how much he liked it.
Text: I bought this watch for use working  in a warehouse where cell phone usage was prohibited, and have worn it everyday for the past 3 years. I just bought it for my father for Christmas when earlier this year he remarked how much he liked it.

Title: All good so far
Text: For some reason my upper left button stays mostly depressed. Is this normal? Seems it is

Title: My shady experience-be careful.
Text: The G shock I got from Casio through Amazon was defective. I pressed the button for the light and it got stuck, not returning to the off position.  I  unsuccessfully tried to free the button with my fingernail. Short of using a small screw driver and possibly damaging the case, I returned it to Amazon for a replacement since I was within the return period. Well, the replacement I got was the same watch I had sent them! It was still programmed like I had set it up, I could see where someone had damaged the case in trying to free up the stuck button and, unbelievably, the button was still stuck! When I returned it Amazon based the refund on the lower current price, not the higher price I had paid. A VERY SHADY EXPERIENCE IN EVERY RESPECT!

Title: Great watch, quick delivery.
Text: Great watch, simple, useful, durable.  Arrived quickly in great shape.

Title: thank you
