Title: Shocking
Text: When it has came down to Casio, they've continued to know how to make great watches not just in price, but also in style and simple convience. That has shown constantly with their line of G-Shock Watches for nearly 30 years. That has came the case with this classic G-Shock Watch. It is definitely a great buy for nostalgia fans of the original Casio watches, but also brings out a nice contemporary look for all shapes and sizes. It is a delightful gift for anyone who wants a simple and fun watch, but also handles very well. I like how simple it is not just to setup, but the sleekness it brings out in its bold, black design. It is also a great buy for teenagers, because they love G-shocks. I absolutely recommend this as a great buy from Casio, not just in price but in the proof of the watch. Price: B Convience & setup: B Overall: B

Title: Best watch ever
Text: Great watch I bought it right before I left for bct and wore it everyday before that and during bct. Simple as it comes buts it's great has lasted me through sand water mud and lots of crawling and it works as if it's new. One glance and I can see the date time and what day it is, I recommend this watch if you want something durable, slim (compared to other G-shocks), versatile and simple to work. The one I have is the all black version tho so the display is blacked out too.

Title: Five Stars
Text: hen xi huan

Title: Excellent watch!!!
Text: This watch is awesome! I got it for about $50 from WalMart (with tax). You can tell it's a tough watch that can truly take a beating. It's lightweight and not too bulky on your wrist compared to other G-Shocks, which I like. I've used it several times when snorkeling. You don't have to worry about this watch going underwater, getting in mud, sand, dirt, etc. This watch is fantastic it will last years.

Title: The only watch my husband will wear!!
Text: I have always purchased this watch for my husband since its so durable, waterproof and sturdy. The last watch I purchased for him lasted 10+ years until I finally got tired of looking at his "doctored"watch. I am so glad that I found this on Amazon at 50% less than what I would have normally paid, had I found it at a local brick and mortar store.

Title: Perfect
Text: Probably the most handsome watch that I own. Perfect for my office attire.

Title: Hardcore Watch
Text: I've had this watch since 2010.  It's amazing.  I beat the crap out of it. (EMT/RN), and it's just as nice as the day i bought it. Couldn't ask for more.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Beautiful! First time to buy a watch from Casio as a gift and my better half liked it.

Title: Recommended
Text: I have bought this. Highly satisfied with the quality. and it's light weight. water resistance really works well (y) . I usually wear this watch when I go to swimming.

Title: What a watch
Text: I had to get a new classic G-Shock....my last piece of junk G-Shock only lasted me 35 years....Best watch ever made, regardless of price

Title: Classic, sharp, and professional looking!
Text: Classic, sharp, and professional looking! Wraps around my right wrist just fine! Goes well with any style that I wear.

Title: Good, but time runs faster
Text: Mostly good. I've had this watch for about 9 years and it's been holding up well despite being exposed to a variety of environments. Very simplistic and traditional looking. The only negative thing is that it's not exactly precise. Time on the watch runs faster and I've had to adjust it frequently...Otherwise, it would be the perfect companion.

Title: Good Watch
Text: A good watch with the classic design.I would wear it in all kinds of sports without worrying about any damage to it.

Title: Rediscovered! They still make the simple watch
Text: I bought one of these twenty years ago and loved it but somehow lost it when I took it off. I went looking for the same model but could only find G shock models that Tom Cruise could have used in Mission Impossible. I bought them but never learned to use all the gizmos. The whirly circles were plain idiotic. SO I am so pleased to fid this model is still for sale. As others have said, it's a simple basic watch that does what a watch should do, but without the bells and whistles. I've used it in salt and freshwater, had it banged up and generally abused. The only weakness is that the straps can wear through where they connect to the watch. It can be hard to find replacements, which are often thinner and weaker. Having refound a good friend, I am going to order one .

Title: Great Replacement of a Faithful watch
Text: The casio DW5600E is an almost direct replacement of my Casio DW4600 that I purchased in 1984 that had had only 2 battery changes and was worn daily for all those years. Casio had a minor improvement in the new watch, the backlight is much improved over the 1984 version. As with the DW4600 this watch has both 12 and 24hour time, stopwatch and alarm functions, and day/date. Anyone desireing a great everyday sturdy watch that will take all the punishnet you give it is well advised to consider this one. I expect this watch to perform to theCasio standard. The other watch I consdered was the Atomic version of this watch which is solar powered and gets it's time updates from N.I.S.T. in Boulder Co.

Title: Five Stars
Text: The watch works just fine when it comes to the design, I prefer this one.

Title: Great Product!
Text: I've worn one of these through two deployments at sea, another deployment to Afghanistan and multiple deployments to Africa. These watches are as tough as they come. Provides exactly the information you want from a wristwatch but can also survive severe abuse. No bloatware. Highly recommended.

Title: if you buy one, buy another one for me plz :)
Text: bought it january 2015. great watch so far. looks great. have lifted weights and went surfing with it and didnt have a single problem. this watch can withstand anything. geat price IMO btw

Title: Five Stars
Text: A happy shopping son is very fond of

Title: Used it in Afghanistan
Text: I'm a marine and this watch is what I used in my 5 years in the marines this is a tough watch it's been dropped, soaked in water oil sand blood name it it kept on going and going totally recommend this watch for anyone out there

Title: 22 years and still going
Text: I have had my D5600 for 22 years and wear it daily.  I replace the band every year or so and the battery every 5 years.  This year I put on the third bezel case.  I found a tool at Walmart and replace the battery myself,  go swimming and have had no problem.  When new this watch went to 120' diving.  I am looking at a new one because the holes for the pins are starting to deform. Great watch and I will replace it with a new 5600.  I have another Casio just a year older, but I like this one better.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Very sturdy and comfortable at the same time

Title: RELIABLE AND RUGGED, BUT A VERY POOR TIME KEEPER.
Text: I work in law enforcement, so this is a great watch in every way except one, the most basic reason for having a watch at all...it keeps lousy time, runs 10 minutes fast. I'm switching to a Casio Atomic Watch, as I have an atomic wall clock in my home gym which keeps absolutely perfect time.

Title: i like this style
Text: it's sample,young.i like this style.

Title: 20 years and still going
Text: I bought one of these when they first came out.  I abused it like I do for watches, hunting, fishing, scuba diving, shop work, everything.  After 10 years or so the plastic finally peeled off it which made it uncomfortable to wear.  And I was getting to the point it was easier see an analog than a digital with out glasses so I bought an analog, wore it till it died, bought another self winding analog and it died today.  In the mean time that old Casio G Shock I bought back in the 1980's is still running.  I dug it out.  It was about 30 minutes off but it hasn't been set in 10 years or more.  The date and the day were still correct.  I think the battery is getting a little weak but it is the original battery.  Same band too.  Anyway I wear glasses all the time now and digitals are a lot cheaper than self winding analogs so I bought another one.  Same watch as the old one though interestingly enough the right hand buttons are reversed, properly labeled but reversed, compared to the old one.  Anyway it's a fine watch.  Well worth the money.

Title: Overtorqued shallow screwheads on caseback back means battery can't be replaced
Text: Was a good watch until it came time to replace the battery.  Screws on the watch back have shallow heads and take a Phillips head screw.  However the heads are so shallow that even a precision screwdriver has practically zero metal to engage the threads and the screws were overtightened at the factory so it takes a ridiculous amount of torque to loosen.  The result is that 3 of the screws just barely came out and the 4th was impossible and the screwhead stripped out. This resulted in the watch being summarily dispatched with the smash of a hammer and being tossed into the garbage can where it belongs. If you want longevity buy a watch with a screwdown caseback.  Otherwise there is a good chance the watch is disposable once the battery runs out.

Title: Four Stars
Text: good watch

Title: the AK-47 of digital watches
Text: Normally I don't care much for digital watches because generally analog watches look better and show the passage of time better with their hands but after doing some research I decided to buy a classic casio g-shock digital for it's functionality and reputation for being a rugged dependable watch. The designers of this watch definitely put a great deal of thought into it. Aside from it's obvious g-shock ruggedness it's very accurate only being a few seconds off from my atomic watch at any given time. It even displays the time in the small box in the upper right when it's in stopwatch and countdown timer modes. I use the repeat function on the countdown timer when I do interval training. The light works great at night. I understand the watch is popular with U.S. Military Special Operations Forces and is also flight certified by NASA whatever that means. It's not a great looking watch but it's functionally elegant and looks like a retro '80's digital watch. Highly recommended for a sports watch!

Title: Sleek and Cool
Text: I had one of the casio watch when I was little (10 years ago) and I loved it. Same for this one, the design is timeless. Rugged looking but not Bulky like the other G-Shock watches. I don't need the solar and the time zone thing, so it wasn't a factor for me. But I wouldn't mind a white one of these. Time to look for one!! Pros: - Not Bulky like other G-shock - Countdown clock - Band is comfortable Cons: - Adjust button is hard to press (designed that way so you dont accidentally change something) but I used the stopwatch alot and need to reset the time constantly, so it is a pain. - Not a complement machine (it is not flashy like other watches so you won't get comments) - Light doesnt stay on for long (2 seconds) overall it is a fine watch

Title: It goes and goes
Text: I bought this watch when i was between 10 and 14, and stopped wearing it relatively quickly, giving it to my father. He wears it when doing dirty type jobs, and to this day it's still running, im 28 now. This is not really my style, but if it catches your eye you really cant go wrong.

Title: So frustrating short adjust button
Text: "adjust button" too short to use. No idea why it's designed in this way.

Title: Superb
Text: The Casio DW 5600 is the best watch I have ever owned. Period.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Excelent product!

Title: Best Watch I've Owned
Text: This watch, at least in my mind, is the quintessential G-Shock. It's everything you need in a watch and nothing you don't, whether it be used for camping, work, school, fire fights, zombie apocalypse. I got mine as a present three years ago, and it's been with me to three continents, spent weeks in the desert camping, been through two different oceans on ill-fated surfing lessons, and seen about 1000 showers, as I never take it off. Through it all it's still on the original battery (expect that to last 10 years from what I read), and the original band seems as good as new. I've worn other watches, some far, far more expensive than this one, but none comes close to its stone-axe durability and straightforward functionality. When you need a wristwatch that'll likely last longer than you'll be around to use it, this is the one to get.

Title: Still Ticking
Text: I first met my grandfather when I was 15 when my family visited the Old Country.  He handed my mother a stack of bills, and told her to buy me a watch, because every man needs a good watch.  My choice from the jeweler's case was the Casio G-Shock.  It caused a bit of a stir among my relatives.  They asked, "Does he have trouble seeing?  Those numbers are so big..."  They were probably expecting me to pick something dressy or more formal. My dad shrugged it off, "It's the style for young people..." My Casio G-Shock has been on my wrist for over 20 years.  I haven't tried to deliberately abuse it, but other than battery changes, and plastic casing changes, it's still there. Through sweat, dirt, bumps, knocks and drops, it's nice to know that your timepiece can handle the accidents that happen. Grampa would be proud. Can't find a new plastic casing, so I'm considering buying another just to strip the casing and put it on this one!  It does look "Terminator" handsome with the STAINLESS STEEL body, but it's less waterproof now, and I liked not having to worry about it.

Title: Great
Text: I have gone through 5 (I think) of these watches and many more watch bands... over the last 23 YEARS!!! 18 of those while working as a firefighter/paramedic, and NO, I did not take it off when I went into a fire... though it got hot enough to burn me once!!!  LOL I have intention of switching anytime soon. PS, only get the Casio replacement bands, the cheaper ones are not worth it!!!

Title: very very very good watch
Text: i bought this same watch in 1985 and had it till 2004 yes IT THE BEST  1 battery change amazing

Title: Five Stars
Text: long lasting easy to use

Title: Five Stars
Text: i bought this for my Son and he loves it!!

Title: Five Stars
Text: Excellent, exactly as described! Very well packed!

Title: Classic
Text: There are products, good products, and classics. This is one of them. Tested by time, selled and worn all the world over in all kind of activities from common to extreme, this watch simply won't let you down. The explorers of those old National Geographic Rolex Ads would have worn one of this if they had the chance.

Title: Good for the Casual
Text: I absolutely love this watch. I needed a watch cuz its been a pain taking out my phone just to look at the time, so I've been looking for casual watches for cheap. This watch isn't exactly what my definition of cheap but it is a very fair price for a watch with features such as these. The watch is shock and water resitant which is a very good thing for a long lasting watch. It is very simple and not doesn't have uneeded over the top features for a digital watch. It contains time, date (day, month, year), a blue backlight for nighttime, a stopwatch and an alarm. This is the best and simplest casual watch you can possibly want on a watch, it is very durable and looks great. People have been saying this watch can last up to 20 years, but the only draw back is the watchband its not very strong and most definetly will break if it is roughly messed with. But other than that this is the perfect watch.

Title: Real Man's Watch
Text: It will last a life time and endure punishment you can't imagine. It is solid, tough, and the display is not cluttered with useless graphs and dials and other nonsense. It is not solar or atomic (thank goodness) and it don't need to be. It is the only G Shock you will ever need.

Title: Best watch ever
Text: Simply the best. No more to say.

Title: By Far the Greatest Watch I've Ever Owned
Text: This watch is outstanding! I've had watches in the past, but none have been like this! I used to be fearful of banging watches against walls or dropping them. But now, I have a G-Shock, so I don't have to care. For Jesus' sake! Marines wear these! Navy SEALs too! They are the best of the best and they wear 'em. Shouldn't you? This Watch - Low Costing - Indestructible (I've banged this against walls, concrete, brick, etc. keeps ticking!) - Fast shipping - Great display - Really simple (Clock, Alarm, Stop-watch, Timer) Only drawback- the 'ADJUST' button for some reason isn't raised out like all the other buttons. Meaning you have to really put your fingernail in there if you want to get it. But 95% of the time, it isn't a problem whatsoever. If you constantly are breaking watches, this watch is for you! These can last up to 20 years! 20 Years for under $40 Buy it now!

Title: Over 2.5 Years and still going strong
Text: I purchased my DW-5600E from Amazon in April, 2008.  Since then the watch has never left my side and never missed a beat.  It has everything a basic watch should in the right feature set.  At a glance I can tell the current time, date and day.  Setting alarms and using the timer do not require memorizing the manual.  The size is great - much smaller (height-wise) than a 6900 series and I have yet to wear a cuffed shirt that did not fall over the watch (larger G-Shocks can keep a cuffed shirt bunched up at the wrist, not good for dress).  While I am in the market for another G-Shock, I am having a hard time justifying it when the DW-5600E is, well, just fine.

Title: TANK
Text: This is a REAL man's watch! This watch is built like a tank, keeps great time, and the battery lasts a really long time. I never took this watch off even when I played football. I kept it on under my wrist bands to inflict pain on the guys I was blocking. About once a year I would adjust it to the Atomic Clock time. It was never more than a minute off. Also, the description says the battery life is two years. It lasted FIVE years on the initial battery for me! I put another battery in and it lasted EIGHT!!!

Title: Coach's Choice
Text: I purchased this watch to use while coaching my kid's football team.  It has everything I need, and it withstands the elements out on the grid iron.  This watch keeps things simple.  It really fits my coach image.  Looks great with gym shorts, t-shirt, and tennis shoes.  I also wear it to formal events with suit and tie.  It is the perfect tool for coaching.  I recommend this watch to any guy that is athletic and requires a watch to keep up with their demanding life style. It achieves perfection through simplicity.  The resin band is extremely comfortable and sporty.  The rigdes in the band allow for air flow around the wrist where I usually sweat.  The display has all of the essential information in the home time keeping mode.

Title: Best watch I've found for the price.
Text: I'm so glad Casio is still making this classic version of the G-shock watch. This is the best watch I have found in this class. I own one of the original versions with the small light bulb for a light instead of the illuminator. The light has gone out, but the watch still keeps good time. It's still tough. It's still water resistant. Been through so much that I've had to replace several bands. Watch remains sound. I bought the illuminator version to have a light and to have a watch that wasn't beat up and scratched up like my original that I've had for well over 10 years. It functions just as well and has taken plenty of abuse in it's own right. Take it from someone who abuses their watches, this is a good watch to have.

Title: Paratrooper strong
Text: I used mine in the 2nd Bn, 2/504th PIR, 82nd ABN DIV during my entire enlistment.  That includes static-line parachuting.  It was perfect for that.  Completely rugged, subdued glow in the dark, multi-function, and the strap breaks off if you were to get hung up when exiting the plane which was always the possibility when exiting a C-130 plane!

Title: easy to use and tells time
Text: Simple, easy to use and tells time.

Title: very good
Text: it is simply,it is callsicy,it is useful for me,it is good enough for me.w will use it everryday.the time is important

Title: Casio G-Shock Classic Watch
Text: As you get to be my age, it is difficult to find the products that defined a category still in production. The new replacements often have modifications that in my mind make them inferior to the originals. Sometimes it appears as though the new product was designed by someone who has actually never used one in "real life." Typically, I am forced to access the pre-owned market to get what I want. Not in this case. The Casio Men's G-shock Classic Digital Watch is very similar to the watch that replaced the stop watch, the dry land and not-so dry land wrist watch, and alarm clock a couple of decades ago. It has just enough functionally to be truly useful - time (24 or 12 hour), date (helps when filling out those forms that are becoming part of daily life), alarm (for those early morning activities), stop watch (for that interval training necessary to retain some of the speed of youth), and a couple of other things that have slipped my mind :-) all in a small and durable package.  Good, inexpensive, tough, useful watch.

Title: Truly great watch
Text: This watch is one of the few certified by NASA for space missions (google it). It's also the overwhelming choice of "high speed" military units like SEALs, Green Berets, Rangers, Marines and so on. These guys dont wear fancy watches that have "Role*, Navy Seals, Omeg*, Tag Heue* on the dial. They want something tough, dependable, simple, common, and easy to replace. This is that watch. Dont forget the thousands, if not millions of laborers, and construction folks who put gshocks through all kinds of use/abuse every day. This gshock has classic looks, and no useless features unlike some modern gshocks.

Title: In the beginning...
Text: The very first Casio watch I had was a 50M dress watch, resin. When I saw a G-Shock advertised for a ridiculous price at a local discount store I determined to get there. Dropped off after work 15 miles away, I forded a 4 ft. deep stream, clambered through a patch of thorns as tall as me, and got hit by a car taking a 'shortcut' to the sale. The store tried to tell me they were out (because the paper had the wrong price) but I wasn't going anywhere without a watch. They finally relented and I got my G-Shock for a real bargain! And it took whatever punishment I gave it. From operating chain saws to cross-country running through mud and dust my G-Shock perservered. Always on time, stop-watch and alarm always ready, there was never a more useful tool in my essential survival kit. I bought it in 1987 and in 1995 I gave it to a homeless man, still running. That was one durable timepiece, it took the most beating of any of my half-dozen G-Shocks. I definitely recommend this series of watches.

Title: Best Watch.... Ever
Text: I first bought this watch (earlier model, slight variations) when I was 12 years old. Since then, I've worn it at sea, diving, skydiving, rock climbing, abseiling, bushwalking, hang gliding, sailing, running, swimming, and for work. Its lasted 25 years! The plastic casing eventually fell off a few years ago, and it started looking a bit tardy for work. Its still working now, but has found a home with my son by his bedside. This year, I bought another, and am looking forward to another 25 years! Really would recommend this no nonsense, solid, well built, and well designed watch for anyone who has an active lifestyle. Best watch... ever (for me!)

Title: Good~
Text: It is the best G shock with Good quality, design at this price. And the best service from Amazone.I would recomend this watch to my friend.

Title: awesome product and fast shipping.
Text: My brother and uncle both have this watch as their job watch.  I bought it because i like how the g-shocks are sturdy but still look nice.  very good price and good brand.  shipping was fast as usual.  i enjoy this watch a lot.

Title: Old style Casio
Text: I have owned a couple of watches like this over the years and forgot how light weight and practical they are. The first watch [in the past] I ever owned that didn't get a rainstorm when worn by a working man. Don't let anyone tell you you can't put a flex band on because it can be done. Highly recommended. JWB

Title: Best watch ever
Text: Jumped with it. Dove with it. Never even slowed it down. I used it to time my radios when on patrol when I couldn't get to a GPS (Because MBITR's are horrible at keeping time on anything but single-channel crypto). Outperformed my issued Suunto for 1/4th the cost.

Title: Form over function
Text: I owned a previous G-Shock (I believe a DW-5600C) - purchased in the early 90s and still going strong (minus the rubber around the screen) up to a couple of years ago, when it was stolen. That was a great watch. Years of abuse and no problems (baring the timekeeping being a little off, but I can live with that). I replaced it with this watch, which is worse in almost every way from the previous G-Shock I owned. The only improvement that I can see is the illumination - the screen lights up green and it's very clear in the dark. The main difference between this and the 20 year old DW-5600C is that this watch has a "let moisture enter the watch" feature, which means that on cold mornings or after a rapid change in humidity/temperature (like going outside) condensation forms on the inside of the screen. I ignored this for the approx nine months that I used the watch. About three weeks ago half the LCD decided to stop working overnight, so the watch is now useless. Anyway, to say that I'm disappointed is an understatement. I was a massive fan of G-Shocks up until I bought a new one. Where did it all go wrong Casio? If you're incapable of producing quality watches at this price point, then they should double/triple the price - I'd be glad to pay it for a replacement for my previous G-Shock (I hate the styling on the other, trendier (?) G-Shocks)

Title: Casio G shock watch
Text: Great product. Accurate and durable.  I wore out the wrist band long before the watch.  Needs a more durable wristband.

Title: Bezel is the weakest link
Text: 5 years have passed,and the bezel cracked in the middle of the letter H in the word G-SHOCK This is my second watch of the same model.First one passed through 3 years of army service,and lasted another 7 years until the bezel cracked and fell apart,total of 10 years. Second watch seems to be of some worse quality. Guess I'll buy something different next time.

Title: Great, simple watch
Text: Didn't want a fancy watch with all the bells and whistles. Just wanted a basic reliable, durable digital watch. If you're looking for a watch that has these qualities look no further this watch is the best one for the money.

Title: Nice and comfortable watch...
Text: Can't ask for anything more out of this watch, simple to operate and pretty much a nice rugged watch, loving it I just hope that the battery lasts for a long time...

Title: NICE WATCH
Text: It's great watch cheap and fashion. Its very comfortable. Classic design. Cat's find any reason u dont choose it. Compare to other G shock advance series. Recommend this one if u jus want a simple watch.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Great watch! Totally worth it!

Title: This watch helped me survive sharks and pretty girls
Text: I bought this watch on sale years ago for normal daily wear. I thought it looked rugged, but I had no idea just how rugged it truly was until I took up SCUBA diving. It survived life banging around boats for weeks on end as I literally traveled around the world. I wore it on hundreds of SCUBA dives up to 140 feet below the surface. Whether getting me get back to the surface before my air ran out or getting me to a sidewalk cafe before a blind date ran out this watch was always there for me. My Casio G-Shock never stopped running, it never leaked and never it let me down. I can't recommend it highly enough.

Title: Classic and reliable
Text: cheap, classic and reliable. I love it! The solar one is better but more expensive, finally I choose this one.

Title: Best Watch Of All Time!!!
Text: How anyone can rate this beauty anything less than 5 stars is beyond me.  The 5600 is an all time classic watch with retro style and great all around function. It's small (and very thin) compared to most other G-Shock watches, yet it's still extremely durable and will easily outlast cheapie Timex watches. It's extremely comfortable and doesn't feel bulkie at all.  It is a great starter watch to anyone who has never worn a G-Shock before, and wants one (but isn't sure which one to get). The only way this watch could be any better, is if it could be muted so that the watch didn't make any noise when you pressed a button.  My 5525 has this feature.  Other than that the 5600 is damn near perfect in every way.

Title: Best watch I ever owned!
Text: Wow, nice to see that I can still buy this one!  Seems like the stores were only stocking the "HUGE" variety of G-Shocks with all sorts of nonsensical features like altimeters and barometers toasters and whatever else they could think of. I like this one specifically for its: 1) lower profile, less bulky than more modern G-Shocks 2) limited features 3) ease of use 4) the thing can no doubt take a pounding I wore my last one for over a decade and replaced the strap like 2 or 3 times until the rubber around the main faceplate finally gave way. I'm putting my order in for a new one today!  ...I might even get two just to have a spare.

Title: Bought around 1987 and still going strong ...
Text: Bought around 1987 while on vacation in California and still going strong ...  That pretty much says it all!  I have owned my Module 691 / DW5600 (no sufffix numbers) Classic G-Shock watch with only 1 battery change in its life and it's still going fine! The only things that broke were the little black plastic strap-end retainer on the black plastic wrist strap; and a crack has *just* (past month or two ~ 10/2009) recently developed in the lower left-hand corner of the black plastic watch casing! Inexpensive and hard-core utilitarian. Not fancy enough to be a dress chronograph. For dressing up, I recently purchased a Casio G-Shock G1000D-7A - which is very handsome and sturdy, but nowhere as simple to use (nor does it light up)!

Title: Long battery life
Text: I had it for 20 years. The battery did not die until I lost this watch. It may run more years. Best watch ever!

Title: Great Everyday Watch
Text: I had a previous Casio G-Shock watch for 15 years.  It always worked, and I never needed to change the battery.  When the wrist strap broke, I just bought a generic strap to fix it.  I loved the watch so much that I would rather just fix the strap instead of buying a new watch. Eventually the anchor points for the straps fell apart (after years and years of abuse), so I had to buy a new watch.  I bought a nicer looking Timex, but that fell apart in a year!  Admittedly, the Timex was not designed for abuse, but I never realized that everyday bumps could destroy a watch! So I went back to Casio to get another G-Shock, and I've never regretted it.  If you're looking for a durable watch for everyday use, this is the one to get.

Title: The Greatest-Shock
Text: This watch is amazing!!! It's the reissue of the old DW-5000  (1983) with two major improvements: the Illuminator and what I call "security buttons". The EL light is very strong, ideal for read the watch even in a dark environment, like a forest. Now the set buttons are smaller than those that came with the original DW-5000, so you can't press them accidentally, what means if you are in TIMER (countdown) mode, you'll stay there until you (not your shirt) prees the mode button again. Do you need more? OK: great design, clear numbers and a very readable LCD. It's light and keeps accurate all the modes: time, alarms, countdown timer (very useful) and stopwatch. Finally it has 200M WR and a durable band. But the thing that I really like about it was the following warning in the user's manual: "This watch has been developed for full heavy duty use." And it's the true. Five stars.

Title: Adequate but With Significant Flaws
Text: I bought this watch to replace my Casio DW340, which was perfect for my needs and which lasted for decades. I wanted another DW340 but it seems that Casio no longer makes that model. Sad. The DW5600 contains almost all of the functions I need EXCEPT that it does not have a second time zone, which the DW340 had and which I kept set to UTC. This function is of critical importance to me and was almost a "deal breaker" on this item. The button assignments are not logical, with the stopwatch reset being in the upper left corner, the "A" button, while the other stopwatch functions are on the right side. Not only is the location awkward from an ergonomic standpoint, but this button is also the "adjust" button, and so it controls access to all the other watch functions. On the DW340 this button was recessed and flush with the case. On the DW5600, the button is both flush with the case and surrounded by rather high ridges, making it almost impossible to access. The composition casing is all hard edges versus the rounded edges of the DW340. When I began to wear the watch some of the edges literally dug into my wrist hard enough to make a bloody mark. One morning at work I took my penknife and "eased" all the sharp edges. I then cut down the ridge surrounding the "A" button so that I could access it more easily to reset the stopwatch. Proper attention to design by Casio would have made my homemade modifications unnecessary. The stopwatch also oddly drops the 1/10s function after it reaches one hour as the area on the 340 that contained the hour now contains the regular time. The only items where the DW5600 is an improvement on the DW340 is that the display is a bit more legible and the backlight function is superior to the light function in the DW340. Unfortunately, Casio made some significant errors in this watch, including the design of the casing with its sharp edges and high ridges, the elimination of the second time zone, and the loss of  1/10s on the stopwatch. I wish Casio had kept the DW340 as it was except for the DW5600's backlight. I'm using the DW5600 but I'm still looking for a replacement for my DW340.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Very good

Title: Five Stars
Text: durable time piece

Title: sweet watch
Text: Got mine in 88 in basic training- still going strong thru basic and infantry training.  NEVER have put a battery in it.  Am now just looking for a new band- dont take all the reviews wrong because of the new band thing...the watch is like 18 years old!!!!! review update- the original battery lasted 20 years- just recently died.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Great watch

Title: Solid & simple, GREAT watch
Text: This watch does not come with whistles and bells, but it is beautifully built and looks very very sturdy and balanced. I like it best among my 4 casio watches. UPDATE: bought the watch in 2011, and it is still going strong in 2017! UPDATE 2: the battery finally died in 2022. It ran about 11.5 years without an issue.

Title: Best Watch I've Ever Owned
Text: This is the best watch, without a doubt, that I have ever owned. I grew up wearing timex ironmans and didn't think much about them only lasting a year or two. But this watch is built solid, and it's easy to tell. I work on a farm, so I definitely needed something that could take a beating, and this watch certainly can! In fact, it's not even showing any signs of wear or tear either. So if you want a watch that has all the basics, and no gimmicks, this is the one. And it will last!

Title: Lasts a long TIME
Text: I received a DW-5200(looks almost the same as this model) for Christmas in 1987.  I am wearing it right now, almost 18 years later.  I have replaced the battery ONCE in that time.  The wristband has been replaced twice, because of the extreme use it has had.  I have hiked, camped, used heavy machinery etc...while wearing this watch.  I love it.

Title: excellent product
Text: I think they stopped making these because the calendar programmed into it goes back to 1995. Nonetheless, I have never had a better watch/stopwatch/chronometer, etc.  And it has the fade-out "indiglo" thing that is better than previous models.  Best of all, when in stopwatch or countdown mode,  a box at the top shows real time. No other watch I know of has this simple yet essential feature.  Completely durable.  Since the previous one of these I owned went 10+  years on the original battery, and I do not know when this one was manufactured, I have no idea how long this one will last, but I know I will wish I had bought two.  The price is right, and I got a $[...] rebate for signing up for an Amazon credit card.  My only problem, at 50, is that sometimes my arms are not long enough to read it....nor any other watch smaller than big ben.  A personal problem, I know.

Title: Casio Watch
Text: We were very pleased with the prompt arrival of the watch.  My husband has been wearing a Casio for the past 25 years.  They are very durable.  I'm telling you he puts them to the test. I hope that this one will last as long as the last four. His only complaint so far is that the watch  grabs the hairs on his wrist.

Title: Five Stars
Text: Very good

Title: Gets the job done
Text: Bought this watch to save my dress watches from the rigors of kids activities. Turns out I like wearing this watch more than my panerai and tag.  Very light and comfortable watch.

Title: Great Watch
Text: The Casio watch is the most comfortable, convenient, flexible, and informal watch I own and it's been that way since I first bought one some 30 (?) years ago when I was doing a lot of running and jogging.  And, the one I recently lost had been working efficiently without a replacement battery for some 20 years.  They are not so expensive  that I didn't feel financially dented when  I replaced it.  My other watch, a more "dress-up" one that  my folks  gave me 48 years ago, is still telling  accurate time.  Guess I'm  not a  good customer because watches  just  last a  long time with me, but only when I buy quality.  My biggest problem was  finding  a Casio like I wanted at a retail store in Tulsa.  They just don't carry them, but that must be a marketing decision.  This was my first purchase ever online.  You also spend too much on the cost to mail it without a benefit of quicker delivery.

Title: 16 years, 3 bands, original battery
Text: I don't have much to add to the other reviews.  This watch is bullet proof.  I never used the light nor the alarm much, but I cannot believe it's still working with the original battery since 1993.  A great watch for real people! Sad update: In late November 2010, after 17 years of service, it finally quit.  I brought it in for a new battery, but the jeweler told me it was all over.  We had a brief ceremony and I ordered a new G-Shock from Amazon.

Title: Excellent
Text: Great everyday watch. Has all thefunctions needed for the everyday, is light, rugged and comfortable to wear. I use this as my work, hiking and outdoors watch and am very happy with it. Great price too.

Title: A Good Companion
Text: My second Casio G-Shock, it was dependable, tough, and discreet. Of course it was a sizable watch, nothing could hide that, but it needed the bulk to protect it's time-keeping core. And it did everything you could ask a watch to do. There's something to be said for a timepiece that you can hold out in a driving rainstorm while waiting for the bus. Tough goes beyond mere words.

Title: A timeless classic!
Text: I just love this watch. I used to have one of these when I was a kid back in the 80's and it used to be EXACTLY what you would expect from a Casio G-Shock: Simplicity Reliability Durability These watches will go anywhere you go, withstand anything you give and survive. Little has changed on the aspect of this model - which makes it a part of some of my fondest memories. A vintage looking classic!

Title: Classic reliability
Text: This is a great, simple, reliable watch. I got dumped over in a canoe in a river and it still works great. You could take a shower with this watch on everyday and it would still work. I like to use the stopwatch function to make sure I don't spend too much time on Facebook.

Title: The Perfect "Beater" Watch
Text: A must have for anyone that loves to wear watches... it has all the necessary functions for a digital watch and it's a G-Shock so you know it can take some abuse.  I started with this one and loved it so much I bought a 5600MS as well.

Title: Greatest working man, sport and retro watch ever!
Text: This watch has seen me through some of the roughest applications I can think of.  from 150 mile bike races, to all day dish washing at resteraunts, to swimming on the beaches of Cozumel!  I have other watches that I wear for style, but this watch is what I wear when I want a watch that does the best job.  It's time is dead on accurate!!  It is digital duh!?!?!  Anybody that loves the 80's, Marty Mcfly, Huey Lewis and the news, as well as working like HE double hockey sticks should buy this watch and not think twice about it!!

Title: Great, simple watch
Text: This is now a modern classic. Simple watch ,takes 2 minutes to learn how to use. Pros Good value Hard wearing Simple to use Stops you look at your cell phone for the time. Cons ---

Title: It's okay
Text: this watch is okay, it tells time.  I didn't like how the strap is kinda stiff and it pinches your skin sometimes.  Other than that, I don't have any other issues with this watch so far. Aside from that, Amazon's shipping has become SUPER SLOW now.  Even though I selected for free shipping, I would sometimes get the items before the schedule delivery date and sometimes on the first few days of the schedule delivery date, but never on the last day of the schedule delivery date. They've been delivering items on the very last day for over a year now.  I'm not mad about it, since it's still within the schedule date, but I'm just pleased as when I was getting them before the schedule date or the first day or two of the schedule date.

Title: It has never let me down!!
Text: The G-Shock hits the spot perfectly in all ways. I used to compete on a regular basis in West Coast open water meets and would sometimes row marathons for hours. The watch was my guide. It has been functioning perfectly since 1989 and I foresee no end in sight. It might outlast me. I don't think I think my Rolex or Baume & Mercier would be able to be so rugged and reliable. A real watch for active people in activities which require stamina and endurance. I have used it in road rallies over the fancy chronometers. It might last longer than I.

Title: My Casio
Text: This casio as other casio watches I have had in the past works extremely well and I have no complaints with this product and would recommend it to anyone who is in the market for a timepiece

Title: great watch maybe the greathest in the world Akos Martin NORWAY

Title: Great Watch
Text: I have owned this watch since 1999 and have never even replaced the battery and only replaced the band one time. I have worn this watch any time I was doing any kind of rough, dirty work. It's a great watch. At a price of $37.50 this is definatley the best watch at the best price available. You may find a more fancy watch but not a better one. UPDATE: I thought the watch died in 2006 but all it needed was a battery and an o-ring which my local jewler was able to provide. This stopped the condensation that I was getting in the watch. So, since 1999 it has needed one battery, one o-ring and one band and I'm still wearing it. Not bad for a $50.00 watch.

Title: Best of The Best :)
Text: Hello! I've bought this product, because I lost my previous CASIO watch. to be honest I knew everything there was to know about this G-Shock, so I knew exactly what I was buying ;-) Tough, cheap and has all features I need! (maybe except dual-time, but I did not use that very often). If you are looking for simple watch for diving or water sports that would damage normal watches - this one is for YOU! :) Andrew Cz.

Title: Over Thirteen Years and Still going strong
Text: I've had this watch for over thirteen years. It never once failed me and I've only replaced the battery once. The only thing I've had a problem with is that the casing around the watch has broken and fallen off, but if you contact casio they will replace it for you for a resonable charge.

Title: Nothing fancy, but still an awesome watch...
Text: This watch does what it's supposed to do--tell time. It's also water resistant to 200 meters, and it's easy to adjust the time and date. You can easily change the time in a few seconds to the correct time, accurate to the second, once a month to compensate for the +/- 15 seconds it gains/loses per month. It also has a timer, so you can time yourself if you go running. The watch is nothing fancy, but it  matches well with both casual or dress clothes. It's a nice time piece, is sturdy, and seems like it will last a very long time.

Title: Comfort and simplicity 5/5
Text: Love this watch............. If you need a watch that is light, manly, and functional save  your money and buy this watch.  It is a classic that hasn't been beat yet.

Title: Great Running and Alarm Watch
Text: This is a great watch for running and other sports that also serves as a travel alarm clock.  I have just bought my third, the first two having lasted 13 and 14 years respectively.

Title: Great value
Text: The price value for this watch is great. It is a very durable product. Cooking is the work that I do and this watch can take the shock of that better than any other watch I've tryed. In and out if water, the heat of a kitchen and the band is flexble and doesn't break the way other watches have.I can set timers and time things to write durations down. The previous one lasted for years longer than I expected I baught 2 because I figure that they will just stop making them and I won't be able to get another one.

Title: Fine product.  Price Oopps
Text: The watch is fine.  I've used this or similar models for 20? years.  The only gotcha, The price dropped $2 the next week. I've got 4 sons.  This watch or it's similar model was given to each when they reached 14.

My only problem is the light, which is sometimes difficult to press! If anyone has any tips to get the light on better leave me some comments =] other than that love this watch!

Title: Best watch I ever owned...

After a few years of salt water or harsh chemicals you might need a new band, but the watch will never let you down. I like this model because the simple and large display. Nothing fancy but functional!

Title: My second in 6 years
Text: My wife originally bought me this watch around 6 years ago. I've used jack hammers, sawzalls, all kinds of power tools and it just doesn,t give up. The only resaon my first one died was because I stripped a screw hole in the back while changing the battery (it still works, its just not waterproof). This watch is virtually unbreakable. This is a great watch for anyone with an active lifestyle.

Title: good value, reliable
Text: This is the 3rd g shock I've purchased. It's not overloaded with features, has just what you need and would use. Good value for the price.

Title: If you use the stop watch function do not buy this watch
Text: Bought one of these watches about 6 months ago unfortunately not from amazon. My previous watch was also a Casio Illuminator and was a great watch. Had it for about 20 years. The G-Shock looks good and at first I thought it was really good. That quickly changed. I use the stop watch function a lot mainly for running and sprints. The buttons are too far recessed and are a pain in the neck to activate. When finishing a sprint I am fumbling trying to press the button - useless. My previous watch did not have this problem. Also find it difficult to press the button to activate the light at night. Don't wish to sound sexist but this watch may have been designed by a female who has no trouble pressing the buttons due to long fingernails. I complained to the seller a couple of times but was ignored. I am now forced to buy another watch but will go for a Timex and buy through amazon.

Title: Great watch for scuba divers!
Text: This is a great, affordable watch for anyone who is in or around the water.  We use ours when we scuba dive and the large numbers are easy to read while wearing a mask.  The buttons are easy to use even when wearing thick gloves in cold water and the backlight color makes the watch easy to read even when diving in dark green water.

Title: Great Watch expect for 2 Drawbacks
Text: This is a great watch and I agree with almost everyone's comments. It is stylish, durable and highly reliable. But there are two main drawbacks that can be improved, one of which is Casio's fault and the other one is just a style issue. 1) the edge between the watch face and the watch bands bends considerably and there is a tear emerging after a couple of months of use. This is more prominent if you have a thin wrist and use one of the shorter holes on the band. 2) It is a bit too thick aesthetically. I know it is very durable and has a great protective casing but I feel it would look better in a thinner version.

Title: Very reliable watch
Text: I bought this watch a month ago. I wanted a shock resistant and water proof watch with stop watch ability. And I can only say good things about it: it has a pleasant design, it is light, and what surprised me the most it keeps very accurate time. I noticed an error of only +1 seconds in this time. It is a very good buy at this price.

Title: casio watch classic g shock
Text: Best watch out there for the price.  Watch bands however don't last  very long.  To purchase an OEM band and not some substitute is very $$$$ considering the overall cost of watch brand new with band.  Third G Shock  watch I'ved owned.  Anything more than this is a waste of time and money.  Does what it's supposed to under the harshest conditions.

Title: Great Watch
Text: Casio Men's G-Shock Digital Watch #DW5600E-1V Awsome watch , this is my second G-Shock and many more to come. This is a old school G-shock with great style. Fits well ,Reads well & Cheap too :)

Title: Good Casio/Small, hard to reach buttons
Text: As always, Casio makes bomb-proof watches. The only down side on this watch is that the buttons are very low-profile, requiring one to use their fingernail to press them.  This makes adjustments tough.

Title: Casio G-Shock
Text: These watches were backups for my very, old original G-shock.  They work perfectly. Although the control buttons are set slightly differently, this has not been a problem.  The blue-green night light is actually superior to the original white one.

Their lowest price is $89 on Times Square - why pay so much if you can buy them here for more then twice less? Resume: nice watch for work, sport

Title: Great watch!!

Title: Awesome...it works.

Title: Dont buy if u have arm hair
Text: The watch is nice but however dont buy it if u have arm hair. My arm hair keeps getting caught by the screws on the back of the watch, hurts and is really annoying

Title: good watch
Text: I enjoy wearing it. It helps me to get to appointments on time. I depend on it to help get me through the day.

Title: STILL A GREAT WATCH, BUT --- ??
Text: THIS MODEL DOES NOT HAVE DUAL TIME??? I have had this exact same watch for many years, finally having to replace it. For some unknown reason, CASIO dropped the DUAL TIME feature. WHY?? All of the other features are still available and no new features were added, so why did they drop a very useful feature for travelers. Even their cheaper ($15) watches have dual time, so it cannot be an expensive feature. Just does not make any sense to delete features from one of the most successful watches ever designed. A little disappointed in CASIO!

Title: Cool retro design, good value, uncomfortable strap
Text: Love the simple, yet retro and classic 80s design. the DW5600 is a good value,  perfect size for big or small waist, the durability and the functionality is great for a field watch, but Unfortunately, like most other G-Shock, the strap is poorly design and very uncomfortable, it digs right into your skin, wish they would use the strap from the GA-2110, aka- Casio oak, which is so comfortable, the soft plastic and the curve design is a winner, but this and many other Casio watch is hard to wear for a long period of time. I recommend you buy the GA-2110 for about $60.00 more, much more comfortable on your wrist, and much more collectable.

Title: Durable comfort, no fuss, just the time!
Text: Comfy without complications. G-shock Vs other cheap watch the oversized update of the classic(F91W) W217 Both are slim and easily slide under the cuff, G-shock bumpers just slightly more proud. W217's digits bigger, viewing angles similar. G-shock screen is mineral glass and protected, W217 asks for scratches. G-shock shaped band curves around wrist is more comfortable, W217 your wrist curves the band. G-shock chime is discrete even if forgotten, W217 is ear piercing. G-shock has timer, W217 does not. Both are nice, and the W217 is half the price, the G-shock is half the trouble, the G-shock wins.

Title: Ultimate work/sports watch for the money.
Text: Decided to stop beating my "nice" watches up at work.  As a kid I had always wanted an original G-Shok since they came out in the '80's, but somehow never got around to getting one.  They are sold about everywhere. Bought on Amazon through a Warehouse deal as it was cheaper than Walmart as the price is pretty standard at just under $40.  There are a million reviews on YouTube and the internet.  I'm not going to add anything meaningful to the discussion, other than to say if you are any sort of watch person, you should own one.  This is as close as you can find to the original in current production. Maybe spring for the solar one if that is important, but the battery life is pretty good on these.

Title: My EDC watch
Text: Have worn this watch every day since I bought it.  It fits my wrist well and is comfortable all day regardless of what I'm doing.  The way the band curves really makes it fit nice.  The matt black look of the watch and sturdy build make it a great everyday wear timepiece.  The only thing I don't like is the recessed mode button.  I know why they made it this way.... to keep from accidently changing the settings. But I would rather have it as easy to push as the other three and take my chances. It's just very difficult to push.  Despite this, I'm still glad I have it and will continue to wear it no matter what I'm doing.  Great, rugged watch.

Title: Only Watch You Really Need!
Text: I bought a few G-Shock watches as Christmas gifts. Its a no brainer, thoughtful gift at a reasonable price. After handling this model, I ordered one for myself. It's now in the regular rotation and really happy with the ownership experience. Fun to use and easy to look at.

Title: Horribly packaged

I hate how smartwatches now track everything you do, and keep you connected 24/7 into social media and the internet. This does the job perfectly. Although, in the beginning, you will have to read the manual to know how it works, because it has many other functions.

Title: This Watch is the Real Deal
Text: Every time I get the itch to buy a new watch I always circle back to the reviews on this one and realize that I have the best watch you can buy in terms of cost and durability. I have had this watch for over a year now. I have swam with it in the ocean, hiked with it, camped with it, hunted with it, have a niece who chewed on it, have a dog  who chewed on it, worn it to work daily, traveled everywhere with it, shower with it,  and have banged it up on machinery and household furniture. I  have generally taken this watch everywhere with me. It has held up beautifully and looks like it did the day I bought it.  I can not think of a better investment I have made on an item that has held up better than this. Battery is still going strong. If you want to spend the money on something with more gadgets and buttons and features where people are impressed with its blingyness then that is your choice.  If you want a watch that tells accurate time and date that is fair priced and virtually indestructible, then this watch is for you.

Title: A Great Watch Never Dulls Out
Text: The DW5600 has been around for more than thirty years, and it’s easy to see why. The functionality is simple. It may be just a bit more complex than the F91W, but it’s not too far off. Doesn’t take much to learn to set it up the way you want, and it stays put once you’re done. The price ain’t shabby for this historic G-Shock. I mean, fifty something bucks is very reasonable for something this tough and cool. If you can find it cheaper, more power to you. Not only is this watch NASA flight approved, it holds a world record for heaviest vehicle to drive over a watch. Impressive to put it mildly, You got the usual functions found in most Casios and G-Shocks; timer, stop watch, alarm, 12/24 hour format, and back light. Dimensions should accommodate most wrist sizes, and the overall design of the watch is simple and sporty. Awesome history, insanely tough, practical simplicity, and affordable. This watch would make a perfect first G-Shock, or an addition to any watch collection.

Title: Hands Down - best watch for active people
Text: The first time I owned this Casio G-Shock was in 1985. Took it on hundred of campouts, backpacking treks, and rock climbs. Never once did it fail me and it took a serious beating. I wound up loosing it in college and so I purchased my second one in 1996. Again - amazing watch. I never took it off (swimming, showering, etc...) As solid as my first one...until I tried changing the battery in 2008. (Did you get that? The battery lasted 12 years...) I messed up and didn't get the gasket seated properly. My wife bought me my 3rd Casio G-Shock in 2009 and I am using that to this day. I just bought this watch for my son to wear as we train for our next backpacking adventure. He loves it and also wears it everyday. I can't say enough how much I love this watch. It's not as fancy as some of the other watches, but this watch is a time tested beast - I guarantee you won't regret it!

Title: Great watch
Text: I bought this as a replacement for my dead Timex watch, which I have used for many years. Usually I’m doing good to get maybe 2 years of service with that brand before they start quitting on me. Well, I decided to do research on another brand of watches for durability and dependability. After reading many reviews about the Casio GShock watch, I felt like this was the best replacement for my lifestyle. I’m a baseball umpire, as well as a football and basketball referee. It’s important for me to have a good timepiece for these events. I’ve been using this for football with the timer, because lately we’ve had to keep the game time on field due to lack of dependable clock operators. This watch has done excellent for this sport and I have been using it to keep the time limit on fall baseball games as well. I like the features of the buttons being more difficult to push in order to keep from accidentally hitting the buttons by mistake. Being shock proof and waterproof is also a plus. The price is very good for what you need in my situation, and I will certainly buy another one if this one ever quits. I’m not being paid for my opinion, but I feel like this is a good product that deserves comments it deserves. Well done

Title: A Practical "Statement" Digital Watch
Text: I like digital watches, and I have collected numerous models from Casio. I finally wanted to try a G-shock. When I ordered it, I wasn't sure I was going to like it. I thought it would be too big and bulky and unattractive. Thankfully, it turned out I was wrong. I really like it. Seems quite durable. It's  just a bit of a step up from some of my Casio Heavy-Duty watches which I enjoy wearing. The watch is very comfortable. I have a narrow wrist, but it fits well, and with all the options with the amount of holes in the strap, you will definitely find a fitting that's good for you. What I also like is the decorative printing around the watch face. The white outline, the grey border around the screen, the white gold and blue lettering...it all works well. Also like the Shock Resist logo on the bottom. The text and outline are in gold, and there's a red trapezoid under the text. It's very symmetrical (unlike the atomic version). Setting up the watch was easy. Similar to other Casio modules. I did not have to set the year (there was no option for that...or maybe I missed it?). Also, from what I recall, it was set close to the actual time when I took it out of the box. All in all, I really like it. A statement digital watch, if you will. Of course, it's not for everyone, but if you like masculine digital watches, and one that will probably last a long time, you will be happy with your choice.

Title: Classic on the cheap.
Text: Look, you know this watch is basically indestructible, unpretentious, recognizable, and cheap. Not cheap in the bad crappy way, cheap as in this watch is $40 and you're probably going to beat it or no be heartbroken IF you kill it. Although, if you kill it, you will no longer be able to appreciate the intrinsic value this watch provides. Yes, it's a digital watch with a rubber strap, BUT, it's a Casio. A purpose built tool watch. You need this in your collection. The other Gs are good, but this is the one to own. It won't break the bank if you're on a budget, and you don't have to wear your expensive watches camping, fishing, skiing, wrenching, mowing the grass (see where I'm going?) and have to worry about damage.

Title: Dependable Factory Watch
Text: I really don't have any dislikes for this watch. I have read that digital watches function well as an anti-magnetic or magnetic resistant watch. I work with tac welders and found long ago that typical analog watches have issues in the factory where I work. This model has worked well in that regard. It keeps time well, it fits well on my wrist and the display is easily read. The display shows the time, day of week, month and day. Are their fancier digital watches? I'm sure that there are, but for a cheap watch this watch meets my expectations. I'd buy another one in the future.

Title: The Best Watch Ever
Text: I absolutely love this watch. I wear it every day at work, which I do flooring for a living so this watch takes a beating. It holds up very well to everything I throw at it. It's waterproof up to 600 feet deep, and I've seen videos of it being run over by a semi and survive. It's pretty much the same watch they've been making since 1987. That's what I love about it, it's retro styling. It's the same watch Keanu Reeves wears in the movie Speed, and Steve Carell wears one in the 40 Year Old Virgin. It's been worn by navy seals, the police, and even by NASA. I just like having the time on my wrist rather than having to rely on my phone all the time, which with my job I can't do without breaking my phone. This watch is very accurate down to the second. It's worth every penny, in fact I think it's cheap for what you actually get. Go back to the basics and get a great watch for a great deal. It's one tough watch, and I highly recommend it!

Title: Old tech
Text: I had this watch 30 years ago,  I am actually surprised to see Casio still selling it. It was a good watch, a reliable piece of equipment.  When the battery ran out I replaced it with something similar.  That being said it does not fit the needs of today's world.  There is no GPS, texting or any other modern convenience.
